{"author": ["Internal Consultant"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How easy it is to use and also the customer service is amazing! Chat boxes are super useful when you need any type of support. ", "What do you dislike?": "Things are consistently changing. Just when I get use to a feature it moves spots and changes the look. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's decently priced for the amount of features you get. They also offer way more features then a lot of other CRM sites - personal opinion from research. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Helps me schedule emails, blog posts, social media on multiple accounts. I use it to track my website analytics and keep track of contacts / my lists (blog subscribers and my Talent Community)."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Sports"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The Workflow feature is an absolutely amazing time-saver, and works great every time.", "What do you dislike?": "There are some features and tools that are missing that seem like no brainers. For example, being able to reset a contact's Hubspot score to 0 rather than using subtraction, or the Reporting tool being clunky and difficult to use.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The benefits are huge - we are able to generate leads, score them automatically based on actions they take, nurture them and convert them easier than ever before. We're solving a huge time problem, meaning our sales and marketing teams are saving so much time with Hubspot."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 19, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a powerful tool that brings all of your marketing tools into one location, allowing for powerful collaboration efforts and marketing plans that involved different channels seamlessly.", "What do you dislike?": "The price is very high, so it's obviously not something for all businesses. It also takes a long time to set-up and onboard properly, so it can be tough to really take advantage of the powerful platform for the first 6+ months.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you are prepared to invest the time and money in the platform. Not only to set it up properly, but to be able to take advantage of all its tools. If you are not interested in doing email marketing, for instance, then it might not be worth it to use Hubspot. However, if you are ready and able to expand your marketing efforts then it is a powerful product that can provide results.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to better execute and track our marketing efforts (blogging, email marketing, social media, CRM, etc.). This has allowed us to have better data to make decisions, and ensure things don't fall through the cracks."}}
{"author": ["Michael S"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Analyst"], "date": ["Feb 19, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot can be very intuitive and easily integrates with almost everything. It's a trustworthy resource for setting up marketing resources and determining marketing effectiveness. Workflows are both easy and powerful, making the job much simpler.", "What do you dislike?": "Wish I could see more data from the ad managers - almost like a BI tool. Want to compare spend, cohorts, etc.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Setting up marketing resources, understanding lead flow, and determining whether marketing resources are being spent effectively."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The user-friendliness of the tool is my favorite part. It doesn't take long at all for a new user to get acclimated.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish it wasn't so expensive or that the social media tools were included in the non-professional level. Most of those I recommend this tool to, are looking for that and it's too expensive for them.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I love being able to see my YouTube analytics in Social - talk about a time saver. I also love being able to respond to all of my new Twitter followers from within the tool. I wish that was available for my other social channels as well."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has really been beneficial condensing our operations (we're a small 40 person start-up).  It's great to have all our activity and marketing area flowing into one hub in order to optimize our efforts company-wide. ", "What do you dislike?": "Reporting is still difficult for use to customize - our business model (freemium software) doesn't fit the traditional marketing/sales structure, so flexibility is lacking in that area. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "We really benefitted when we pulled the trigger doing the advanced onboarding. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Segmenting our prospecting and reaching out to our user base.  Again, having all automation and data live in one spot has been really beneficial to weigh the overall success of campaigns."}}
{"author": ["User in Events Services"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Love the organization of all my contacts and their companies.  Makes it very easy to go in and search for someone.  I also love the tasks feature.  But, my favorite feature is the email tracking and notifications.  It is super helpful that I can see when someone opens my email or even when they click on a document I attached.", "What do you dislike?": "I think the pipeline side of it all could be handled a little better.  I had a better experience with PipeDrive as far as that side of it all goes.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It is helping us learn what works and doesn't work.  With the email tracking we can see which emails are being opened and clicked and which aren't getting a response."}}
{"author": ["Ney L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Social Media Analyst", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Sep 07, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I like the best on Hubspot is that I can do 90% of my job without any other application. I can integrate everything into one platform. Not only all the resources I need to o my job, but I can use it and share it with my company so that everyone can have everything on just one platform.", "What do you dislike?": "The email marketing and landing page builders are not that flexible, so I have to work hard to get the best out of it, which makes me lose some time on things that would be easier.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are looking for a complete solution for implementing, managing and analyzing your digital marketing campaigns, Hubspot is the right one for you.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The first one and more important business problem I am solving with Hubspot are the time. I can save a lot of time centralizing almost everything in one platform, and we know that every modern marketer needs more time to put everything together. It's easy when you change your staff, when you hire new employees or when you are trying to find something. Since building customized reports, to track sales activities, you can do on one platform. The benefit that I have got from Hubspot is that as everything is integrated, you can have a better understanding of your campaigns, your results and it's all there. Once you have it, you can't live without Hubspot anymore. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Building Materials"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 07, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how easy it is to use and you don't have to be an IT wizz to use the system. It is  very comprehensive at the same time as it is easy to use. We used another competing platform before hubspot and what took us 6 months to get to (with the additional professional services/onboarding we had to pay for), we did more in 6 weeks with hubspot with no additional professional services fees and self implementation (they gave us a success manager to help guide us at no extra charge).", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't a whole lot to dislike, but I would love to see a native ERP platform for manufacturing built into the system. I believe you can connect an erp to hubspot with different connectors or through their API but I like the Idea of one system for everything.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Just go for it. Also it helps if you have someone dedicated to using the system regularly to make sure you are getting max ROI on it, as is the case with any marketing automation system.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Helping our marketing team have a unified approach to our marketing efforts and generate high quality leads that sales can act on immediately. Also taking the complexity out of digital marketing, just making our whole marketing effort easier and less complex."}}
{"author": ["Brenda C"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": ["System Engineer", "Food & Beverages"], "date": ["Oct 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Integrate each Marketing platform in our company, blogs and workflows can be easily created, everything can be managed from a marketing portal.", "What do you dislike?": "There are few drawbacks that can be seen in this software as you will not get the full valos of the campaign if you are producing separate content that prices are somewhat high.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "In general we were able to change the generation of the Leads to include Hubspot in the main software, after that the growth has always been constant.\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a very useful tool for managing contacts in the company. I really like how the data shows and the metrics it delivers. ", "What do you dislike?": "Similarly, I believe that the Landing Pages creation system is too limited. It has a lot of black box that does not give developers freedom to integrate it with other tools.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I recommend Hubspot because it is good software. It is very complete and useful for work in the inbound cycle. It allows you to manage everything in one place.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has helped us manage an optimized flow of our customers' management with the inbound cycle."}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 07, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Customer support is quite responsive and fast, workflows are versatile, great as a database of lead history and contact data, email and social media tools are effective and easy to use", "What do you dislike?": "Occasional service outages, flawed integrations with some other platforms, and frustrating link-shortening in social media (all links are automatically shortened, either with our Bitly account or their in-app service. Even if we repost the same content, the link is re-shortened which burns through our quota of custom Bitly links each month), landing page builder is obtuse and extraordinarily difficult to customize ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The versatility of workflows has proven to be very helpful to automate marketing emails and assigning leads to our business development team, particularly because we get leads from many different channels and tailor our marketing for each. Without Hubspot, this process would be far more time-consuming and less precise. "}}
{"author": ["Brian G"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Chief Revenue Officer", "Executive Office"], "date": ["Oct 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the way I can see the whole package of a deal on one page.  I use the PIN attribute to keep the focus of the deal in view while taking notes on phone calls.  It helps keep me focused on the deal.", "What do you dislike?": "The cost of add-ons is too high.  There are a lot of great add-ons for email marketing and social marketing that are too expensive for a small startup.  It would be better if there were scaled pricing based on the number of employees or revenue.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "awesome product", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are running our sales org on Hubspot.  We don't use security so that everyone can see everyone's deals and contribute if there is another connection potential. "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Internal Consultant in Computer Networking"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 18, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the automated process which  sales is a cloud-based sales automation software designed to build, automate and accelerate the sales process and it very effective in what I know ", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing for now the software is okay and works perfectly well it has unique features which enables sales process very easy and to be managed ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is fantastic product and very effective it has valve for its money and helps in solving problem very easily ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I used it in sales marketing and its very effective and am getting very positive results for me to track scales  and get daily reports "}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how clearly everything is explained in a real-world context. Examples are always helpful for learning, and the videos are full of them. Also, everyone seems passionate about the topics, especially other \"guests\" that are brought into the videos. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish transcripts were available for everything everyone says. It would help for studying and clarifying definitions. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's worth the time to learn the software.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As a you marketing student excited to break into the marketing field, I have realized the benefit of being able to bring lots of knowledge to interviews and internship tasks. My familiarity with many of the most relevant marketing topics has been impressive and helped me stand out."}}
{"author": ["Sam G"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["President of HOCOA San Diego", "Consumer Services"], "date": ["Jan 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The face that it will alert me when I need to follow up.  Or my team.  ", "What do you dislike?": "It's a little confusing at first to setup.  But once you are up and running, it's a breeze.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are starting out, want to keep your overhead low, this is a great tool.  It can grow as your company does.  If you need more tools and features, you can add as you like.  Very affordable and can be robust", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Being able to keep all of my prospects in one place at a very low investment and much better than using excel"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "You get great overview metrics that give you a solid sense of how well your blog, blog posts and other content is performing.", "What do you dislike?": "The integration between HubSpot and WordPress isn't ideal. You're limited with how deep you can go with analyzing content data across these platforms. It seems HubSpot would prefer you host your blog with them and, therefore, could be intentionally leaving limitations in place to get you to switch. We tried to, then HubSpot said our site was too comolex, so we're kind of stuck with what we have.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Mainly email campaigns and CRM-Related stuff. I wish we could leverage with better for content marketing."}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We did not get a chance to use it so can't say", "What do you dislike?": "- Did not meet our marketing needs for A/B testing -  not as easy as other tools and required \"work-arounds\"\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "- Was going to require a partner to setup whereas we can easily use other tools that are easier to setup and get data in/out", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our marketing director selected this product and then left. We tried to use it but the cost/time to implement was more than we were willing to do.  We could not get out of our year contract - which I guess we signed so stuck with.  I would just never work with a company that requires a year long contract and no option to get out.  Only option was to spend more money and we did not feel it could meet our marketing needs for A/B testing.  As a startup, we should not have initially made this decision and I would not recommend buying any product for a year long commitment without some time of extensive trial or POC stage. "}}
{"author": ["User in Retail"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The versatality of Hubspot is awesome. There are so many things you can do with this program to help push the goals of your company forward.", "What do you dislike?": "I sometimes have trouble working within the limitations in design.  I wish there were more options or flexibility to create.  Sometimes I also find that you have to figure processes out, and that there's no one simple and straightforward way to do something. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Fabulous product for getting feet wet within consumer marketing products.  Definitely will keep you busy not only figuring but making use of the tools available like automation, landing pages, groups, etc.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We've been able to utilize it a lot for landing pages and keeping up with our audience. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 13, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really appreciate the 'all-in-one' aspect of HubSpot's marketing software and its ease of use, but what I love the most is HubSpot's support, all the R&D they do, the learning center, and the fact that HubSpot \"drinks their own kool-aid\" - most EVERYTHING they promote/encourage is something they themselves have done.", "What do you dislike?": "There's not much, but sometimes with the 'all-in-one' software, you're able to find more features and functionalities with another standalone software...however, in my experience, HubSpot is already working on these \"setbacks\" and/or they integrate with the standalone software. Another \"issue\" is how frequently the product is updated so you have to stay on top of these updates to get the most out of the software (this is really not a big issue, but a consideration)", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Just do it. :)\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "(of course if it makes sense for your company and its business model)"}}
{"author": ["Sarah C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["VP, Client Services"], "date": ["Nov 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Everything is in one place and easy to integrate. While working on a campaign, you can create landing page, schedule social, create redirects and CTAs all in Hubspot.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish page editing was a little more intuitive. But I have enjoyed learning, and the resources are great.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Helping track leads and keep everything in one place."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The interface is easy to use and intuitive. It doesn't take much time to learn how to set up a workflow, email campaign, landing page, or anything else! There's lots of great resources with step-by-step instructions and recommendations to help you roll out various campaigns. ", "What do you dislike?": "HubSpot forms don't link up with Google Analytics. They want you to use their proprietary tracking.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We had to outsource to a developer to create some complicated custom programming to get our Analytics working for Ads."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how easy Hubspot is to use. Once I went through all the trainer and actually started using most of the features available it became my best friend! I love creating workflows, landing pages, custom create emails, track the leads and schedule social media content. ", "What do you dislike?": "It takes a while to get used to the system. You will actually need to study and learn certain skills. It isnt completely intuitive. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great CRM System! You won't regret it! ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our website is created via Hubspot, we use it to create landing pages, track leads, new contacts, and manage our social media channels. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has an unbeatable customer success team, which is perhaps the biggest differentiator from their competitors (who will often charge you when you need help). They set the bar high and exceed it every time.", "What do you dislike?": "Since Hubspot started as a contacts-based system, reporting from an account-based view can be incredibly difficult. They're constantly improving reporting functionality relative to their Companies and Deals categories, but it's still pretty far behind the competition for comprehensiveness. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Absolutely do it. It's worth evaluating against other competitors if you are a larger business-- if I worked for a company that could afford an entire marketing automation team, I would likely consider Marketo over Hubspot. For the growing marketing team, however, Hubspot is priceless. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We joined Hubspot after using Pardot with no success, and I have to say that it completely transformed our small marketing team's capabilities. Social media management, organized file storage for content and design, workflow automation and comprehensive campaign support... there is not one part of our marketing efforts that has not been vastly improved by switching to Hubspot"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Love the shortening of links, I like seeing who new Twitter followers are - would be nice to see that for LinkedIn and Facebook followers. Like seeing easily what conversations & mentions are featured. ", "What do you dislike?": "Can't tag people in LinkedIn & Facebook like you can with Twitter. Unable to use polls features on Facebook and Twitter. Analytics are sometimes off from what Google analytics says. Often a few hours lag between when we're mentioned on social media and when I see it in the Hubspot feed. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm able to manage my company's social media accounts and bulk schedule posts with ease. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I work in HubSpot every single day and the ease of use really makes my job much better! HubSpot makes marketing efforts more effective! The capabilities within the software are never-ending! I love being able to segment our different markets using HubSpot filters!", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that once a contact's email is unsubscribed you are never able to email them again in the future. It is a little nerve wrecking to know what one you import fields that they could be permanently over-written. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Worth all of the back work it takes to get it set up the way it works best for your business! ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our business is now able to thrive using marketing automation. We are able to create email templates and build out multiple emails to send very easily. I love being able to schedule emails based on date and time as well as time zones. Creating emailing lists and segmenting your different customers is very beneficial in our business!"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Setting up automation workflows can be complicated, but Hubspot makes it easy, and helps lay the groundwork for you with lots of suggestions and tips. ", "What do you dislike?": "I don't dislike anything, but Hubspot truly is an all-in-one platform, which means there is a LOT going on. There are so many different tools and functionality that the on-boarding process can be time consuming.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "You are provided with an onboarding liaison for three months. Take advantage of this person as much as possible, they really help you get up and running and are very quick to respond to any questions or roadblocks.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are a very small marketing department, so bringing more automation to all of our efforts makes us seem like a bigger operation. We're able to do more with less people. It's especially valuable for a startup with limited resources."}}
{"author": ["Cole E"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Associate Marketing Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 22, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The internal menus are clean and snappy. Objects are where you expect to find them and reporting is built into the views. You can't help but digest how well you're performing even while you're just doing administrative tasks.", "What do you dislike?": "The actual reporting tool is a little harder to use and optimize. It's confusing to get answers to questions you might have unless you have a deep understanding of how things are connected on the back end. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "You'll not find a better support team in the space. I could call them up and get an answer to my questions within minutes, instead of spending hours digging through forums. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Make sure you have clear naming conventions and use dynamic content to its full potential. "}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 08, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use, easy to understand, can do almost everything from one platform. Building landing pages, blogs, website, workflows and more under one roof is really nice. We don't have to go anywhere else except HubSpot for (almost) all of our needs.", "What do you dislike?": "The add-on's can be a little ridiculous. You would think it would come with SSL, but that is an add-on per month. It seems a little over the top. Also, the Ads add-on is really lacking, I think it is being developed more, but it is not worth the price at all. We did a trial and cancelled it. Not in-depth, and leaves out Twitter so you still have to reach another website.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have been able to get marketing projects done so much faster without any need from an engineering team. Once we get our website moved over, we will have everything moving more quickly. We can run campaigns and see their results with the touch of a button. I feel much more knowledgable about how we are doing as a department."}}
{"author": ["Shawn l"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot offers a plethora of features great for business.  The CRM is easily adaptable for our companies needs, The blog feature is used for three of our companies blogs, and the support they offer is great and fast.", "What do you dislike?": "There are certain coding aspects of hubspot that can be hard to utilize with our backend.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot helps to tie all of our sales reps together under a great platform and has great social media options for our company as well."}}
{"author": ["Lola D"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The integration of the Sales, CRM and Marketing tool and the design of the software as well as the functionality of the dashboards in each tool available on the software", "What do you dislike?": "There are some logic features not available when it comes to integrating workflows, sequences and emailing newsletters", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Analyze your goals, talk frankly with the support and sales team to qualify your decision, be ready for a 3 month set up and on boarding process", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automatization of processes, conversions of contacts and social media management"}}
{"author": ["Alyssa Z"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Associate Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I use Hubspot every single day for marketing and workflow automation. It is easy to use and streamlines campaigns. My team can all work on it together in an efficient matter. Having everything in one spot has been amazing", "What do you dislike?": "There isnt really anything that I dislike about Hubspot. The cost can be pretty high, but I think it is well worth it for a medium-large sized company", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Workflow automation, list segmentation, social media publishing and report, lead generation"}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The true value of HubSpot Marketing is the integration of every marketing platform. Blogs, email, landing pages, workflows and more can easily be created - and integrated - for an easy to use, all in one marketing portal.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Primarily, my company uses HubSpot to quickly build and publish blog posts. With the built-in social media tool, you can easily share the blog post to your audiences. Then, you can repurpose the content you already created for an email campaign.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Nirav S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["SEO Analyst"], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The best part about HubSpot is sequencing the emails. Customisation using template creation is another beautiful feature crafted by HubSpot. They also have a feature to manage global database. ", "What do you dislike?": "The only drawback is the price for the tool. Also, many a times the tool gets disconnected with gmail. Notifications has some error because at times it shows older notification as new one.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you do not have any budget constraint then this is the best tool.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It has helped us as a CRM tool, for marketing analytics, marketing automation, and managing customer database."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 04, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that I can do it in my own time at my own pace. It\u2019s really useful and I think a great tool. I like that you can go back and reference what you need in their education videos any time. ", "What do you dislike?": "The girl who runs the email marketing videos.  I don\u2019t need the acting and such. Just here for the information. Other than that, which isn't even that horrible I don't dislike anything.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely use it! Its great, easy to navigate, will help you accomplish your business goals quickly. I think Hubspot is great for any type of business. I have used it both in a general marketing environment, and then marketing within a Financial firm, a more niche environment. Hubspot has successfully served me for my needs in both very different jobs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing. How to send more receiver focused emails and better communicate with the customer. We as a team have learned how to make the emails more personal and better geared towards the customers thinking. "}}
{"author": ["Dustin W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Ambassador Success Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Jul 13, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "A wide array of tools to address thousands of new and existing contacts in many different ways based on where they are in their buyer journey.", "What do you dislike?": "Some tools are newer than others and there are still features waiting to be added.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot can fill a lot of needs. It's worth looking at how you can reduce the number of tools you use by keeping it all on one platform.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot drives all of our marketing and sales efforts thanks to a thoughtful integration with Salesforce."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how everything is very simple, and user friendly. It has so many different options to achieve  my tasks, and is very customizable! ", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't too much I dislike about hubspot. The only issue I have with the platform is that I do not currently have authorizations for certain parts, like scheduling emails or publishing landing pages.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I mostly use huspot for marketing campaigns. One of my favorite aspects of hubspot is that you can see the marketing analytics. It is very beneficial to see where leads come from, specifically from different social platforms. "}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Updates and new email marketing campaigns can be set up and executed with minimal training.", "What do you dislike?": "No downsides yet, have been using the product for almost a year.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would recommend using Hubspot, it's a great tool for mid to upper mid market clients. Larger enterprise clients might require a more heavy duty marketing automation platform, depending on number of campaigns run per week.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We've been able to launch and see more success with Hubspot that we had in the past with Marketo, and targeting specific industries with unique messaging can be completed in minutes."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Using HubSpot has ensured that we are constantly thinking about every part of the user journey through every campaign. There learning centre and community support are invaluable for best practices and seeing what other people are trying to do with the software. There are a hundred different ways of executing a marketing strategy in HubSpot and that is its biggest strength. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are so many aspects of the suite it is hard to keep up with all the changes, especially small changes that are not highly publicised but a lifesaver for you.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Much better data analytics and understanding of our users attitudes. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that all the marketing automation tools are under one roof \u2013 it's a robust software set that allows for CRM to forms to email automation and landing page building.", "What do you dislike?": "The lack of new designs in the marketplace. The designs are becoming somewhat dated and are not as plug and play as other options in the market \u2013 especially on the landing page side. It would be nice to have a builder more like Unbounce.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's a solid option for CRM and marketing automation.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using Hubspot for our email marketing, lead gen, and CRM."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 28, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot was the most user friendly CRM platform I have ever used! The filters were simple, and I loved that I could save them. I worked in multiple territories, so this helped me easily keep track of my best prospects in every city. I enjoyed how the individual prospect pages were organized, where all of the communication was organized over a timeline. I personally think that SDR roles have outgrown the \"spray and pray\" technique were you mass email in people in cadences (like on Salesloft). ", "What do you dislike?": "Not much. I will say upper management had issues with there being a lack of analytics, but since we have switched to a platform with it-they OBSESS over it. We spend way too many wasted hours in meetings because they saw a 3% drop in calls on Fridays (translation=we had about 10 less calls made!!).", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would improve your analytics to keep customers! User wise (sdrs and marketing) you are doing great, but management wanted more control over our reach out. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I think it gives you the chance to offer a more personal approach to prospects, because it doesn't offer all of these bells and whistles features."}}
{"author": ["Kelly P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Account Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Pages a simple to create and maintain, and also fully customisable to our design. ", "What do you dislike?": "We use translated pages, which is a great feature, however this consequently means we cannot make use of the staging feature. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Managing the website through the marketing team, having full control over the website without the reliance on IT or tech teams. "}}
{"author": ["McClintock E"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Technology Department Administrative Assistant"], "date": ["Dec 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The features. Hubspot is packed full of features to automate our marketing process. We're still learning everything it can do but keep stumbling on new things every day.", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing at this point. We're still going through the on-boarding process but so far the experience has been great.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great for beginner or experienced marketers. Especially useful for companies with limited human resources to dedicate to marketing.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Brand awareness. Cross-selling & Upselling. Content marketing. We're coming from nearly no existing marketing efforts. We're still early on but can see a ton of untapped potential that hubspot will bring for us."}}
{"author": ["BB F"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Designated Broker"], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that everything is integrated, the whole team is synced together, using the same content for marketing, lead nurturing, and sales follow up.  ", "What do you dislike?": "The learning curve is high.  Sales people hate CRMs, but of the ones we've tried, HubSpot seems to be having the greatest impact.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take the Courses", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing to Sales hand off\r"}}
{"author": ["Consultant"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I liked about hubspot is the plethora of options they offer for email marketing and landing pages. They suite of tools is unique and complete, and they can most likely do what you are trying to achieve for your email marketing needs. Their support is also top notch, and they will even do things for you in your own account!", "What do you dislike?": "They platform feels a little bit outdated and clunky. It can sometimes take a while to achieve what you are trying to do, and it happened a couple times where we just couldn't do what we wanted to do, and their support team wasn't able to help at all. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are looking at Hubspot, I would recommend checking out Klaviyo as well. They offer advanced marketing automation that may fit your needs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing automation, email marketing campaigns, landing pages"}}
{"author": ["Nicolette B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Associate", "Facilities Services"], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Definitely eases all marketing processes and offers easy to use reporting tools and numbers. Also any questions you have from support are answered quickly and efficiently, often providing solutions that go beyond my expectations.", "What do you dislike?": "There are a lot of product changes that often feel unnecessary.  They often decide what we should be paying attention to, rather than our own needs (Keyword tool).  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Creating workflows to automate and simplify the sales funnel and distribution of our content. Campaigns have become more organized as well."}}
{"author": ["Thao N"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing and Sales Assistant", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 14, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really like that the navigation around Hubspot is intuitive and easy-to-use. I especially love the email automation and bulk social media upload features.", "What do you dislike?": "The only thing I dislike is how the workflows are visually laid out. I don't enjoy having to scroll back and forth, and having to zoom in and out all the time on more long-winded workflows.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using HubSpot to manage our online presence and it's been great. Building out our actual website, posting to our blog, uploading and scheduling social media posts, and automating our emails have been very beneficial to our company."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot captures the foundational needs of many small businesses with an all in one crm/marketing automation/seo tool. When I am a team of two with a sales group, it is my go-to answer. Everything is in one place and they work hard at making it better all the time", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot strives to become a salesforce with huge walled gardens when they just do not have the same capabilities. Hubspot cannot be an smb tool but still own data and make it hard to connect outside apis when you want to extract. I often find myself using zapier to transfer information to outside sources because hubspot restricted structured data import practices.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Be sure your team is ready for an all in one software, hubspot is hard to mix in with outside softwares", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I run the entire top of the funnel and drip marketing for my team through hubspot at the core. Our sales team does not use hubspot for their own sales org so I have to transfer all data constantly to salesforce as well. Hubspot serves as my back of the house database for managing all email, social and seo with website management. "}}
{"author": ["Consultant in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 25, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Form collecting is a breeze and user information is the basis for all great marketing.", "What do you dislike?": "The customization is a bit clunky as you have to be familiar with the \"Hubspot shortcodes\" so to speak which can be frustrating if you are a web developer.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The overall product is a bit pricey and add ons can get you throwing large amounts of money into this product quarterly, however, if you sit down and have a plan before going into this product, you can get exactly what you and your clients will need all in one place. If you do go with this I would consider using it to run your website rather than trying to use a customized template from an outside product as the styles are a bit of a hassle to match up.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation is easy with all of the integration built into Hubspot. We are able to connect so many different tools and let Hubspot do the rest."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "As a growing startup with a small marketing team of three people, HubSpot is a critical tool in our stack for hosting our blog content, posting social, and disseminating emails to multiple key audiences - all in one location. I definitely appreciate how comprehensive the platform is.", "What do you dislike?": "The inability to tag individuals when scheduling LinkedIn posts directly from HubSpot is frustrating, as is the process of tagging company handles, which does not always work well. The design side of emails is also difficult for our designer to work with. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely consider the integrations with other tools in your tech stack ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As a small marketing team, HubSpot enables us to do many activities, all in one portal. A/B testing is helping us identify preferences for emails and the analytics provide us with insight into what content is working the best. "}}
{"author": ["Cassandra P"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Partner"], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The continued learning that you receive from Hubspot is fantastic. They are continually updating the lessons with the changes being put forward by the various platforms. The help centre is amazing! They are responsive and extremely helpful so that whatever issue or question that you have is taken care of.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes they prioritize other training updates over others. SEO certification needs to happen!! ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It may feel overwhelming at first but take the time to go through the training and work with the system. It helps on every level.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I use Hubspot to the full extent from Sales to Marketing to Website management. I love that it is a one-stop for everything."}}
{"author": ["Carol R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Communications Specialist"], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "With everything in one place, we can track all tactics by campaign. The platform is very flexible and user-friendly. The training videos were awesome and the service is exceptional!", "What do you dislike?": "What's not to like? Hubspot is great! It's expensive, but fits our budget.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I save time building forms, email, landing pages and scheduling social media posts. Best of all, everything is tracked!"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "its an easy and fast way to keep your social media channels in one single place. It is also great to have the possibility to schedule these posts so you don't have to update them every day", "What do you dislike?": "That is not possible to add videos on the Instagram channel through hubspot.. so I have to do this with the phone.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "don't hesitate about using Hubspot! it's a very nice Plattform and system to use at your company and also has a great customer support", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "it helps my work to be faster and precise. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the fact I can access a directory of current and potential clients. I also like that I am able to see all interactions that have occurred. ", "What do you dislike?": "I do not like that you cannot filter (as far as I'm aware) contacts by who have been interacted with and who have not. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am able to keep a large collection of clients all in one spot and am able to see all my interactions with them. I realized that I can see what kind of interactions work best with certain potential clients. This can be used to cater my outreach. "}}
{"author": ["Vivian P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Content Creator "], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Being able to schedule multiple social media posts at the same time. And assign them to different campaigns.", "What do you dislike?": "GIFs don\u2019t work on Facebook when you post them through Hubspot. You also are limited in terms of what you can do unatively versus natively.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am able to keep track of what I\u2019ve posted as well  as their performance on social media. "}}
{"author": ["Katie K"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Operations Specialist"], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is a huge asset to our company! It allows us to manage multiple aspects of our digital marketing efforts without paying expensive developers. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the templates can be hard to manipulate without experts. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to offer our colleagues personalized webpages without building out a separate website. Content management is also a very nice perk to this platform. "}}
{"author": ["Felix A"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Real Estate Consultant", "Construction"], "date": ["Aug 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "You can plan and manage your  activities very effectively ", "What do you dislike?": "I think there isn't anything I would say I dislike about  Hubspot", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would advice other companies to  use or rather try hubspot", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The benefits are many\r"}}
{"author": ["User in Animation"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot allows me to create custom GUI's so our content creators who aren't comfortable with HTML code are able to add and edit content without having to go through me.", "What do you dislike?": "It would help me a lot if HubSpot made it possible to use personalisation tokens in email IF statements.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Best tool for what it does out there, especially for designer/developers.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I often have had to make changes to templates, or alternative templates, when another team's requirements change. In HubSpot modules, I can create a toggle so we still have a universal template that content creators can adjust to suit their needs."}}
{"author": ["User in Higher Education"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 14, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "They're very customer oriented. Extremely supportive in terms of features. While these actions are not done natively, there are several eCommerce integrations available (i.e. Zapier, Magento, Bigcommerce) that make HubSpot a great match for selling tangible products.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Companies that sell products find HubSpot extremely useful because they can track which products their customers are considering and serve them relevant content that helps them make a purchasing decision. They can also track behaviors and set up abandoned cart emails to close more sales.\r"}}
{"author": ["Mohamed Poujul Ameen S"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["UI Team Lead", "E-Learning"], "date": ["Oct 30, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The custom module concept of HubSpot saves a lot of time and is very intuitive. ", "What do you dislike?": "Inbuilt latest version of Bootstrap version is not available", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot when implemented using a experienced Partner can show its value very quickly", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot CMS helped save a lot of man hours in recreating landing pages for multiple campaigns and events"}}
{"author": ["William D. D"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Sales & Marketing Operations", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The simplicity. HubSpot takes tasks that used to be quite cumbersome and turns them into easy projects. The way it connects sales and marketing is honestly amazing and I can't imagine using any other tool.", "What do you dislike?": "I can't think of anything I dislike about HubSpot. I guess maybe sometimes the website is slow?", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The customer service team they have is second to none. They really make sure you get your moneys worth and are so incredibly helpful we strive to be as good as them.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Creating landing pages and marketing emails faster and easier than ever before."}}
{"author": ["Liudas B"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["Owner", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Aug 30, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "You can control all your marketing all in one place.", "What do you dislike?": "It gets a bit complicated to navigate throughout all the tools.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you need a robust tool to handle all your marketing, then you should check out hubspot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helps to manage my social media marketing efforts all in one place and I also use their website builder. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's amazing having everything in one place. From social media scheduling to content calendars, marketing emails, and contact profiles - everything is a mere click away.", "What do you dislike?": "There are so many different tools and ways to use HubSpot - which is great, but also creates a slight learning curve for new users. Luckily there are so many classes and helpful videos in HubSpot Academy that you'll quickly be finding your way around.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot increased our relationships, communication, and efficiency. It has allowed us to follow up with prospective and current clients much quicker and with more relevant information than in the past. "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Emma M"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Chief Engagement Officer", "Management Consulting"], "date": ["Jul 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot really helps us to organize and grow our relationships with our customers. There is everything that we need in order to organize our email, sales, service, and marketing all in one service, which is fantastic!", "What do you dislike?": "So far, there isn't really anything that we dislike!", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "This is an awesome service and they really walk you through everything you need in order to set it up and generate the leads you need for your business", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing and client organization, as well as marketing analytics"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how you can do everything all on one platform. You are able to schedule social posts, create blog content, upload straight to your website, and monitor all of your insights as well. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that they just recently changed the training program in the education guide. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot is a great tool to use when trying to find an integration platform for your company.  It is great because it pulls data and insights for you, as well as offers educational courses so you and your team can become certified. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are a digital marketing agency that uses hubspot both for ourselves as well as other customers. WE are in the process of getting more clients to use hubspot as well. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that it's easy to use and includes a sales CRM so everything is in one place. Easy to create dashboards, run reports, and share with teammates. Over the past year and a half, HubSpot has made many improvements and moving in the right direction. It's definitely a very modern solution that's appealing to the younger generations. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are some gaps when it comes to a contact vs company vs deal. It would be nice if information flowed through all the way to the deal. Also, when it comes to logging meetings, it would be ideal to have drop downs like there are for other sales activities. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot helps us align our Marketing team with our Sales team. It provides us with full visibility, automates tasks, and streamlines overall processes making us more efficient. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability for automation and connectivity isgreat. Linking whole campaigns together is easy and works well within HubSpot. It's something as an organisation we use a lot. This also makes it easier to report on whole campaigns and incorporating Emails, Landing Pages, CTAs etc.", "What do you dislike?": "The Reporting for campaigns on Social seems to be a bit wrong - not counting posts properly. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Workflows have been a great way for us to qualify leads for our campaigns. We've been able to accurately determine who we should be contacting better with our emails and qualifying people into our own MQL lists."}}
{"author": ["Miko\u0142aj B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing specialist"], "date": ["Jan 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is giantic, powerful tool for marketing and sales management. There are almost everyfthing You may need to proceed stunning, and fully measurable inbound marketing actions.", "What do you dislike?": "There are still some cons in workflows management, that can occur Your work - eg. it's impossible to AB test a workflow or easily redirect users from one place in workflow to another, so sometimes You need to arduously copy the same actions in different branches of workflow.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The HubSpot is really complex tool, so it's good to invest your time in learning tons of HubSpot how-to and documentation pages. Involving developers into implementation process, will also enhance Your benefits from using HS thanks to expanded API integration.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot lets us completely track and measure our users' behaviour and automatize marketing and sales communication to them."}}
{"author": ["Internal Consultant in Computer & Network Security"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Rolled out the free CRM at a small startup. I'm blown away with the functionality, which is intuitive and innovative. IMHO, it's more advanced than Salesforce.com, although I cannot compare the two in terms of scalability and customizability because I have not tested these things with HubSpot.", "What do you dislike?": "For the CRM, I don't see drawbacks. The rest of the platform used to have scaling issues for larger companies about 7 years ago, but I'm unsure if these are still the case today. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great solution for smaller companies (e.g. businesses <$50m in revenue). Definitely evaluate other solutions side by side (Marketo, Eloqua, Salesforce, CMS) for larger companies. Main benefit is the insane level of integration between the parts, which makes life very easy. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Central source of truth for customer contacts, pipeline management, lead capture."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Accounting"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We use HubSpot to track all of our inbound marketing and lead generation efforts - for our firm and our clients. It's great for tracking history of your visitors and using that information to help in the sales process. We also tie that into our email marketing to help automate and personalize the process.", "What do you dislike?": "It can be tough to build-out custom features without having an in-house programmer. Their tech support group does not offer much on the customization side.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Work with an agency that can help customize the product for your specific needs. It will help you realize higher cost and time savings in the long run. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has helped cut down our lead gen process, and improve the quality of leads delivered from our inbound marketing efforts. We have realized a significant ROI from the product, and are always looking for new ways to incorporate its functionality to our parts of our marketing and business development processes. "}}
{"author": ["Agency"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how simple it is to sync up with Gmail, Wordpress, Google Analytics, e-commerce software, Facebook and the list goes on. There is a large number of workflow and integration features available and made simple. Overall, out of using three different CRMs in the past, HubSpot thus far has been the best overall in fulfilling our company's needs. ", "What do you dislike?": "It is quite on the expensive side and the deals and quotes section feel very limited at times. SEO features and design templates can use some work as well, but the main issue to many people I've recommended it to is price. There is a free version, however it is missing a lot of key features such as email templates.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Quick automated emails, tracking and recording conversations by phone and email, and sending out Proposals to clients through deals."}}
{"author": ["Manan E"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Specialist"], "date": ["Jan 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The system is very easy to use and the creators have thought of every element that you would require for your sales and marketing. Right from maintaining tasks, sending emails, running drip campaigns etc. is very easy and intuitive.", "What do you dislike?": "The cost for each section of the app is quite high", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are automating our entire sales and marketing workflows and maintaining all our data in a single place with Hubspot"}}
{"author": ["User in Hospital & Health Care"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is easy-to-use and makes managing all of our marketing activities incredibly easy. We use it to manage our website, landing pages, emails, workflows, and reporting. We have a number of users licensed on the platform, and we're able to collaborate seamlessly. The product is also quite scalable. We've grown quite a bit recently, and Hubspot has been able to grow with us.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish we could segment analytics by business unit. \r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Some templates are not as flexible as we'd like. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have some difficulties with the contacts, but that is mostly an internal issue, not a HubSpot issue."}}
{"author": ["Agency"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is extremely user friendly. It has an easy learning curve, it makes sense for most new users, and because of the simpler learning curve its easier to get into more advanced areas of marketing automation and personalization", "What do you dislike?": "Reporting capabilities aren't fully flushed out. We need to export data from reports to get the data we want. There are also just a couple nuances in the email builder. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is a very comprehensive tools for both sales enablement and marketing automation, so you should really make sure that you are using all available resources accessible to cover your needs. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is our sole platform for email builds. By allowing us to keep our contacts, contact history, emails, all in one place we can create more targeted emails, and start developing actionable marketing insights. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 12, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's amazingly easy to build landing pages and emails, track data, post social, post blogs, and monitor campaigns through HubSpot. The all-in-one feature is wonderfully convenient because it means I'm not bouncing between different sites to build basic marketing campaigns. HubSpot makes it easy to keep everything in ONE place without you losing your mind. Their support is also great!", "What do you dislike?": "Major downside: price. It's hella expensive to keep your website on HubSpot and would be a pain to take it off of HubSpot. Just-marketing plans can still be really pricey, too.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot can't do everything you want it to do to customize your site or campaigns, but it can do a lot. If you suggest a feature for HubSpot to add to its platform, you can post it in a forum, then folks an upvote it for the HubSpot team to review. While it can't do everything we want it to do, it by far does more than any other platform can do. \r"}}
{"author": ["Massiel Alejandra M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Front-end developer"], "date": ["Aug 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot helps me develop my work in a more organised way, since it allows me to personalise which modules I want to work with so it avoids a messy workspace.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubl is not as easy to understand at first, and even if there are many modules, there could be even more -and creating them requires understanding of logic.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Be patient! You'll eventually get the handle of it :)", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I mostly use HubSpot for building websites and landing pages. I like having all the content in just one site but in different templates at the same time."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Automating emails within workflows\r", "What do you dislike?": "Automating social media posting from multiple accounts so you don't even have to think about it\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "So easy to create landing pages, emails, forms, etc.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "There's nothing I dislike - everything works logically & is simple to use"}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Networking"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "For my job keeping track and replying to social queries is paramount, which Hubspot has done a great job helping with. I use Hubspot daily to keep track of hundreds of tweets our company receives weekly and am able to reply to them, retweet and like all in one simple platform. I also really enjoy being able to check out competitors' streams in one click. Hubspot makes monitoring really easy! ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish the platform was as simple and easy for Facebook as it is for Twitter. Right now I feel like Facebook's interface still tackles managing a large volume of messages better", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Keep in mind (at least socially) that right now it won't make all aspects of social platforms easier, managing on Facebook still has it's major advantages with ease of use and analytics available - but this is a great tool especially with Twitter ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Managing a large volume of messages, all of which that need to be responded to hourly. It really cuts down on my clicking around to accomplish social management as well. "}}
{"author": ["Olivia C"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Creative Director & Marketing Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["Dec 15, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Call me brainwashed but I LOVE how transparent this has made our customer touch-point process. Anyone on our team can take a look at our customer contact history and know exactly what was said and what the customer's concerns are.", "What do you dislike?": "How inbound-based the program is. I wish there was a bit of outbound...or just ability to do more outbound process. Also, it is extremely pricey.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Dip your toes in the water with their free program and then see how you want to expand from there!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Workflow automation for our tiny team. Keeping in touch with our clients."}}
{"author": ["Peter D"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Head of Growth", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 15, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use landing page and email creators, intuitive workflows, and for rich reports options.", "What do you dislike?": "Only one type of report for me is missing, and I'm using something like 25 report types at the same time. Second thing - there's no direct integration with Intercom.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "All our website and email marketing activities are done in HubSpot. Benefits:\r"}}
{"author": ["Sarah H"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Jul 27, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We've been using HubSpot for one year, but it's our 2nd automation platform in 4 years. I am a big fan. We used Scribe Online to integrate it with Microsoft Dynamics CRM and we're loving the in-house ability to manipulate that integration. It also has superior landing page and email builders compared to our previous tool, and I'm a big fan of the reporting capabilities (we're on the Enterprise platform). There's also a great online Academy to help with onboarding and ongoing training, and other online forums and local user groups have been very active. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are really just some minor optimizations I'd like to see, primarily to aid with daily navigation and hopping back and forth between different areas of the tool. We also occasionally have some lag time with page loading, but it's infrequent. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I evaluated many systems of many sizes. Some were too big for my team, and some were too small. HubSpot was just right, and there's still a TON that we haven't tapped into. I would highly recommend it to any organization. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using it to manage all inbound efforts - content offers followed by outbound email nurturing - as well as improved tracking of the visitors on our site. We've got some pretty complex workflows in place to trigger the right notifications to different groups based on who/how the individual is assigned in CRM, and that's working really well for us. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 08, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ease of use and great support from their team. Flexible with your needs and very accommodating. The user interface and experience is beautiful, a big step up from Pardot. The organization and intelligence of the system makes your day-to-day much easier in managing information and finding what you need in your content. ", "What do you dislike?": "Limitations with workflows and reports, but both are being worked on :) Also that the sales and marketing sides are kept separate in terms of email notifications to the sales team. It would be helpful if the marketing initiated emails were also flagged to sales as opens and clicks occur - they find that very helpful.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take advantage of their support team. Getting the package with the implementation specialist and customer success manager is worth it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "automating lead nurture and streamlining lead generation. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 28, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the Learning center most to get into the marketing Hub for the beginners and i love the inbound methodology in Hub spot which got automated in a very systematic way which leads to increase productivity and performance of the business organisation. coming to analytics it gives very nice trends to track the performance of very stage. ", "What do you dislike?": "I think its not integrated with some of the websites and functioning as per user friendly interface for the micro websites integration in the Hub spot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is very good tool and great support with some flaws in website UX issues.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As of now we have integrated our HR module and Marketing and Sales funnel and automating the entire marketing and sales funnel in hub spot without more manual interaction.\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We are a \"Mom and Pop\" shop, just my husband and myself. Using HubSpot makes working on the website easy. I can always call support if I don't know how to do something. They are always available and incredibly helpful. Additionally it's easy to set up emails and follow up campaigns for leads. HubSpot has so many features built in, it's great.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't have any real dislikes about Hubspot. We haven't run into anything that can't be taken care of.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Happy with the website platform and building tools. Great email capability. Great tracking capability."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 25, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "In all seriousness, Hubspot is great. I've been currently using at my job for about a month and I can't express how cool it is. It's like MailChimp, HootSuite & Google Analytics all rolled up in a beautiful package ready to muscle through any the of digital marketing. I will say it took me a good week long learning curve to figure out how everything links together. Also, some of their steps seem redundant such making a new template every time you want to you want to add an extra block of text. More than that! Hubspot host a yearly conference & it's such an amazing experience.", "What do you dislike?": "That you have to make a new template every time you want to add something simple like an extra text block. Also, when they make an update to the platform, it really slows you down trying to find everything again. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take your time learning it. It's like a bicycle, it seems very complicated in the beginning, but once you got it, it totally clicks! The videos and certifications help tremendously, so please don't overlook that valuable resource. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm currently not having many issues with HubSpot, except navigation. But all in all search function within the site makes it easy to find files, templates, and tools. The search function is not only smooth but helpful. Also, they have educational courses on how to use their program that comes with certificate, which is perfect resume builder!"}}
{"author": ["Andrew F"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Web Designer/Developer"], "date": ["Feb 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is the best all-encompassing digital marketing platform I've ever used.", "What do you dislike?": "They seemed to have done a major revamp of their UI recently, which looks amazing. A few of the view are still using the old UI so I hope they roll out the new versions soon.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The ability to group and segment our audience based on their actions and data across multiple platforms (email, website, social, etc.)"}}
{"author": ["Anirudhan V"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development Associate", "Accounting"], "date": ["Jan 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "- The various reports and the ability to create reports easily\r", "What do you dislike?": "- The Plugins make data and deal entry so much easier\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "- It offers everything a start up needs in its free version\r"}}
{"author": ["Madeline D"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Sales and Marketing Operations Analyst ", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Jan 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that Hubspot is user friendly and easy to learn. Furthermore, it can be used and be useful for all levels of experience across our whole marketing team. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that it does not have many integration option. If Hubspot could offer a few more high quality out of system integrations it would be great.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are using Hubspot as your Marketing Automation and Website building tool and are a SMB I think you will find value. But if you are not using Hubspot for website building and are using a CRM that offers a similar tool then I would use that over Hubspot. The lacking of Hubspot integrations with other systems makes it difficult to have all your information consolidated. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use Hubspot mainly for Marketing Automation"}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The email reports are easy to digest and have interesting information. The Hubspot Academy free training is great and the customer support team is easy to get on the phone and very helpful!", "What do you dislike?": "There are a few specific features that I am surprised Hubspot can't do--for example, when uploading a contact there isn't a way to prevent it from writing over old data--as a previous Eloqua user this was a feature I took for granted. I also preferred the drag and drop editing of Eloqua over the templates in Hubspot. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "While they are always making changes and improvements, every once in a while I find something that I feel like should be simple to do isn't a feature.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use Hubspot to communicate with our customers and prospects and track their engagement overall. It's been great to reports on social media, website, landing pages all in one place.  "}}
{"author": ["Suhas S"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Online Marketing Manager"], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is one of those tools which is user friendly, packed with many useful features to manage multiple tasks at one place. And backed by world class support team who are always helpful", "What do you dislike?": "Few features in terms of segementation can be improved, may be make it easier to pull out data.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Sending marketing communication,Managing social media channels, Hosting pages and Workflow management"}}
{"author": ["Felice F"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's very intuitive and easy to use and it's brilliant having virtually all parts of digital marketing in 1 place.", "What do you dislike?": "Functionality is sometimes a bit less than if you would use spot solutions. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I'd recommend anyone looking for a new Marketing Automation/CRM software to start by defining their own current and ideal process. It's such an important system to get right, and it needs to fit your current and future needs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It gives us all the tools we need to attract and convert leads into customers in an efficient and effective way."}}
{"author": ["Debbie W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder/Chief Content Officer", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 28, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot makes it easy to manage your entire online presence in one place. From website to landing pages, or social media channels, blog, emails and lead generation, everything is tied together for you to measure success and analyze results. The educational offers are amazing, and there is so much great content to help you, it's almost hard to stay on top of.  It's very user friendly yet constantly evolving. ", "What do you dislike?": "The social monitoring tools are not the most ideal. Using Twitter lists in the channel is much more effective. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot is the tool to use if you are serious about inbound, and leveraging results from content marketing to make smarter decisions. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead generation, site and content optimization, SEO, content publishing.. all in one place. We are a HubSpot agency partner and work 100% inbound for us, and our clients. "}}
{"author": ["Katherine Z"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development Executive", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Jun 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that Hubspot is able to sync up with Outlook and track emails to prospects in Hubspot- it is nice to be able to review previous emails sent, what emails were clicked on. It is helpful to see what messaging or subject title might have sparked an interest from a prospective client.", "What do you dislike?": "It is not a great overall sales tool compared to SalesForce. The notes category where you put notes from a call or meeting, load your message into the main profile.. so you have to sort/scroll down the page often to find your notes mixed in with your email messages. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Good for a marketing department to use-- able to track emails, start to generate data to see what subject lines or messaging is sparking interest. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our marketing department is able to send more email blasts on behalf of our sales team to get a mass email out about training or events we have going on, which we've been able to use that data to gauge what clients are opening emails, if certain messaging is working, etc. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 05, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I don't have massive experience with CRM's but Hubspot was easy to learn and navigate. The one we use at my place of work currently lacks in a lot of areas that Hubspot does quite easily. ", "What do you dislike?": "I think that Hubspot was a little less able to be customised than I would have liked. The options available were good enough, but I feel like if we wanted a very specific system we might have struggled. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you want a CRM that is out the box ready then Hubspot is a good start. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Using the CRM that the company built that failed in almost every respect, Hubspot showed the marketing team how easy it is to manage data. Even the free version of Hubspot was better than what was made. "}}
{"author": ["Agency"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Content calendar organization. It is nice to see a calendar view of when content is pushed, and then have the ability to click on the content to view it. However, it would be nice if you could export this.", "What do you dislike?": "Tool is clunky, and it is hard to export raw data reports. It would be nice if you can export the content calendar, to view marketing efforts within an excel version. It would also be nice to add in marketing activity and links to this activity that were not implemented through HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Website content and marketing content. Also, trying to use it for reporting, but reporting capabilities is not great. There are also large differences in metrics on HubSpot vs Google Analytics (specifically, email clicks to your website vs landings from the email)."}}
{"author": ["joi  g"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that i can call in for support, but don't like that people cannot help. Or call in for 4 days and still not have it figured out. Or person 3 left out information. They tell me to hold on so they can figure out how to use their own system.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot has a lot of things it's not capable of doing. limitations on what you can do.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Pay the extra money and go to Marketo.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "none! Coming from Marketo there are PLENTY of limitations that that hubspot has."}}
{"author": ["David L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Market Development Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Jun 29, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The tool is so easy to use and even if you are not a tech person their support team is always willing to help out! ", "What do you dislike?": "If you are looking to do very complex lead scoring it can be a bit challenging, but overall it is ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are just starting your marketing efforts or have not been happy with your current marketing efforts this is the place to start. They start with the very basics of who you need to market to, what their pain is, and how can you provide them value. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are hosting our website with Hubspot and the ease of tracking page visits, conversion rates and email marketing."}}
{"author": ["Bas Z"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 10, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really enjoy the seamless integration of marketing tools and sales tools. This really supports the idea that the connection of these two jobs are the core driver of your daily business. \r", "What do you dislike?": "Usability of the tools is great and permanently improved. I also value the support and the educational content that HubSpot provides. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Compared to other marketing and sales tools there is not much I dislike. Sometimes I wish the Android App would be as cool as the iPhone App.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It is vital that you and your team understands the idea of inbound. HubSpot is built around the principles of the inbound strategy. "}}
{"author": ["Katie C"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Graphic Designer", "Graphic Design"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I find the platform extremely easy to use and navigate.", "What do you dislike?": "I was very quickly sent to the forum to request help on a design problem when the customer service agent didn't know the answer.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take advantage of the hubspot community for problems. They are very helpful. Also the online education classes are super helpful in the beginning. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It is where our main website is hosted and it is very easy to edit content, webpages and design."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The fact that you're able to test it out for free before you decide to upgrade.", "What do you dislike?": "Still a bit glitchy, but understandable and they're always working on improving it and implementing new features., ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you try before you buy. The one thing that is irritating is that they claim you have up to 1000000 contacts you can manage for free, but this is only if you're using the sales hub. Once you start expanding into the marketing side, you're going to be charged based on the number of contacts you have. Would be great if we could divide the marketing contacts from sales contacts. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're using it as our primary CRM. Has the typical benefits of a full-fledged CRM, with new features always coming."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Cosmetics"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How you can have a million different analytics for what you are working on, seeing that the time and ideas invested to see your company thrive is working and Hubspot is a big part of it.", "What do you dislike?": "That sometimes the images on an email sent does not render well (it happened yesterday) and I have to go back and send it again (in the middle of a meeting) ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do all the certification courses you can before using the tool, it will come in handy.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Seeing how our communications are working or not towards our customers."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How detailed it is to segment contacts in different markets and level of engagement and how much information is possible to get from them with an email campaign, for instance.", "What do you dislike?": "Gather and analyze data properly to know and understand how much impact and revenue a campaign created. Data centralization is not well defined in HubSpot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It takes a lot of work to set up, but when it's done, it is magical!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Content distribution, lead scoring and tracking. Marketing automation is also something that is generating quite good benefits in generating leads and business opportunities."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 07, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Everything is largely intuitive and can be figured out without a lot of extra training.   ", "What do you dislike?": "There is a lot of bifurcation of tiered features that you have to request to be unlocked.  Fewer tiers would be easier to deal with.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use workflows as much as you can, not only to automate email nurtures but also to automate internal processes. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're solving the closed-loop visitor-to-lead-to-opp challenge with a combined Hubspot CoS and marketing hub.   We're more efficient using Hubs as the solution for this, rather than cobbling together several different solutions.   "}}
{"author": ["Caleb J"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Analytics Specialist"], "date": ["Sep 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is very clean, has lots of nice features, and is very easy to use.", "What do you dislike?": "When merging contact records, it doesn't merge the email lists that the contacts are apart of, so either that has to be done manually, or that information is lost, which is bad for email marketing.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Compare to other tools that have a CRM, email campaign manager, social media manager, and sales all in one.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Having a CRM with clean contact data that is easy to access and modify, connecting to email campaigns, social media, and sales deals."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Internet"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really like how easy it is to use HubSpot to segment users based on a few simple users. It's quick and easy to create lists to use to either send emails, report on how they interacted with the site and much more.", "What do you dislike?": "I'm not a fan of the newly organized menus. I've used HubSpot for a while now (5 years?) and the recent update made it harder to find things I was familiar with. Also, the screen seems a little glitchy going between old and new editors.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "They're a great and easy way to market, capture leads, view how visitors interact with your company online and off."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a complete tool that allows you to align your inbound, marketing and sales efforts when you are at a growing stage.  Having everything connected in one unique place saves time and improves the integration between processes. It's easy to use and the learning center is very helpful. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some key integrations are missing, as the one with Likeding Lead Gen Forms. A part from that, maybe the reporting side included without any add on is a bit weak, should be improved in that sense and take more profit of the integration of functionalities to provide also integrated analytics in the reporting. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Try to dedicate time to follow the trainings and videos from the learning center, as some of them provide you insightful tips and recommendations.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm implementing the inbound and content strategy using Hubspot as a CMS and as a platform for all our marketing automation."}}
{"author": ["Jacquelyn K"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Public Relations and Communications"], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Our team can use HubSpot for not only sales, but all of or marketing as well.  We are in the process of transitioning our website to HubSpot too.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes contacts do not transfer over with all of their properties through the onboarding process.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We can now manage all of our social media platforms in one place."}}
{"author": ["Edwin C"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Lead Generation specialist", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Mar 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The search option for every field (Name, company, campaign) is very smooth and easy to navigate. ", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes, the integration of skype call causes delay when you are doping cold calls ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Easy to use and easy to manage for potential contacts for lead generation specialists like me. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to identify the possible need of a particular company based on previous conversation and proper tagging of lead status. We can make multiple leads on one contact as long as the logging of notes is accurate and on point. "}}
{"author": ["Paul B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Logistics Optimization Consultant"], "date": ["May 30, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that the whole history of any prospect or customer is right at your fingertips in the timeline of the CRM.  And it can be filtered by 22 different variables.  I like the dashboards as well, most info is right there to view.", "What do you dislike?": "The dashboards could be more customizable, as they are now, they are limited in what can be shown.  It would be nice if the user could build their own dashboards from available data and not just rely on the pre-fabricated ones that Hubspot provides.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our sales team members were not using our old CRM, it was not user friendly at all. With Hubspot everyone is using it and loving it!"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Harvest is an amazing tool that allows your entire team to seamlessly manage all of your front-facing operations when it comes to keeping your customers happy, closing more deals, and marketing to your customers.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish that they would implement a dark mode for their platform and native apps for the Apple ecosystem of devices.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you have a limited budget and/or need a feature-rich set of tools, Hubspot is the tool that you need.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to solve our CRM, Sales, Marketing, and Customer Service needs with Hubspot."}}
{"author": ["Maresch B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Head of Communications", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Jun 13, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Having all contacts in HubSpot with up-to-date data synced across multiple platforms is great for streamlining external communication. Email marketing and social media management (monitoring, scheduling & reporting) are also surprisingly good for an all under one roof solution. Last but not least, HubSpot Academy is super helpful.", "What do you dislike?": "Prior to HubSpot, I was mostly using more specialized marketing tools like Google Analytics, Buffer or MailChimp that do one thing really well. Compared to these tools, HubSpot is not intuitive and lacks some features. Due to the complexity and structure of HubSpot, it's sometimes difficult to find the feature you're looking for. All in all, HubSpot's look & feel is not very consistent. It feels like a product that has been designed by different product teams.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's probably the best software in its category for startups that want to scale. UX & Product lovers will have a tough time using HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We want to grow awareness for our product, get more leads and help Sales convert them with as little manual work as possible. Having all contacts & data in one place turned out to be the biggest benefit so far. List segmentation and tailored content help me deliver the right content, to the right people at the right time. Being responsible for the external communication of our company, HubSpot is also a convenient way to see how people from other departments like Sales communicate with customers."}}
{"author": ["Irene R"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Owner", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Advanced design and coding abilities using a modular template system. ", "What do you dislike?": "Having to learn a new coding program (Hubl) in order to do web coding.  I think that vendors should be using topensource, robust coding languages, or having that option. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great if you can afford it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I converted a website from WordPress to HubSpot. It had over 500 pages so at first I didn't think it could be done werll. But the amazing support at HubSpot did most the work. Now converted, it is easier to manage, update, and analyze and track. "}}
{"author": ["David D"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Content Manager"], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot offers a wide range of features for sales and marketing automation, making it a good one-stop choice for SMBs.", "What do you dislike?": "The platform can be a bit glitchy at times; for example, I've had trouble from time to time updating contact lists or changing email modules. It doesn't happen consistently, but can be annoying when it does.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot's allowed for smoother integration of marketing and sales processes. We could use it to bring leads from the discovery phase, through to the customer phase, and follow them through the entire process."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Jen S"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Strategist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Mar 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has come along way since the first time I used to this platform for inbound marketing only, about eight years ago. The new analytics capabilities and progressive profiling through smart forms are exceedingly helpful for strategic marketers.", "What do you dislike?": "Lists are a pain to maintain and clean. Building landing pages is complex and time consuming, and a lot of simple tasks have to be done manually by experts. Also, the reporting system is a nightmare. There is no single source way to find and report on all metrics for email social etc. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead scoring and profiling have been exceedingly helpful for my client."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is incredibly comprehensive. With everything that Hubspot is capable of, I'm positive that I'm not using it to its full potential.", "What do you dislike?": "While it can do so much, it's very difficult to learn everything. My team has had to rely heavily on their customer support team which is not always the most helpful. Instead of listening and talking us through our problems, often we're handed one-sheets explaining certain features that we don't need and aren't necessary.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would recommend Hubspot if you are willing to take the time to sit down and learn. Their suite of learning tools is vast and comprehensive but it certainly takes time to sift through. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot covers all the bases for us. It works as our email tool, our webpage creation tool, our gated content creator. It really is a one-stop shop for us."}}
{"author": ["Ashley V"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder", "Consumer Goods"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The usability of the platform and how easy it is to not only create projects and conversion pages, but to be able to track users on the site.  ", "What do you dislike?": "It is a pretty complicated platform, you have to know how to use it and most of the time I feel like I am paying for a lot but not using it to the fullest potential. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use all of the resources provided to learn how to use the system. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing and conversion. \r"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Having everything in one place, contacts, deals, communications, etc is incredibly helpful. The marketing tools (automation, templates, etc) are really user friendly. And the support team is so good. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are some features that we wish were available, certain reports, different ways to sort contacts, etc. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's a really good tool. When starting, definitely take advantage of some of the training they have available. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Having everything on one system is incredibly helpful. It allows everyone to have a big picture of how the business is tracking and that has been good for accountability and progress tracking. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 04, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot easily integrates into my email, calendar, and phone-- making it really easy to unify all communications & sales priorities in one place.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The reporting, pipeline, and interface is also very customizable-- leaving a lot of flexibility to tailor a CRM platform to any team's needs/desired reporting", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Not much to dislike about hubspot.. at least for my team's needs, they are generally met.\r"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 07, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has the easiest databasing software I have ever used! It has got a very clean, simple UX and UI, easy navigation and sharing/report options.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish that the import and export of excel spreadsheets was a little more advanced and integrated as right now I have to manually update change to each contact instead of updating the entire sheet with changes. The import system needs to be a little smarter to recognize the contacts being updated and change the info in the profile instead of duplicating the contacts.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great tool for databasing, record keeping, maintaining a digital directory.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It is mostly used for databasing, record keeping, digital directory, and reports. Our social media team uses the blog section frequently - it has some great content and helps utilize the Hubspot features to the max."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to be able to sync all social platforms in one place and schedule posts in advance. It saves time and effort, plus the bonus is we can monitor interactions over a period of time. ", "What do you dislike?": "Would prefer to have some better deep dive analytics on social. The current analytics is to high level but gives us what we need for now. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I've used a lot of CRM, CMS and email platforms over the years but HubSpot is by far the best in terms of usability, simplicity, interface. From sales, marketing to customer success, these are all housed under one system and ultimately makes my job easier to get things done. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Intention is to build engagement and optimise brand visibility. We've been able to do this through HubSpot."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "You can do a lot with hubspot - CRM, CMS, social management, email marketing are all in one place. ", "What do you dislike?": "Because hubspot does so many things, it doesn\u2019t really do any one thing exceptionally well. I much prefer Wordpress as a CMS and mailchimp for email marketing over hubspot. Also the UI is not intuitive at all, making training new employees more work than ideal.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We\u2019ve downsized our hubspot usage to simply creating forms to embed on our website. Form creation and contact management through the toool is pretty good and embedding works well with our CMS - craft. "}}
{"author": ["Kathy K"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Digital Marketing Manager", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Dec 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Their online university makes the platform easy to learn.", "What do you dislike?": "Not as powerful as Marketo but also not as difficult to learn as Marketo. Their web hosting service can be extremely complex, and you can expect to spend many hours on the phone with customer service while you were learning the platform. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot is a great product for managing inbound leads, and their marketing automation tool is incredibly well integrated with their site hosting service. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot to manage our inbound database and to qualify leads before sending them to Salesforce as MQL's. "}}
{"author": ["Cheryl C"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["May 18, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I enjoy how easy the tool is to use. It takes seconds to build forms unlike other tools like Eloqua and Liveball , which are much more time consuming. Landing pages don't require any coding experience at all making them very easy to build.", "What do you dislike?": "The reporting ad on is absolutely terrible. It's nearly impossible to report on anything using the tool. Reporting in general I find is very challenging. Everything lives in different places making it impossible to report on multiple things in one place especially when you try to build out a dashboard.  When using Hubspot for email be aware that they will not send emails to anyone who has hard bounced from anyone in their database. So your emails could not be delivered because they hard bounced when they were sent an email from anyone of Hubspot customers using their tool. We recently discovered this when several emails weren't delivered from people who had never hard bounced from our emails. After doing some research we have actually realized that this information is actually not accurate, so Hubspot is now is the process of fixing this issue. So emails were being not delivered based on inaccurate information in the Hubspot system. It has been a complete disaster and has taken over a week for Husbpot to take responsibility in fixing the error. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are using the tool for email automation and you can pull reporting from GA then it is great. If you rely on very detailed reporting then I would go with Eloqua of Adobe. Those tools are much more expensive. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Trying to aquire more inbound leads for sales. Using Hubspot allows us to build out inbound campaigns easily and collect leads which are then passed over to salesforce."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The reports dashboard and queue are so beneficial for me. In sales, I am constantly calling people, so having all my contacts in a line, ready to go for the day is great.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that when I search a name or a template it has to be so exact. Sometimes I know I made a template about a certain topic, but unless I know the exact name it will not come up. A suggestions section that pops up would be nice. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are reaching so many people and being able to see when. We can efficiently track our connection points to make sure we are reaching out, but not too often. It's great being able to see who in the organization has contacted each person as well. "}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot offers perfect e-mail integrations, deep filtering options, an easy-to-learn UI and best of all, the new Sequence option which I absolutely love!", "What do you dislike?": "At times there are errors appearing while working on my contacts or deals, but otherwise there are no real cons. It is a little bit pricey to get extra features, but manageable", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "They have a pretty solid blog which I highly recommend. E-mail sequencing combined with integrations and signatures are a very nice feature. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Me and my Sales team use it daily as a lead and deal database and to semi-automate some of our Marketing and Sales tasks that we previously did manually, which was just tedious. HubSpot saved us a lot of time as we can now focus on more important and complex tasks."}}
{"author": ["Janine G"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Principal, Marketing & Sales", "Architecture & Planning"], "date": ["Aug 16, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the free CRM side of Hubspot a lot.  I appreciated the technical support in setup.  I also like the regular webinars. ", "What do you dislike?": "When I was in the decision phase, I was not given a clear picture of the resources required from my end, to leverage this product  -- 8 to 15 hours/week, they told me after I'd signed up.  As a SOLOPRENEUR I have found the platform to be overwhelming.  A year went by (I paid of course) and I did not leverage the capabilities.  Just begun year 2, I am trying to make a fresh start. \r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "And not a surprise - I bought in at the lowest level, and I feel like they are hovering over me to upsell -- I got a shocking email about my cost rising when my # of contacts went to 201 (limit is 200), several weeks ahead of the  term, and two of those contacts were THEIR president (prepopulated) & myself.  When I complained, the rate was corrected, with a lot of self-congratulations for their own generosity. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "DO set aside 1-2 days/week in your calendar to \"onboard\" and figure this out early.  DO have a plan to create or source content  (blog posts).  DO have \"buddies\"  (if you are a solopreneur like me) to help with idea generation. "}}
{"author": ["Amrita H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Content Marketing Coordinator", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Apr 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is very user-friendly and sums up all I need as a content marketer in a CRM software. The support team is very quick and solves all the problems within an hour. \r", "What do you dislike?": "The lessons available too are pretty easy to understand.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The analytics can get weird at times. I use google analytics for tracking the traffic on social and website."}}
{"author": ["Jessica M"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I can connect everything I do on social media, create professional emails and blogging", "What do you dislike?": "The blog template is hard to customize and you have to spend more money to get a better template that's functional - on top of all the money we spend right now for the enterprise. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Solved posting on all social media accounts, "}}
{"author": ["Eduardo H"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Head of Marketing"], "date": ["Sep 30, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Tons of feature to use. Workflows and website management tools are great.", "What do you dislike?": "Price - it's quite expensive. Most of the best features are paid, so it can be quite challenging for small companies to make full use of HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot for most of our marketing activities. From blogging to email marketing."}}
{"author": ["Eric J"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 27, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The system is powerful for nurturing prospects along the buyer's journey toward conversion. I like the simplicity of how it works. I do not need to be a coder to be successful with HubSpot.", "What do you dislike?": "The only complaint I have is that the CRM is not as full-featured as we've needed. We've always had to use something like Salesforce to get the CRM tools we need. Then, connecting the flow of information from the CRM to HubSpot is always a challenge.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot provides great, easy-to-use tools to build landing pages complete with SEO and forms. It allows you to send workflows and sequences (automation) to nurture leads. It is great at tracking prospect/customer activity on your site and emails. "}}
{"author": ["Consultant in Higher Education"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 24, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Always been a fan of Hub spot, LOVE their podcasts & their website. Extremely helpful I have been a faithful follower for many years now & their podcasts even helped me focus on going back to school for marketing", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing so far the website is very user friendly & I find I use it all the time. I have not had any issues what so ever.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I've recommended HubSpot to several friends & classmates ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Problems I'm looking to solve- simply gain Education & knowledge, I've learned a lot from. Benefits I've come to realize are a deeper understanding of marketing, advertising & how to see both sides of the fence from the consumer & the firm."}}
{"author": ["Jennifer B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Human Resources"], "date": ["Jan 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot provides a simple user experience that packs a punch for all of your organization's marketing activities. Forget managing multiple campaigns in different programs, you can do almost everything right from your HubSpot account. We've increased our lead generation, improved lead conversion, and driven up our SEO using HubSpot.", "What do you dislike?": "The coding can be limited, and sometimes e-mail marketing can be cumbersome if you're formatting in HTML. Social publishing does not include Instagram (yet), and that is a big focus for our company, so someday it would be nice to see IG available!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are improving brand awareness, departmental efficiency, reporting, and ROI for all of our marketing efforts. HubSpot has supported higher lead volume, increased lead conversion, and greater overall synergy between all of our marketing activities."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 29, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The fact that they give you all the tools you need to learn and leverage Hubspot as a marketing automation tool. Marketing automation is a beast to deal with, especially with learning and implementation. They have educational courses to teach you principles of their software, digital marketing, and other subjects related to use of their software with both sales and marketing teams. Their service team is incredible and a great resource.", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing yet. There\u2019s so much to learn and so much you can do with HubSpot that I haven\u2019t completely dived in yet.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We\u2019re solving tracking performance of digital ads with various media vendors. While the data will never be perfectly 1 to 1, it at least gives us some footing to verify the reporting we get."}}
{"author": ["Jared P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "From a users standpoint, I like that help is always just right around the corner. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish our customer success manager was more accessible.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "This company (and product) are constantly growing and improving.  If you want Inbound Marketing Automation and a provider that stays ahead of the curve, you wont be disappointed with the HubSpot arsenal.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to automatically touch and guide our buyers through the funnel."}}
{"author": ["Jennifer S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Staffing and Recruiting"], "date": ["Feb 09, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "My favourite thing about HubSpot is the Sequencing, this has definitely freed up my time to work on other engagements.", "What do you dislike?": "Since the update done in Jan there have been a lot of bugs that have affected me being able to use HubSpot without running into a problem every other week, and slow follow-up response time when issue aren't able to be resolved when on the phone. I would like to add on HubSpot marketing, however, these issues have made me question whether it is a good idea or not, especially since HubSpot marketing is kind of a hefty investment for a smaller company.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "With HubSpot, I have been able to keep in contact with potential Clients/Leads without having to remind myself through an excel spreadsheet."}}
{"author": ["Abhijeet S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Founder", "Information Services"], "date": ["Nov 08, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy UI and a free tool that can be leveraged for multiple horizons of marketing and sales. ", "What do you dislike?": "I didn't find any quick support from the team when I was stuck in the beginning. Also, Hubspot doesn't offer integration with other platforms like Pandadocs. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "With user-friendly UI it turned out to be easier for me to guide my team about same. So, the handling marketing turns out to be a bit easier. "}}
{"author": ["Daniel P"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Sales and Customer Success Analyst", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The workflows and automation within in HubSpot is simple and easy to to use. The amount of time it has saved me and my sales and success teams are invaluable.", "What do you dislike?": "Adding the functionality to have lists of companies and not just contacts hamper productivity at times.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Scaling of our sales team, sales conversion rates, reducing customer churn the list goes on. The automation allows us to have all the data and tasks in front of our customer-facing teams which allows them to take the correct course of action."}}
{"author": ["Bill B"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Visual and Social Media Coordinator"], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Using Hubspot's Social Media manager helps me plan ahead for social posts and keep track of engagement. It helps me and our department recognize trends and focus on posts that engage our customers and prospectives.", "What do you dislike?": "It's hard to find any faults with Hubspot. It's a powerful tool for marketing and engagement.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "One of our uses of Hubspot is tracking post engagement in social media, and focusing on organic reach without having to spend advertising dollars on Facebook advertising. It helps us measure our goals in email campaigns that in turn link to landing pages and form submissions."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Website CMS is really easy to use and allows easy integration of forms and other elements such as calls to action.", "What do you dislike?": "It's a really expensive system but it does represent great value for money when you compare the features. The SEO tools are fairly limited in my opinion and it hasn't improved my traffic.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It takes a while to get used to the system but is powerful once you know it", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Full service crm, sales and marketing system. It allowed us to remove multiple other systems and replace them with our single hubspot subscription."}}
{"author": ["User in Banking"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is very very user-friendly. Its UI is simplest and designed very well. Unlike, thousands of other marketing tools available in the market with highly complex features; HubSpot is the perfect tool for small businesses as it does not requires any coding.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot's pricing structure is not great. Firstly, many tools that are integrated into one bucket at HubSpot are individually available for free. Also, it costs very high to integrate CRM with HubSpot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot is very useful tool. If you are planning to invest in marketing, web analytics, social media management, HubSpot should be one of the first choices. It is one place for all tools and integrates with CRM, marketing and e-commerce platforms. It is very user-friendly as well.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot integrates with MS Dynamics CRM which is very useful to our company for running social media campaigns, web analytics and optimising our web feed. Also, other features like integration to SurveyMonkey helps us get feedback of our services easily and plan our strategies accordingly."}}
{"author": ["Matthew Z"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 21, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The onboarding process is way above anything I'd ever experienced or expected. They're there for you every step of the way and when your dedicated rep isn't available their support team not only answers you quickly, but thoroughly. \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The platform itself is insanely robust and advanced. There's very little you can't do with it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The social publishing tool doesn't currently allow me to set different schedules for several different consumer brands that I handle, making scheduling slightly more manual, but I've actually found that it simply forces me to pay more attention to what I'm curating and scheduling. "}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 20, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot's lead tracking is way better than anything else out there for marketers. Their marketing software homepage has all of the info I need to get quick overview of how we're doing on inbound leads for the month, like traffic, lead sources, and grouping.", "What do you dislike?": "The price. It's crazy expensive for a small startup like ours, and it's tough for us to afford all of the features we'd like to be using.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Try out the free trials before you commit to purchasing, and get a Hubspot rep working with you to help you find the best deal for your company's needs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Inbound lead tracking is a problem we've solved with Hubspot. The software helped us find pain points in our sales funnel to develop better inbound content via drip marketing campaigns."}}
{"author": ["Jennifer  H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["CRM Manager "], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "When using the full stack, CRM, marketing, service - everyone has full visibility into the contacts actions and behaviors. This leads to better decisions and empowers our team to take immediate action.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish the sequences were more intelligent, similar to a workflow. The reporting has gotten better, but it could still use more work at being intuitive.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take the time to get your initial set up and data correct at the beginning of the project.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are discovering opportunities we never knew about and are on pace to increase new and renewable revenue."}}
{"author": ["Nick P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Project Coordinator", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 03, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Allows our agency to provide results to clients. Excellent customer support. Integrates with several add-ons. Customer service is top-notch, especially for a SaaS company. HubSpot truly follows its own Inbound Methodology:  Attract --> Convert --> Close --> Delight.", "What do you dislike?": "From what I hear, developer tools could be much better. Possible training course / certification specifically for CRM users? We've had clients asking us to train them, and it would be nice if HubSpot provided more resources in this area.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Try it! They offer free trials, and they have excellent support to get you started. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Providing results-based marketing, and delivering ROI back to clients. They're also very transparent; they'll roll out different tools or features with ideas on how they'll work... Sometimes they do, sometimes they don't. That's marketing! If something isn't working, HubSpot will adjust."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is one of the best-integrated CRM platforms on the market and it is very useful for Digital Marketing. I mostly use social media tools, which allows me to schedule in advance, customize graphics for each platform and organize them.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish the was an opportunity to extract social media reports.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The best CRM platform on the market at this moment. I would definitely recommend considering if you do not use it yet. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows me to connect all social media accounts(more than 80 pages) post and track engagements all at the same place.  "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We love the tracking and the integrations with GoToWebinar. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish it was easier for their team to make a custom email template. I would rather them make it than me having to create it in photoshop first. We don't have a graphic designer, so this is just a harder step for me personally. Also, wish Hubspot made it easier to end automatic emails  and reminder after someone signed up for an event. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "With Hubspot we're able to track our CAC easily which is great. Carolyn Van Ness our support manager is very helpful! "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 27, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that Hubspot allows me to see what companies have visited my website through the prospects tool. I also like the lead gen functionality and email sequencing.", "What do you dislike?": "The pricing structure is very confusing and you need to buy different packs to use their functions. I would like to see an a la cart option, where you could add additional services on a one-off basis without having to move into the next tier.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have been focusing more on lead gen and using Hubspot to do so. Our lead lists have grown and we have a better understanding of who is interested in our product. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I think the APIs are pretty easy to use and our development team has found them simple to implement. ", "What do you dislike?": "I would love it if the Salesforce connector would connect to custom objects more easily. It seems we don't have nearly as much control as we would like to connect data via the connector.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I think the software is really simple to use. Prior to implementing ensure you have a defined plan around how you will store your data and create custom fields. We have a lot of custom fields that have been added over time and restricting this will allow you to keep records clean.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to collect incoming leads via Hubspot and able to perform demand gen activities with the software."}}
{"author": ["Renwick W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Analyst"], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot's platform offers lots of features that are really useful across different parts of businesses, from sales to marketing.", "What do you dislike?": "There's so much that it can be confusing at times, and difficult to troubleshoot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Ask lots of questions from others who have used HubSpot before.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Merging sales and marketing efforts, reducing duplicative efforts."}}
{"author": ["Dean A"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Copywriter", "Higher Education"], "date": ["Aug 05, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot does combine everything you need to run your marketing endeavors in one place. This is especially useful for companies with multiple divisions, who might have multiple domains and social media/blog presences to maintain.", "What do you dislike?": "The UI gets clunky in some places, and minor changes that probably weren't necessary are fairly frequent. It's not uncommon when editing an email or landing page for the tool bar to block a section of my email I am trying to click on to edit because the responsive design put the tool bar in the way. There are also times when features can be found in one place but a week later and without warning they move somewhere else \u00ff often with more clicks involved \u2014 which makes the UI frustrating at times.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you utilize email, landing pages, social media and blogging to deliver content to your customers and prospects, and would like a tool to allow you to competently manage all of those things within one system, Hubspot is a good choice. There are lots of analytics options as well, although in my role I personally do not manage or utilize those so I cannot speak to their efficacy. That said, the people on our team who do produce reports seem to be able to do so easily and with a great amount of detail, so it seems safe to assume they are good.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It's gotten much easier to both draft, schedule and send emails and has truly shifted the way we handle marketing to our own customers and business partners."}}
{"author": ["Heather S"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Super simple interface, integrated systems, amazing/responsive support team, accessible how-to guides, marketing tips via newsletter, drag and drop editing capabilities", "What do you dislike?": "Lifecycle stages mismatch Salesforce making it difficult to identify customers vs leads vs subscribers", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easy content management, social integrations, and analytics make it easy to promote our offerings and measure our success. "}}
{"author": ["Ashley J"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Inbound Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jul 17, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "New campaign analytics offer deep insight into what's working across every channel. Native integration between CRM/Marketing tools is a major plus. Tools are scalable and easy to use, plus frequent updates and a strong community forum mean you have access to the strongest marketing automation technology on the market. ", "What do you dislike?": "Digital ad reporting, sources and campaign tracking could use some enhancements to drill down to individual ads. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Invest in training", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Connecting inbound lead gen efforts with offline marketing channels."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 01, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is friendly system both in being easy to use, with a huge wealth of information online to solve most questions; and with their readily available support. \r", "What do you dislike?": "It is a bit clunky for multi teams and multi language marketing: country field not alphabetising when translated (how is that user friendly) and not being able to segment email reporting into teams who sent them. Saying this, HubSpot are slowly working to solve these things. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Holistic marketing view for sales and marketing when before they were operating on separate systems"}}
{"author": ["Britney L"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Account Manager"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that HubSpot helps me to manage my workflow and keeps me on track to best assist my customers. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are times it isn't super intuitive when searching but this has improved recently.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helps me manage a large book of business much more effectively. It has helped me better accomplish my personal KPIs."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "My sales and marketing is in one place I Maple to host my website easily and see all the analytics that come off of it.", "What do you dislike?": "When it's had little troubles glitchy but they always catch it up", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hub spot is really easy to use they have a learning program if you need help with anything they're always available it's all around just simple.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm able to have my sales and marketing tabs in the same place and be able to see all the analytics coming off my website instead of having a 3rd party hosting it"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Banking"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It\u2019s all in one approach, I can do more with one program and saves me time. I like that this product tracks and manages interactions between a my company and my customers. It also enables my to forecast revenue, measure sales team productivity, and report on revenue sources. It is great for a small business like I have or if my business grows into a larger one it will still work for me. ", "What do you dislike?": "I can't keep up with the software changes. There's too much to manage, From developing your personas, to creating content calendars, to finding time to write your blog \u2014 it's a lot of work. Only then to realize you need to make calls-to-action, landing pages, content downloads, workflows, lead scoring and more.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Monitoring and responding to social media inquiries. Over all keeping track of all my social media and email marketing was hard to know what was reaching people and what was working and not working but this helps me manage that! "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Marketing tracking of emails and opens for follow up", "What do you dislike?": "too many keystrokes to get to an end result. For sales, it takes so long to complete the process of recording a call it slows you down. You have to work around the system to get it to segment the market by a person within the account.  Also, if you use URL to enter a new company you don't always get what you entered. You enter a city URL and it comes up with the Sanitation Department.  You have to rekey all that. The same is true for contact records. If you import contact records, the email address after @ doesn't always attribute to the right organization. More manual checking.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "if you need marketing this is a good product. If you need a CRM product only , no.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Sales, marketing, sale and marketing metrics"}}
{"author": ["Johnathan Sheaffer S"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Creative Designer and Webmaster", "Graphic Design"], "date": ["Jan 05, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that I know when my emails are read and I know when they are reopened. When someone reopens my email they are usually working on the project or have a question about it for me. Helps me know that it is being worked on or be prepared to ask a question.", "What do you dislike?": "Occasionally the notifications get stuck in the top right corner of my computer and they only way to get them to go away is restart my computer. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I use it to know if someone has read my email or not. It is great to be able to wait to check in with someone until after they read your email. Or call them if they have not read your email and you need an answer fast. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 15, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that I can create different pipelines for my various clients and keep all of their contact info and put notes in/move them into different buckets when something moves forward.", "What do you dislike?": "There are a lot of different menus and screens - it takes a lot to remember what exact screen to go to depending on what I want!", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Just go through it all and see how much you can implement within your day to day actions for any CRM needs - I think it does way more than even I know about!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Keeping all of the pipeline investors together. I can contact people for follow-up emails without even leaving the platform."}}
{"author": ["John M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Technology Coach", "Consumer Electronics"], "date": ["Aug 01, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's tough to put a finger on the best feature of HubSpot. We use the email workflows to great effect, the CRM to keep track of all our clients and prospects, and the COS to create awesome landing pages and blog posts. Perhaps the best part of HubSpot is that it does a number of things very well and easily adapts to your processes and workflows.", "What do you dislike?": "The HubSpot platform offers a ton of features so there's definitely a learning curve if you've never used a marketing automation platform before. Thankfully HubSpot's training academy is there to help you through it (although some of the videos can get long). It's a powerful tool, but you need to really dig in and learn it to get the most out of it.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "While the learning curve can be steep, the support and training offered by HubSpot is outstanding. I'd also recommend working with a partner agency if you need more support or are feeling overwhelmed.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're using this platform on a number of levels. As our CRM it's taken the guesswork out of who's contacting a client/prospect, what they've talked about, when they have a meeting scheduled, if there's a deal in the works, etc. From the marketing side, we've used workflows to automate email and other communications for various webinars and downloadable content, and are even using them in conjunction with our social selling efforts. We're using the COS to develop websites, landing pages, and blog posts, and the amount of data we get back is awesome to see clearly displayed in one place."}}
{"author": ["Chad B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Solutions Director", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["May 16, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is the best all-in-one CRM solution for companies focusing on both inbound and outbound sales. \r", "What do you dislike?": "With the ability to guide customers through the sales process, from a potential lead to a closed sale, it's a seamless experience. Your marketing is automated, and all you have to do is drop in your contact info while the system records every interaction for you, and fills in the gaps with automated emails that YOU set up. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Internal Consultant"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "If an CRM can\u2019t be dependable then it isn\u2019t very valuable. HS has rarely disappointed me when it comes to accessibility and accuracy in the data I need to achieve professional goals. ", "What do you dislike?": "The mobile medium needs to be easier to access and have similar functions to the computer medium. Personally, I am in an office as much as out of an office when I need to access my client\u2019s data and having a more apt mobile app would be helpful. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It\u2019s provided a centralized base for communication, logistics, and memorializing client-company contact.   "}}
{"author": ["Anurag A"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Manager, Marketing Operations", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to view all user interactions, across platforms in one place. Setting up automated workflows for nurture email campaigns is another useful feature that helps make life easy.", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't much to dislike, but I wish the conversation feature was a part of the marketing hub rather than sales. As a product, I feel it fits better there.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automation tasks and email campaigns are the biggest benefits. When you're operating at full capacity with a lean team, these features add a lot of value to the process."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how everything is easily organized and easy to track where all of your leads are as well as the ability to see when you emails get opened from your leads.", "What do you dislike?": "There is not much to say about dislikes to be honest. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would definitely jump into it if you are considering HubSpot. It is extremely easy to use and very efficient. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Able to make follow ups extremely easy and trackable. It really helps you stay on top of your leads as opposed to forgetting to reach out to them. "}}
{"author": ["Zachary M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Creative Director Assistant", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Mar 07, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of use. The methodology, all the courses and information they provide. We are a partner and love working with the Hubspot team.", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing. They are super help and if their were a real issue they would be quick to resolve.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hop on the train, you can automate so much and do so much with this one tool than all the others combined.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Having an easy to use CSM, having a sales CRM, help clients use both of those. Building sites with the COS."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Insurance"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is easy to use and it allows us to capture great stats. I like how it integrates with GotoWebinar, social and other tools. We've barely scratched the surface with all of its capabilities and I'm beyond impressed. ", "What do you dislike?": "There's not much to dislike. There are things I would like to improve, such as having the ability to have an internal contact list for internal communications. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It helps to have someone technical on your team to help you implement. HubSpot doesn't use html... but it helps if you know some. They have a tremendous resource of training tools so you won't be lost for long.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are easily building landing pages and blogs, integrating our lists with Salesforce, publishing social media posts to multiple company pages, and have even put some of our websites on the HubSpot platform."}}
{"author": ["Joanna S"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Insurance"], "date": ["Mar 07, 2019", "May 19, 2014"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "All in one platform, easy to use, great support - great account managers. ", "What do you dislike?": "Not transparent pricing. Only after you've signed notified of more fees. This is my second implementation of Hubspot and the company has changed. Asked to pay an additional $100 a month to achieve basic functionality only after we signed contract. Not notified of fees prior to signing contract. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "There are other options available at a much lower cost so may want to consider those as well, ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As it currently stands we can't access any performance analytics because we can't afford the additional fees. Looking into other solutions. "}}
{"author": ["Licia M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Customer Success Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["Feb 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to manage customer's stages, store customer communication from different platforms and to keep and share customer data throughout the company.", "What do you dislike?": "It serves its purpose well, I just wish I had more time to learn all of its features to use it fully.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It allows us to easily view and manage each stage of our customer's lifecycle and take action to prevent churn."}}
{"author": ["Tiju T"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Manager Marketing Operations"], "date": ["Jun 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The email marketing part. Preparing the list, writing the content and scheduling is so much better compared to other tools in the market", "What do you dislike?": "I expect more customizations to happen on every level in this tool. I believe there is lot of room for more innovations.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing activities in our company. Its become much easy to manage now."}}
{"author": ["Nick S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["CEO & Co-Founder"], "date": ["Jul 26, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "As a start up, we wanted to find a solution which worked for us straight out of the box and didn't need to deal either with sales guys or consultants to configure the package.  We trailed a couple of CRM systems and HubSpot was the clear winner for our needs.  I know there are tweaks we need to make and know that we can easily bespoke HubSpot when time allows and no major re-writing of data will be necessary.  Best feature for us is the 'free for life' access to the basic product.  We will certainly be upgrading and adding the premium features for enhanced functionality as and when funds permit.", "What do you dislike?": "Very little!  Rogue companies are created automatically when HubSpot spots a corporate email being used by a customer for a non-corporate entity, but this is in no way HubSpot's fault.  We spot them and quickly delete the newly created company record.  Some correspondence doesn't always automatically file itself, but we haven't yet spotted why.  It isn't a big concern for us though.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Settle down with a cup of coffee and watch the training videos.  Bulk uploads from CSV files would have been far easier had I done so...!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have built a remote sales team and HubSpot is fantastic as it prevents duplication of effort on the potential customer.  At the same time, it allows for collaboration for a common goal.  Tracking a lead's relationships across multiple organisations is extremely useful."}}
{"author": ["Shane S"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Media Production"], "date": ["Jul 26, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has everything you need in one integrated toolset, and with the CRM add-on it is hard to beat for focused B2B marketing and sales.", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the tools are disjointed and lack interfaces that guide the process. You can spend a lot of time jumping around between modules and tools with a fair amount of mental gymnastics in play to keep everything organized. No visual mapping tools for organizing and diagramming automation campaign flows.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are building out a B2B marketing solution, Hubspot is probably the best bang for your buck.  Selling products or services online that are similar to Hubspot is what Hubspot is best at. When you read their marketing materials and experience the process of self educating on Hubspot, you are experiencing the best you can do with it. If you are packing up a company for online digital marketing and inbound strategy, Hubspot needs to be on your options list. If you do not already have a CRM, Hubspot's built in CRM could be exactly what you need for $50 / user... it is not usefully free... even though it has a free version.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Digital marketing and sales."}}
{"author": ["Sunil N"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Manager - Digital Marketing"], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Supporting multiple domains. Easy to manage marketing campaigns of multiple LOBs. A/B testing, Team level access", "What do you dislike?": "No option to track all submissions of a particular domain in a single list", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are trying to automate our marketing activities, the quick launch of marketing campaigns using this tool is really great."}}
{"author": ["Heather D"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Sales and Marketing Operations Manager", "Human Resources"], "date": ["Feb 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot can be used for the website and marketing automation software.  Doing both gives you a decent amount of analytics surrounding prospects.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot has a terrible sync with Salesforce.  At two different companies, I had major issues getting records to sync properly.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you have a large or growing company, this may not be the best solution for you.  If you are a small business owner, this would be a great product.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot provides a place for housing prospects and sending out automated emails.  It was a good tool for a small business, as it's easy to use without much training."}}
{"author": ["Christian C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Specialist - Graphic Designer", "Graphic Design"], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Tracking our customers, segmentation tools, form builders, email tools, list management.  I really like the ease of use and the customer service, also having a customer sucess manager to talk best practices with", "What do you dislike?": "price is high but there are a lot of features we don't use that i think would bring more value", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Get the right package for your companies needs", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "customer insight and higher targeted emails"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Research"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 10, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's very easy to use across a wide array of areas. I use it for sales, customer support, marketing, customer communication, etc. As I reach out to potential customers, HubSpot makes it easy to promote my product across social platform. I would definitely recommend. ", "What do you dislike?": "The main flaw is the price. If the price was lower, I think it would fare much better with its competitors. Additionally, I wish there was better integration of Youtube and HubSpot. If I can show a Youtube video directly to customers using HubSpot, I think it will make a much more compelling advertising platform. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot helps me optimize where I target my potential customers. Instead of having to manually figure out the type of audience I am trying to target for marketing, HubSpot does it for me and stream-lines the process. I feel that in the long-run I am spending less money and time on optimizing marketing when I use HubSpot. Certainly, this product was worth the investment!"}}
{"author": ["Philippe L"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["Game Designer", "Graphic Design"], "date": ["Jan 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like having the ability to track which of my emails are getting received by my prospects. Additionally, Hubspot is by far the best marketing automation software I have ever used. The price is affordable, the capacity is almost unlimited, and the automation/drip campaign capabilities are easy to utilize.", "What do you dislike?": "Keeping data clean, cross-checking, and ensuring prospects do not get double touched can be difficult.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Try the free options first and you will find its super easy to use.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot integrates with our website. Contact form submissions go directly to our reps. As a Game Designer, I appreciate the layer of accountability HubSpot provides."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Religious Institutions"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Our business is people.  Hubspot has allowed us to keep in touch with our customers in very personal yet automated ways as people run through our onboarding and recruiting flow.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it is a little hard to track down which workflow is initiating which action.  Would be nice to have a universal search feature for within workflows.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's pricey, but worth it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot helps us to manage our incoming candidate flow, allowing us to communicate, collect the proper information, and work through our onboarding and candidate process."}}
{"author": ["John M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["VP, Marketing"], "date": ["Aug 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "A lot of the web site tracking tools are integrated or embedded as part of the platform so makes it easy to monitor and report", "What do you dislike?": "Pricing not really designed for startups. The per contact pricing is a barrier.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Good integration between marketing automation and sales automation. I don't have to buy multiple tools."}}
{"author": ["Consultant in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 10, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The system works, it does what it claims it can do. This may sound sill but I have used multiple marketing automation systems that claim to compete with HubSpot and that is just not the case. Many lack capability or simply do not work. This is the best in the business right now and I would tell anyone that.", "What do you dislike?": "The price. Very high & limits contacts and email sends.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Don't let the cost scare you. This platform does all it says and more. It is a great investment and will help small companies grow or big companies better market to their audience.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot to run campaigns, create workflows for leads to enter and be nurtured, send emails, monitor landing page success, and push/monitor social"}}
{"author": ["Natalie H"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Copywriter | Content Strategist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jul 27, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how easily the software integrates certain things - like attaching blog posts to tweets. I like the content calendar, making it easy to share information with my team about what posts and activities are happening when. It makes my life easier when creating things like landing pages without having to get developers involved. ", "What do you dislike?": "We don't have the reporting add on, so I find the reports to be a little limited. Having a free trial that includes all features (rather than the ones from the package you're choosing) is frustrating, because it's not always clear which features are premium/enterprise level. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take advantage of the HubSpot Academy training", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "At the moment we're focusing on increasing web traffic, which has been successful. Our traffic has increased massively, and our social profiles are getting more engagement, again bringing people to the site. Our next step is automated workflows to nurture leads. "}}
{"author": ["Justin W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Specialist", "Non-Profit Organization Management"], "date": ["May 02, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The templates for landing pages, emails, and other forms of communication are top notch in style and ease of customization. They provide great starting points for you to build off of.", "What do you dislike?": "We were short-sold on its integration capabilities. We found we could not do some basic features we had available from a HubSpot competitor, and these shortcomings ultimately drove us away from the platform altogether. If you have an advanced CRM setup, I would look for other solutions.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It may be a great platform for smaller operations, or if you are using HubSpot Sales. If you have a large client base and work with multiple opportunities on an ongoing basis, I would steer clear.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We were hoping to use HubSpot for advanced social media tracking and lead nurturing. While it delivered on the social media aspect, it wasn't enough for us to use the platform given its failure to meet other requirements."}}
{"author": ["Preena P"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Assistant Account Executive", "Pharmaceuticals"], "date": ["May 02, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really liked the fact that it was really simple to use. It was great to have a product on the market where i could update all of my social media accounts and keep track of the analytics all in one place. I liked that there were different levels of the product which was great for my company because we didn't need all the bells and whistles since we were a smaller company. ", "What do you dislike?": "i did not really find any difficulty using this as a product. However, there were issues in the beginning of trying to get a hold of a support team when first setting this up. However that was years ago so this may have resolved itself. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would recommend using HubSpot because it was really easy to set up and use. I thought that it was nice that it was able to hold all of our accounts in one easy to use site. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "My company used this to create, automate, optimize, and measure all of our online marketing tools. We used it to help keep track of our campaigns as well as see the social analytics that we were receiving on our account. It was really nice that you were able to not only use this product for your social media accounts, but your email lists as well. "}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot does an amazing job creating content that is simple and easy to understand while still engaging. I've taken several online courses and they are by far my favorite. There tools are pretty straight forward and they have GREAT tutorials and customer service.", "What do you dislike?": "I sometimes felt like it was being dumbed down too much. With that said it was appreciated in certain areas. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Costly for the business versions ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has allowed all our marketing efforts to be stored in one platform. We also have a much smoother process and helps new employees to understand our funnel more clearly."}}
{"author": ["Stefaan P"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Managing Director", "Management Consulting"], "date": ["Jul 19, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The intuitivity of the application and the automization in reporting on marketing activities. ", "What do you dislike?": "The fact i cannot apply mandatory fields in collecting/inputting certain company or contact data.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The content management system is not that evolved yet to be comparable to Wordpress. We decided to wait further developments in Hubspot before switching our complete website to the Hubspot platform. Also the lack of multilingual blogging setup retains us from switching to hubspot for our blog edits and publishing. However this is solved by some very good wordpress tags to collect data from the Wordpress site and blog.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Make sure you thorougly analyze your own website/CMS before switching to hubspot. if you need a straight forward website or blog in one language hubspot certainly does the trick. We decided to wait until the multilanguage utilities in Hubspot are further developed. It is something they are aware of and are developing on to be improved."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I've been loving how easy it is to manage requests and distribute them to our employees. Our employees used to have a different application but the switch over to Hubspot has been for the better. ", "What do you dislike?": "It can sometimes be difficult to find the answer to a question because there are so many different features available. However, the online chat has been able to help me with any questions I may have.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to keep track of everything in one spot so our client management has been better. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is just that a Hub for all marketing needs. It is very user friendly and makes tasks a breeze ! I can post to all social media accounts from one spot, while creating an email campaign and landing page- all in one program.  ", "What do you dislike?": "Waiting for some better email editor- more of a drag and drop function instead of backend editing to get the theme just right. Some functions for sending email campaigns are a little funny , ie. opt-ins. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot as increased my production without sacrificing time!"}}
{"author": ["Jeffrey N"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder and DJ", "Music"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ease of creating workflows. Attractive UI. Dynamic sequences. One of the best and most responsive customer support teams I've had the pleasure of working with. I consider you all a partner, not a vender.", "What do you dislike?": "While sequences are great, I wish they could be tied to workflows.  Reporting is limited.  I want to be able to build more dynamic dashboards/reports using contact properties.  Time can only be measured by using the deal pipeline, it's limiting.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Multiplying my sales output.  Task management tools.  I can identify bottlenecks faster, and function far more efficiently."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The flexibility of landing pages and automation. We have created hundreds of landing pages using HubSpot across 100+ domains.", "What do you dislike?": "The new domain name connection fee is insane. HubSpot used to let you connect infinite domains to your account - Unless you only want to set up a redirect, they now charge in the realm of $700 to connect a new domain!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation has been helpful to our business. We are now starting to use the social suite and ads instead of third-party apps."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Juha I"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Growth Hacker", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Apr 30, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "For a HubSpot Marketing user, the software is a marketing automation machine. It is feature-rich and intuitive to use, meaning almost any automation you can imagine can be done with relative ease. Scaling activities is easy thanks to effortless duplication, template management is powerful yet flexible in both web pages and emails. HubSpot also has extensive and high-quality training section on their website, both teaching universal principles of modern marketing but also how to get the best out of their tools. Their customer service is top-notch and prompt.", "What do you dislike?": "As it is so easy to create new content, templates, stylesheets and sometimes also overly complicated workflows and lists, managing the account proves a challenge. I easily find it hard to keep organized and figure what is needed and what isn't. Sometimes during the past two years HubSpot has deployed new UI features perhaps a bit too eagerly in the beta mode, which has resulted in some anxiety, but have always been open for feedback. For a smaller business, a dislike and discouragement would be their pricing.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "For those needing a comprehensive set of marketing automation tools and content management, tied with CRM, HubSpot seems a great choice. Note that it is not very advanced SEO tool, and you'll most likely need that separately. For more light-weight users, mostly looking for some simple email automation or newsletter publishing, alternatives like MailChimp may be more suitable.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am mostly using HubSpot Marketing as a digital marketer and designer to create campaign landing pages, automated emails, workflows and lists. HubSpot let's me do this efficiently and offers time savings to our entire marketing team thanks to it's powerful features and automation."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Commercial Real Estate"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use, design is pleasing to the eye.  Allows for customization and automation of daily tasks to keep you organized.  The system truly works for you while you sleep!", "What do you dislike?": "Certain features don't offer as much functionality as I would like, however, Hubspot is great at listening to feedback and making updates based on customer requests.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great tool for manage sales and automation.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We organize our daily tasks through Hubspot and utilize the tool to prospect for new business as well as manage our pipeline of current and past deals."}}
{"author": ["Matthew T"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Consultant", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 12, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Above all, there are not many CRM systems that are free for small businesses. As a user, I have access to their customer support even under the free plan. The drip campaign features are powerful for creating a custom follow up series that speaks to the recipient. It also disables when contacts respond, so it's very easy to implement and update according our communication with leads and customers. ", "What do you dislike?": "It does not allow me to send to multiple emails, you are forced to send one at a time. For example, after a networking event I have to manually communicate.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is simple to use for communication with our sales funnel. From first contact to ongoing support as a customer, it helps us to stay on top of all communication."}}
{"author": ["Annie R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing and Brand Management"], "date": ["May 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is super organized and really useful. It can be a great tool for all of our salespeople, as well as for the marketing team to utilize.", "What do you dislike?": "For it to be useful, all of our salespeople have to know exactly how to use it and then ACTUALLY USE IT. It's all manual. Some people still don't understand how it really works. It's definitely not easy on the phone.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot is a useful tool for salespeople, and especially for marketers. It keeps everyone on the same page and makes it simpler for salespeople to know where they're at in the sales line.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Organization mostly. It helps our salespeople know who they need to talk to and who they don't."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like all of the I integrations and automation this software has to offer, like the easy to use landing pages and email campaign triggers.", "What do you dislike?": "The onboarding process has been slow and learning curve steep.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot appears to be a great product but it's almost a full time job implementing it and transfering data. I'm sure if my budget had allowed for an implementing specialist then I would be in love with product. However, I would only recommend for large companies with a robust budget. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It's helped with keeping all of my work in one place instead of toggling between applications.  "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Publishing"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 31, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is incredible. It allows you to track your customers in real time through email automation. You are able to create from scratch any business email you'd want to send. From there, you can pull lists together from HubSpot's Marketing and Sales platforms. Once you send out the email, you can track all customers - you can see who's clicked on what, who's opted out, etc. It's a great platform that allows transparency and constant improvement in your marketing channels.", "What do you dislike?": "There's not much that I dislike about HubSpot. When I used it, we were able to send emails directly from the HS site, but once someone responded to the email, that response never showed up on site. (It was only in your Google inbox). That was one of the only limitations - it made it hard to keep track of your emails, and basically forced you to stick with GMail.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Most of the platform is FREE! Definitely consider even a free trial to see what HubSpot offers. From the Marketing to the Sales platforms - HubSpot has it all. The company is also very good at catering to your individual company needs. HubSpot built out an entire platform for my department based on what we described as being crucial. They were very helpful and made the platform intuitive. Highly recommend.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows us to view our customers in real time. We can see what they are interested by analyzing the emails they open and the links they click on. It also paints a picture of what our customers do NOT like by outlining who opts out of what and when. This then enables us to cater our emails to a very specific audience and really hone in on our target market, saving time and energy. Very impressed!"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The overall ease and data! There are so many wonderful helpful modules and tutorials that if I am ever stuck, I can easily find the solution. The marketing side and sales side link together brilliantly and there are more features than I can even explore!", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes there are minor glitches or saving issues, but I have never \"lost\" work because of it.  Usually the program auto-saves at some point so I can find older versions in the revisions section.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Terrific CRM system. More than I could have asked for literally has the ability to do it all! Very helpful staff, trainers, and account reps. I was thrown into it without any guidance or training and was able to teach myself the basics and furthered my knowledge with the academy certifications! They continually update features, add new helpful ones and quickly fix any problems that come up, which aren't that often. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot helps us communicate with our customers, where they are. It allows us to post, create ads, and monitor social media channels and connect on a one-to-one level. We use it for our educational blog. It stores great data which we can analyze and send off to our CEO. It easily allows us to organize campaigns in an efficient way and connect more content pieces using the cluster feature. We can stay on top of tasks with the projects and calendar feature. It is easy to show other team-mates what we're working on and status of projects. A lot of helpful business solutions! It also enhances our company's continuing education program with the pieces of training and certifications in the learning center and academy. "}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I use HubSpot in my personal business for its user-friendly CRM and email nurture campaigns. The ability to nurture leads from MQL to SQL. One other side note, and that I want to add is the incredible blog content they consistently write. I just got their July email which revolved around how to build better email. I have already started to implement their suggestions, and have so much more to do with them. ", "What do you dislike?": "The form builder could allow for more customization. It works well for what I need it to do, plus the ability to then trigger emails is invaluable to me. I would like to fully dive into Hubspot, but I can't quite afford it yet. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "This is an amazing tool for anyone getting their start in business with email campaigns. I would have designated more of my budget towards HubSpot (because I love it) and it has so much more potential than I initially realized. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead nurture, automated sending, and email composing. Plus blog posts to better coach me one how to build better emails. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 29, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": " As a former salesforce.com user, I was a bit nervous that I was but would not be as robust in terms of features and functionality. However, I love the dashboard, the list features, the email marketing capabilities, the social media integration is, and simply the way is organized by sales and marketing functionality.  As a marketing manager for a software company based in New York City, HubSpot has allowed me to send targeted emails to our prospect and current customer lists, perform a B testing on a variety of email campaigns, and track the success rate of our email marketing campaigns.  You can also easily manage different email templates, CTA buttons, and marketing assets  (ie. PDF\u2019s, logos, corporate imagery, etc.)  for use in email campaigns and/or landing pages.  You can also easily create forms (for use in landing / website pages) to capture prospect or customer information and easily store it within a system.", "What do you dislike?": " Right now I wish they were better marketing dashboards to take advantage of, since the sales dashboard\u2019s are super robust and informative. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": " HubSpot isn\u2019t easy to use CRM platform that provide you with everything you need to track marketing activities manage customer and prospect list, create targeted marketing campaigns via manual effort or automated workflows,  and easily manage the results of your sales and marketing efforts.  The platform is a bit pricey, and may not be as robust as a salesforce.com, but I prefer HubSpot because it provides me with tools I need to do my job well without being overwhelmed with unnecessary / extra features and functionality. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": " We currently use HubSpot to manage all of our customer information, track email marketing campaign, and manage our sales pipeline.   It provide us with a one stop shop for all things customer related-   Providing us with insights into how and when we\u2019ve engaged with customers, what activities they decided to participate in, and where in the sales cycle they are. "}}
{"author": ["Jussi P"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Project Manager"], "date": ["Apr 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Relatively easy to use and intuitive, but it takes weeks or even months to figure out all the tiny details of each feature HubSpot has to offer. Compated to for example Salesforce (although a complete different product, just comparing easy of use here), HubSpot is well thought out and works logically.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Lists and workflows are great, although you could achieve the same results using either in some cases. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has a best-in-class user interface. The platform is constantly capturing feedback and pushing updates. Above all, HubSpot feels like it's built by marketers for marketers.", "What do you dislike?": "HubSpot and Salesforce integration could be smoother. While HubSpot's landing and blog pages work, I tend to default to simpler tools.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Most enterprise marketing platforms offer similar functionality. I would give thought to working in the platform daily. HubSpot puts a strong emphasis on UI and UX, making the platform enjoyable to use daily, versus alternatives like Pardot and Marketo.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot campaigns are rooted in buyer personas. This helps my team segment and automate content. The platform houses quite a few powerful features, meaning I can use one platform versus many specialized tools."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 20, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like knowing which companies visit our site through the FREE prospecting tool in the marketing section. ", "What do you dislike?": "There's not too much i dislike. I think the pricing structure is kind of confusing with all the available add-ons but with the free tools you can find your worth and what you may need most and then from there make purchase decisions. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Utilize the free tools first to find your groove and then you will be able to discover which of their products can help benefit you most. Their product menu is huge and it's sometimes overwhelming but their customer service is great in helping you figure out what you might need and which tools would be best for your specific company. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead generation and really finding out if our marketing is working towards our goal audiences."}}
{"author": ["Pere V"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": ["Logistics"], "date": ["Aug 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "One of the best things of Hubspot is that they actually teach you a lot about online marketing, also the easy to use interface and the fact that all that you need is concentrated in one place, you will not need several programs to do the task, it is an all-in-one for e-commerce", "What do you dislike?": "money money money, everything requires payment, the support, the tools (many of them you could find for free elsewhere, but they compile them for you and it has a cost) and the subscription is based on 12 months contract", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "First try the trial version", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The contacts that they offer and the formation for the small and medium companies"}}
{"author": ["Kate J"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager"], "date": ["Feb 07, 2019", "Apr 26, 2018"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 24, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how I can manage all of the social posts for clients. It gives me easy access and organization. My job requires me to stay two weeks ahead on all social media posts for our clients, and I can do that with HubSpot by scheduling posts. This feature is my favorite because once I schedule a post, I don't have to worry about it again.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't like that it can be glitchy sometimes. I'll often get an error stating that the page cannot be loaded when my computer is working fine. I'll often have to reload the page in the middle of typing text for a post, forcing me to start over. However, this is an issue that I foresee being fixed in time.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely give it a try and see if it is right for you. You won't be disappointed.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Getting leads and content creating are much easier with this product and have changed my life for the better. Before, creating content for clients was something of a hassle and quite disorganized. Hubspot allows me to keep everything in one place and send it out all at once, doing away with the stress associated with social media management."}}
{"author": ["Devyn Michele H"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Host / Social Media & Content Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["Jul 11, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "it helps me keep track of my contacts...", "What do you dislike?": "it's clunky and visually unappealing. doesn't offer me as many tools as i wish it did. it's a little rigid in it's design as well. sometimes the search function doesn't perform that well as well. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "don't make any typos when data entering. hubspot's search is very rigid. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "hubspot is a great place for me to keep all my contacts together. i can keep track of who i've contacted and who i haven't. i use it often to categorize my client base and schedule times to contact them. i just wish it wasn't so clunky and rigid. "}}
{"author": ["Industry Analyst / Tech Writer"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the fact that you can build several module to make different pages.\r", "What do you dislike?": "I like the menu which is build automatically.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I don't like :\r"}}
{"author": ["Brianne L"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Owner", "Hospitality"], "date": ["Feb 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is very easy to use and set up.  I love that I can customize my dashboard and tool bar to highlight the parts I use most often.  I also find the email tracking tool incredibly useful as I can see when emails are opened, if links are clicked, etc.", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't anything I truly dislike about this product.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I use Hubspot to track sales, marketing and as a CRM.  It has helped me stay much more organized with all of my daily tasks"}}
{"author": ["Christopher M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Director", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 14, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "As a SaaS tool, HubSpot is always improving", "What do you dislike?": "Licensing model.  We are charged more for having more contacts.  This seems backwards to how we want to leverage the tool.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot for:\r"}}
{"author": ["User in Hospitality"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 15, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "-Ease of use\r", "What do you dislike?": "-super helpful support team when questions do arise\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Although I do find it to be easy to use now, there was a learning curve and it took me a month or so to get the hang of it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Definitely go for it! It's improved the way I do my job. When you do have a question don't hesitate to reach out to their support team, they are always there to help and are quick to respond. I'd also suggest checking out their yearly conference, Inbound, held in Boston in September. "}}
{"author": ["Cassandra C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 04, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "As a director of marketing HubSpot allows me to have one tool to execute and monitor almost all aspects of my marketing program. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are so functionality that are just better in other tools so while HubSpot offers them (chatbot + live chat) we leverage an additional tool.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "All sales and marketing are performed and monitored via the HubSpot system allowing for transparency across the agency."}}
{"author": ["Emilee C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Client Engagement Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["May 10, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that I can build and manage everything from my marketing to sales process in one window. In addition to the tool, Hubspot customers see a lot of success because of the consultative process that follows the purchase of the tool.", "What do you dislike?": "It is A TON of work. I wouldn't say I \"dislike\" this aspect, but its definitely a commitment to get started with inbound marketing and keep things moving forward.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you have the budget and time to put in, Hubspot can revolutionize the way you market your company and your clients.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have defined our sales and marketing process while optimizing the performance of our website and blog."}}
{"author": ["User in Higher Education"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that everything we need is available in one place. From websites to emails, it is convenient to have one platform for so many of our marketing needs.", "What do you dislike?": "I find that the navigation is not very intuitive. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure that you are utilizing the platform fully. There are so many more features beyond just the basics. Taking the time to discover them is well worth it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "This is more a fault of our own, but file organization and versioning can easily get out of hand. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really like the Analytics Tools feature where I can get great insights and data points about our traffic and leads.", "What do you dislike?": "I would like to have more options when it comes to the design and modification of the Lead Capture Forms.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot provides us with a clear and comprehensive perspective of where our traffic and leads are coming from and from what channel. In addition, we can see what landing pages convert best. All these insights help us understand our performance and make better data-driven decisions going forward."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a great tool for getting most out of our websites. Websites are easy to build and the tracking tools are useful. Linking hubspot to social media is also great feature.", "What do you dislike?": "For some features I've had to search some time. For example editing navigation bar wasn't in a logical place for me.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I build our product web pages, advertise new products and link blog texts to social media. My main goal is to get our products known to customers and to get new contacts."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Kathleen L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Strategist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is a great tool for introducing marketing automations to your business development process. With a small sales team, there's great opportunity to outline clear, valuable processes for marketing and sales teams to partner more closely.", "What do you dislike?": "There is a significant learning curve for anyone unfamiliar with customer relationship management tools. The capabilities and nuances of the tool require time and dedication to build out comprehensive marketing and sales processes.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you get one user to specialize and understand the full capabilities of the tool to make it worth your investment.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot to gather, organize, and prioritize leads collected through website lead generation marketing."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot makes it fairly easy to create and post new landing pages. Very straightforward editing and our design are consistent. Whenever I run into an issue, I have no problem contacting customer support and getting a quick resolution. ", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes I want to make a layout change, like spacing, that feels more difficult than necessary and even editing on the backend doesn't always work. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot landing pages allow our company to quickly add content to our website in a seamless fashion. We also utilize these pages to help us track event registration."}}
{"author": ["Erik M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Lead", "E-Learning"], "date": ["Dec 14, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the fact that HubSpot is constantly improving their interface and workflows. I have been using HubSpot for over four years and am responsible for four separate instances. The HubSpot tool makes it easy for me to manage the digital assets and more importantly push the leads through the inbound life cycle. ", "What do you dislike?": "Because I use multiple instances, there seems to be an inconsistency between some of the roll outs. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have increased our software subscriptions specifically bringing in new leads using the inbound methodology, blogging and email marketing. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how many different features hubspot has for a company. You can schedule and manage social media, you can send emails, you can build landing pages AND you can use it as CRM.", "What do you dislike?": "The user interface can be a bit confusing. It's sometimes hard to find what you are looking for. For example, social media is a bit hidden.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use hubspot for campaign creation, ease of landing page building, social media scheduling and management.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Landing page creation and tracking, social media scheduling. We've realized that setting an entire campaign up in hubspot allows for better tracking and reporting."}}
{"author": ["Marek W"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Campus Manager Dublin", "Professional Training & Coaching"], "date": ["Oct 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I find hubspot more intuitive and easier to work through than other CRM's", "What do you dislike?": "importing can be difficult to import contacts", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I found Hubspot more intuitive and easier than Salesforce!!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automation of communication. All my communications are automated to a certain point, saving me a huge amount of time"}}
{"author": ["Witek B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jun 13, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Capability to build your own pillar pages, emails, lead flows, robust analytics, templates, excellent customer service help. I  also love the app where I can scan a business card and convert it to a new contact within seconds! ", "What do you dislike?": "Need to know some code if customizing telplates", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's a great tool that utilizes a lot of the latest features that any marketer or sales professional will benefit from. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Saving our sales team's time and organizing thousands of contacts."}}
{"author": ["Justin C"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Delivery Team Manager", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Aug 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The UI for website/blog/landing page administration is very intuitive while still providing access to advanced functionality.", "What do you dislike?": "At first the learning curve of how different areas are connected to each other can be high.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easy content management of website, blog and landing pages along with the call to actions used on them."}}
{"author": ["Raphael M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development"], "date": ["Aug 05, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It does what you expect of a CRM. Simple/Intuitive to use with all the features you need.", "What do you dislike?": "There could be some more features to work more efficiently. Shortcuts for example. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Calling List optimization. "}}
{"author": ["Jay H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["VP of Marketing & Partnerships", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Jan 03, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ease of use, email templates, integration", "What do you dislike?": "Very little - some UI issues that make some things difficult to find, but you get used to it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We can manage a variety of marketing activities with HubSpot, with the best being email nurturing. We really like how we can allow customers already in our database to directly download white papers/guides and skip form fills - Marketo and Pardot don't let you do that. We can easily track and manage all contacts and create all sorts of filtering for campaigns."}}
{"author": ["Arjun C"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Arjun Singh Chauhan"], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is free of charge. Like other CRM platforms, you need not pay anything.", "What do you dislike?": "There is nothing that I don't like. It has everything that a CRM should.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It is easier to manage tickets and contacts using Hubspot. Apart from that, we can also teach somebody else easily."}}
{"author": ["Katie S"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Content Director", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 30, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is a great inbound marketing platform that simplifies content as well as contact management. It's social media, email, lead generation, analytics, and sales tools help us (and our clients) reach the right prospects and track their interactions with our company/content. ", "What do you dislike?": "The social monitoring tool only tracks Twitter interactions; it would be nice if it worked with more social media channels. Also, HubSpot updates the platform so often it's sometimes hard to keep up with changes. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Being able to not only generate leads but also follow their journey and interactions with our company and content is very useful."}}
{"author": ["Tara P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to track emails! This is so important when figuring out what reporters may be interested in pitching opportunities and knowing when and how often to contact them.", "What do you dislike?": "The customer service is not great. We are paying customers and when I had a problem with payment, I was told to read the FAQs next time I had an issue (I reached out over social media) the FAQs never would have answered my issue.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Pitching contacts, and getting results in a timely manner"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The best thing I like about Hubspot is that there is very minimal learning curve. You can get started very quickly and become a pro-user, unlike some other systems where you have to spend weeks to learn the platform before creating your first email or landing page.", "What do you dislike?": "Currently there are very limited form completion actions, though you can achieve the desired updates via workflows. But I would like to see more options added in the setting of form completion such as changing contact property value, lead score etc. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using Hubspot not just as our marketing automation system but also as a CMS. It is super easy for both purposes. My team are not experts in sending email or setting up landing pages in minutes."}}
{"author": ["Kaylee E"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Demand Generation Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Aug 08, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has many perks. You can manage your contacts, email, automation, workflows, landing pages, forms, social, reporting, literally almost everything straight from Hubspot. And it even integrates with Salesforce which is huge. They also have a great onboarding process that makes you feel comfortable with the product very quickly so you can get to work on the things that make a difference for your business.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't currently dislike anything about Hubspot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "With Hubspot we create landing pages, forms, post to social accounts, organize customer/lead data, create lists to sync to Salesforce, and create reports for visibility into our metrics."}}
{"author": ["Annelise L"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Director of Marketing and Operations", "Music"], "date": ["Nov 08, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how everything is in one spot. I have to do a lot of social media publishing for work, and Hubspot makes it easy to hit several birds with one stone in that I can publish the same message over twitter and facebook simultaneously. I can also easily schedule duplicate tweets for later, which I do just about every day. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that there seems to be no connection to instagram, pinterest, or tumblr. That would be really helpful. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take advantage of all the features it has to offer. You can gain so much insight on your audience! ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can get my social media posting done efficiently. I also love that Hubspot tracks so many different things about each post so I can gain insight on my audience. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 30, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I personally like the ability to create if this than that sequences. For example, creating campaigns  that generate tasks given the receivers actions (if clicked link, send notification to sales rep, etc). I also really like the reporting functionality Hubspot offers. This helps us a ton when it comes to reporting to our board, as well as making strategic decisions regarding the business/ ", "What do you dislike?": "The formatting features are not always the best when using the web content management. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We utilize Hubspot for our Marketing Campaigns and as our Sales CRM. Our marketing team create campaigns geared towards particular customer segments, then notifies our Sales team when further action is warranted. The analytics have helped us out a bunch when it comes to improving our sales and marketing processes. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Gambling & Casinos"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "My personal favorite feature is the CRM tool. It is so easy to use and provides you with all of the information. Within the CRM, you have access to the pipeline which you set up the parameters for. Managers are also able to see the progress of all the salespeople. Very useful tool. ", "What do you dislike?": "In my opinion, it is difficult to set up reminders. Also, I think it would be much easier if any reminders or notifications are desktop enabled. To the best of my understanding, this feature is not yet available. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I owned a very small company. HubSpot was satisfactory for us at the time, but the more we grew. we felt it appropriate to switch to a larger platform. If you are working on a start up, or are a stand alone small business, I would highly recommend this product. Additionally, I can really only speak to the CRM tool. I understand that there are other very useful tools in this product, I just unfortunately was not privy to them. Other members of my team were. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am not particularly solving any business problems, but I can see how it could be useful for doing such a thing. I primarily use this tool to modify a sales process and using the hubspot formula, maximize the possibility of closing sales within an appropriate amount of time. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that Hubspot is intuitive and powerful, it is pretty much possible to do anything with it as long as you know a little bit about the software. I really enjoy all the training they got available and customer support is always happy to help with anything.", "What do you dislike?": "Might be a little challenging to use Hubspot to its' full potential, as I said, it is pretty much possible to do anything with it but that requires sometimes some engineering support or more advanced knowledge of the platform, for example in customizing some templates or when Hubspot is integrated with other software like Salesforce. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Having everything in one spot is great to me: blog, emails, landing pages, contacts, etc. We have Hubspot integrated with other marketing platforms which is a big plus to me. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We use HubSpot to manage all content marketing and demand generation activities. We manage everything from email campaigns to social media to SEO in the visually appealing platform.", "What do you dislike?": "There is a lot to learn as a new user, and 9 months in we find ourselves having to clean up some of the areas which had been incorrectly implemented during those first exploratory months. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The tool has allowed us to design workflows to nurture our leads at each stage of the buying cycle. It's also provided transparency and ease of reporting on content efforts and marketing campaigns. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 06, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Everything (CRM, Marketing Automation, Website and Social, Service, and Sales Tools) are all in the same place which makes cross-team communication much easier. The UX is very slick and their support team is knowledgable and friendly.", "What do you dislike?": "The flip side of Hubspot doing almost everything is that it takes a while to get our team members and data on boarded and everyone up to speed. There are also some small details that I would love to see included. For example, the automation workflows have if/then options which essentially allow for a yes/no outcome. Many marketers, including myself, would be very likely to create automations that have more complex outcomes.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Centralising CRM, sales and marketing data. The ability to build automation into these processes."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Many tools come together in one system and teams can work together better.  From social media via e-mail marketing and support to entire landing pages, anything is possible. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are no basic functions in all areas.  This prevents one from using HubSpot as the sole tool.  It is complicated in some places, so employees need training", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The entire marketing and support team can work centrally with HubSpot.  Campaigns can be created across platforms so that, for example, newsletters and social media can be analyzed together."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The Salesforce integration is great, I like the customizable lead scoring based on the client interactions that it automatically tracks, the API has great documentation and is pretty easy to figure out. ", "What do you dislike?": "While it has a lot of benefits, it does lack the flexibility and ability to do what some of the more well established CRM solutions offer. It is still relatively new and growing, but I would like to see more detailed marketing communication segmentation abilities.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Patience with it. It is still growing.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Integration with Salesforce, any easy solution to adopt, Marketing lists, scoring leads, form fill setup."}}
{"author": ["Michael D"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Sales", "Information Services"], "date": ["Apr 04, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ability to bulk upload all contacts and match them by email (reducing duplicates)\r", "What do you dislike?": "Ability to organize based on company\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Ability to see who interacts with your website and receive lead notifications for those who drop by\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The layout is easy to understand and intuitive. \r"}}
{"author": ["Landon B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder"], "date": ["May 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has good free options to get started, and a variety of paid options to meet different business needs.", "What do you dislike?": "I find that the ease of use is a little bit lacking; the setup process could be somewhat clearer.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot helps with marketing analytics \u2014 informing us on what we\u2019re doing well and what we can improve."}}
{"author": ["Claire E. G"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing & Event Specialist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Apr 03, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is super easy to use and I can do whatever I need to get done with just this one program. I sometimes get confused with the interface but I am easily able to find tutorials to help me out and get me back on track just by googling.  HubSpot always helps me figure out what I am doing, and has really helped me with my website when I have been completely lost! I love the HubSpot certifications they've really helped me and my company as well which has been awesome! HubSpot is definitely my one stop shop for everything I need to get done. ", "What do you dislike?": "The social media app could use some help as well as the bulk uploading feature is very... well, bulky. The SEO stuff I feel like I don't get my moneys worth, but I love the content features. That being said the other features make up for this 10-fold. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Go for it! It is a great option and has everything you need!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It has really helped me integrate everything I need as a marketer and improve my business and my site. I "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The UI is incredibly intuitive making almost anything that you want to do possible as long as you have a great understanding of how hubspot works in the backend.", "What do you dislike?": "Like everything that I like, it would be a lot better if it were cheaper.. or free! Otherwise, if their were better features for outbound sales. Although we are very Inbound focused, like most organizations, it is not the sole channel of growth.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have been able to drastically increase our conversions, online reach, and improve our communication with minimal added manual steps."}}
{"author": ["Neville W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Sales & Marketing Support Specialist", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Jul 21, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love anything that teaches you how to use it. Certifications are a growing collection of mine so the Academy is great with Hubspot.  I like the ease of use this platform gives me as a marketer.  I have used others in the past and they were very clunky and scattered either within themselves or within the CRM they had to live in.  Hubspot is just easy and does what it is meant to do. ", "What do you dislike?": "The only thing I dislike about it is that reporting costs extra.  There is an add-on you have to pay a lot more (for SMB) a month to be able to get all of the reporting tools that makes Hubspot really awesome.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Get ready to write a lot.  Inbound is never ending, but it works. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Getting our name out there.  Boosting marketing efforts. Crushing the competition on SERPs.  Driving more business. "}}
{"author": ["Seb A"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Search Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Even in it's free version Hubspot CRM has a lot of powerful features making it great for Small Businesses. I use it in my day to day job as well as using the free version for two side project businesses I am working on.", "What do you dislike?": "Not all the sales tools work with an email set up via IMAP, you need a Gmail or Outlook system to really take advantage of the full features", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The support team is very helpful and will point you in the right direction even if you have a free account!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Improve lead generation using the CRM. Automate follow ups with potential clients. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really like the look and feel.  It looks great.  I also like the website and landing page capabilities.", "What do you dislike?": "Support and the SFDC integration is lacking ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you use SFDC you need to really evaluate this.  The integration hasn't gone well for us and support hasn't been the best.  I've never used another product that had SFDC hiccups like this before, and the lack of urgency by Hubspot was beyond belief.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use Hubspot for email nurture, landing page creation, and we host our website via Hubspot.  The website is great though it was a ton of work to set up.  We also create a lot of individual landing pages for different campaigns."}}
{"author": ["Jonathan D"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager", "Medical Devices"], "date": ["Jun 24, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Slick feature rich marketing automation and content management platform. It's easy to use but doesn't back down for power users. You have great deal of control with work flow logic, segmentation, dynamic content, and content creation.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Their customer support is a breath of fresh air compared to other SaaS providers. They were answering questions about advanced workflow logic (with multiple if then conditions) and code. My web development company charges us $200 an hour to answer these things, but with Hubspot it's all part of the package.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Brianna H"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Graphic Designer"], "date": ["Dec 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Having an actual teacher and not just a voice over.", "What do you dislike?": "The length, but it is necessary to obtain all that knowledge.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The community that also uses hub spot is always there to assist and help you along the way. I have realized my issues with HubSpot can easily be resolved with the FAQ.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I wish you could upload .GIFs through this platform for Facebook."}}
{"author": ["Claire C"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Content Marketing Specialist", "Public Relations and Communications"], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "This certification course is one I will reference back to my entire career. I feel as if I not only learned tremendously but have seen our sales/marketing efforts increase significantly. It's amazing! Very interactive & very beneficial for all aspects of a company.", "What do you dislike?": "The testing can be difficult, however, it's definitely worth your time/taking notes. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Sales/Marketing relationship & communication, teamwork, and campaign brainstorming sessions"}}
{"author": ["Jacob N"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["VP of Marketing"], "date": ["Apr 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's so easy to run marketing operations using the suite of tools and integrations", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing substantial. The social publisher could be better but it hasn't stopped us from achieving our aims.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's amazing - the perfect marketing platform. Do a trial, read the blog and  read reviews.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Website CMS, blog, email, nurturing, landing pages & workflows."}}
{"author": ["Jonathon T"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Founder", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 22, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like Hubspot because it removes the gap between sales and marketing to create a fully integrated marketing management system. It connects analytics, social media, CRM, marketing automation and more.", "What do you dislike?": "The price. It's not the most expensive, but it's far from the least expensive. They've also added a lot separate tools that are add-on items that can give the impression that you're being nickel and dimed.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you're ready to dive right in. This is a robust system that requires team buy in and commitment. I recommend running through the trial, and if you'd like to move forward with Hubspot, contacting an agency to help you with it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has allowed us to get rid of numerous disparate systems to streamline our offering. "}}
{"author": ["Consultant"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The template editor is a good tool that can be used to customize the website in a friendly manner for people who are not much into coding", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it is a bit confusing to find a css and edit since it can be in several places along the hubspot. On the other hand, when you are creating the landing page it is very simple to define the css that will take effect on that page\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": ".", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It is a simple solution solver. Will get you quickly into creating the content pages and build the site. Has a good option of staging were you can set a validation process before taking the page live"}}
{"author": ["Dustin B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["CEO", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jul 28, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The team at HubSpot are fantastic. From our CAM, Jacob Carlson, to the tech support staff. They are always on top of it and make sure that they are as helpful as they possibly can be. The software is fantastic, but the team behind it is what separates them.", "What do you dislike?": "There are a few features that I'd really like to see added such as exportable reports, but they are constantly working to add new features.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "This is where marketing is going. Inbound is the future and the present standard. We prefer HubSpot over any of their competition and have not regretted our decision for a second. HIGHLY RECOMMEND.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have become a HubSpot Partner Agency and it has completely transformed how our agency functions. We are all in on inbound marketing and they've helped us get there. Hoping to be a Gold Partner by September!"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The automation and integration of contact properties. Ability to use workflow pretty much for every CRM related automation imaginable. Sales pipeline and deal management for sales staff is very useful.", "What do you dislike?": "The conversation management is pretty problematic. With recent updates, the intuitiveness is in fact reduced. The Forms submission do not appear on the main inbox, and although this is a known issue to Hubspot, there has still been no fix provided. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Managing the support, sales, and subscriber related tickets, conversation, meetings and deals from one place is pretty amazing. With HS control of the sales pipeline and its connection with customer success and support has become seamless and apparent. The automation of marketing campaigns, saves major pain point in sales automation."}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how you can clone emails, it's easy to navigate (i had never used it and found it intuitive to understand and learn), the easy scheduling is good, basic performance monitoring of campaigns and simple design.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes emails don't format correctly when you send through the test emails. HTML codes don't always work and sometimes when you ask for help they don't really give you advice to fix it. They recommend to speak to a designer who checks the code and it is correct but the email still doesn't format so you have to clone and paste it in to a new email.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is good but sometimes the emails format oddly", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing - easy to schedule and automate "}}
{"author": ["Jason Z"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Managing Director", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jun 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how nearly every inbound growth tool we use is built into HubSpot. I also love the level of support and education they offer. ", "What do you dislike?": "In the past, there were a few bugs in the system, but their support team is responsive and helpful.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Ask a HubSpot user to share their experience. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use it for our clients to increase sales through inbound and outbound tactics. We see an immediate uptick in traffic and lead generation. "}}
{"author": ["Karl G"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Head of Software Development", "Internet"], "date": ["Jun 19, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot shows me all of my information at a glance and allows me to easily manage my content Marketing campaigns. Blog articles and Social Media are all managed through HubSpot and it makes my life easy.\r", "What do you dislike?": "I was new to Content marketing and the HubSpot Academy provided me with  a great understanding of what Content Marketing / Inbound Marketing was, how I could use it for my business and gave me hints and tips to get me going. The ongoing support from my account manager is second to none and I highly recommend looking at HubSpot. there is an excellent range of integrations from partners, including BlogMutt, a great source for blogging content.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The entry level product has 100 users included, which is a limit you can quickly exceed and a higher user limit would help. There are lots of add on products, but I would prefer to see different pricing tiers, depending on the size of business.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The HubSpot academy is a great place to start learning about inbound marketing, from a very experienced and dedicated team."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I had a great user experience all the way through, including the interface, learning curve, and customer support.", "What do you dislike?": "Needs more customization in areas such as email creation.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are looking for CRM and marketing automation platform that provides a seamless experience, and doesn't involve as much of a learning curve as other options, HubSpot is the way to go.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It has equipped us with the tools to properly nurture and manage our customers from one centralized location, rather than using multiple martech solutions."}}
{"author": ["Hector G"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": ["Partner - EPM - SAP BusinessObjects Strategy Management", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Mar 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy integration with our current data and processes and very easy integration with our website www.cipherbsc.com", "What do you dislike?": "No dislikes, we would like the platform to be less expensive. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Problems:\r"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I appreciate the intuitiveness of the platform and ease of use. Our current plan doesn't have all the bells and whistles but it's just enough for what we need at this time.", "What do you dislike?": "The reporting features aren't as powerful as some competitors and it can be cumbersome to maintain list hygiene. A/B testing is only available on emails of a certain recipient size - troublesome if you're still growing your subscriber base.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automated emails and workflows make nurturing our existing clients and prospects easy. The time saved is valuable."}}
{"author": ["User in Education Management"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The contact views you can create for prospecting (sales), email tracking, and the ability to store marketing content in Hubspot so that you can easily add documents to emails (when synced through GMail) and either gate or un-gate them accordingly", "What do you dislike?": "Making calls out of Hubspot proved to be glitchy and regularly got complaints that the service was choppy ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "We've had less than awesome experiences with the Hubspot support team for small errors in Gmail sync, etc. but all of it has eventually been resolved. In general, the more you use this product, the more you'll get out of it", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are solving the problem of consolidating marketing and sales efforts and understanding the effectiveness of all outreaches (either by marketing or sales) "}}
{"author": ["Adriana B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Demand Generation Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Nov 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "- good automation capabilities (workflows, sequences etc)\r", "What do you dislike?": "- the tool brings marketing and sales together\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "- easy to make edits on your website\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Something I find really helpful about Hubspot is the smart view tab for emails", "What do you dislike?": "It would be great if you could split a list in half yourself rather than having to use the A/B Setting. That way, if your A/B test had several rounds you could have individual lists that you could use rather than importing new lists from previous emails, which feels rigid. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot presents a huge amount of data accurately and accessibly. It's criteria is also great for ruling people in or out of Comms. "}}
{"author": ["Peter P"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How diverse the marketing functions are. It offers everything from CRM to email to blogging to slide-in CTAs (called lead flows).", "What do you dislike?": "Can be too simple. For example, I'd love to be able to customize CSS for mobile and desktop separately without having to know HubL, their specific code syntax. Ideally I'd love a bit more customization options without totally sacrificing the simplicity. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Go for it! The platform is able to meet nearly any marketing needs and requirements. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We switched our company blog to HubSpot and have seen it pay dividends with how simple it is to use CTAs. We've also been able to considerably boost our email marketing efforts. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There are many things which you can use from your Marketing Automation like workflows, eNurturing campaigns, lead management etc", "What do you dislike?": "They don't provide any option to take website back-up.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "While creating page on HubSpot, always facing challenge of Cache.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I would recommend to set-up weekly call to know more about HubSpot features that customer can use"}}
{"author": ["Lois J"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Consultant", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Apr 26, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "All functionality integrated in the one dashboard.", "What do you dislike?": "It doesn't really group contacts together in the one organisation, which in a B2B can make life difficult as we're not talking about one person buying one thing. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Be prepared to dive head-first into the inbound marketing methodology to get the most out of HubSpot. The tool will work best for you when you are feeding the marketing engine with great content and offers that your market will love. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Jesika B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Owner", "Research"], "date": ["Jun 10, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The entire sales team loves this thing. I feel very gratified to have found it and recommended it. It will supercede Salesforce as the tool we use because it is easy to learn, has a great, simple interface, and users can get up to speed quickly. It does not REQUIRE a boot camped administrator to learn how to use it, and it fits our needs quite well as an SMB startup.", "What do you dislike?": "The marketing component of HubSpot's offering is super duper expensive and I'm not sure why. Also, great free CRM component but $200 per month just for reports seems a little...avaricious? Carrot-and-stick, like. But overall, quite happy with the adoption.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Free CRM is good, but they will get you with the additional things you need for a complete solution.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Buy-in from ALL the people who need to use a CRM. And buy-in. We are just starting but already finding it solves A LOT of issues."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Isaac B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 10, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Excellent CRM and sales side of things, intuitive, easy to understand, fast to train new salespeople on how to use it effectively. In general, the product is easy to use and even less tech-savvy people can quickly figure out their way around it.", "What do you dislike?": "The website functionality is hindered by a lack of customization options (namely plugins) and there aren't too many affordable Hubspot developers out there. They aren't transparent about the quality of their servers they use for shared hosting making it difficult to address TTFB issues.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Keeping track of our thousands of customers and having a lot of features offered under one SaaS."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 05, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I have just recently started using this product but so far it's amazing!  I can see all of my potential customers and which ads they clicked on.  This allows us to specifically target certain customers and to see which ads are bringing in the most leads I highly recommend this product!", "What do you dislike?": "I have not found many problems with HubSpot just that some of the technical support could be better times.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It gives us all the analytics for our ads in one spot which saves us time which in turn saves us money!"}}
{"author": ["Tristan D"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Apr 18, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The scheduled posting on social media saves huge amounts of time dipping in and out of different platforms. Also, the landing pages and automated processes make things run more smoothly.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The onboarding process and ongoing support are both knowledgeable and swift.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Segmenting data can be rather frustrating as rules can't be put in place (such as 'select anyone who has visited a particular page in the last 2 months) so you have to detail each individual element separately. "}}
{"author": ["Kate B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Consultant", "Real Estate"], "date": ["Jan 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Pretty easy to use ... the company is leader in inbound marketing so it's great to review their articles/knowledge base and have a customer success manager always available. Their live support is great too.", "What do you dislike?": "I'm used to Pardot so it's been a transition. I wish there were easier ways to pull reports and there was the ability to tag customers with specific attributes. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Review several marketing automation platforms for features and pricing. really evaluate what you need most and select the providor based on that. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Serves as our primary marketing automation tool to nurture prospects and current customers."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I love of using HubSpot is that you can easily launch landing pages and blog within minutes, customizing, adding style and animation is really easy, also you can reuse the styles. The community is really helpful, they answer your questions in a short amount of time. I like the way HubSpot manages the assets of the webpages to improve performance. ", "What do you dislike?": "I struggled with the page caching the content (stylesheet), so I had to flush the DNS, everytime I change the stylesheet. I had to add a naive piece of code to avoid this bahavior. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Wit HubSpot we can have a fully featured CMS, with marketing tools included, managing the content is so easy. We can move from one implementation or design to another without hassle. "}}
{"author": ["Agency"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is an extremely user-friendly service, offering an endless array of tools to mix and match in order to customize the best experience for your respective clients. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are times when improvements are rolled out with little notice or direction, which necessitates a bit of an adjustment period, in order to incorporate these new features. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot's ability to pinpoint traffic flow to particular site pages, to track email open and click rates, and to rank blog and topic cluster performance trends are all integral to pinpointing the best strategies to implement with certain clients. "}}
{"author": ["Remy W"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Faculty Support Assistant"], "date": ["Oct 30, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot provides a lot of great features for marketing, such as multistream functionality and live analytics on marketing campaigns. It also is pretty useful for tracking emails sent to clients.", "What do you dislike?": "There are almost too many features and the layout is not always intuitive, so it takes a lot of training to really get up to speed and a lot of trial and error.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make use of the Hubspot support staff, as they are usually very helpful.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Management of marketing campaigns and client development."}}
{"author": ["James B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Media Specialist", "Non-Profit Organization Management"], "date": ["Jun 06, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "At first glance, HubSpot could be just another software/company looking to make a buck. But let me tell you - HubSpot has the most amazing support I've ever experienced. It's one thing to provide a great software, but to provide an academy to learn how to do my job better?! That's above and beyond. Every time I've worked with the support staff, they have devoted themselves to fixing my issue, answering my question, and making sure that I feel valued and heard. HubSpot's software rocks, but their support really makes them shine.", "What do you dislike?": "The price for all this amazingness is a bit steep for my industry (non-profit/ministry). So it's been a bit of a challenge to convince my organization to stay with it. Thanks to great results it's gotten easier.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The price may seem steep, but if you can afford one year with HubSpot, do it. I believe that the software and support will have paid for itself within that time if you really utilize it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Purposeful website visits that lead to relationships, rather than dropping every potential contact out the bottom of an un-optimized site. Nurturing leads into customers by providing relevant content and encouraging stories that show results of donations to our donors."}}
{"author": ["Keith P"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["VP of Client Success", "Legal Services"], "date": ["May 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The mobile app and marketing campaign tracking is very useful.", "What do you dislike?": "The ability to customize and complications internally to understand the distinction/value of contant vs. company vs. deal. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you want this product to be your 360 degree view of customers...", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Looking for one source of a digital truth for our prospects, customers, and partners."}}
{"author": ["Tal V"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Freelance Writer and Strategist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jun 05, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is a jack-of-all-trades solution. Building emails, landing pages, and workflows is relatively intuitive, and its centralized campaign management is fantastic for obtaining ROI and measuring it. Perfect for small companies and agencies looking to manage them. ", "What do you dislike?": "Jack of all trades, master of none. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Jess M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Lead", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Apr 24, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "My favorite feature of the Hubspot platform is how easy it is to understand and translate into your business model. We have been using Hubspot for about 2 months now and have learned the ins and outs of inbound methodology. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike the price of Hubspot. I do agree that it is worth the money, but if you're a smaller sized business the price tag might seem extremely out of range.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would definitely consider Hubspot if your business generates over $100K in revenue, the price tag is 100% worth it. If you're at all worried about generating inbound leads or coming up with a strategy, Hubspot is the best tool out there for you.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are solving all inbound strategy problems. With Hubspot you are assigned to a specialist that helps you understand the software and plan an inbound strategy from the ground up. "}}
{"author": ["Ron W"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Analyst"], "date": ["Oct 27, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is your one stop shop for all of your marketing needs, and is a great way to keep track of your marketing campaigns and adjust them based on live data. It is also great for customer management and logging communication.", "What do you dislike?": "There are so many features that sometimes HubSpot's platform can feel overwhelming.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make use of the HubSpot experts, who are on call to help you with any hurdles that you come into.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Creating unified marketing campaigns and tracking these campaigns with data."}}
{"author": ["James R"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Director", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ease of use, simple interface and depth of capabilties. You have to pay a pretty penny for it, but the full suite of features can't be beat anywhere else.", "What do you dislike?": "The cost is quite high for the full suite of features. Although, I do believe it's worth every penny. Just might be cost-prohibitive for certian busiensses.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead scoring and marketing automation. Since implementing a lead scoring framework, we've been able to get a better idea of what our funnel looks like and spot areas we can improve."}}
{"author": ["Ryan G"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot does everything. In addition to hosting our website, we use it for crm, email automation, analytics and more.", "What do you dislike?": "Some features, like PPC ads, are just dumbed down versions of tools you can get elsewhere for free. However, it is nice that they are all accessible in the same place, without having to leave my dashboard. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot's codeless web design tools have allowed a coding beginner like me to build pages in minutes instead of days. Automation workflows have saved our sales team countless man hours."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The fact that the software is intuitive and easy to use is by far it's best quality. Anytime I have a question or am unsure there are also plenty of resources online of troubleshooting ideas.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't like how there are often delays in updating or changing something, or the lag that sometimes exists in reporting.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has helped us be more centralized using mostly one software to manage a multitude of different things. For this reason, it's more convenient for multiple teams to use at my company."}}
{"author": ["Shikhil S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["CEO", "Computer & Network Security"], "date": ["Jul 03, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the fact that this tool comes from people who themselves are crazy marketers. Been personally following Hubspot's blog and what they preach is exactly how their products are aligned. ", "What do you dislike?": "While free versions are available, the costs are sometimes a bit confusing. Sometimes you want to use all their products as they work seamlessly together but then the total costing comes out to be a lot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Interesting tool for customer retention and management. However, we have better ones in market too.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using Hubspot to increase customer retention and increase interaction points with our customers on our website."}}
{"author": ["James S"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Director Sales Operations", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Oct 01, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is so easy to use and the support is absolute top notch. Very useful university. Easy Salesforce connection", "What do you dislike?": "Not much really. To get the best out of hubspot I feel you need hubspot sales as well and that can easily double the cost", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I have used Eloqua, Marketo, Pardot and Acton as well. For me, Hubspot is the easiest to use, and the quickest to realise benefits. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automating the follow up process. Automating marketing and flow of leads from the website into SFDC"}}
{"author": ["Richard B"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Media Manager, Communications Dept.", "Higher Education"], "date": ["Jul 21, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": " The automatic updates about emails being opened, whose opened them and what links/files they're going for after opening. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are lot of options and it sometimes feels very overwhelming to have all of that laid out at once. Especially with the marketing and CRM options, I'll feel like I'm trying to make a website in terms of complexity. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": " I'm using Hubspot to drastically alter how I compose pitch emails,  especially with cold contacting clients. Because of all the tracking options,  I can see in real time what strategies work and how to direct the eyes of potential clients. "}}
{"author": ["Jacob J"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Owner", "Writing and Editing"], "date": ["Jun 01, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The thing I like best about Hubspot is how easy it is to use. They also go above and beyond to educate their users on using the product. You will not be thrown to the wolves or have to resort to endless youtube videos (although some of them may be of benefit) in order to use this product.", "What do you dislike?": "The main thing I dislike is the potential for price creep. The price for using Hubspot goes up as the amount of contacts increase. Also, if you require ongoing technical support odds are you will have to pay for it.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure to weigh your options. Many of the tools that Hubspot offers can be found freely if you know where to look, but Hubspot offers them all in one place. This makes using the features of the software much easier.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has streamlined how we communicate with contacts and allows us greater marketing capabilities."}}
{"author": ["Francesco P"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Specialist"], "date": ["Jun 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The all-in-one platform for digital mktg", "What do you dislike?": "everything is so cool, I can not remember any issue (maybe mobile issue once)", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "You can activate a free trial, let's see on your own HS full potential! it's awesome", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HS allows me to manage my inbound marketing campaign from the begin (content creation) to the end (share on social). I saved a lot of time and money thanks to an incredible all-in-one platform and automation functionalities."}}
{"author": ["Blair P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Online Marketing Manager", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["May 31, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "When my most recent employer purchased the hubspot platform (and I had used it with past agencies and larger businesses, now working for a more startup business), after a month I was very worried. I wasn't seeing the same results. But I quickly realized - thanks to Hubspot's amazing onboarding period, why and how I wasn't seeing the same results I was used to seeing with my other previous agencies/larger business positions.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Using hubspot in a start up isn't easy - it requires dedication, and work, and for an employee to be capable of wearing multiple hats - but hubspot's industry best features are what separates it from every other total marketing package.  (And I truly can't speak highly enough of utilizing the onboarding period and process!)", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I wish the onboarding would last a bit longer - I feel like while it was super helpful, I wasn't able to get the most out of it, because as a start up, my multi hat wasn't entirely focused on inbound marketing/hubspot efforts and so the great suggestions they had I couldn't implement in time to get results/suggestions/ideas."}}
{"author": ["Sophie H"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Specialist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of the tools to automate and boost your marketing systems", "What do you dislike?": "Emails don't look the same in Outlook which is a Hubspot error", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation, once in place, takes a lot of small jobs off of my plate so I can focus on developing & optimizing our website. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Higher Education"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 17, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Compared to many other competitors, HubSpot is relatively easy to learn to use and is quite robust in terms of useful features. Customer support is typically quick to respond by email and works hard to get questions and problems resolved.", "What do you dislike?": "Over the past year, the HubSpot platform has been going through a major UI overhaul, which has resulted in an inconsistent and sometimes unpredictable UX. It seems at times as though they have over-engineered certain aspects of the UI and removed some functionality that I previously found helpful.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure that you do your due diligence in your comparison between marketing automation platforms. While HubSpot has been great from my experience, it all depends on the needs of your organization. Ask around for opinions and place greater emphasis on those that align well with your use case.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows the full integration of website, email marketing, social media, and CRM for one-stop shopping for all things digital marketing."}}
{"author": ["Jo\u00e3o Marcelo M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Country Manager Brazil & Portugal", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 10, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot allow our team to centralize and track a great a amount of campaigns in different markets we are running.", "What do you dislike?": "There are a few improvements that could be done to the platform in terms of email workflows.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Also in the CRM side, the tracking of each conversation with leads and clients lack some features that are already available in some services.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'd definitely recommend Hubspot if you are looking into better organize your marketing efforts.\r"}}
{"author": ["Hannah C"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Content Marketing Coordinator ", "Internet"], "date": ["May 28, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I was a very big fan of the analytics this tool offers. The amount of data they can gather and aspects of clients interactions on your site they can measure is amazing. I was also very impressed with their customer service team who were always very helpful and quick with getting back to me with any type of questions/issues I may have had. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wasn't the biggest fan of their \"templates' for landing pages, emails and even the blog. It is built for very simple use, unless you want to buy outside templates. We still kept Unbounce, and our blog on wordpress for the sure customization aspect because we just didn't fell Hubspot was close to what Unbounce offered (landing page wise) we were even told when purchasing that many clients keep Mailchimp and Unbounce for these same reasons.  It made us kind of wish hubspot has an al la cart offer since we really were only using them for half of their features but had to pay for the entire system. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Better creative aspects, better customization, better landing pages and blog templates and creative options. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The metrics and lead nurturing programs we are able to flawlessly run within them is wonderful. Its great for organizing our marketing leads and contacts and managing a wonderful lead nurturing workflow. "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User in Consumer Goods"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Publishing social posts on Hubspot is easy and seamless. I like the calendar view because I can see what i have planned out for the month, make drafts and schedule them, and move them around if needed. I especially love that it sends posts to instagram automatically. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish that you could do a bit more, like post multiple images to instagram or add video captions to facebook, but i get that that might be difficult and has to do with the social platforms themselves. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easy scheduling, especially on weekends when i am not working and need the social posts to go out. Having drafts is helpful becuase if it is not approved and scheduled it won't go out. "}}
{"author": ["joe m"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager"], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's simplicity - so easy to start with. Support is really good, easily accessible and helpful.", "What do you dislike?": "Can be a little limited as a result of it's simplicity, and is too easy to setup multiple, overlapping campaigns, workflows emails, CTAs etc.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "lead capture and automation"}}
{"author": ["Joshua T"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Founder, President & CEO", "Philanthropy"], "date": ["May 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The CRM is so easy to use, we love this the most, the marketing, emailing and analytics are good too, but CRM is highly recommended.", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't much that we dislike about Hubspot it does everything we need and again is very easy to use", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "IF you need something easy, choose HubSpot, you will not be disappointed!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our biggest problem we had when switching was having a good CRM, this provided that and so much more!"}}
{"author": ["Nicole M"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Automation Manager", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["May 27, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The user interface. The entire set up is extremely intuitive, which is extremely helpful when you're just starting out. Everything is exactly where you would expect it to be and basic tasks (creating/sending email, workflows, landing pages) all function exactly the way you would expect.  The workflow tool in particular is extremely straightforward and easy-to-use. Hubspot support is also incredibly responsive and helpful.", "What do you dislike?": "The reporting side of things leaves something to be desired (even with the much-hyped new reporting add-on), but between GA, Salesforce, and our other reporting tools we are able to get what we need. We have occasionally encountered glitches with our Hubspot-SF integration, but Hubspot support has always been very quick to help us resolve these issues.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take advantage of Hubspot's many educational resources. Between blogs and the Hubspot academy Hubspot gives you all of the tools and knowledge you need to create and implement a successful inbound marketing program.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Trying to acquire, score, and nurture more leads. The scoring model enables us to ensure that our sales organization is only working the best leads, and the easy to use workflow tool makes setting up nurture tracks a breeze."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 31, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the ease of use of Hubspot and the robust capabilities that are perfect for our growing organization.", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't much that I dislike when it comes to Hubspot...have yet to find something.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great tool that will do almost everything that you need when it comes to marketing automation, content management, sales enablement tools, etc.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The business problems I am trying to solve using HubSpot is streamlining our marketing operations and being able to capture all analytics related to marketing activity from different channels. The benefits that I've seen already is in the reporting functions and being able to see real-time where campaigns are at and what type of content is working best in our marketing mix."}}
{"author": ["Carly D"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Tier 1 -  Account Manager with Intel and IBM", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a Fantastic tool. It is to user friendly and I find it easy view the forms that were filled out for a quick response.I\u2019ve also noticed that the link below to salesforce is a need to have", "What do you dislike?": "I don\u2019t have any dislikes at this time but I would like to see AI Automated tools that can integrate with both HubSpot and salesforce", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot easily integrates with Salesforce so it prevents a lot of strange third parties and unprofessional form making"}}
{"author": ["Haley T"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder/CMO", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 17, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is great for the team to share information and we love blogging out of Hub spot. Also used heavily for creating landing pages and workflows. ", "What do you dislike?": "The social integration is terrible. We are very limited on what we can monitor and social engagement is huge for us. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are looking to focus on landing pages, lead generation, and blogging, this is a great tool. You can also utilize their videos for more knowledge. Very helpful. However, if you need a solid way to organize social platforms and messaging, this isn't worth the time or money. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have become more organized and identified our buyer's journey. We have also been able to successfully monitor conversions via blog. "}}
{"author": ["User in Human Resources"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 05, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that everything is in one place so that when it comes to reporting, HubSpot can give you detailed results. The workflows are definitely my favourite tool - being able to automate actions rather than having to do everything manually. ", "What do you dislike?": "Adding/removing people from lists - it would be great if there was a quicker way of doing this, rather than having to go into each contact. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do the training on HubSpot academy", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Being able to automate our actions - time-saving and less room for error."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Design"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It wasn't until after we switched to HubSpot that we realized how much we were missing out on with our digital marketing. We love the ease of use with the email and landing page designer as well as the tracking available through the system.", "What do you dislike?": "We wish there was a better way to link contacts and companies to have field information flow from one to the other. When you have a lot of generic email addresses (@gmail, @outlook, etc.) this feature doesn't really work.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Improving our marketing automation processes with targeted CTAs and landing pages that allow us to have a nearly seamless campaign from start to finish."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 23, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "One place to manage all inbound marketing. Support is brilliant. The ease of use just makes life easier. Never have a problem if I don't understand something or need to asking a question. The academy is an incredible resource. Great for any level of sales or marketing individual. ", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing worth noting here. They really are working towards a better product even when they already have a great one. Just check out their ideas forum, it is full of amazing enhancements they are working on. Even saw the found in there contributing to some of the ideas.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Get it now.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Insights. Where we should be spending our budget. Conversion Optimization. Abilitity to A/B test our landing pages."}}
{"author": ["Daniel N"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 14, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The user interface is very simple and easy to use. We were able to pick up the new system almost immediately and start using more advanced features shortly after.", "What do you dislike?": "Drag and drop could be utilized more. It's one thing we miss from our old system.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot put our newsletter campaign on the next level. We're able to easily and seamlessly put together new campaigns and get them out to the right people with little to no fuss."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The marketing aspect of it allows for great content creation from emails to landing pages.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that it doesn't allow you to fully edit some of the templates they provide and some of the things require a weird work around to get to properly work.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is incredibly easy to use but do not be afraid to reach out to Hubspot with questions", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing and webpage creation and it is incredibly easy to make quickly with templates I have previously set up"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Seamless experience by utilizing existing templates or creating one on the fly! Clear directions, simple tool with enough flexibility to make a good looking page. ", "What do you dislike?": "The spacing of modules can be a bit difficult sometimes to adjust. At that point I believe you have to dig into the coding to adjust some of the breaks. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have created a more comprehensive yet seamless user experience. We realized the need for segmentation for our audiences and had the tools to do this quickly."}}
{"author": ["d m"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Lead Management"], "date": ["Oct 29, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The Hubspot customer service team is like no other!  Truly the best customer experience", "What do you dislike?": "There are some obscure features that I wish Hubspot had but you can always post in their forum and recommend that they implement the feature, or ask customer support if there is a work around.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "You wont be disappointed!  Very easy to use, incredible customer support team!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using Hubspot to manage our entire database, we use it to report on company numbers, we use it for all marketing automation, and we use it to gain valuable insights to drive sales, and improve our marketing efforts."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Our organization loves Hubspot for its CRM, Marketing, and Analytics features. It is easy to learn and not too difficult to scale as your organization grows. We love that Hubspot support and our customer success rep is easy to get a hold of as well.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot is continually growing and the constant updates can be frustrating.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has really increased our ability to find and engage with our customers - and our ability to provide them with a stellar customer experience."}}
{"author": ["Gary C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Creative Content Writer"], "date": ["Feb 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The Gmail integration to log all my contacts, track opens and clicks, and schedule emails to send at a later date! ", "What do you dislike?": "The dashboard is a bit confusing and pricey for the paid accounts. Our agency uses it so I can still log emails.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Knowing when my emails are opened by leads outside my G Suite (gmail) organization. "}}
{"author": ["User in Higher Education"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I don't necessarily use HubSpot for the whole business aspect, but I really like the feature that allows you to see when emails are opened. It helps me ensure that the necessary people are receiving my message in a timely manner. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that sometimes, especially if the email has multiple recipients, it does not specify who opened the email. Additionally, sometimes when I open the email sometimes that registers as the other person opening it which I feel like is a feature that could be fixed. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I mostly just use it for the emailing tracking feature, but I would recommend not using it for mass emails if you're using the basic/free version, because it does not tell you exactly who opened the email, just \"someone.\" It only gives you 200 free notifications per month, and in my opinion these are wasted numbers and for each person/open for that mass email it would count as one. So they can add up really quickly and you won't get the best benefit out of it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I never used to know if people were reading my emails or if they were responding to me in a timely manner. This has really helped solve that problem!"}}
{"author": ["Caleb J"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Data Analyst", "Aviation & Aerospace"], "date": ["Feb 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Many basic essentials are free! It works well as a CRM in its own right, and also has email, marketing, sales, customer service, and project management tools as well.", "What do you dislike?": "I honestly don't have any complaints, I just wish we had switch over sooner as the pain point now is connecting it to our prior CRM, Microsoft Dynamics (which will still be used by some of the company).", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Compare to other CRM/Sales/Marketing/Email tools such as Dynamics 365, Constant Contact, Pipedrive, etc.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "A Marketing & Sales-focused CRM and email tool also allowing for project management as well."}}
{"author": ["Agency in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 22, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how user-friendly the tools are and how everything is included. I am able to do emails, social media, landing pages, workflows and even the CRM all in one place. Not only that, but I can connect them all together into campaigns.", "What do you dislike?": "The problem with being easy to use is that it also has technically fewer capabilities than say, Marketo. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use their Support for all of your questions. They respond quickly and reliably.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Working at an agency I have to solve all sorts of business problems for a variety of industries. One benefit that I;ve realized is that HubSpot allows smart lists that enable me to target specific markets  that are identified by numerous variables at the same time. And, as opposed to Marketo, it's simple to do these lists."}}
{"author": ["Christina K"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Lead Strategist, Nurture (Contract)", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jun 07, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The intuitive interface and the training / support. I really like that you can easily change modules without any design experience if you mess around with templates you can really make it personalized to you. I ", "What do you dislike?": "I would have to say that only enterprise allows A/B testing. The add-on analytics and COS additional price is not ideal. I love the COS platform and I wish it was included in the platform / software price. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Really think about if you want to build your business... Well I know you do so HS is the BEST way to do that. They support you the whole time! ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "My company is a new partner and we really enjoy the great help from our CC and CAM at HubSpot... so we don't have problems currently. I am really excited to get things going for BoldVoice. I previously came from another HS agency. "}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot remains the only software that combines CMS + marketing automation - this creates great efficiencies for marketing teams in having an all-in-one product to manage those areas plus email, nurturing, social media and more. HubSpot is constantly innovating and adding new features, and the Inbound community is a great marketing peer group to be part of.", "What do you dislike?": "No issues day to day. The only reasons I've heard moving away from HubSpot is if your business reaches an undesired level of complexity for managing business rules around your marketing - not a desired place to be but some businesses may be there.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Growth system to manage all aspects of marketing and website. A consolidated approach for website & marketing automation management. "}}
{"author": ["Justin L"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Search Engine Optimization Specialist", "Management Consulting"], "date": ["Aug 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is amazing! Have been using it for years and love their marketing tools and forms!", "What do you dislike?": "The paid version may be expensive for some...", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Keep up the great work!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are tracking leads through their marketing software to see when people are ready to make a purchase."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I would say that the best thing about hubspot it's its usability, which makes things easier. It kinda of an all in one solution, with good results on lead generation. Customer support is good. Their knowledge base and free ebooks are actually interesting (which is not that usual for marketing companies- there are a lot of click baits in content marketing).", "What do you dislike?": "too much emailing. some team members find hard to keep their lead management up to date. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "lead tracking: keep track of new prospects \r"}}
{"author": ["Agency"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I thoroughly have enjoyed using HubSpot because of its robust marketing automation tools and strong CRM capabilities. One of the most useful features that makes hubspot stand out is its pre built templates for marketing automation flows. It\u2019s a great tool that lets any level of marketer immediately create powerful drip campaigns. ", "What do you dislike?": "They always seem to be increasing their price. They know that they are the gold standard so they don\u2019t mind increasing rates on startups. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Best when used integrated into your marketing tech stack ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Having the sales and marketing teams be better aligned using a single platform, being able to train new marketing team members much faster thanks to the pre built templates, and a hidden bonus benefit is hubspot academy. "}}
{"author": ["Emma B"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator"], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Landing pages and processes are so much easier with HubSpot", "What do you dislike?": "I wish you could schedule videos on instagram", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Event management and social media management is a huge benefit to my team. Also, the calendar for posting visibility and the tasks section is so convenient for our planning."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Agency in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use, the interface is easy to navigate. The redesigned design manager for email is great and the live preview makes it easy to edit templates. The workflows are easy to implement. ", "What do you dislike?": "The constant changes - layout or naming of sections. While easy to navigate, the changing of names can make it difficult to find what you're looking for. There are a lot of quirks that make things like deleting lists difficult. It would be nice if there were an easier way to update/merge lists. It would be nice to be able to see all the ways that things are linked together (lists, lead scoring, etc.) in one spot. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has made it easier to do my job quickly and efficiently. "}}
{"author": ["Manish N"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Software Engineer", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Aug 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is a great software to build Templates/Landing pages/Forms etc..", "What do you dislike?": "There should be an option to see forms revision history ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot makes easy everything to me. I'm using HubSpot as a CMS as well. Along with marketing tools, this is very useful to AB Testing and variations. "}}
{"author": ["Kerry P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Web Project Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I like best about Hubspot is their continual improvement. ", "What do you dislike?": "As a web developer, I dislike some of the aspects of page development. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot helps me build landing pages quick and easy. I've realized some of their website modules are superior to WordPress. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that it can automate sequences for my emails, and helps me save time with all my email writing! I also really like the reports that it generates so I can see my team's progress with our pipeline. The deals page so that we can see where all our leads and deals fall under certain categories (such as discovery call, qualified, etc) is very useful.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it's been clunky. Thankfully, it's been recently streamlined, especially on a deal page where you can categorize notes, tasks, etc.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Saving time! "}}
{"author": ["User in Religious Institutions"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "They really do a good job of guiding you along the entire marketing to sales process. You can host an entire website on their platform, qualify leads, create workflows, and make a complete package. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some of their offerings are lacking, but it's difficult to customize for what you need. Some of their lead qualifying is very questionable, and basically all their forms look atrocious (they're just simple javascript on the page) .", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "You have to \"drink the Kool-Aid\" a little on HubSpot. They have a way of doing things then make sure you know how great it is. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Brian K. J"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["VP Research"], "date": ["Apr 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "So far, I really like how this app interacts with my Gmail account. It seems to be relatively seamless and intuitive. I have read some of the issues regarding the interference with email, but have not experienced that myself.", "What do you dislike?": "Still evaluating, which means I haven't come across and deal-breakers, and hoping to continue in this direction.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Looking good, so far. Getting hopeful that I have found what I'm looking for.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Right now, we are simply looking for a way to share lead and customer information among our very small sales team."}}
{"author": ["Katlyn M"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Social Media & PR Manager"], "date": ["May 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of publishing posts and the social listening aspect where you can create streams. ", "What do you dislike?": "Lots of updates - little conversation that it's happening. You all have been getting better though!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Social Media metrics and reporting to the C-Suite so they know the importance of social media today for B2B business. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 27, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The CRM product is FREE! For a small business, I felt like we got the better end of the deal by having a solid, reputable product that we could trial with little investment other than our time. There are a lot of features to take advantage of, including email plug-ins and dashboards that really make this a robust CRM system.", "What do you dislike?": "As with any system, what you put in is what you get out. We did not have an account manager but I would have liked to have some guidance or templates to help us identify our use cases that would then be mapped to the right fields and functionality. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would make sure that whomever implements the system knows what the business users are looking for before going through the process of setting up HubSpot. I would also encourage team training or involvement in a demo to ensure that everyone is on board and will adopt the system before rolling it out. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As a small business, we were hoping to use HubSpot as a CRM system to manage communications for the sales cycle as well as for our account managers to keep track of communications with existing clients. Essentially we needed a contact management system. As of now, we are not using HubSpot to its fullest capability largely due to the change management required for user adoption. "}}
{"author": ["User in Real Estate"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 17, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that I can assign tasks to teammates and leave notes regarding what we recently spoke about on the phone. This tool is a lifesaver for our company in keeping tabs on all of the real estate agents that choose to office through us.", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing at the moment. The only thing is that it's not very intuitive at first glance. Many applications and websites are easy to navigate but Hubspot seems to need some real teaching involved with my teammates. Some people have a hard time using it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Retention for the agents that choose to office with us. We now know what conversations they've had in the past with other teammates and can follow up accordingly. There are no guesses and we always know where the agent is in our \"onboarding process\""}}
{"author": ["harry j"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["manager"], "date": ["Mar 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The software allows organizations to track anything and everything.  it can be customised to suit all business types.  It presents you with powerful tools to run reports, create dashboards, and search for info. The Dashboard is customizable and can fit to what their client needs and requires for the specific process. It is easy to navigate as well.", "What do you dislike?": "The software have a steep learning curve, other than that all is good. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It provides a single, organized location for everything from personal notes about potential clients, to the ability to track potential profit."}}
{"author": ["Carlo D"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketeer", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Their marketing automation is truly easy to learn, hard to master which makes it so you can have nearly endless possibilities in regards to new options to explore.", "What do you dislike?": "Pricing is very high. Don't be mistaken, this is a luxury product. But if you can afford it, it's amazing.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We not only manage our entire marketing but also most of our sales department with this one single tool. That's 15 people working day in day out. Cuts downtime and adds to scaleability."}}
{"author": ["Adrian C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["CEO"], "date": ["Jan 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Obviously - it's free. But it doesn't mean that it is cheap in the product way. \r", "What do you dislike?": "It helps us to take control over our clients and sales process. We integrated it with many other software like Woodpecker or Typeform to collect all specifics about our clients and their needs.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Kerri E"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing and Communications Specialist", "Textiles"], "date": ["Jan 23, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Automation - being able to schedule ahead is what really sold this for us. We also enjoy the social listening tools - this is something we were desperately needing and it has proven very successful ", "What do you dislike?": "The amount of training that is needed to use - it took most everyone on my team a good bit of time to understand the process and how the platform works. Once we did it was much easier to use. If there was a way to streamline that process that would be great", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "More user friendly dashboards - once you understand them, they are great but it takes a while to get to that point\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "email marketing\r"}}
{"author": ["Sarah B"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Specialist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["May 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Everything is connected - you can view your contacts and their activity and track it across multiple campaigns. ", "What do you dislike?": "I don't have any complaints. It's an excellent tool.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The ability to create landing pages and collect information via a form helps us build our database and enhances our email marketing efforts, etc."}}
{"author": ["Amanda A"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Content Manager", "Public Relations and Communications"], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that it automates my marketing so I know we are reaching our leads consistently, and the support team is super helpful with both technical uses and overall marketing strategy.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot can be expensive for a smaller business. However, if you use it to the best of its capabilities, it's worth the spend.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to reach more leads in more ways through Hubspot. We've realized the benefits of marketing automation when it comes to nurturing leads and increasing sales."}}
{"author": ["Jenna Jean B"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Product Marketing Specialist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that I can schedule ahead of time and see all the metrics I measure in one easy to view dashboard.", "What do you dislike?": "I would like to be able to attribute social media posts to moving people down the marketing funnel and increasing their HubSpot score.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I use HubSpot to boost SEO in blog posts and post to our social channels. Myself and the other people that use HubSpot at my company have found value in the ease of use and reporting functionality."}}
{"author": ["Jen B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Shows all activities of your database of contacts so you know what is working, and what is not.\r", "What do you dislike?": "Ties your CRM and marketing automation together seamlessly.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Allows you to test content, whether its an email or a landing page.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'd like to see a tighter integration between a HubSpot contact and a HubSpot company, it's difficult to track some items since they are considered separate.\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that Hubspot helps me throughout the entire campaign process including defining our consumers, discovering insights and forming a strategy that can be scheduled. ", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot can be updated to allow us to organize our leads a little better by giving us more filtered options. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Go through all the features before you start. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We develop campaigns and organize our sales and lead information. We've been able to learn more about our consumers and discover trends from our social media campaigns. "}}
{"author": ["Brandon  C"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Salesman "], "date": ["Nov 01, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It was fine for tracking accounts but it was just ok overall. ", "What do you dislike?": "Pitiful support on my Samsung phone. I had to use the browser. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I was definitely abel to get to information about clients, but I had to dig not very user friendly. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot allows you to do almost everything in one place. The CRM portion is easy to use and intuitive, the sales tools are world class and the marketing tools allows our small team todo big things.", "What do you dislike?": "The weakest part of HubSpot for me is their source tracking if the default is \"Offline Sources\" and in my opinion, they could be much more precise but don't seem to care to outside of the obvious source tags like Organic, PPC, Referal etc. Probably not a huge issue for most people but I find it to be annoying.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We literally run 85% of our business on HubSpot. We solve account management, sales, and marketing all within one platform, which if you think about it, is really amazing. The biggest compliment I can pay is to say that my team lives in HS platform and I have taught them to use HS support, which is the best, by the way, to teach themselves new skills."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that HubSpot has all of my inbound marketing solutions in a centralized space.  I can see how all of my marketing efforts from social to email marketing to PPC affect sales and traffic to our website.", "What do you dislike?": "HubSpot can get very costly, very quickly since the yearly bill is based on contacts.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Watch the videos in the beginning and get started right away so you can fully utilize the onboarding.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Since we are a small team, the biggest benefit is having everything in one place so everything is organized and projects don't fall through the cracks."}}
{"author": ["User in Mining & Metals"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "our marketing team uses hubspot, and I have been in the process to help work with sales and get them using it as well and I can say that Hubspot has changed the way we work here. Before, we used so many different softwares to do everything we needed to do and now, it is all centralized in one place.", "What do you dislike?": "The only thing about Hubspot we did not like was the on boarding process. It was expensive, and we truly did not need it. We were able to work with the regular customer service and get all set up on our own. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I 100% recommend Hubspot. Not only is the service amazing and offers so many capabilities you probably never considered before, it also can help make the things you are already doing as a company so much easier. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have a location that holds ALL of our information. Sales leads, lists, contacts, forms from the website. It is now all in one place. "}}
{"author": ["User in Education Management"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that they have a wide array of functions all in one place. Their integrations for having forms, landing pages, and emails that all tie together are great.", "What do you dislike?": "Email & landing page design is difficult. If you make a landing page look good on mobile, it looks bad on desktop or vice versa. It is hard to find templates that do what you want them to and they are not very editable. Social media integration could stand to be more robust- like Hootsuite or Zoho social standards for scheduling, listening, and replies.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "They have a lot of potential and seem to be improving. If you want a tool that can do it all, they are great! If you want to do things in the easiest way possible, however, it's better to get multiple products that specialize in the tasks you need them for.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Centralizing many of our functions. Great address book for tracking leads and where they are in the buyers journey."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is really easy to use and offers good customer support. They always seem to be making updates to make it easier and better to use based on customer feedback. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some things are a bit difficult to find and under odd categories. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take advantage of the forums and QA to find out new things going on.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "CRM for clients is easier. We can create tracking URLs and keep them all in one place. It's also nice having forms all in one place. "}}
{"author": ["Christina R"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Account Manager"], "date": ["Mar 28, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The user interface is very user friendly, the support team is always easy to get in touch with. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish the chat box would answer my questions, not just direct me to the phone number.  The templates will not load a lot of the time when using my Gmail. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It will freeze occasionally or not search a name / email in the search bar. Just says \"loading...\"\r"}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "For smaller teams, I think this is a great tool. Easy to set up, their onboarding process is great and depending on your license, you will most likely have a customer success manager who guides you through the fundamentals of the platform and works on solving your unique issue. \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Amazing Customer Support - never had an issue that wasn't resolved within an hour or less. "}}
{"author": ["Jeff S"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Sr. Solution Architect", "Media Production"], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "web-based, with great connectors to Office 365.  A bit cumbersome on a Mac,  integration isn't as tight as a PC", "What do you dislike?": "interface can be difficult to navigate.  Shortcuts would be great", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "great for planning out of sale, client contact as well as social and  marketing campaigns.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "SEO,  realization of sales campaigns and their effectiveness."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Internet"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There are so many amazing tools in this suite that I haven\u2019t even uncovered all of them. MY favorite features are the academy which provides additional resources about everything related to sales and marketing. I also love the workflow tools and the forms. ", "What do you dislike?": "We do very personalized email campaigns, and I wish there was a way to schedule auto follow ups from marketing emails based on if people have not responded to your email. Alternatively if there was a way to message multiple contacts at a time through the sales platform with integrated auto follow ups that would be great. I also wish there was some kind of mobile app that was available where we could see any messages that come in from the messages feature. Or at least have desktop notifications. It is a bit annoying to have to leave open the messages tab all day in case someone sends a message. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I don\u2019t know if it is worth their full price, but we get a discount and it is definitely worth it at the price we are getting through their startups program.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "CRM, deal organization, email tracking. The best benefits have been the automated workflows and the additional video resources."}}
{"author": ["Kyle W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Managing Partner"], "date": ["Oct 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is cloud based and easy to use for our entire team", "What do you dislike?": "Doesn't work great for a C to C and short sales cycle customers", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It has allowed us to communicate effectively with our customers and track sales as well as lead capture."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 30, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Great for marketers who want to host a website in an easily edited platform.\r", "What do you dislike?": "Also great for web-based content offering and automation.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Web, Email, Social, SEO, Page performance, AB Testing metrics (essentially all metrics a marketer would look at can be tracked on HubSpot)\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Workflow and Campaign Automation tools\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It does a good job of tracking bookings and upcoming deals to keep them on track.", "What do you dislike?": "There is no way to track a credit system in which a customer has a set number of credits and they use them throughout their contract so it makes customer management difficult. It really is only good for tracking the sales process rather than the renewal process. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Keeping track of next steps like MANA and logging calls has been great. Tracking the probability has been really helpful. "}}
{"author": ["Amrita H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 24, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It\u2019s super easy compared to other tools to learn and use. There are plenty of lessons to give you training on using the features. The support team is quick and solves queries within a day. ", "What do you dislike?": "It is not best recommended for big companies. I work at a startup and it works great for us. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I use Hubspot for social media scheduling, blogging, and for running marketing campaigns with in-built CTA\u2019s that you can customize. "}}
{"author": ["Shaine B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing & Advertising Coordinator"], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot's CRM integrates well with multiple automation platforms. It has strong workflow management options, and has a good content strategy visualisation tool for website content. ", "What do you dislike?": "The email marketing tools could use updating, they lack some basic features that other providers such as mailchimp, sendy, etc have. Also there's some operational issues like lack of multiple timezone support for accounts. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Primarily sales process management and content management. HubSpot's tools and workflow automation definitely provide time saving benefits"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the fact that all of our contacts and businesses that we need to reach out to are all in one place. It's very easy to reach out to people because of the emails and other contact information already being loaded into the platform. ", "What do you dislike?": "The only thing I would say I dislike is the fact that there are so many different things to learn when using hubspot. It takes a lot of time and questions to really know what and how to do a lot of different things. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Being able to quickly and easily send out emails to potential clients without having to look them all up or have the sales associate enter them their selves. "}}
{"author": ["Don B"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Account Executive", "Computer Software"], "date": ["May 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot gives you great insight into who is opening your emails.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Don Baker, Utah \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Document / Information Management Expert\r"}}
{"author": ["Gabby d"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Business Owner", "Human Resources"], "date": ["Jan 29, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that the free version still has plenty of resources and tools to help me with my new business. I also LOVE the Gmail integration!!", "What do you dislike?": "I honestly can't think of what I dislike besides the limits of the free account.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I've realized the benefit of Hubspot's Gmail integration! I love that I can add/track clients straight from there and knowing when someone has opened an email I sent is something I didn't realize I needed until now!"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I like best is the way everything is structured in the tool. Starting from landing page creation, email template building, form integration and further to analytics and competition tracking all is available inside the tool. ", "What do you dislike?": "Though there is nothing as such to dislike about Hubspot itself, there are things such as Hubspot marketplace which is still at very basic, though it is growing but at present you will not find amazing buy and use resources. Example: For users who are not very technical and developing a good custom email template is a pain-point, buying out an email template is not an option, because everything in marketplace is non-impressive. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are currently using Hubspot to solve everyday marketing automation problems and for further integration with Salesforce. We run email campaigns and track them using Hubspot. Apart from already using google analytics, we also use Hubspot tracking to understand our visitors and leads in a better way."}}
{"author": ["Laura L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Freelance Marketing", "Facilities Services"], "date": ["Dec 08, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "They are continually making changes to meet their customers' needs", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the platforms can be very simple and rigid which limits creativity and ends with a very boxy feel to pages. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take advantage of all the programs/ options that they have available so that you have one point of contact for all of your marketing efforts. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Controlling all of our marketing efforts on one consolidated platform which generates superb data and analytics for us to evaluate the effectiveness of our efforts. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Staffing and Recruiting"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 07, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the convenience of having all the data in one location.  It makes it easy for me to track potential and current clients.  I also like the support they offer.  Whenever I am unsure about a feature or how to get something done I am able to quickly and easily get a response from support. ", "What do you dislike?": "More times than not I have to double check that information I have added for a new contact and/or company is correct.  For example, I will add the website link for LinkedIn or Twitter for a new contact and after I have saved it I find that part of the description from the page has been added.  It's a simple fix, but I'd like the data I input be saved the first time. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to add new potential clients into HubSpot and then send a series of emails to them.  It is helpful for our team to be able to put notes in as different members of the team send emails.  Then we are able to strategize our next steps by running reports.  The benefit for us is that we can all be current on the same client  because everything is done in one spot. "}}
{"author": ["Dayne T"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Content Strategy and Brand Promotion", "Non-Profit Organization Management"], "date": ["Dec 07, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Our marketing team makes use of HubSpot on a daily basis. The functionality and ease of use are in a class of their own. It feels as though there is nothing that cannot be done in HubSpot and they're consistently updating their software to keep up with the times. ", "What do you dislike?": "From time-to-time it can take a little while for metrics and data to be \"live\" or reflective of real-time.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automating some of our marketing processes, communications, and workflows have been revoluntionary with HubSpot. "}}
{"author": ["V. Wynne P"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Content Manager", "Management Consulting"], "date": ["Mar 30, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's so easy to manage content in Hubspot. I can easily add in a blog post, do SEO for it, include images, and schedule it for publication and social media in no time. So easy to quickly get content out. ", "What do you dislike?": "The spell check isn't great, there are frequent updates that change the entire site (roughly twice a year) so you have to relearn the system, and analytics take a little longer to show up than other analytics systems", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Read the fine lines, there are only certain times you can cancel, should you wish. This will replace several tools you already use, like a CRM, email marketing, social media tool, blog publishing, and more. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I really like the social media publishing tool. It's easier to connect a blog post through there and see when posts are being shared; to me, it's easier than Buffer. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is very user-friendly and it is easy to learn the tools it offers marketers. It's painless to design emails, workflows, and landing pages. ", "What do you dislike?": "I'm not a huge fan of how Contacts are set up. Hubspot is extremely focused on contacts rather than companies, and while I think that's beneficial in some areas, it can make my job slightly difficult based on the industry I'm in. TL;DR it's tough to get all the contact properties sorted straight in my head.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot can be a great tool for your business. My only suggestion is make sure that if you sync Hubspot with Salesforce or another software, that the data in the other software is as accurate as possible.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Customer engagement and lead generation are improved from our last software. "}}
{"author": ["Kenneth H"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Apr 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot knows how to do marketing and their feature set covers it perfectly. I trust everything I send out using HubSpot, which I couldn't say for previous system.", "What do you dislike?": "Tiered pricing locks away some features. It is frustrating to have true reporting locked behind an additional paywall.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do the free classes! HubSpot certifications are industry standards in Marketing.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is our marketing automation platform. It solves our needs for sending emails, tracking email and social media KPIs, and monitoring traffic to our website. The social media monitoring has been a major plus, as it allows our small team to keep up to date on the social media conversations happening about our brand."}}
{"author": ["Jess K"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing"], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "User friendly, easy to track therefore leaves me more time to spend more time on creative", "What do you dislike?": "Building some reports can be difficult, I need to get a hubspot property of when a contact completes a form or pop up.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do the training!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Landing page optimisation = more higher quality leads"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Sports"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that Hubspot allows me to have all my marketing assets in one place and giving easy access to my entire team. ", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes Hubspot will behave slowly. I also don\u2019t like that booking a meeting cannot be used as a trigger in workflows. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot does this well, and although other places might do it \u201cgreat\u201d the benefitting of having everything in one place in invaluable. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Better sales processes. Easier to book meetings. A great way to organize our CRM. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 18, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is amazing! I use Hubspot every day as my primary CRM system and I love how easy to use it is as well as how fresh and clean the overall look it has. I've also frequently used Hubspot Academy which has an incredible selection of resources and tools for marketing professionals.", "What do you dislike?": "There are times when I find it hard to find exactly what I'm looking for quickly but it's all there - it's just a matter of knowing where to look.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I love that Hubspot keeps track of email correspondences across our company!"}}
{"author": ["Ashley I"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Consultant", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I find HubSpot to be very intuitive and easy to use.  Not to mention, it does almost everything that I need it to do as a marketing pro.", "What do you dislike?": " HubSpot is incredibly expensive And often times they require yearly contracts.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": " I always tell my clients, \u201c if you can afford HubSpot, you should get it. \u201c", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": " HubSpot gives me the ability to automate my entire day. From emails to landing pages to blogs to social, everything becomes a lot easier."}}
{"author": ["User in Management Consulting"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has a great catalog of classes and guides that has helped me learn as I go using their tools. They recommend taking the certification courses in the beginning and after almost a year with them I see why. It is worth carving out time to learn about their platform specifics and general best practices.", "What do you dislike?": "The advanced menus in their website editing tool is tricky. I can eventually find what I need to edit, but it isn't as intuitive as I would like being a novice website editor. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The cost is affordable and is easy enough for a non-technical person to learn to use the platform.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our company website was on a Drupal platform but we had no developers on staff to manage the site. We migrated to HubSpot and now have both an easy website editing capability along with the marketing platform to see results on our content."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ability to automate most workflows and manage contacts autonomously. ", "What do you dislike?": "A recent change made it so that uploading contacts no longer automatically makes a list of those users, this was a primary way that we segmented given our own restraints. It now takes an extra step to upload and process the contacts and create a list from the import list. HubSpot likes to make these types of small changes without warning and without a legacy option to continue as things were.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It is a our primary email service and helps us track our users along their journey."}}
{"author": ["Joseph A"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Client Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["Nov 13, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how HubSpot is looking forward in how we can change marketing and sales.  The addition of AI and using it to automate tasks that need the technology is great.  ", "What do you dislike?": "There is a lot to HubSpot.  One of the harder things to deal with is to know where to start and what to do.  While they have the academy and other tools to learn, those just getting into the field may feel overwhelmed with just how much HubSpot puts out and offers to fix problems that these young people don't know exist.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has assisted us with keep our goals in check, constantly evaluating ourselves and proving our worth to clients and can help our clients manage their own leads.  "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is easy to use, very user friendly, guided steps, don't have to learn a lot to start using the product. They make everything simple and use step by step methods to help get you up and running. ", "What do you dislike?": "There really  isnt one thing that i dislike about this product. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure to take adavantage of all their features. Make sure to have them do a demo of the product so that you are able to see everythint. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helps us stay organized and helps us work in a more effecient and speedy manner. It makes everything so much better. "}}
{"author": ["Dana G"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Associate"], "date": ["Oct 18, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is an incredibly easy to use CRM system. You can create emails and hold contacts all in one spot.", "What do you dislike?": "While it is easy to use it also doesn't allow for much \"out of the box\" designing for things such as emails. You have to personalize their template.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you need an easy to use CRM system, hubspot is the right one for you", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Connecting with clients and keeping them all in the same place for easy lookup and digestibility. "}}
{"author": ["Brandon K"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There are a lot of good functions with Hubspot that can be integrated into other platforms.", "What do you dislike?": "I spent a few hours integrating the Chat Bot and then it suddenly disappeared. Also, you have to pay for a lot of features if you want to upgrade.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot as a CRM tool in order to track leads. "}}
{"author": ["Katie D"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 31, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The support they provide is amazing. They ALWAYS pick up the call and resolve the problem. The dashboard has everything you need to view how your website is doing overall so I can make adjustments when needed.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't have much that I dislike. I wanted a video to be playing across the page and they couldn't make it look right so that's upsetting.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "ROI on website leads. Capturing leads that come to the site is huge."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that I'm able to enroll users into a flow to control the type of emails they get on a scheduled basis!", "What do you dislike?": "I don't have the greatest knowledge of the product, but something I found frustrating was the inability to customly add a list of emails to target in an already created flow, it appears as though I have to rely on an integration to get an email into a flow. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using Hubspot to email users in a variety of ways. I personally use it to create a campaign of set emails new users to our platform will receive as we onboard them. It was been great in helping us educate our new user base. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has a very nice user interface and is capable of performing most marketing automation tasks. If you're not a huge fan or their CRM (or if your organization uses another CRM) they have integrations with companies like Salesforce. It is a very user friendly platform with a massive library of resources.", "What do you dislike?": "My only complaint is that you don't get a ton of flexibility from the platform. You'll be able to do MOST things that you need to do. That said, if you don't do it exactly as outlined, you might run into issues (like going out of order when building Ikea furniture. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use Hubspot as our marketing automation platform. We're able to execute most campaigns with ease. "}}
{"author": ["Randi W"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "This platform includes everything all in one place for the most part.", "What do you dislike?": "It can be a little complex for users that don't know how to use it to it's full potential.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you're able to use all of it's features. Otherwise, explore cheaper options on the market.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Tracking customers has been HUGE for my company. Seeing what they look like is very beneficial in our sales process."}}
{"author": ["Gaurav G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Maketing", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The tool is simple and easy to use. It make sense for marketing team to use one platform instead of multi-platform.", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't anything which I dislike as the product has helped us.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our marketing automation and sales pipeline problem has been solved."}}
{"author": ["J. Brent T"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["real estate agent"], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "the Ease of use and breadth of products from hubspot", "What do you dislike?": "nothing at all - hubspot is great and user friendly", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "CRM is what has been most helpful and the social media marketing platform....but I feel I have only scratched the surface on the many tools hubspot offers. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 18, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The customer service is without a doubt the best part of this product. Rather than spending hours trying to resolve an issue, you can just pick up the phone and get a friendly person on the phone who will walk you through a solution. This has saved me tons of time. If they can't provide a solution they try to provide a work around. ", "What do you dislike?": "The email templates are pretty basic and not friendly for all mail servers. We've had issues with emails getting sent to spam and high bounce rates and we didn't really get a solution other than it was a problem on the receiving end. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Internet"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I had not been in a email marketing position before using Hubspot, and I LOVE that they had so many education resources for me  to use and learn the software. Hubspot is the ultimate tool for marketing automation, and it integrates with so many other tools like Salesforce, SurveyGizmo, and Wistia. Plus, the Support team is always really helpful and they respond so fast with plenty of information to help you!", "What do you dislike?": "I wish more info would send between Hubspot and Salesforce. The data sync is limited.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing, nurture campaigns, workflow automation, contact segmentation and personalization. The benefits of Hubspot is that if you set it up right, it will do the heavy lifting for you. "}}
{"author": ["Saerang C"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing associate"], "date": ["Apr 18, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I like best about HubSpot are the workflow functions which make it easier to assign those leads to business representatives. ", "What do you dislike?": "We are currently experiencing a lot of problem stemming from salesforce and hubspot integration. I don't think HubSpot integrates will with Salesforce.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Assigning leads, sending out emails internally or externally "}}
{"author": ["Paula V"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Project Developer"], "date": ["Oct 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The integrations and how easy you can personalize everything.", "What do you dislike?": "Conversations, aesthetically speaking the conversations feature is really bad.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Features with conversations. A lot of things need to be changed in regards to what the client is asked for (survey) before a chat."}}
{"author": ["Matt E"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The platform is an awesome all-in-one solution for marketing automation. This tool really is a one stop shop for most people. ", "What do you dislike?": "The pricing is pretty high compared to other things, so the customer has to see the value. Unfortunately, HubSpot doesn\u2019t always get the customer to understand the value and the relationship sours due to a lack of care about customer retention. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The platform offers strong tools for email, social media monitoring and publishing, blogging and more. "}}
{"author": ["User in Management Consulting"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The entire software is easy to navigate, even without much training. Usually speaking, the entire team is able to understand what goals we are trying to achieve with our customer/prospect information, and they are able to ensure accrurate data entry as a result. ", "What do you dislike?": "The mobile features are poor.. It\u2019s essentially useless, and there are a number of CRMs that provide fantastic mobile features for iOS and Android devices. That would be extremely helpful for our business objectives. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Organizing contacts, creating marketing lists, prospecting new targets, and housing contact information. Our sales and marketing teams find the software easy to use, and they enjoy being in it on a daily basis. "}}
{"author": ["Paul S"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Marketing Strategist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Mar 27, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how all of the tools are connected to the CRM. This makes it so I can easily create personalized emails, landing pages, workflows and more.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that I can't always get a support employee on live chat. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We help clients with lead generation, lead nurturing, reporting and marketing strategy."}}
{"author": ["Leslie W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Program Coordinator"], "date": ["Mar 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot not only provides so many services to fit all of your marketing needs, but has step-by-step videos, practical exercises, and quizzes to help show you how to utilize their services. ", "What do you dislike?": "I'm still very new to HubSpot but the price to access all services.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Creating campaigns, landing pages, CTAs to help me market."}}
{"author": ["Clayton O"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Business + Production Director", "Furniture"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has reduced the amount of manual data entry for our sales reps and account execs.", "What do you dislike?": "the learning curve for those not as tech savvy is quite steep from the start", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "automating contact workflows to reduce manual entries. Generating new sales leads faster"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is very easy to use. The support is fantastic, you can always call or chat for help. ", "What do you dislike?": "It is expensive. You can negotiate the first few years of the contract to be relatively cost efficient, but costs quickly increase after the initial contract period. The social media scheduling is not great. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you need a tool that is easy to use, consider Hubspot. It is, however, expensive.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use it for all of our email campaigns and it syncs with Salesforce so we can track engagement. "}}
{"author": ["Juan Camilo R"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Socio Fundador + VP Comercial", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Apr 20, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "El equipo que te ayuda a ver las oportunidades a trav\u00e9s de el nuevo marketing.\r", "What do you dislike?": "El acompa\u00f1amiento de cerca te permite entender como puedes mejorar.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "En poco tiempo la agencia empez\u00f3 a reactivar sus ventas y hoy despu\u00e9s de solo 6 meses hemos crecido como nunca cre\u00edmos poder hacerlo, tienen muy claro el rol de cada una de las personas que ayudan en la implementaci\u00f3n de la plataforma.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "De pronto muchos partners en todo el mundo.\r"}}
{"author": ["User in Education Management"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 10, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Email marketing is a really useful tool and that is something we use on a primary basis. With Hubspot, we are able to send out mass emails, depending on price of subscription, and check open rates and click rates.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot has many tools to learn so it is difficult to learn everything at once. Also they are changing some designs which has made it a little more complicated.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We can see exactly how many emails we've sent out with Hubspot and track what each contact is doing. Checking which email they've opened is a good thing too because we weren't able to do that before, but now we can set up workflows and send out Marketing emails which actually are useful to them."}}
{"author": ["User in Non-Profit Organization Management"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a powerful tool! Love the versatility of being able to send emails, create landing pages, and manage contacts all in one tool.", "What do you dislike?": "As a millennial, digital tools come easy to me. Hubspot definitely has a learning curve. There are a lot of components that require significant training, such as building landing pages and workflows.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "My organization has used HubSpot to develop workflows for lead generation and customer retention. This is a great way to set it and (mostly) forget it!"}}
{"author": ["Nina K"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Operations Associate"], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is certainly very useful and helpful with organizing huge databases of contacts. Workflows make it ridiculously easy to automate tasks that would otherwise have taken me weeks to complete. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are some features that don't make sense and need revising. But Hubspot releases updates constantly, so I am sure these issues won't be problems for long. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I have to group and sort through about 30,000 contacts. Creating email campaigns and giving personalized experiences to that many people would be impossible otherwise."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has helped with our digital marketing automation tremendously. It conveniently integrates with our Salesforce platform, making sure that all our contacts are up to date. And we've been able to create a Marketing ROI dashboard with Salesforce using HubSpot workflows for engagement.", "What do you dislike?": " Sometimes the email templates can be a little clunky and not as customizable as I'd like.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I've used HubSpot as both a marketing and sales tool. Overall it improves the process by automation and is very easy to use."}}
{"author": ["Amanda S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Founder"], "date": ["Feb 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The free account is easy to use and keeps track of when your emails are opened, clicked, forwarded, etc. It's simple to add the tracking to individual emails (or uncheck them).", "What do you dislike?": "There are sometimes messages prompting you to turn on HubSpot in your email that get annoying. And the email open-tracking software isn't 100% accurate (but mostly accurate). Sometimes when I open the email, it indicates that \"someone opened [email x].\"", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I sell courses & products and it's important to me for follow-ups to know who has opened emails vs. who hasn't."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Carol R"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Demand Generation", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Nov 03, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The workflows and email system is excellent. The forms are smart (pun intended).  Campaign management is great. All the add-ons and integrations give us a flexibility we need. I have been using HubSpot for a couple year snow and still discover functionality I could be using but haven't yet. It's a super comprehensive offering.", "What do you dislike?": "I think social monitoring and publishing need some updates and improvements. Little things like not being able to upload a video and have it auto-play on Twitter or being able to do a unquoted retweet at a scheduled time is an issue for us.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have a load of leads coming in that need a lot of nurturing and engagement and this tool works wonders for this."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hence the title of this review, the user-friendliness! It is useful to have everything in one place, on one tool. There are so many different tools out there but then that gets confusing! I also found the training qualifications really useful and they taught me a lot!", "What do you dislike?": "It can be confusing at first (although the HubSpot software qualification helps you learn this). It would be better to have a CTA or an email etc to show users where they can get training resources on their first login.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Clear metrics. Great understanding of customers. All in one place. By using HubSpot we can easily understand our customers while comparing them to personas. "}}
{"author": ["Rachel P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 12, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easily create landing pages, forms, emails. We also host our website on Hubspot and it's easy to modify any content on the page. My assistant loves the bulk-upload for social media posts. ", "What do you dislike?": "Integration to GoToWebinar is a little cumbersome - I have to remember to go and click the checkbox to sync-up the sign-ups. For some reason, all the content from the sign-up doesn't seem to sync well. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Inbound marketing, tracking our leads' activity online, social media monitoring and publishing."}}
{"author": ["Carolyn W"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Marketing Manager", "Insurance"], "date": ["Feb 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We had another software prior and Hubspot is definitely better.", "What do you dislike?": "There are so many add-on products. Seems like every time we want to do something new we have to pay more.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "We did a full RFP and compared products thoroughly our second time around. All of the products have great features. And all of them have their downfalls. Pick one that works best how you work. Hubspot would be great for first timers.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing Automation platform."}}
{"author": ["Agency"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 31, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot CRM is a free product but we recommend it to our prospects because it allows them to keep track of all their contacts and activities so they are on top of things. No dropping the ball and the best part is we get a dashboard to tell us of the activities and results. ", "What do you dislike?": "When a contact leaves the company and starts or joins another one there is a little hassle to manage that as well as the registration process. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to schedule our appointments and have  a sequence created which lists exactly what steps were taken in the sales process. "}}
{"author": ["Jan Peter V"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The combination of available functionalities, the free CRM, the user friendliness.", "What do you dislike?": "The fact that is not really built for multiple brands within one company, at least not the versions below   Enterprise.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing, landing pages, social monitoring, automation, segmentation, revenue attribution."}}
{"author": ["Ashlee T"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Marketing Analyst", "Insurance"], "date": ["Apr 15, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love HubSpot! I love the ability to set up automated workflows so that I don't have to worry about setting up a million follow-up tasks. I can simply import contacts with a few clicks and all the correct emails go out to our leads and customers. I also love the email and landing page capabilities. There are so many templates available, so it's easy to try out new designs. The drag and drop modules make it so easy to customize the email or landing page to how you want and need it to look and function, all without having to know html or css. Being able to create CTA's and then use them on other web pages through the embed code is also a great feature. The HubSpot knowledge base has been a great tool as well. If you're not sure how to do something in the platform, that knowledge base will walk you through it step-by-step.  ", "What do you dislike?": "The search function in many areas (images, file manager, emails) doesn't work very well. It seems to not pull keywords even if they are in the title of what you are looking for. \r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I also wish they would implement more exclusive properties, rather than only inclusive. Sometimes we need to exclude people from receiving emails or other marketing materials and the exclusion properties are very limited. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 04, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Automation / Workflows\r", "What do you dislike?": "Close Integration with other Hubspot products\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Considered the industry standard for web marketing\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Excellent for digital marketing professionals\r"}}
{"author": ["Jason M"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Virtual Chief Growth Officer (CGO)", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Apr 14, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a powerful well built system. Many of its strengths are tied to it's powerful email automation workflow tool-set. We can automatically followup with leads, communicate with customers and stay in touch on a regular way.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "In addition, their support is awesome. They've got a ticket system or phone network to help answer any questions I have about using the program or responding to problems that come up.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Some of their automation workflows are limited to the advanced types of things we are doing, but most users won't face those issues. Their content management system is good, but compared to some of the better ones, it is lacking."}}
{"author": ["Drew L"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Communications Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Mar 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Everything is so easy to use and find within the software. Whether it's blog posts or social media posts or even landing pages & website pages...they're all conveniently located.", "What do you dislike?": "When you are creating a blog post, sometimes the editing isn't smooth or intelligent and the text develops weird spacing, especially when dealing with images around the text.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Creating content, campaigns, and other forms of lead generation tactics. We've brought in more business!"}}
{"author": ["Alyssa Z"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager"], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that HubSpot puts everything you need in one place from contact management to social posting and email marketing", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that you cant embed GIFs or videos in emails yet and that they are not supported in Outlook", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I definitely recommend for a big enough business", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "CRM, contact management, social marketing, email marketing, lead generation"}}
{"author": ["Pranjali G"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Sr Marketing Communications"], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the way Hubspot tracks the visits from original sources.", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the features are complicated and need a lot of time, practice and attention.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The way things were set in Hubspot were incorrect. So we are struggling to streamline data."}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 04, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "When we first started our marketing team, we did everything on HubSpot - we hosted our website and blog, used it for email marketing, managed our client lifecycle etc. It was great for our size and competency level at the time. It's nice to be able to manage everything our marketing team did in one place. We've also benefited from the community that HubSpot has created. There are endless resources for us to use to learn talk to other users. ", "What do you dislike?": "Unfortunately, the functionality just doesn't work for us anymore. It takes far too long to make any sort of customizations that we want to (eg. making changes to a website page, or creating a newsletter template). It was great when everything we needed to produce was simple, but if we want anything customizable, it turns into a nightmare. This also has to do with the fact that somewhere along we stopped keeping track of how much code we were changing in the backend, and a lot of the issues stem from that. Keeping track of prospects and clients is also difficult to do with the features currently offered. I think for us, this is simply a case of outgrowing a platform. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot is definitely a great tool if you want to educate your marketing team. My favourite feature is when you're generating content, HubSpot makes it really easy to ensure the content is optimized. There's a great step-by-step process that you follow and it's super helpful.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot helped us make our inbound marketing strategy more efficient when we were first starting out. It gave us a way to create and execute campaigns, and at the time it saved us a lot of time. It also gave us insights into our leads that we didn't have prior to HubSpot, so that we are thankful for. "}}
{"author": ["Igor B"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Igor"], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Automations, support forms, relations between objects.", "What do you dislike?": "Some limitations in support forms like, no more than 1 dependency. Limitations in buget and proposals.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "No recomendations at this time.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Integration with all areas in our company, chaning fresh desk for Hub support forms."}}
{"author": ["Eric A"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Company Owner", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that they offer a free version and it's very user friendly", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike the ability to make phone calls directly from the CRM without high fees attached.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Give it a try and go from there! You will see for yourself how great it is!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our company has become very organized thanks to HubSpot."}}
{"author": ["Madison T"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Sales/Business Development Representative", "Internet"], "date": ["Jan 06, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The way HubSpot tracks user interaction within our product and website makes it much easier to target and prospect engaged leads. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that the permissions are so expensive. It would be more helpful for our company if all of the sales people could see the specific HubSpot Intelligence, not just the brief overview. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would recommend taking advantage of the way that HubSpot interfaces with Salesforce.com to provide leads with HubSpot scores and intelligence that makes it easier to prospect viable leads. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're saving time and energy by making sure that our prospecting time is well spent and that the leads we're going after are engaged and more likely to buy. "}}
{"author": ["Micheal O"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Project manager"], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I love most is how easy it is to sync up with Gmail, Wordpress, Google Analytics, Woocommerce, Facebook and the list goes on and on. . Hubspot offers suggestions for how to compose and email, a landing page, an offer pop up. Another great feature is the analytics tool. You can see the performance of every marketing element in one detailed dashboard. Hubspot is very functional and complete tool.", "What do you dislike?": "Design Manager is confusing for someone without coding knowledge.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our company works in much more organized manner now."}}
{"author": ["Daniel C"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Brand Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Lots of functionality and tools. Easy to learn and solutions for simple to customizable integration. Has allowed us to automate so many time consuming business needs and integrate with other key services.", "What do you dislike?": "Love features. Wish outside of original contact source could track source that drives most recent conversion or purchase action.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great to start with and grow into as need more features.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Using landing pages to capture leads, workflows to stay engaged and resell, email marketing."}}
{"author": ["Christopher K"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Creative Director | Principal", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the streamlined interface and the way everything just works together. From posting to social, sending email, building website and landing pages, CTAs, etc., everything just goes together like peas and carrots.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I'm quite addicted to checking Keyword and Alexa Rankings on an almost daily basis because they make it so easy to do so.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Occasionally working in the Design Manager building page/email/blog templates can be a bit cumbersome without a firm grasp of HTML and CSS. Once they're built though, watch out!"}}
{"author": ["Ron W"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Outreach Coordinator"], "date": ["Oct 27, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot have a beautifully designed product. Given the complexity of marketing automation software, they have done a great job of making it intuitive for small business owners with little or no coding ability.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot troubleshooting can be difficult and I have found the staff to be unresponsive at times.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure to receive training before hand because the scope of the platform is quite exstensvie.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Utilizing one platform for a one stop shop for marketing and customer development."}}
{"author": ["Tal L"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Manager Marketing", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Oct 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "i'm using the sales module and i just enjoy the templates and the customer's management abilities and tracking. the added insights about the leads with the clearbit integration, the direct link to the company's website. it's a great tool. ", "What do you dislike?": "i really have nothing bad to say about hubspot. just recommended them yesterday. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I think this whole review build my recommendation. easy, smart, saves time, do the work, adds intelligence. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "saves precious time, helps manage leads and creates business opportunities. helps understand the lead better from a behavioral point of view and adds additional data from the web. "}}
{"author": ["William M"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How easy to record contacts with prospects, sales and contact info.  Also, relative ease to customize records, dashboards and reports. ", "What do you dislike?": "Email rules are cumbersome.  Sometimes I am hindered in email marketing due to your rules.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Try it before buying; make sure it fits your needs....but it is a powerful tool.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Can target our email marketing to the right prospects.  Can track who is opening our emails....and then follow up with a targeted email."}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 28, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I used to work for Oracle and we used Oracle's CRM tool. No one in the company seemed to know how to use the tool/liked using the tool. In comparison, HubSpot is so much easier to use and has a much more pleasurable experience. The UX looks nice and when they have updates, they let you know in a number of ways: via email, a persistent in-app banner, and various in-app messages. This keeps me informed and never feeling lost in their product. I also feel like they're always innovating their practices and staying on top of trends. It feels like I always have the newest product on the market--in the very best sense. \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I also really like the email part of their tool. You can create email templates that will auto-generate certain properties that allow you to create some-what personalized emails to all of your prospects. You can also create sequences that help you stay organized and stay on top of your leads as they come in. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As any software product, HubSpot has its bugs that can be annoying. It'll randomly log me out at times or drop down menus will close before I can click on the item. Nothing earth shattering, just annoying. I also think their support is only OK. I try to report these bugs and when I take the time to do a screen recording and send it over, I don't typically receive a response. I also had an issue one day and they sent me a number of docs to try to solve the issue and it ended up being a bug. I prefer honesty, and if they knew this was a bug, I would have rather known that then spending an hour or so reading through their docs and trying out different solutions."}}
{"author": ["User in Food & Beverages"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 29, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I absolutely love how easy and efficient sales tracking is and the email tracking feature let's me keep client interactions organized too.", "What do you dislike?": "There are a few bugs here and there but mainly seems like some notifications are delayed at times but could also be die to how many users are on at the time.As with any software program, there will be glitches but the customer support is on top of any issues or concerns, which is above and beyond most these days.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Maybe tweak the email notification a bit because it seems to show that emails are opened repetitively at times.If client is in email preview mode it will show read even if the email was actually never opened. It is important to see which email templates are reacted to or received by clients better than other are overlooked or not acted on.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "If simple is what works for your business, Hubspot is your answer! This is by far one of the easiest and best tracking systems for our business and customers."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Higher Education"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the way that they allow you to communicate and track your communication with your contacts all in one place.", "What do you dislike?": "I haven't found anything that I dislike about it yet, other than we have to pay to access many of the features. But that's how they make their money, so I understand.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It allows me to really stay in tuned with where each of my potential customers are and the progress my team is making on them."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has an existing reputation of being a word class. Trusted platform for marketing campaigns with perfect seamless integration for WordPress in minutes. A comprehensive report of campaigns, most importantly for better mitigation. Awesome and acceptable.", "What do you dislike?": "Their contact does delay a bit in response. Probable as a result of the exceedingly high number of users", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Excellent Sales and Marketing platform to initiate boost sales. Act fast and get it", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Functioned as the main platform for our marketing and sales campaigns. Renders detailed analytics reports of campaigns to ease mitigation."}}
{"author": ["Melissa S"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development Representative", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 27, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Umm, there are so many things I love about HubSpot it is hard to pick an absolute favorite, but since I need to I'm going to say that when I click it responds quickly, there is no lag time ", "What do you dislike?": "Honestly there is not anything that I dislike. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely check it out, I have used top of the line outrageously expensive CRM's that had the spinning wheel of death, every time we clicked to the point where we had to use spread sheets just to hit our metrics because if we would have just worked out of the system it would never happen, I have used \"homegrown\" solutions that were expensive due to customization needed, basically I have been doing this for over ten years and I have never worked out of a system that was better.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Well we are able to score our inbound leads so that we reach out personally to prospects that reach a certain threshold and not chasing the right ones.  wait on others instead of wasting time and money either chasing every lead or  "}}
{"author": ["Christopher K"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Associate", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 06, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Very easy to learn and has lots of features.", "What do you dislike?": "Groupings need to be made by lists instead of being able to do so in the graph tools.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It has allowed me to show things about our audience that is hard to put to words."}}
{"author": ["Ginny C"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Product Marketing Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 20, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The interface is pretty intuitive.  Reg page creation is easy.", "What do you dislike?": "Very bad connection with Salesforce.com - some fields you just \"can't\" build a smart list with - no logic to it.  Difficult to navigate the analytics.   The workflow/drip campaign is clunky.  Email template options very limited, unless you want to pay more.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Mostly use for direct email campaigns, not really using for demand gen or nurturing.    Good to see the click rates / open rates of each email.  "}}
{"author": ["Krista F"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital marketing trainee"], "date": ["Jul 15, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "creating and modifying web pages, reviewing social & creating posts to many platforms at once", "What do you dislike?": "not having language variations in blogs, hub dp doesn't update after editing.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is a handy platform for creating & editing web pages & looking at analytics and social media."}}
{"author": ["Marisa J. L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Customer Success Specialist", "Financial Services"], "date": ["Feb 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that it's fairly user friendly.  I haven't used many email marketing tools but I was able to use hubspot without much training. ", "What do you dislike?": "I do wish that exporting/importing contacts was a little easier.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to filter through the contact lists to email only the folks we want to :) "}}
{"author": ["User in Cosmetics"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 27, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We\u2019ve been using hubspot at my company for the past few months and it has made everyone\u2019s role in the office so much easier! We used to use another software for emailing automation but with hubspot you can create an email, select your lists to sent t to, and the track the open and click rates which is so beneficial for seeing what\u2019s working and what\u2019s not. Hubspot also allows us to plan social media posts in advance which takes the stress out of having to post every single day. Hubspot has other features such as crashing landing pages, which is handy for tracking data as well. There\u2019s also a sales platform of hubspot which is the sales side of my company says has been so helpful as well. 10/10! ", "What do you dislike?": "The only complaint is that hubspot doesn\u2019t have social media planning for Instagram, so we are still having to take time everyday to post on this platform. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Tracking data, CRM, faster way so plan and post on social media. "}}
{"author": ["Agency in Internet"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how it functions as a CRM and marketing outreach tool. Lots of great features, like being able to see the path a user took through your site before submitting your contact form. It had (not sure if it still does) a feature to see whether a person has read an email you sent them. This makes it easier to know when to time your next reply without wondering if they even got or read your email to them. Another great feature is being able to create Facebook and Instagram ads that trigger a form to fill out. We'll see how useful this is going forward now that Facebook has altered its content display algorithm to emphasize organic social graph content over sponsored content. Emails you send through Hubspot are sent through its already-trusted servers so you don't have to worry as much about your emails being flagged as spam.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't love the price for entry-level folks who don't have high volume of client outreach. It's also not a direct replacement for MailChimp.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Get a sales workflow devised before you get involved with this product. Approaching this with a plan will make the purchase more worthwhile.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Mostly I just use one of its WordPress plugins to get basic data about people fill out my website contact form. I have one other client who uses that plugin as well. But neither of us has such a great need and ROI that the price justifies a whole service plan purchase."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The tool is very easy to use and I love the customer service they provide. You can easily get someone on the phone to assist. Additionally, they have tons of great resources to help you learn the tool and marketing.", "What do you dislike?": "Our company has many different divisions. It would be nice to have one shared instance but the ability to separate reporting.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation.The ability for marketers to self-serve in creating email without needing an expert in HTML>"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 24, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Not only are all of the different features in HubSpot do exactly what you want them to do, the user interface is extremely easy to navigate and their support team is INCREDIBLE. You can reach them by chat if you have a quick question, by phone if you need to talk something out or have them call or email you at a later time if you're not in a rush. The support team has helped me through some pretty intricate projects and tasks - they're so patient and explain things in a way that's really easy to understand.", "What do you dislike?": "The only complaint I can think of is that sometimes certain areas of the interface change without notifying you first. Nothing too drastic, but sometimes certain tools or functions move to a different tab or just get a face lift.. it can be a shock at first if you're used to something different.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Utilize every aspect of your account manager and support because they will get you set up on the right path and continue to help as you implement new projects in the platform.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We initially signed on with HubSpot for an automated email platform and a place to store our database of contacts. We soon realized that the opportunities to build our landing pages, blogs, call to actions and so much more were endless.. we probably use nearly every area of the platform to date."}}
{"author": ["User in Design"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 24, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The strategies and insights that were provided in the training sessions were helpful to learn more about inbound marketing. There were lots of examples of what \"good\" inbound websites looked like.  ", "What do you dislike?": "Huge learning curve, very very difficult tests for \"certification\" that did not seem necessary at all. The questions were confusing and sometimes downright incorrect. We could find statements in their classes that were contradictory to their tests. There was also not enough guidance in the email automation processes. Very confusing; would have been helpful to have pre-built automations to customize and build off of", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would research other alternatives. I think you could find one that is less expensive and more value. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We were wanting more inbound business, were very interested in automation side of things, however I think there are more efficient, less expensive options. The training on inbound tactics was over-abundant, but very little training on how to actually use the product led to frustration. "}}
{"author": ["User in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 24, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I primarily use hubspot for email. i like the ease of use and that I can include and exclude lists as well as send to more. It's super convenient to schedule emails as well. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike the extended features. I don't use hubspot's landing pages, personas or blog because I already have a website built. however, this makes it difficult to automate things and hub spot hasn't been the most helpful with this. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you simply need an email platform you can get something else cheaper. However if you want to use all of their features just be prepared to take a bunch of time converting to hubspot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We were having issues tracking our marketing efforts. It's great that in hubspot i can see how many emails are opened and how many call to actions are clicked. However again, I can't completely automate it as then our website is built on it's own platform so I switch over to our website to see what leads actually converted. "}}
{"author": ["Allison G"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Director", "Non-Profit Organization Management"], "date": ["Dec 15, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how easy it is to build an audience workflow. I also love how they are beefing up their reporting tools.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't think the landing page content editor is very intuitive. You really have to know what you're doing to use it, so it's not ideal for the average marketing manager to use to create campaign landing pages.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are trying to reach a new audience. We have seen more conversions since we started using HubSpot. "}}
{"author": ["Maureen H"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing & Brand Publishing Lead", "Pharmaceuticals"], "date": ["Dec 21, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I liked being able to track all of my marketing campaigns -- whether display, ppc, email, or individual media-buys -- and compare metrics and conversions all in the HubSpot dashboard. ", "What do you dislike?": "The HubSpot - Salesforce.com connection wasn't as transparent and easily viewed by the sales team as I had expected when we licensed the system. Salespeople could only see a particular prospect's status, web interactions and downloads when they clicked on and reviewed that prospect's file--which only works for prospects that a rep is actively engaged with. To bring their attention to new MQLs, marketing had to compile reports or a weekly basis to send to inside sales for follow-up. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I think Hubspot is a great all-in-one starter tool for SMBs. You get a lot of bang for the buck It is actually possible for one FTE or 50% PTE to handle all your WCM and marketing automation needs from HubSpot. But if you have more sophisticated CRM integration or customer experience management needs, you may want to check out  some of the bigger players in the field.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm a marketer, not a web developer, and HubSpot has to be one of the easiest and most intuitive web content management systems I have ever used. It definitely helped us build a robust content marketing platform on our website, manage both inbound and outbound campaigns, and track A/B variants to optimize CTA's and landing pages. Marketing could be faster and more responsive than if we had to go through an agency or Web IT department."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 20, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot enables our marketing department to be proactive with our lead generation and get more qualified results.  We have also been able to start a blog and we are expecting great things from it. ", "What do you dislike?": "Because it is a comprehensive solution, there is some patience needed in learning the entire platform and customizing it to solve your pain points. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "From day one, you will see instant results from using Hubspot.  I found that the landing page creating and forms were easy and effective. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have eliminated any unqualified leads from entering into our sales funnel and this has saved our sales team time.  Through our nurturing campaign, we have enhanced the experience for our prospects and been able to present different forms of material to them.  We also now have a better experience with our search engine optimization and know how to make changes in how site visitors are engaging with our pages."}}
{"author": ["Patricia G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Pat Gracia"], "date": ["Aug 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really like the way it helps you to improve your content for SEO without needing to become an expert.", "What do you dislike?": "You need to learn to code in Hubspot or find someone who does otherwise you won't build good sites. The tracking is also confusing. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Study and research a lot to use it the right way. Make sure you have at least 1 dedicated person in the team that manages and encourage other users to use too.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "User acquisition and nurturing."}}
{"author": ["User in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how easy it is to navigate and find things within HubSpot. It's very user-friendly and extremely straight forward on where to go and what to do.", "What do you dislike?": "There aren't anythings that I've run into that I've come to dislike about HubSpot. All I've had were good experiences!", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take your time to learn and navigate all of the resources and options HubSpot has to offer. Don't miss out on anything valuable because they have a lot to offer.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has helped me become more organized and efficient in my daily work. I'm able to schedule social media posts in advance and that allows me to focus on other important tasks throughout my work week."}}
{"author": ["Adam G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Internet"], "date": ["Oct 10, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Much easier to use than Marketo, and a lot less clunky. They keep the UI updated and when I used Marketo less than two years ago it was really old looking and not seamless. ", "What do you dislike?": "HubSpot gets ridiculously expensive when you have a significant number of contacts. We had to delete a ton of contacts and use MailChimp instead for one campaign. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The integration isn't seamless, but it's the most integrated marketing tool I've found.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation\r"}}
{"author": ["bhargav b"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["field marketing manager"], "date": ["Jan 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Customer support is phenomenal. Even when it's not something they know, they go and find out and make sure my problem is resolved before we hang up the phone.", "What do you dislike?": "Pricing model is not very healthy for young companies that aim to grow quickly. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation is the main problem being solved. Benefits = convenience."}}
{"author": ["Michael F. R"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Feb 16, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy content management and SEO components followed by the ease of inserting calls to action into content. Helping my company get found to grow leads! \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Competitive tools are just what is needed and SEO measurement tells you in an easy to view interface how we're doing.  A powerful suite built into one easy accessible platform and the good thing is - I know HubSpotters are working hard on a continuous s basis to improve functionality and capabilities.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Like I tell my wife - please don't compare me to a perfect husband - compare me to the real world. (So at least I have a fighting chance!)\r"}}
{"author": ["Ken U"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Communications Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 17, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The functionality is comprehensive, and will integrate between our lead generation/nurturing and CRM on the sales side. Their client on-boarding is first rate and personal.", "What do you dislike?": "Getting started is a bit overwhelming, and there is not a really concise searchable knowledgebase to access for the many nitty gritty questions that come up with the set up. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Establishing a full, campaign-based platform for managing our sales funnel. Capturing more website leads, nurturing leads, and strengthening customer support."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 01, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "we have recently started using it, hopefully, it will start showing better result but has good coverage of the functionality. we are using it for running email campaigns, social media campaigns, etc", "What do you dislike?": "Designing and customization of the template could still be better but much better than other competitors", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Create your own research, look at the demos, checklist for the functionalities required , involve sales team as well as it cuts across different departments", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead scoring problem, better-targeted campaigns, getting a better insight into traffic"}}
{"author": ["James L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Course Consultant", "E-Learning"], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love being able to track all of the past marketing emails. Too often I'm not sure what a customer is referring too but I can go back and see exactly what they have seen. ", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't much to dislike. There are times where the reports dashboard can get a little confusing but that just takes time. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am better able to track customer progress. I love having everything in one place. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 17, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot caters to the majority of marketing needs, from website hosting and management, CRM, blogs, email, and social. All of it can be done from one place, thus reducing the number of tools (and integration points) required. There is something to be said of benefitting from a reduction of costs by consolidating all online marketing activities in one platform.", "What do you dislike?": "Does not have the capability of creating a password-protected portion of a website. Dislike having to learn a new coding language that is proprietary to HubSpot (Hubbl). It's like having to learn Esperanto - it only benefits a specific group of individuals who know the language. Would have liked that Hubspot employ a more mainstream coding language like Ruby or GoLang.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Clearly define what your business requirements are, and whether if Hubspot will suit their needs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We needed to centralize all online marketing activities into one platform. Our former marketing agency used to manage our WordPress website, and making changes was a painful and costly process. We now have the flexibility in making changes to the website ourselves, and progressively enhancing it using new functionality and tools that are conducive to an effective inbound marketing strategy."}}
{"author": ["Kelsey B"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": ["Paid Search Manager", "Real Estate"], "date": ["Aug 23, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Love how user friendly HubSpot is and how easy it is to create everything from landing pages to emails to custom contact lists.", "What do you dislike?": "It would be nice if the contact lists had more options for viewing the history of a lead. Currently any time someone becomes a new lead, their source is updated with the most current lead source. It's very difficult to see the full path to conversion by exporting a large list of leads.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easy email automation & list creation for our landing page forms."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The autosaving and clearly labelled menus", "What do you dislike?": "The WYSIWYG cannot really be trusted and I have to spend an awful lot of time in html to get the content how I would like.  Very easy to have bad page design/CMS accepted as valid and this causes some of the problems.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "To maintain sections of our website, create customer emails and develop landing pages. Within the limitations outlined above I am now able to maintain and improve communications with key sections of the audience"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 15, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the HubSpot university a lot. So much good training material to help you get started. I also like the easy access to support staff. ", "What do you dislike?": "The UI was clunky. I also didn't care much for our certified HubSpot marketing agency, they struggled to add value to the project and ended up adding way too much overhead to our budget. Had to cut them loose. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you have vetted other options. I think HubSpot thirves on selling an all-in-one solution, but sometime mixing your own cocktails is the best solution. I think using a simple web publisher like squarespace and then mailchimp would be a great solution as well. Sometimes adding a ton of lead nurting tools is a waste of time and resources, espeically if you have a small marketing team with a limited number of products. Get your companies elementary marketing efforts dialed and then start adding complexity. Adding too much too soon, often just create confusion and analysis paralysis. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead gen, web site creation, lead nurturing, and email. Sadly HubSpot had difficulty adding value, but this could mainly be attributed to our marketing agency not having the chops to work in our industry. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 14, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Highly feature rich tool\r", "What do you dislike?": "Superb Integration with other tools\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Very good reporting capabilities\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Decent (but not excellent) field history tracking\r"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It provides the same level of capabilities as its bigger competitors, as well as a huge library of helpful resources that go beyond the uses of HubSpot alone.", "What do you dislike?": "We've run into glitches more often than we'd like, but their support team has been able to resolve most of them pretty fast. Easy to get help.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It has helped us gain a lot of insight on customer trends, as well as be more organized in our lead capture."}}
{"author": ["Charity R"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Marketing Intern", "Retail"], "date": ["Nov 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is a great place to start for people who are new to Marketing. It is a great way to learn for free!", "What do you dislike?": "I don't like that you cannot create email sequences for free and have to pay for that service.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "How to market to the business I work for. It is a valuable learning tool."}}
{"author": ["Grace W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["VP of Marketing"], "date": ["Aug 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot combines the Essentials of each tactic a small business needs for basic, multi-touch campaigns. They incorporate data from GoogleAnalytics and Salesforce. Those integrations are easy to set up. Their support staff are ever-present, knowledgeable and thorough.", "What do you dislike?": "It's not a good tool for marrying opportunity and touch data. It's not a good tool to cheaply set up weighted marketing attribution on your touches. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are capturing leads we would not have otherwise captured via Hubspot's forms and email nurture capabilities. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 25, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is very easy to use and get the hang of. If you get stuck, the Success Managers and bounty of resources make it fast and simple to get back on track.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes really cool features are disjointed. For example, we love the pop-ups for collecting additional info but they are only included on lead flows but can't automatically connect them to a workflow. I'd love to be able to use pop-ups with either of these lead nurturing mechanisms.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're improving our lead conversion! Our traffic was increasing but conversions weren't and HubSpot has given us new mechanisms for fixing that."}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 13, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is extremely easy to use. It has the same type of user experience as something like Mailchimp. There are more advanced features that help you scale as your business grows, but you can start with the very basics very easily. \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Also, our account team is phenomenal. I've learned so much about marketing automation in general - but if we know we need to change a process or improve a function, our account team is very accommodating. They've gone above and beyond to do a lot of heavy lifting for us, sometimes just doing all of the work. They always provide educational material, how-to's, best practices. Our demand gen processes improve every time I meet with them. This has added the most value to our investment. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I feel like some of the more advanced features you'd want from a marketing automation platform aren't there. But Hubspot is growing and their newer features are generally impressive. The reporting could also be much better. We're currently in the beta-test version of email analytics. It's nice to have, but I can't export those analytics, which has created some headaches."}}
{"author": ["Meghan C"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Specialist", "Education Management"], "date": ["Mar 25, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's hard to narrow down the one thing I like best about Hubspot. I think that those who use Hubspot don't just use it like they would any other software product. It quickly becomes all-encompassing in the way you market overall. \r", "What do you dislike?": "- Need ideas for content creation? Check their blog posts. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "- Need to extract some data? Pull a customizable report. \r"}}
{"author": ["Jim R"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Songwriter/Musician", "Design"], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is very versatile and completely scalable! It has a wide range of features for most aspects of marketing/business. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the features such as website pages could be released for smaller packages but limited maybe in amount of pages you can create. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "This tool will without a doubt accelerate you're marketing/business output. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Quick and easy landing pages with great analytics. You can automate and track all your social in one place making it very versatile. "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing automation specialist"], "date": ["Aug 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The user experience and the support is the best part of the product", "What do you dislike?": "Reporting could be more friendly, A/B testing is a little problematic and no heatmaps", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great software would recommend using if you are in B2B", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation, social media sequencing, blogging"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like being able to track email open and click rates and use the data to analyze subject line and template performance.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike how you're not able to curate a list of people to send follow-up emails to based on in they responded or not - at least not when emailing through gmail.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot makes mass emailing easier and allows you to create and store templates that you can use through gmail or send directly from HubSpot. It makes creating contacts effortless as well."}}
{"author": ["Tom R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Managing Director", "Financial Services"], "date": ["Apr 05, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The onboarding and consulting process is excellent.  Great online tutorials and ideas for marketing.  They keep a close eye on their email reputation which is important.  Constant usability upgrades which are appreciated.  Good calendar functionality.   Unlimited users which is appreciated.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you buy into the inbound marketing concepts you can make a big difference in your business and become more targeted and efficient.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Their pricing policy where pricing can never go down even if you reduce the number of contacts - that is unsustainable.  There also has been a fair amount of turnover among the support staff - some growing pains."}}
{"author": ["Camilo Andr\u00e9s L"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Director", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the academy, I like the partner team assigned", "What do you dislike?": "not having time to learn all they create", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "get it as soon as you can, the platform just keeps getting and getting better, Its team is rally knowable. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "get got a clear vision for setting sales and marketing goals, "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the ability to change the deal stages quickly. It keeps things very organized. I also like all of the search filters that are available. ", "What do you dislike?": "I definitely liked the old layout better, and am still adjusting to the update. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helps keep track of touchpoints and making sure different prospects are being reached out to. I also really like the email tracking to see when prospects are opening emails in order to see what the best time to reach out to them is. "}}
{"author": ["Vishal M"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Manager"], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Advertising Dashboard, Workflow , Chat bot.", "What do you dislike?": "Need more improvement in page creation..", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Please make Landing Page admin more reliable it is very complex to use make it like simple drag and drop.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to track customer behaviour and activity with the HubSpot."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 05, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the ability that HubSpot gives me in gmail to track who opens my emails. Just check the box in my compose screen and it sends an alert to my desktop when they open the email - every single time. You can also log in to your free HubSpot dashboard and see a record of the times they opened. Very handy! ", "What do you dislike?": "I haven't found anything I dislike about HubSpot yet. I've only been using their simple free features. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great tools to streamline your business! ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The ability for me to see when people open my emails is huge. No more wondering if I should write someone again. If they didn't open I just send another email a few days later!"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 04, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like certifications and training that Hubspot has within the website. Doing email marketing is literally the bare minimum you can do so I like that Hubspot helps train and educate on what they provide. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike their customer support. I've called to receive help with one of the files that automatically pulls. I want to it pull to a different spot and I received no help, instead just \"oh no, that's how it pulls.\" \r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I also dislike how the emails look. It doesn't allow you to make it very creative unless you literally upload a graphic you build in photoshop. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 04, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The platform itself is great. I loved the ease of use and the fact we could manage our emails, landing pages, blog, and social from one system. ", "What do you dislike?": "The only thing to dislike really is the cost. While we had a good price the first year we were with HubSpot, the significant increase we were going to see upon renewal is why we ultimately had to leave them. If you have the budget to spend, do it. But if you have a smaller marketing department with little to no budget, it's costly to use the paid versions of their system.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot really is a great marketing automation platform and their sales tools are great as well. However, they need to be more mindful of the budgets of smaller marketing departments so there isn't a doubling of price from year to year.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We were able to automate our email marketing, blog posting, and social posting, as well as tie it all together into actionable analytics."}}
{"author": ["Fran\u00e7ois B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Inbound Marketing Strategist, Marketing Consultant, CEO", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 30, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use and time saving Inbound Marketing Software featuring a Blogging platform, Email Marketing, Customer Database, Keywords Grader Tool, Competitor Analysis, Social Media Management and Campaigns Workflows / Automation as well as Analytics.\r", "What do you dislike?": "HubSpot works worldwide and has now it own CRM integrated. In addition to the landing pages you may host your website on HubSpot too, allowing you to personalize the content.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot allows you to build an extensive history of the leads which eases lead conversion and sales.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helps you align marketing and sales, making the process of implementing a service level agreement easier and more effective. It supports you improving customer service and It lets you turn existing customers into brand advocates."}}
{"author": ["User in Real Estate"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 14, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I fell in love with hubspot when I first started to use it - mostly I think because of the witty email campaigns you can send you from there. ", "What do you dislike?": "I didn't like how I would manually have to start and stop whether hubspot tracked my emails. It got tiresome after a while to stop it from tracking.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Determine what you are looking for before you set it up and then determine if this can fit your needs. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I was using it mostly for tracking, to see when people had opened emails etc. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Leisure, Travel & Tourism"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 07, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy and intuitive to use and many product integrations are available, which we use frequently. I also like the education section, because it helps you really get the most out of the product if you use it regularly. ", "What do you dislike?": "It takes some time for support to email you back. If you are really in a hurry, it's better to just call. It can be difficult to design newsletters or figure out where to change the specifications. It can be really difficult to use with our really long sales cycle, but I think this would be the same with any software. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Not really a lot to add here... just make sure that allot plenty of time, switching over is always complicated and you need to make sure that your systems make sense. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "This is our CRM and content system. We moved over primarily  because of the ability to track where many of our leads came from, which is critical for us. Now we enjoy the automation of routine marketing tasks and have been fine tuning our reporting. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is great for workflows, content creation, social media scheduling and training.", "What do you dislike?": "You need to have all the software options to fully realize its capabilities (CRM, Sales, Academy, Service)", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do the trial period and really run it through the rigors of what your company will use it for, they are great about support and can help you accomplish whatever you want with this software", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have become an actual lead generating machine for our company because of Hubspot and the platforms it offers!"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Having used HubSpot for many years, and have seen many different iterations, my favorite thing about HubSpot is that it is so darn easy to set up and use.", "What do you dislike?": "Often it takes a while to successful launch new tools and their sales tools are tough to use with a larger sales team that wants to use tools that HubSpot doesn't yet offer", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Just start working on things and get stuff up, if you want to do everything at once you'll get sucked down rabbit holes. HubSpot is very easy to implement and fix so don't be afraid to make errors. Also the integrations to most tools are good but it's not the easiest to use with Salesforce unless you're an admin of both tools.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows small marketing teams to automate processes to allow teams to do more with less. It was also a good way to track marketing efforts and interact with prospect and customers."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The platform is very easy-to-use and they have a very well organized resources section for you to learn how to use the platform as well as how inbound marketing works. I liked having a monthly check-in with our customer representative. Her recommendations were quite helpful for me since at that time I had a limited experience with the platform. Also, building a landing page was super easy.", "What do you dislike?": "I like it very much there is almost nothing I dislike but if you use SalesForce, you are better off using Pardot. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's a perfect match for small marketing teams especially with medium or low technical knowledge. They have an amazing support process, great articles to keep you updated on what's going on in marketing, and user-friendly UI. You can quickly pick it up and get amazing results.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I've used it mainly for the B2B lead generation for more than a year. Making it up and running, configuring everything doesn't take much time. It helped me and my team (about 10 people) to identify the most effective marketing channels. We were able to leverage email marketing capabilities with automation. We increased our online leads more than 25% within 1 year. "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Chemicals"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot works hard to make their service as user friendly as possible. Their workflow tool is one of the best I have seen, because it focuses on their core user - the marketer. The process is visual and dynamic. \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The level of information they distribute about using their service and about marketing in general is fantastic. However, that doesn't mean their customer service is totally reliant on this information. The customer service team has helped me resolve a large number of unique issues successfully.  "}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The hubspot interface is intuitive but the breadth of the system is wide. There is tons of functionality hiding behind an inviting user face. ", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes the dashboard can be a bit laggy; social posts will hang for a few minutes before appearing. The email designer is a bit more limited than some others I have used. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great support and great reps. This is working for our mid-sized firm. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Having email, social and campaign and lead management housed under one roof has been very beneficial to us. "}}
{"author": ["User in E-Learning"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The platform has a lot of flexibility and configurability.", "What do you dislike?": "Price is high. Despite being flexible, sometimes very basic functionality is missing. I think more of a focus on improving the existing products over adding new ones would be helpful.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Compare other marketing automation products and project your needs--you may not need HubSpot in your budget yet.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We need to automate our email marketing, track users, and create beautiful landing pages. We have definitely reduced the time spent on these activities and it is nice to have so much functionality under one roof."}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 30, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that I can create emails, forms, landing pages and manage my database all with this one piece of software. I honestly don't know what I would do without this software. I certainly would not be getting the same amount of leads, that's for sure.", "What do you dislike?": "Not much at all. HubSpot has great support for it's customers. Sometimes it is difficult to navigate a new template...but that is really it.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would say to go for it! I have loved the whole experience from on boarding to the present.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We needed a way to manage our leads, move them down the funnel and help convert them. This software is the answer to this and more."}}
{"author": ["Amogh B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Head Of Marketing", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Jul 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the tracking feature and the dashboard. It allows us to measure productivity in real time. The notifications are very handy when it comes to tracking opens, clicks and so on. ", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing in particular. The mobile app could be a bit more user friendly - UX wise", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Productivity can be measured in real time. We also get real time notifications about how many times our mails have been opened and so on which helps us send appropriate follow-up mails and pre-empt the next actions to be taken,"}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ability to scale and automate a lot of our marketing functions. ", "What do you dislike?": "Expensive and their landing page design feature is horrible", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you have the budget, use it if you need a full suite for both your marketing and sales team. It's a great tool that helps us provide visibility in our prospects behaviour and nurture our leads.  Just be aware that their support isn't as great and their customization toolset need a lot of work. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We need to nurture leads throughout their buyers' cycle and hubspot does a great job of it. There are a few areas where they can be better but overall a good tool to use. "}}
{"author": ["Frankie M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Social Media and Marketing Support"], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Being able to schedule posts in bulk makes it much easier to create a concentrated marketing and social media plan for the upcoming month or months.", "What do you dislike?": "There is not much to dislike but the reports section in the marketing hub is sometimes inaccurate.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has allowed me to analyse what's best to post across our social media platforms, whether that is the best time to post, types of post or which posts do better on some social media platforms than others."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's user-friendly, easy to create templates for emails and easy to put together a landing page.", "What do you dislike?": "Character limit on blog titles. I don't like that when I want to change little things in an email such as adding an additional block of text or image I have to go into the template to add the block.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can easily send out our monthly newsletter and record stats provided. I can quickly set up a landing page with a form."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 17, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Super easy to use and has pretty much everything you need. The tool is very user friendly and once you get used to it the things you can do are endless.", "What do you dislike?": "It doesn't have certain features like the ability to attribute a closed deal to multiple marketing assets instead of just the asset that converted the lead. Its reporting could also be better/easier.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Utilize your account manager and support. Pay attention during on-boarding.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use all of the features - emailing, social, list building, etc."}}
{"author": ["User in Automotive"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot provides an excellent dashboard view of our marketing team's overall performance without getting too gritty or overly detailed. It's also been crucial to our organization;s understanding of what types of outreach get the best engagement from our customers, who are not traditionally plugged into digital outlets.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot seems wildly broad in its applications, which can actually impede our organization's ability to understand how best to apply it to our particular business needs. Hubspot provides tons of useful content for better understanding how marketing works in general, but the software itself doesn't always seem too tailored to our business needs without heavy consultation with Hubspot SMEs.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Be very clear on your business needs for this software before buying into it. The amount of features that Hubspot offers can be overwhelming and confusing if you don't already have a plan of action for it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Unlike previous years, we now have a go-to dashboard for digital marketing performance tracking, which has been an enormous boon to our marketing team's ability to justify company expenditures on digital marketing via social media, email, etc."}}
{"author": ["Mario B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing & Communication Specialist", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Mar 16, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "As a marketer of the age of the customer, I'm always looking for helpful tools to improve the inbound strategy of the company I work for. The main goal is to integrate all different aspects of the job into one - easy, yet comprehensive - platform. Hubspot was the answer to all marketing prayers. I've been using it for about 7 months and I'm still finding new exciting features, day after day. At Neosperience, my sales colleagues specially love the possibility to integrate Hubspot with other services - Salesforce, to name one - to build a truly omni-channel strategy, and accompany contacts from awareness to post-conversion. Even if you're not a marketer, but a content manager or communication specialist, you will find everything you need: blogging, emails, newsletters, landing pages, smart lists. All options at your fingertips.", "What do you dislike?": "There is nothing I really dislike in Hubspot. I would love to see more social media options available to extend the reach beyond the usual Facebook or Twitter. Oh, and maybe the possibility to add/delete easily contacts in a smart list (it can be a bit confusing and time-spending). ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Choose their training calls, follow their webinars and courses. Get everything you can from the experts that follow your company. Don't be scared to ask ... and to try new approaches to your marketing questions.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Before starting using Hubspot, my daily duties were the same, but I had to struggle between different tools and platforms that - more often than not - couldn't be forced to work together. Right now we have everything (well, almost everything) in one single place, easy to find and very intuitive to use. The one single thing that we love the most? We are now able to track the integrated process that guides users to become contacts and then leads and customers, offering useful and personalized contents and staying top of mind. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I like is how user friendly the system is. The training was very detailed and prepared me to use live in the system. Support is quick to respond for the most part. ", "What do you dislike?": "We are having some issues with hard bounces when it comes to email blasts and we can't seem to get on the same page to find a solution. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to link our eventbrite page to Hubspot and collect data through Hubspot. "}}
{"author": ["Conrado L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Advisory Partner", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Aug 05, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Robust and simple to use. A must in marketing automation.", "What do you dislike?": "Because I integrate it with Salesforce, I wonder if Pardot's integration is better.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The best benefit of Hubspot is being able to determine our website's visitor path from beginning to the end."}}
{"author": ["Erica F"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["Marketing Associate", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Sep 05, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We rely heavily on automation, and HubSpot allows us to easily create engaging emails and workflows. ", "What do you dislike?": "There is nothing so far that I have found to dislike. Their customer service is amazing, and we have never gone without a solution to our problems. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As stated previously, we rely heavily on automation. We have realized that we can give personal touches to our automated emails which allows our workflows to remain engaging with our prospects and we see good response, as well as good conversions. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Hospital & Health Care"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 05, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Nothing great as of yet. Even reporting is subpar and costs extra", "What do you dislike?": "Landing page, sales tools, chat function all worse than what you can find anywhere ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We were convinced to switch over to hubspot after 4 years with a smaller CRM combined with mail chimp plus a whole lot of other software. Hubspot had the promise of putting it all together but falls on its face. Nearly every tool in hubspot is worse than what else if available (case in point, their landing page software). Worse, sales and customer support seem so separate that things we were promised never came to. Fruition  or were charged extra on an already very expensive platform. Cannot recommend "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Connection to other tools and easy of use", "What do you dislike?": "limited social media features (less than what is native in the social platform) & glitches in the posting features / emoticons ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you need basic functionality for Social Media, it will work for you. However, if you want advanced features go with another provider.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Social Media Management and Scheduling--there are benefits in keeping posts on track and scheduling. Also, their chatbot and web design features are useful."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 28, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I'm able to manage my database, create well designed emails, landing pages, and blog posts.", "What do you dislike?": "The biggest thing that could be improved on is the filtering of lists/workflows. To be able to say you want to filter by criteria ((1 and 2) and (3 or 4)), you have to say (1 and 2 and 3) or (1 and 2 and 4). It gets tedious sometimes.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The switch to Hubspot couldn't have been more simple. You're assigned a friendly Customer Implementation Specialist to help guide you through the process. You're given steps to follow, so nothing is missed. You have regular calls with your specialist to check in and make sure you're on the right track to achieving your goals. I've also never seen a more robust resource library as Hubspot's. It's incredible and has the answers to everything you might ever need help figuring out.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot allows us to manage our database and nurture leads before sending them over to the sales team. It benefits our sales team by not cluttering their sales funnel with leads that aren't qualified yet."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 01, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has been such a great platform and made marketing easier for the buisness. I have experimented with different platforms and this is one of my favorites. The platform offers software for marketing, customer service, and most importantly sales!", "What do you dislike?": "One complaint would be that it is not as user friendly as some programs. An experienced user had to teach me, rather than learning on my own. It is a little expspensive when comparing some other platforms.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take advanted of educational courses on HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is a great tool if you are in the sales or in marketing/advertising fields. I highly reccomend taking advantage of this platforms software. Ive been using this software for marketing and sales. The leads generated have given me an increase in sales."}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 22, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "A great centralized tool to track marketing efficiency. Pretty user-friendly, and with the correct setup, can provide a lot of great insight into how people are interacting with your brand.", "What do you dislike?": "I am a very visual marketer, so creating extremely customized assets was a bit difficult. Required a lot of coding knowledge. The HubSpot team created some customized templates for our company, but when I tried to tinker with them, they seemed to break easily. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot does a fine job at managing many marketing channels from one internal UI. I would recommend it to a smaller team or company. However, if you have dedicated teams to different marketing channels (i.e. social, email, etc.), there are better solutions out there that are tailored to each channel.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is a great tool to manage most basic marketing channels from a single UI. It's great for a smaller team that needs to cover a lot of ground, but doesn't require anything too customized or detailed. It's also a really great tool for connecting Marketing efforts with Sales efforts, as it provides a decent CRM."}}
{"author": ["Luke G"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Media Specialist, Industrial Marketing"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I appreciate the documentation and level of support provided by their team.", "What do you dislike?": "With many changes, sometimes things break.  It would be nice to be able to opt-in to new UI layouts, instead of them just appearing all of a sudden.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Sign up for their free tier to get acquainted with the product(s).  Definitely take any of their certification courses which apply to what you are going to use the platform for.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use this platform for marketing emails, customer segmentation, and engagement."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 22, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The interface is very easy to navigate and everything is where I would expect it to be.  I also like being able to see a Contact's entire marketing history through HubSpot and see what campaigns they responded to.", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the integration pieces are a bit difficult to configure but HubSpot is still way ahead of many of the other platforms in this area.  Workflow functionality is a bit limited in terms of timing and pathing, but HubSpot Support has been helpful with finding ways for us to make it do what we want it to.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Have one or more campaigns you are trying to launch in mind when you are looking at HubSpot.  Make sure to train your team using HubSpot's certification materials.  Having this knowledge on hand can be very helpful when you are trying to build things with it in the future.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing, SMS marketing, staying in touch with Contacts."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has been a great tool for funneling inbound leads. Great to see how much actual interaction this prospect has had. ", "What do you dislike?": "I am not in Marketing, so I am sometimes a bit confused with some of the functionalities. May need to do a bit my research on my end for the future.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "With any SaaS product, look into competitors but do remember Hubspot is the most well-known/best.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is attached to our website and is used to funnel inbound opportunities. Gives us a great understanding if the prospect is qualified and how the contact was created."}}
{"author": ["User in Public Relations and Communications"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It was good for integrating sales lists and logging information regarding the interaction. It was an easier wya to track email lists, social media campaigns, and general call or trade show engagements.", "What do you dislike?": "It was expensive and the automations were a little difficult with regards to formatting/design issues", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are a small business or do not maintain large lists of sales leads, connections, it can be costly. Also if you are used to more DIY formatting for automation and campaigns, it is difficult to adjust. Overall, for multi-users or large organizations, this is good.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot was a good way to track sales leads and see which member or coworker reached out to what company and which person without overlap or double dipping, so to speak. "}}
{"author": ["Amanda S"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["Director"], "date": ["Apr 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot makes it simple from within your email client to add a tracking tag to your outgoing email. And through the browser extension, you can easily check to see the status of those tracked emails.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes someone has clearly opened their email that I'm tracking - because they've responded to me - but I don't get a Hubspot notification. On the flip side, sometimes if I open my \"sent\" email that is tracked, Hubspot tells me \"someone opened this email.\"", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Managing follow-ups with clients"}}
{"author": ["Emma H"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Account Manager - Brand Partnerships", "Sports"], "date": ["Oct 29, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Love that you can connect hubspot to trace all emails and communications with clients and internally. You can easily see what was last said, and what meetings you have had and have coming up. ", "What do you dislike?": "Have not found a room to add general notes on accounts yet", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Keeping track of deals made and up-sell deals with companies. "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to build workflows, email and landing pages. Great reporting and leads acquisition and management.", "What do you dislike?": "constant changes and updates though they are usually valuable but they are not communicated other then in notifications", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's very user-friendly in comparison to other marketing automation solutions, and while constant updates may be annoying they are definitely for better", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am running almost all my current digital activities and reporting via HubSpot: emails, landing pages, PPC/Facebook ads integration, social posting and nurturing. It's fast and easy so I can run everything effectively by one person., "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 13, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the activity log, because every tracked email my coworkers send I can see and vice versa. This way we can be on the same page without having to take time out to have an extended meeting. ", "What do you dislike?": "I do not like the leads section, and the difficulty level of adding information to the preview portion of the contact or company. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use this when you have large businesses with lots of new leads coming in. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We can stay on the same page and know who we are talking to without having to take to much time out of our day. "}}
{"author": ["Ryan B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Chief Strategy Officer", "Entertainment"], "date": ["Nov 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is an embarassment of riches when it comes to customizable features. If I had a complaint, it would be that there are so many things it CAN do that it can take a while to learn how to use.", "What do you dislike?": "The interface isn\u2019t 100% intuitive. There are so many features and options that it takes a little time to create a working knowledge od how the system is operated. Though, I\u2019m not sure how it could be improved upon- it\u2019s more like there\u2019s just so mch available that it takes time to adapt.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Watch the tutorial videos. Seriously.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We\u2019re using it for tracking relationships of every kind: media tracking, potential investors, and potential vendors."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 13, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that Hubspot is easy to use, never goes down, and there is always support if I need it. We run our website, bog, and social through Hubspot. ", "What do you dislike?": "there's nothing really that I dislike about Hubspot, they change the layout frequently so that takes some getting used to but it's always for the better!", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Ask the sales reps for an ROI sheet and also talking points for convincing your boss or board. It's worth it!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We needed a platform where all of our stuff was in one place. No more disparate systems that aren't connected for campaign tracking, etc."}}
{"author": ["Robert W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Social Media & Creative Content Executive", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 23, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the reporting tools available especially for the social media part of the software, The software as a whole as saved our company in terms of money as we have been able to disregard certain other pieces of software like reporting and emailing tools.", "What do you dislike?": "The only thing i dislike about the software is the amount of notifications and emails you get at one time. However you are able to turn the notifications off its just hard becuase some emails you need to see, and some you dont, however they bothf all under the same sub category to turn them off. Other than that, i dont really dislike anything else.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Don skip any tutorials, read as much about it as you can and if youre stuck, ask for help. The customer servcie team are amazing!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Were solving one problem, that one problem being the amounf of different tools and pieces of software we had to use/pay for beforehand. Hubspot has allowed us to reign in our tools and software, and save money on a number of different areas. Without Hubsoit we would still be paying for 6+ different tools to do the job hubspot can do."}}
{"author": ["Agency in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 22, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "- Hubspot CRM\r", "What do you dislike?": "- Hubspot keywords - Keywords analysis is also a tool I use every day. \u2018Rank\u2019, \u2018monthly searches\u2019, \u2018difficulty\u2019, and \u2018CPC\u2019 are very helpful because they help my team and I determine which keywords we need to use for our campaign.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "- Reports on blog posts, emails, landing pages, and thank you pages\r"}}
{"author": ["Gretchen L"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Director", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Mar 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Our marketing efforts are finally becoming organized!", "What do you dislike?": "The social reporting and publishing function could definitely be more robust.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take your time and come up with a list of can't live without functions your team needs. Hubspot is wonderful but it isn't a perfect fit for everyone.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead nurturing and generation. We are no longer letting the little things that aren't actually so little in impact fall through the cracks."}}
{"author": ["John P"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["President and CEO"], "date": ["Jul 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to automate the sales and marketing activities and the contact-based CRM, meaning all info on a contact's activities are in their individual record. ", "What do you dislike?": "The price is very high when compared to similar products, such as the Zoho suite, that are rapidly approaching the same functionality as HubSpot, for 1/10th of the monthly cost. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure to implement it effectively and use all of its features, or you will not see an ROI. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Centralizing all advertising and marketing efforts. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Education Management"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There are a ton of features that can really help marketing and sales. The marketing automation and having everything in one platform is ideal. ", "What do you dislike?": "The pricing is of course a bit prohibitive. I would like for them to go away from pricing per contact. It is often a reason most people won't sign up because they have large contact lists. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely test out the CRM. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Customer experience problems. From creating initial follow ups for interested parties to following up after engagement it's really. "}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 14, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how Hubspot integrates everything and is somewhat user-friendly for people with different skillsets. I think their customer service and education platform is great. Everything I learned about inbound marketing was from Hubspot.", "What do you dislike?": "I think Hubspot gives impossible goals so that people funnel more money into it without seeing the return they deserve. I think you can get the same education and tools elsewhere for a lesser cost. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would consider looking into other options. Make sure you have the financial stability because once you start selling it to customers, you're pretty much hooked. I think if you have the right resources and knowledge, it can be a helpful tool for your company, but it's not for everyone. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Helping employees and clients understand what inbound marketing is and how to effectively implement that into your marketing strategy. It's helped me realize what the benefits of inbound marketing can be if you use it properly. "}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 17, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that I can see the contact record and company record side by side now. I work my entire day in this system and am able to do a lot with all of their integrations", "What do you dislike?": "they some how miraculously \"are not available for chat once I am writing a chat to them\" and you cant bulk enroll people into sequences you have to do it manually", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use this for our CRM as well as Marketing automation- saves us a lot of time!"}}
{"author": ["Dennis M"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Marketing Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["Jul 31, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of use and the intuitive interface are awesome. It allows you to accomplish core marketing tasks in an incredibly simple way.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes simplicity can be a downside as in when there is only one option to do something but it\u2019s not the option you need.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Executing content marketing strategy, blog cms, inbound lead generation, email marketing, running nurture campaigns"}}
{"author": ["User in Non-Profit Organization Management"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ease of setup and tracking, especially for email, as well as the ability to sort into folders. Easy access to support and articles which are well-written and helpful, along with generalized marketing advice from their content team through the blog.", "What do you dislike?": "Laborious process for formatting landing pages, interface can be wonky and strange at times. Hard to write to the designs, have to create multiple templates for everything. Can't switch between email type.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Check out the blog for some amazing marketing tips, in addition to general content about how to use. They have an amazing content team.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Helps to track metrics, create pages that don't need to be deleted and managed from our website or by a centralized web team, gives marketing control over how we are presenting ourselves and meeting goals."}}
{"author": ["Brett T. R"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Communications", "Higher Education"], "date": ["Jan 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is easy enough for those new to content marketing to use while offering enough features to allow for continued growth on the platform.", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the email templates can be buggy. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has improved our student recruiting capabilities by consolidating our emails into one CRM and giving us a channel to deliver content that is attractive and practical to our audience - making them more likely to enroll/apply for our program."}}
{"author": ["Joseph C"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Administrative Assistant", "Higher Education"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is phenomenal for marketing training, tracking of web traffic, and drip emails / data storage and collection for your clients / customers ", "What do you dislike?": "The web design integration platform they use is complex, bulky, inefficient, and not user friendly. I would much rather recommend designing your own site through Sqaurespace and linking it to Hubspot for data collection and traffic monitoring. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great for marketing and traffic analytics, not so great for web building and design. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing Analytics, target markets, ideal clients, etc. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Email, list generation/segmentation, and workflows are very user-friendly and easy to use. Lots of integrations with third-party apps.", "What do you dislike?": "Adapting lead categorization to your internal company structure can be difficult. Creating custom landing page templates is not very user-friendly.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "We had a terrible implementation partner, do your due diligence", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Gauging the interest level of a lead via specific interactions has allowed us a much more pinpointed approach to how we acquire targets for the sales team."}}
{"author": ["Elaine N"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 31, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Dynamic workflows and personas, campaign tracking and templates", "What do you dislike?": "HTML editor, HTML editor, HTML editor. It's a terrible interface and cumbersome. For such a sophisticated software, the crappy editor is a real pain.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The addition of a built in CRM is great and a step in the right direction for an integrated approach to generating leads and building a pipeline.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Mass email campaigns, segmented and targeted database marketing, A / B testing"}}
{"author": ["User in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I enjoy all the functionality that HubSpot can provide. From workflow automation, to form building, landing page creation, and more. It is a marketer's dream when pushing out content quickly, efficiently,, and effectively. It has enhanced our website traffic since starting under 12-months ago and great reports to track our results. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are some integrations that don't work with SalesForce currently, but we are hoping those integrations will be on HubSpot's roadmap soon. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The ability to automate is a huge problem solver when it comes to creating email campaigns and sending out mass email blasts. It is a huge time saver and allows our teams to be more effective throughout the day. "}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the easy to used dashboard display and how simple it is to set up emails. I like that email flows can be setup to make the email sends automated.", "What do you dislike?": "It is not integrated with some other softwares that we use (i.e. loyalty programs)", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot is great for basic email marketing and communication with customers. For my uses within my company, we were able to do what we needed. However, be aware that there are not many current integrations with Hubspot with other software you might have.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email contact was made easier because I could automate emails, and based on their actions that would trigger another email. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of use and the outlook add-on. The add-on has completely changed my life with the access to templates and the ability to share them and collaborate. ", "What do you dislike?": "That customer service is only available via chat or email for my subscription. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "A great tool at a reasonable price! I would suggest anyone who wants to increase marketing and or sales automation and efficiency check it out!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Template sharing and automating emails! Tracking analytics of emails!"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot's customer service is unmatched. Hubspot Academy is incredibly helpful and continues to help me even months after taking most of the courses. Their services are great, there is nothing bad to say.", "What do you dislike?": "I do not dislike anything about Hubspot. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I highly recommend taking the Hubspot Academy courses. They will help you with your Hubspot use, as well as with your day to day marketing/sales work.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot helps with social sharing, tracking emails, contact management, and everything to do with our website!"}}
{"author": ["Mark W"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We like we can easily see leads as they come in as well as the endless options to track and classify leads", "What do you dislike?": "As an office that does require HIPPA, we wish Hubspot was also an EHR that was HIPPA compliant \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Housing leads and all information about leads in one spot. The ability for us to upload forms to the person's profile is a huge benefit of keeping everything digital"}}
{"author": ["Dawn S"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing & Communications", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot makes it easy to track and market to prospects and integrates well with our CRM and other marketing tools ", "What do you dislike?": "Email templates and landing pages/ blogs are not easy to customize or edit so we've had to use other tools for more advanced design or CSS requirements", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing to and tracking interactions, leads and conversions. We can accurately track and report on marketing qualified leads and seamlessly pass leads to sales for follow up"}}
{"author": ["scott s"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["CTO"], "date": ["May 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Free to use most features you can pay to add on as needed ", "What do you dislike?": "have to clear cache to use phone dialer reliably ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is better than getting a free trial from other CRM's ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "has all of the functions of any CRM without the price"}}
{"author": ["Liz S"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Director Of Special Events", "Entertainment"], "date": ["Apr 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The CRM is so much more user friendly than competitors. I didn\u2019t even have to take a training class to become adept st working with the different features of V\u0169 spot. I took one webinar and played around with t for a bit and I was good to go! ", "What do you dislike?": "The added on costs which apply if usin. Many of the features.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely take a webinar or two. And play around with the different features. Also, if there\u2019s no integration built in already, try Zapier. It works well with gubspit! ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Streamlining myclients and sales funnel as well as integrating with email and SEO optimization apps."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Aria M"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Specialist", "Real Estate"], "date": ["Nov 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is user-friendly, attractive, and useful for different levels of expertise. Hubspot also has the ability to have multiple team members within one account. This is the most used feature for our company.", "What do you dislike?": "The reporting could be improved, other than that can't think of any con.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The marketing features are very easy to use and everything can be integrated. I honestly found it more user friendly than other softwares.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": " HubSpot CRM integrates other softwares like Gmail, and keeps communication seemless between staff and leads. I highly recommend it to small business owners."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "contact database with manually editable properties, automation workflows with different layers, tracking of paid social media campaigns, marketing analytics in every detail required", "What do you dislike?": "detail features need bigger \"audience\" to get implemented (e. g. delay for workflows), reporting can become complicated depending on where you start", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "complete the academy, which will give you plenty of insights into every detail of HubSpot", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "newsletter automation, lead qualification, automation of publications and brochures, marketing analysis, social media planning, publication and advertising"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 17, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "This application provides tools to measure the affluence of a website, measures each user who enters the site and creates a history of what they have seen and how they have interacted with the content of the site", "What do you dislike?": "Does not grant global statistics, only for a given user", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It is a tool that allows to measure and manage the contents of social networks associated with the company, and helps to track the strategies in terms of projects of the mThis application provides tools to measure the affluence of a website, measures each user who enters the site and creates a history of what they have seen and how they have interacted with the content of the site.\r"}}
{"author": ["Oussama H"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["May 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The automation on the sales and marketing ends have been super helpful to our business. It even comes with trainings and certifications so that you can learn how to strategize and use all the tools better", "What do you dislike?": "There's not much that I dislike about Hubspot. Their customer support and love chat have helped me with all my problems ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automating sales processes and aligning everything with marketing efforts while keeping full transparency on the performance of our business and accounts to our operations team"}}
{"author": ["User in Entertainment"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot makes it incredibly easy to schedule social media posts. It's very easy to create posts for multiple platforms, upload multimedia, and schedule times for each post. ", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot does not provide great analytics for social media. We have decided to use another service to receive analytics for individual posts. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use this to manage your social media/posts feed. It makes things incredibly easier. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Scheduling social media posts ahead of time. Benefits are not having to worry about posting live on Instagram, Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how HubSpot keeps me organized with all of my leads and sales. I really like the task reminders. I use the sticky pads less because of this great feature. The templates are also helpful. I am looking forward to my continued use of HubSpot, and I can't wait to see the future additional features!", "What do you dislike?": "There is nothing to dislike, this is really the best program I have used for sales. There is a lot of features but it's simple to use. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Knowing my leads are important. HubSpot is helping me to ensure all information is grabbed for my leads. The more information, the better. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I tracks everything in one place - email campaigns, customer and prospect website interactions as well as social posting and listening. ", "What do you dislike?": "It takes a quite a while to learn, because it is so comprehensive. The support is good, but you have to spend time to get the full benefits out of the system.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are creating and tracking all of our email campaigns to help us improve our marketing practices. We have also improved tracking and distribution of leads from our website and ad landing pages."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love HubSpot's ease of use. After experience with other Marketing Automation systems, HubSpot is the cleanest, easy-to-use system I've come across.", "What do you dislike?": "The system navigation has changed a bit since we first implemented, so it has been a little confusing trying to remember where everything is. Fortunately, a global search solves that issue pretty quickly.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Don't bite off more than you can chew. Understand what you think you might be able to accomplish with Marketing Automation, and select an appropriate account level. You can always scale up as your maturity level grows.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has dramatically improve our email deliverability and made contact management very simple for us."}}
{"author": ["Peter Y"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Advisor | New Media Technologies and News Development & Integration", "Information Services"], "date": ["Feb 22, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Here is a company that not only gives away information and help for free in many instances, but is very easy to talk with and interact with... they are simply the model for the future of customer outreach!", "What do you dislike?": "Actually nothing... well I always like when companies adjust their respective prices to match the size of the business... we are currently looking at our overall budget and will most likely join these folks in the next quarter... I think that they are a high-value relationship!", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "You will have access to a tonne of content... divide up the duties of sifting through this treasure trove and have round-robin sessions to discuss this material", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I needed to get employees trained/educated as well as look at current trends and wanted to read the tonnes of material that these folks produce... amazing material"}}
{"author": ["Sandy S"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Technology Integration Coordinator"], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the social media component the best. It allows me to make posts on different platforms at the same time and schedule them for different times.", "What do you dislike?": "The workflows can be overwhelming to create the first time.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Getting our message out for prospective families."}}
{"author": ["Josh M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager"], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's very clear and concise. Intuitive and easy to use. ", "What do you dislike?": "Very easy to mistakenly move deals around in the sales admin, potentially triggering all of our automation. Not necessarily an issue with the software more of a quality of life issue. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Shop around. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Helping "}}
{"author": ["User in Medical Devices"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 08, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the convenience of the platform. I can do all things for our clients in one easy-to-use portal. It gives me (and them) insights on what's working and what's not. ", "What do you dislike?": "Because I'm in the software constantly I run into bugs sometimes. Things not saving or reverting back to earlier versions. I wish the social part of the tool was a little more robust. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would recommend taking advantage of their certifications and free training. I've learned a lot using both of those. Also, if you get stuck, their help section is easy-to-use and usually provides an answer. If it doesn't support answers quickly. For planning and how-to's you can also lean on your assigned channel partner. Mine is very good at strategizing. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are an agency doing internet marketing for multiple senior living companies who have multiple communities. Hubspot allows us to manage start to finish marketing campaigns for them and social profiles for all of their communities in one platform. "}}
{"author": ["User in Writing and Editing"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 15, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the blog and email marketing tools. I think they're pretty simple once someone walks you through how to use them. ", "What do you dislike?": "I liked Hubspot a lot once I had been trained on how to use it. I don't think you can really use it to it full potential unless you read through all their user blogs, Google a few things and have your manager train you a bit on it if you are a first time Hubspot user. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Get an expert to walk you through all the cool functions that Hubspot has to offer. I don't think I really realized its full potential when I was working with it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We used it to manage our blog and CRM. Again I think if you are just using Hubspot for the basics its easy to navigate and you can get your stuff done relatively quickly. "}}
{"author": ["Sumant L"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Tech Blogger"], "date": ["May 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It has almost all marketing features and analytical functionalities to monitor lead campaigns and analyze growth substantially.", "What do you dislike?": "It has a few complexities which I think a beginner will not understand in the very beginning. If that is taken care of then this software is a masterpiece.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you want to use this software then learn all features one by one and then get going.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I liked it because it made easier for me to monitor all marketing activities at one place."}}
{"author": ["User in Management Consulting"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There are a couple of things that I like including the Marketing Dashboard which gives me an overview of all the work we are doing from a Marketing Automation perspective including email campaigns, the default SEO enabled settings for creating a blog and the seamless social media post scheduling feature for social posts.", "What do you dislike?": "The issues with uploading images when scheduling social posts for LinkedIn. Sometimes images don't display correctly and it's a task getting customer service to figure out the issue. Also, reporting can sometimes ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has helped improve the reporting efficiency of our marketing analytics with an integrated dashboard that displayed our email, landing pages, social posts and blog stats."}}
{"author": ["Sarah Lee E"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Educational Outreach and Marketing", "Environmental Services"], "date": ["Feb 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how easy it is to program my to do list, see my upcoming tasks and cross off completed work. It's a way to see everything that is coming up without combing my calendar.\r", "What do you dislike?": "I disliked that I already have a crm account with another company and hubspot just can't let it go.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It's very easy to stay organized and meet deadlines. Nothing gets past my hubspot task list."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that HubSpot is a marketing centric platform that contains enough features to help both our Sales and Marketing teams work together.", "What do you dislike?": "There are limits on file sizes for social posting that the social networks don't have, because of this I can't do all of my social posting through the HubSpot platform. The mobile app should also have social posting features so I can post directly from my mobile device, through the HubSpot app.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Coordinating both sales and marketing efforts in an Industrial B2B industry. We are much more organized and aligned in our sales and marketing efforts now."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I LOVE the ability to design custom email templates specific to my needs depending on the email campaign I am running at that time. With HubSpot, I am able to customize every detail of the email. ", "What do you dislike?": "I do wish that A/B testing was an available feature for the Marketing Starter package. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot to run large, multi-touch email campaigns as well as a reporting and analytics tool.\r"}}
{"author": ["Glen G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Human Resources Manager", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Mar 28, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Able to manage candidate database , store resumes, see when they revisit the web site.", "What do you dislike?": "Not a true applicant tracking or HRIS system, but we customized it, so missing some core features.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It can be used as a candidate database and communications tool if you do not have an ATS or HRIS in place.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Ability to manage applications and candidates quickly and in an organized fashion."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 08, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We can customize the fields that we track for our leads in HubSpot, allowing us to get the data we need to send email campaigns. ", "What do you dislike?": "It's hard to track the entire lifecycle of leads in a visual way", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows us to track a lot of information about our thousands of leads. It also makes it really easy to share information with the rest of the team. All of my emails are tracked so if I'm out of the office or unavailable, one of my team members can easily pick up the conversation. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot's workflow are my favorite feature. They allow us to automate some of our day to day activities that would otherwise be manual. It makes things a lot easier to do and gives us a lot more freedom to do things we previously couldn't do. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are some features that seem intuitive that HubSpot doesn't have. I do, however, like that we have the ability to submit feedback and feature requests. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Reporting, automation, logging,etc."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Based on the Inbound methodology, HubSpot gives you the guidance and the tools to be a powerful marketer and target your customer personas to create awareness around your product.", "What do you dislike?": "Because it is such a large platform, it's very difficult to become an expert at everything - though that's a decent problem to have...", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do your homework, but HubSpot is a great addition to your marketing and sales team.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're identifying our target personas and creating content to engage these prospects. This is giving us more authority in our industry and increasing our organic rankings through SEO best practices like creating a \"pillar page\"."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot's new update makes it so much easier to design/customize your own email. I use it to send out a monthly newsletter, and I can do all the design on my own now without any help from our company's HubSpot pro.", "What do you dislike?": "There are so many fields to fill out when sending out an email from HubSpot!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is the easiest platform I've used to send out regular employee newsletters. The tracking information (like open rates, etc.) is super helpful, too."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the statistics on HubSpot that keep track of calls, emails, and meetings. They motivate you to work harder and allow you to see your progress. ", "What do you dislike?": "An improvement that could be made on HubSpot is being able to see a list of contacts while on a Company's page, rather than scrolling through the activity feed to pinpoint who all have been contacted from that company. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Recommendations listed in what I dislike above. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am learning how to narrow down potential clients by how often they open emails, the response rate and click rate from a marketing email, and the ability to listen to recorded calls and take notes if I don't remember a conversation."}}
{"author": ["Jolene R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Owner", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Mar 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "They have a huge suite of automation tools to make life easier which I love", "What do you dislike?": "How much they charge to get access to those tools.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you're aware that you might not get everything you are hoping for. There are cheaper options out there.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email automation"}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Andrea W"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Pharmaceuticals"], "date": ["Nov 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that Hubspot has everything you need in order to fully maximize your inbound marketing strategy. ", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot reports are a little tough to understand because of their layout. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "One of the biggest benefits of Hubspot is that everything you need for successful inbound marketing is all within the platform. My company has really been able to better nail down our marketing strategy due to Hubspot campaigns, website integration, and social media posting. "}}
{"author": ["Chris N"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Chief Operating Officer", "Building Materials"], "date": ["Oct 31, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Having absolutely no code-writing skills, changing and tweaking content on our websites is so fast and easy.  Creating effective calls to action is simple and it has increased our sales leads exponentially.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Writing blogs is a cinch and nearly 1/3 of our web traffic is now generated by blog articles.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Shekar J"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Clinical Trials Systems Intern", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Jul 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The software has a lot of custom features to manage contact lists. The tracking feature is also amazing as all the conversations are recorded timely. Moreover, the dashboard is clean and intuitive", "What do you dislike?": "The free version has not been updated since a while now and also the paid version is a bit high priced. Nevertheless, the free version does a great job!", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Very much recommended for small to medium-sized organizations for managing and tracking contacts", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "This software is maintaining our contact list and also keeping a track of the records of each contact which is great for further communications."}}
{"author": ["Ife A"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Portfolio Manager", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Jun 02, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The app is intuitive and easy to use. Total training time for our staff took about an hour and half at a stretch. We have more than enough features to use. The ability to schedule calls via Uberconference directly from Hubspot makes things easy. Integrating the entire suite with the sales tools, marketing tools and crm makes for a wholesome experience. ", "What do you dislike?": "The price per user subscription is quite costly. In a situation where you have 18 plus sales staff it gets costly for startups. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's great to start with your business but a bit of a hassle to import data after building your database. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have been able to track our leads, sales pipeline and easily transfer leads with full conversation history and notes to different users. "}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 13, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the full array of features this platform allows. It has helped us save a ton of time at fill holes that we were currently trying to fill manually.", "What do you dislike?": "Unfortunately, because of the complexity of the platform, we had to hire someone to help us implement and integrate into our current marketing funnel.  I'm sure for the majority of users this wouldn't be the case.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you're planning on using this to fully integrate into an already developed marketing/sales funnel plan on spending a lot of time and possibly hiring an outside consultant to help integrate platforms.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation and ability to track prospects throughout the entire sales cycle.  We've been able to save a lot of time and resources by automating many parts of our process.   We also get a notification when prospects do certain tasks which allows us to reach out at the perfect time. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's easy to use and the customer service is great. ", "What do you dislike?": "We did see a high number of bounced emails and it was somehow related to HS but we were never able to get a straight answer. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are looking  to start automating or an easy to use application then this is the best option. Their customer service is great and it is an intuitive and easy to use platform. Reporting is very limited and some features were very basic - but we've switched to a different platform and I can say that HS was far better.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "All things marketing automation and email. \r"}}
{"author": ["Prabhjot S"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Manager"], "date": ["May 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We are using the HubSpot Sales account. Sales are going very good.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes some issues happened like, Last time PayPal integration was not working for 10-11 days and because of that we faced many problems.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are tracking page views and CTA clicks."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Internet"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 27, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot makes email automation fairly simple, even for inexperienced users. Building and segmenting lists is really easy, and creating and sending emails follows a logical, step-by-step process that checks your work along the way. Support is very responsive and knowledgeable, and has helped solve every problem that I've had with the tool within one business day. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some bulk actions are difficult in Hubspot - for instance, bulk deleting contacts and adding companies in bulk to a list (as opposed to contacts) are both pretty challenging to accomplish if you're trying to use an excel spreadsheet to manage data and merge that with a list in Hubspot. Also there are some pieces missing from some integrations that would be super helpful to include, but they work fine enough without being perfect. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Using Hubspot has allowed us to build an email automation program that we use for prospecting, lead generation, lead nurturing, retention, and customer engagement from the ground up. We also use sales pro features to save our team time with scheduling and email communication. "}}
{"author": ["Amanda F"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Sales and Marketing Coordinator", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Oct 27, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the fact that it has just about everything I need!  Like the title says - All In One Platform.", "What do you dislike?": "I do wish it would include for us where our website clicks are coming from.  If the visitor isn't in our database we don't really get much information on them other than the source they used to get there.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you spend some time going through the training tools and meeting with your Implementation Specialist.  I went into each meeting with our specialist with a good idea of every topic we covered because I already went through the training, watching videos, reading guides, trying it out, etc. before the meeting.  This allowed me to gather the right questions to ask in the meetings and made the transition really smooth. They offer SO MUCH in forms of training and I highly recommend putting aside the time to dive into it before really starting up.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have seen a pretty significant growth in our website traffic which was a problem we were really looking to solve.  The blogging tool has made it easier for us to write better quality content and we are already seeing the benefits from that.  We have been using the social media tools and love being able to post to all of our social media accounts from one spot. "}}
{"author": ["Katie C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Manager", "Education Management"], "date": ["Jul 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how intuitive Hubspot is to use - we are big on blog, email, automation, and social and I'm consistently impressed with how easy it is to learn about the tool and figure out how to utilize new features as we go.", "What do you dislike?": "We are connected to our Salesforce CRM and sometimes data is overwritten that needs to be fixed, based on IP addresses, which can be tricky at a school with a shared computer.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have become much more efficient in our content creation, and use this great tool to track and measure success of our efforts."}}
{"author": ["User in Media Production"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 25, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot offers a lot of guides and resources to get someone started. If I need help with something, I am 99% positive that there is an FAQ, a blog post, or something else on it. Very resourceful in general.", "What do you dislike?": "The hubspot lessons on inbound marketing and other hubspot lessons are very repetitive. I completed the inbound marketing certification and attempted another hubspot certification, but I felt like I was watching the same videos with little tweaks. Also, coding in hubspot is an awkward experience. Hubspot doesn't make it easy to understand where to go to find the right files or how to publish the HTML/CSS/etc codes on a blog. It is almost like Hubspot has it's own strange coding language. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot can be really useful for improving SEO and is also very resourceful, but it takes a while to get the groove of it if you plan to extensively use it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot makes it really easy to improve SEO. I've noticed that the ranking for our blog is generally higher than it is for our own product's website. "}}
{"author": ["Allison H"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Market Researcher", "Management Consulting"], "date": ["Oct 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The hubspot platform is very powerful and well built. It helps us organize our marketing strategy. I also love all the resources they provide to help creating a content strategy. ", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing so far. We are pretty immature users so I\u2019m sure there is a lot more we could do. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot is not easy to use without proper training but it is really beautifully built. The certification is a must. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing content strategy and workflows. "}}
{"author": ["Linda K"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager", "Events Services"], "date": ["Feb 01, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I always get help from the support team and the software itself is continuously being developed but still maintains to be easy to use. ", "What do you dislike?": "I'm finding it hard to think of anything I dislike about Hubspot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take a free trial and see the benefits yourself. The software is a big investment, but it is also the best marketing automation software out on the market. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has solved the problem of communication between sales and marketing. Through an integration our sales team can see all the marketing details of a specific lead and also all the leads generated by the marketing team. "}}
{"author": ["Glen M"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Executive Account Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Jul 13, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the integrated approach Hubspot has to sales, marketing, CRM, website, landing pages, email, social media, marketing and all related systems.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes responsiveness of system is a little slow. Changes in system sometimes lead to navigational challenges.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are interested in Inbound Sales and Marketing as a way to improve your business it is a great tool", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Markets are changing people have performed research before they buy and we needed a marketing and sales system that better addressed this new way of purchasing."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is well known by most people in the marketing world. Not only do they provide great resources for learning and earning certificates, but they have many programs that allow our team to handle social media and content management more easily. ", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't anything I've found to dislike about Hubspot yet. Overall a great platform, but I am fairly new to it. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take the time to get to know the platform and all that it offers. Hubspot offers many different services to date. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot allows our team to align on marketing topics by all collaborating from learning from their courses. However, it is also a helpful platform for social media management and content management. "}}
{"author": ["Christie P"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Account Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["May 11, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "All marketing features in one place. Lots of integrations. Robust email/landing page/CTA integration. Syncs well with SalesForce. Good information in Hubspot academy and resources for setting up account and keeping informed on inbound marketing.", "What do you dislike?": "Cost is too high for small businesses on the marketing platform. Some of the CRM integrations can add a significant cost to the monthly price as well. Social features are not as robust as I would like and can be difficult to do comprehensive reporting on. Facebook ads not yet integrated fully with Ads package.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email automation\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I especially like the new campaigns feature. It sums up performance at the campaign level. \r", "What do you dislike?": "The web site builder is very easy to use. Also landing pages and forms are easy to create.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Sometimes problems when creating new active lists (have to wait a few minutes after saving a new list and then you can use it)."}}
{"author": ["Jordyn A"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Associate"], "date": ["Oct 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that I can use it for scheduling emails, blogs, and all other content as well as organize contacts and create lists of them.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it could be a little confusing if you do not have \"super admin\" access to all of the tools.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Share results and numbers from all marketing tools."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Entertainment"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 22, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I use Hubspot to track emails to see if they have been opened. It is very useful to know that people open/read the email and then ignore it or to try and understand why they wait to reply. I also love the plugin - its great to see it on the side and not have to go to a website each time. I also like the app for similar reasons.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes when I click on an email it notifies me that I have someone opening it. I know it usually only happens with emails to multiple people but it can annoy me sometimes.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Wonderful service - definitely worth a try to see if it fits your needs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Making sure people receive my emails and trying to understand why they don't reply or why they wait when usually I have a call to action in my emails."}}
{"author": ["Daniel J"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager"], "date": ["Nov 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to create workflows is very powerful for marketing funnels", "What do you dislike?": "The frustration of posting across multiple platforms using one image", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Spend some time using the learning platform", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Its a good all in one platform"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the 2 days a month when it actually works. ", "What do you dislike?": "Every other day when it does not work. The emails sometimes take months to write because the website is so slow. Other times, the email tracker will never work. My favorite one is when other contacts information will accidentally get mixed up in another leads profile.  If your employer is willing to spend more money on a platform that actually works do that.  This program is such a headache.  P\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Gabriela M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Jr. Account Executive"], "date": ["May 27, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Very straight forward.  Easy to use and a responsive friendly support team.", "What do you dislike?": "Lot's of small bugs occur that prolong my work sometimes.  Usually, there's a quick resolve time but seems to happen quite often.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Customer pipeline management, chasing deals and closing them."}}
{"author": ["Ureeda A"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Executive Content Marketing"], "date": ["Aug 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Blogs and Guides\r", "What do you dislike?": "Sales deal boards\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing flow/funnel \r"}}
{"author": ["Michael S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Customer Success", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 14, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Comprehensive and robust. All sales and marketing in one place, as well as a great CRM to store our customer data.", "What do you dislike?": "Not much. There is a ton that it can do, so learning your way around can be a bit of a battle, but they have great resources and a super support team.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's a great, robust and fully featured system.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing analytics, tracking, lead tracking, sales and deal recording, and customer data (CRM)."}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 07, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I have used around 5 different CRM\u2019s and Hubspot comes on top in terms of quickness for high call environments and reliability. The extremely user friendly platform allows for infinite amounts of customization on top of an already very pleasing platform", "What do you dislike?": "The UI change is something I am not a fan off, it makes it harder to find information. The change cannot be reversed anymore, I wish the UI could be arranged by the admin to their preference.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Instead of having everything on different pages, I can have all my information on a prospect on one single page making information easier to spot and quicker to move onto the next prospects "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Rafaela C"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["Associate Founder and Mentor"], "date": ["Jan 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "A principal caracter\u00edstica que gosto no HubSpot \u00e9 a de ele buscar informa\u00e7\u00f5es sobre o lead ou a empresa automaticamente na internet e enriquecer os meus dados sem eu ter que fazer esse trabalho. Isso, unido com o visual f\u00e1cil de uso tornam ele um \u00f3timo software para manter os processos de vendas e Mkt funcionando", "What do you dislike?": "Faltam algumas funcionalidades adicionais na vers\u00e3o gratuita, como produtos, penso que isso deixaria muito mais f\u00e1cil a ades\u00e3o e depois compra do software.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Facilidade na opera\u00e7\u00e3o do dia a dia."}}
{"author": ["Steven K"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["CEO", "Consumer Electronics"], "date": ["Sep 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy and flexible.  Can have paid and free accounts", "What do you dislike?": "We moved to HubSpot because of their great customer support.   Then they took away the phone and chat support without warning.   Now, the only support is email, with a one day turn around, or spend $200 a month.    They did this without any notice.   We are using the paid service for a few seats, but with limited email response times for support, we are going back to something else.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Bring back the customer support.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead and prospect tracking.   Multiple users with access to information."}}
{"author": ["Marilyn M"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Product Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Feb 05, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We transitioned to HubSpot this year, and so far it is a very comprehensive solution that allows you to do things that, as a marketer, you thought were only possible in your dreams. Specifically: \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "1) workflow automation is out of this world. Create a workflow, set criteria to tell it who to pull in automatically, use if/then logic to determine what content they get and when, and - this next one was a biggie - dynamically shift them from one workflow to another when they take an action or no longer match all of the criteria.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is king in terms of ease of use. It's a breeze to sync your CRM with all of your marketing/automation efforts and keeping track of everything. Also a great platform for setting up landing pages quickly. My go-to recommendation for B2B marketers.", "What do you dislike?": "A few things are a little tricky to customize, but make sense once you have things up and running. For example, creating a custom email template can be a bit tricky at first.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automating interactions with our sales team, nurturing inbound leads, and sending marketing campaigns."}}
{"author": ["David K"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": ["Sales Marketing Consultant", "Broadcast Media"], "date": ["Jun 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The workflow when using Hubspot works great.  After learning the how to make the workflows, there were some slight issues, but all and all, a good product.  ", "What do you dislike?": "For the marketing portion, you can only have one photo when you post, which isn't feasible. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Increase the photos for marketing...I don't use it because of the limit which means I don't have the ability to track my social media through HUbSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Being able to keep up with what is going on with our website, who is visiting it and having the people that visit be directed to the correct person.  "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "My experience with using HubSpot for the last couple of years is that it is fairly intuitive, provides good metrics for email marketing campaigns and content management. It automates lead generation and pairs well into CRM platforms like Salesforce", "What do you dislike?": "Previous versions needed UI improvements, this has been rectified in recent updates.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "With Hubspot, we solve issues that impact the Marketing team, such as lead qualification and conversion and Web development. Its website building capabilities are strong and intuitive. "}}
{"author": ["Andrea C"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The features that the CRM has to offer to manage your agenda, meetings, leads, customers and prospects in just one tool that's organized and efficient.", "What do you dislike?": "Not all features are free. You might need to pay for the Marketing & Sales tools in order to complement your CRM.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "You might need to consider assigning an extra amount of money to pay for its other features. But it's totally worth it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The many excel files that you need to have in order to keep your contacts in order. In their CRM you can organize everything in one user-friendly tool"}}
{"author": ["Siva Kumar  S"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Animator"], "date": ["Jun 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Qualifying leads through live chat and Bots so that all leads are responded , and no leads are left unanswered.", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing like that as it provides to maintain and increase leads.It also involves in mail tracking and automation of the mails.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "To increase the  inbound marketing and also increase the sales and engage the customers through live chat", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Leads are generated and it also helps in the marketing automation ,meeting scheduling and also gives quick response through live chats"}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubpsot is generally easy and intuitive to use for marketing purposes. Product support specialists are extremely helpful at answering your questions and helping with glitches/bugs that you may occasionally encounter. Hubspot academy is AWESOME; a very smart model for the Hubspot team to attract and retain users.", "What do you dislike?": "The sales tool is \"meh.\" For sales, I would recommend Salesforce instead. Perhaps the sales features will improve in coming months.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot Marketing has been fantastic for running marketing email campaigns; it is very easy to build both static and smart lists of contacts, schedule and deploy emails, and track their performance. Moreover, built-in personalization tokens, document links, and more make personalization and deploying quality information a cinch. I also like Hubspot landing pages. "}}
{"author": ["Agency in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The Analytics are superb, I can see an overall of how social impacts new contacts or visits to the website. I can easily review lists of posts to see which ones have the most engagement, clicks, impressions, or comments. ", "What do you dislike?": "The scheduling platform would be awesome if they had an added approval workflow option such as comments on posts. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot is a great platform if you're looking for an all-in-one platform. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Having all the analytics in one place has been helpful in seeing what is effective and what is not. We are seeking to organize and collect contacts for the organization and ECLAT makes it easier and we can monitor progress better. "}}
{"author": ["Mukta A"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Head Marketing & e-Commerce", "Retail"], "date": ["Jul 13, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy drag and drop automation, needs time", "What do you dislike?": "The strategy support is average quality ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "A great tool at a great price for medium sized business. Be sure what you want from it before investing in and you will need a dedicated resource to implement it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Setting up ecommerce \r"}}
{"author": ["Alan R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Expert", "Market Research"], "date": ["Apr 21, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The complete integration and the need they have for you to learn to use their tool the right way. Their tools really help to know what things relate to what and what elements of your digital marketing campaign help to drive costumers. ", "What do you dislike?": "It cost a big amount of money and could improve in some integrations with the web design part; however, it's all good.  \r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It need some improvements in the Social Network part, but you can do with free external tools. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "If you have the money, don't think it twice is a must. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has a lot of positives. It's easy to customize webpages, blog posts, etc. The UI is easy to navigate.", "What do you dislike?": "The analytics dashboard can be a bit confusing. It can be challenging to navigate this to make sure you're looking at the most important data.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot makes updating our website and blog very simple. I like that it keeps versions of pages and blog posts so I can go back to alternate versions if necessary."}}
{"author": ["Executive Sponsor"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We love being able to handle our marketing and web design in one place, which makes it easy to keep in contact with clients and try new marketing strategies. ", "What do you dislike?": "Would love the ability to copy and paste modules in the design builder! I spend so much time creating the same modules over and over again. It would be easier to copy the format and swap out the text as needed. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing, keeping coworkers on the same page."}}
{"author": ["Queency B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development and Communications Analyst", "Financial Services"], "date": ["Feb 03, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "- Great customer service, They are friendly yet professional.\r", "What do you dislike?": "-  HubSpot is so user-friendly.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "- They have amazing certification programs that takes your marketing skills to the next level.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "- Incredibly useful tools such as social media publishing, tracking URLs, forms, content management with custom landing pages, emails, calls-to-action, campaigns, being able to track and convert leads, etc."}}
{"author": ["Vanessa B"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Social Media Management", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jul 11, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a really great way for a team to organize information on leads, business partners, options to explore. It's great for staying in touch throughout the course of a project and tracking goals.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish there was some way that I could get emails/text alerts about the most important things, but not everything that people are taking note of. Some of it doesn't apply to me.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're solving communication and planning problems, and we've realized it helps us set and work towards goals."}}
{"author": ["Tom P"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Owner, Chief Executive", "Internet"], "date": ["Jan 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the way it brings together the overall Inbound Marketing effort, into a single platform - that can be relied on, and is not buggy.", "What do you dislike?": "It's not cheap. But entirely worth it. The price may put some people off - however, I see it a solid investment - and we expect to get 5-20x the return back.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Swallow the high price and go for it. Although you will need to put work in to get it going too. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead generation and management. Landing page creation. Boosting website traffic. Email Marketing. \r"}}
{"author": ["Dustin H"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Project Manager"], "date": ["Dec 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is a very easy platform to customize . It allows me to set up tasks very easily to follow up on leads and maximize my time.", "What do you dislike?": "The only thing I dislike is that it takes a few clicks to get to the deals section.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are looking for some way to manage leads for free, hubspot is the way to go.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We we're solving deal tracking. The benefits of hubspot were that we are now able to track the leads through the software for follow up."}}
{"author": ["Erwanda L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Performance Marketing Specialist"], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The simplicity mechanism to design and create a landing page. Even we can download and use existing template and put the content directly.", "What do you dislike?": "No ability to create AMP landing page like Instapage", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is a very good marketing platform, but you need extra effort to build the website based on HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "1) Engaging the customers. It is better when we use HubSpot (Email Marketing and Workflow).\r"}}
{"author": ["Miriam A"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Property Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Organization of many tools in one place.", "What do you dislike?": "Pretty sharp learning curve in the beginning and to become advanced. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "- Email management & organization\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that I can use the same tool to plan and schedule my social media posts, and then go back and analyze their performance", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the reporting for each individual social channel isn\u2019t always up to date or 100% accurate. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We\u2019re scheduling social media far in advance which is great, but I wish analytics were a bit more accurate/up to date. I wish the social dashboard was a bit more organized as well.  "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot was always extremely responsive when it came to support. They would fix the issue within a few hours. The only problem with the support is that they do it for you without showing you how to change it, so you don\u2019t really learn how to use the platform more efficiently. It seems like Hubspot has some great features, but it\u2019s hard to access them without a deeper knowledge of computers and coding.", "What do you dislike?": "Working on Hubspot wasn\u2019t always smooth sailing. It\u2019s difficult to customize emails and landing pages without having intermediate HTML knowledge. Over time you learn work arounds, but as a marketer with no background in coding was frustrating. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is one of the leaders in CRM for a reason: it is simple to use and tracks the lifecycle of deals very well. It is simple to split out data into useful sets, tracking by seller, by company, by contact and by deal. The addition of customizable dashboard data helps to track trends in real-time as well. ", "What do you dislike?": "Would be helpful to add the ability to create an org chart or some other type of matrix to see contact shifts and track relationships with customers. In addition, a column-view organization (similar to PipeDrive) would be helpful to visualize deals in the pipeline. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "At any given time, I may have up to 100 proposals in various stages of business development. Keeping track of all of them at once through HubSpot is invaluable to organizing the deals and ensuring they go through. "}}
{"author": ["Amity R"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Owner", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Oct 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Tracking leads, creating workflows and automating emails and social posts all in one place makes my job as a marketer so much easier!", "What do you dislike?": "A few things that need working on are A/B testing functionality for translated pages, and we are currently unable to archive inactive workflows instead of deleting them.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We can translate our pages to help with SEO in other countries, which is a great benefit to our sales in the USA."}}
{"author": ["Emma  G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the fact that it is cloud based so I can log on anywhere. I think it is laid out in a simple and effective way that also looks engaging. \r", "What do you dislike?": "It is easy to log activities and edit if needs be. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The only thing I dislike is the fact that I have to login separately to my ATS system - it would be handy if it could smart feed through to the ATS as well. "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Gaurav G"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing"], "date": ["Oct 15, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We have been using this for automation, lead assignment & nurturing our lead and its the best tool available.", "What do you dislike?": "There isnt anything. We loved this platform.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead Management\r"}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It has a nice interface and is easy to navigate. Has lots of features. Includes product training and certifications. ", "What do you dislike?": "I find it to be a little confusing and hard to use. There is a lot of going back and forth between editing pages and templates. Every time I want to try something different, I seem to have to create a new template. I have an abundance of templates and assets, it's hard to keep track of everything. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "See if you can get a free trial first. It appears user-friendly and has a nice interface, but unless your a developer, designing with it is not easy.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Company website, email automation, contact lists, reporting."}}
{"author": ["Agency in Real Estate"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that hubspot covers a variety of needs. Between a CRM system, sales, learning resources and more - they have something for everyone. ", "What do you dislike?": "I think the downside is being overwhelmed, I feel like there might be a better way to organize everything. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I have great client relationships because I\u2019m able to efficiently (and consistently) stay on top of projects and communication. I love that I can stay relevant with articles and resources they offer. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 18, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Email marketing portion, particularly automation, is more user friendly and helps with visualizing the flow of the automation with the update.", "What do you dislike?": "Some of these are minor quibbles and might be more indicative of the field I work in. First, if you are a B2B company, this might not be the software for you. It's more for direct and consumer sales. It's lacking the ability for sales uplines as well as cross-team use. Second, results may vary with landing page creation and integration with your site. I felt it easier to build my own LPs using another service.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Third, list management is poor. You will get charged for adding customers to your overall database, and you have no choice in the matter, including those people who have chosen to opt out, dropped off, or who are duplicate accounts. So for example, our real database was about 40,000 people, but we were being charged for 120,000 due to a multitude of common marketing reasons (duplicates, dropoffs, etc.)."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to toggle between live landing pages and the backend Hubspot landing page editor with one click is a nice feature.", "What do you dislike?": "Everything else. Complex workflows are not possible (cannot reference fields with tokens in workflows). UI is terrible as long names of objects are clipped so you can't differentiate between 2 versions of the same thing. Support asks you to log your own feature requests instead of passing them on to the product team for you. There are many more issues.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "If you can afford it, buy Marketo."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer & Network Security"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 15, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that the CRM, Marketing Automation is user-friendly and keeps everything in one place. ", "What do you dislike?": "I don't like that the LP builder is so complicated, not user-friendly and requires a developer.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is still a work in progress, but it is great for marketing automation, and keeping everything in one place for ease of tracking and analysis. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to keep everything in one place for tracking, measuring and communicating"}}
{"author": ["User in Public Relations and Communications"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Intuitive product and really easy to use. From emails and workflow automations to list management and website development, Hubspot does it all and has helped our team take our digital marketing efforts to the next level. ", "What do you dislike?": "Wish the website analytics could drill down further and help.you uncovermore trends with the Google Analytics integration. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Increasing efficiency without having to add more team members. Hubspot helps us automate repetitive tasks and helps us focus on work that matters most instead of the day to day admin stuff "}}
{"author": ["Vladimir G"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["API Developer", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Jan 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has a very good user interface. It takes a lot of data and presents it in a way that is both easy to understand and efficient to navigate through.", "What do you dislike?": "There are a few things that could use improvement. For instance, the search feature can make it a bit hard to find what you're looking for at times. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot helps our team organize data and communicate better."}}
{"author": ["Agency in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 27, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I enjoy the marketing automation and drip campaigns you can do within their marketing hub program.", "What do you dislike?": "The email design manager is terrible. It is not the best for editing multiple emails at once and making major changes to many at once.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use a different email manager if you need to edit mass emails.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "CRM and contact organization, setup pipeline for sales, deal stages, setting up our client's marketing portal for email campaigns, and integrating their website with HubSpot analytics as well as managing Social media accounts."}}
{"author": ["Timothy B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "So much is included in HubSpot that you can easily customize based on whatever you want it do or show you for your business without getting overwhelmed", "What do you dislike?": "More advanced reporting customization can be a bit tricky if you don't really know your way around HubSpot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Strongly recommend HubSpot for Marketing side of your business. They have a lot to offer.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing analytics and blog SEO"}}
{"author": ["Eric F"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Media Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Feb 23, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that you can house social, email, blog and website all in one place. The functionality of Hubspot is amazing and so far this is the best system I have used. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that Hubspot puts extra code in emails. For instance, when I am uploading a logo it adds a code to shrink it so the image looks blurry. We have found ways around this, but it's a very annoying feature.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would go through the training if you can. Also go ahead and get certified! These will both help you navigate all of the features that Hubspot offers. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to house all of our marketing in one platform. It's great to track everything you are doing in one platform instead of pulling reports from a different platforms. If you want the really cool features, you are going to pay though.."}}
{"author": ["Samuel H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development Executive"], "date": ["May 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How everything can be managed from Hubspot, and how it compiles the information from all aspects of your online business.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it can be difficult to locate tools or features.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Manage our sales with tasks and lists has been extremely helpful."}}
{"author": ["Christa S"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Social Media Coordinator", "Non-Profit Organization Management"], "date": ["Aug 24, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is an easy to use platform which assists with social media scheduling as well as analytics which is a big help. I appreciate that I can schedule multiple messages at once across multiple social media platforms.", "What do you dislike?": "That once I save messages as drafts I can only edit one message at a time. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do it!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "They assist you with whatever you need and they also take feedback when you think something can be changed for a better user experience."}}
{"author": ["Stephen  S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The integration with my gmail. It allows me to easily follow up with clients while piping in and out of accounts. ", "What do you dislike?": "Have not figured out the best way to organize multiple contacts. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have used multiple software for our account management and it\u2019s nice to have it all in one place now.  "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "My very favorite aspect of HubSpot is the ability to management multiple social platforms seamlessly.", "What do you dislike?": "I would love to see HobSpot incorporate the use of automatic posting to Instagram Stories.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot is a great tool for all businesses to incorporate into their workflow. Highly recommend.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our team has been able to minimize the time spent on manually posting to social media. We love that it automatically shortened the URL links as well."}}
{"author": ["Liam B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Communications at ChangEd App", "Public Relations and Communications"], "date": ["Apr 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It really organizes and helps keep track of my emails. Makes everything efficient.", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing to really dislike. Has never given me trouble.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Do a lot of emailing and helps keep track of them all. Makes it efficient with the email templates as well. "}}
{"author": ["Charisse D"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Real Estate Agent"], "date": ["Apr 18, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I loved the mere fact that it gave me the capability of seeing who would open my emails.", "What do you dislike?": "I kept getting kicked out the system.  And they then changed their whole product.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure they let their customers know about changes.  I got kicked out so many times that I never returned, therefore that is the reason I might have not received any changes.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Making sure that my clients confirm that they have gotten the information that I sent them."}}
{"author": ["Andres M"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Web project strategist"], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The hub is a very easy to use platform. ", "What do you dislike?": "The design tool Limit developers in the use of codes", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure that Hubsot fulfills your webiste or business requirements", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Coding, website & lead generation"}}
{"author": ["Andrea M"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["National Co-chair", "Political Organization"], "date": ["Mar 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is super intuitive to use and very handy to integrate with my gmail.  I can leave settings checked to always log the contact, so it's foolproof for when I forget!", "What do you dislike?": "Getting templates set up with fields was a little difficult.  It was hard to tell why the system wasn't accepting my changes.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It's helping me with recurring notices and boilerplate initial emails."}}
{"author": ["Marc H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 23, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to control everything marketing-related is amazing. Whether you are interested in deep-diving through your marketing data and analytics, creating an entire website in the COS or doing all of your social media in one place, Hubspot has it all.", "What do you dislike?": "The portal and software can sometimes be a little glitchy, but with so many different things working at the same time, it's to be expected.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The company is fully committed to ensuring the software will work for you, from their excellent (this CANNOT be overstated) customer support to their experts who are willing to take the time to teach you everything you need to know about the product to make your campaign successful.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "What once took multiple programs and dozens of different people and skillsets now can be performed by one or only a handfull of people with the use of Hubspot's software. You no longer have to wait for development to help you create new landing pages or even site pages and you can more easily track the progress of your entire campaign to show real ROI for different aspects of your digital marketing."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 15, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The program is very organized and gives you the option to custom the set up. This makes it very easy to locate contacts and history info.", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the filters don't work the best. Is a problem when you working with over 2,000 contacts", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take the time to learn the tools there are to many options that are worth while that you might miss other wise.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Schedules meetings and fallow up. Helps up keep in touch with a large group without burying people."}}
{"author": ["Zachary B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Systems", "E-Learning"], "date": ["Mar 27, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Integrations with a lot of apps.\r", "What do you dislike?": "Fantastic customer service.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Extremely easy to use.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The service is growing very quickly. Sometimes features come out faster than tutorials can be produced."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I like best about Hubspot is the ability to allow teams to relay on less tools to get clear insights into how various strategies are performing.  Coupled with sales tools (also available with Hubspot), your handoff from marketing to sales is truly \"sales enablement\". I recommend anyone who has access to the tool to get certified.  Also, just getting certified in the basic course is essential to a modern marketer's success online.", "What do you dislike?": "The challenge I faced with Hubspot is that there are different naming conventions and different ways the data is recorded when compared to Google Analytics.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It was obvious that Hubspot enabled our team to see campaign activity in one centralized location, but what was less obvious was what our group could collaborate in one place; which also helped us speak a unified language."}}
{"author": ["User in Package/Freight Delivery"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 13, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot allows for the best insight into marketing activities by providing comprehensive analytics that tie back to the campaign level. It makes it easy to compare how different landing pages and emails are performing within campaigns. ", "What do you dislike?": "Landing page customization is not as intuitive as i had anticipated. You need to pick a very simple template for landing pages when doing the skinning process because you can not customize easily and changes need to be made in the template. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you create simple landing pages when going through the skinning process. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We decided that we needed more analytics and insight that we are looking for to see which of our marketing tactics are paying off. We did not feel like we were getting all we needed to out of Pardot, and they had a limited amount of forms and Hubspot didnt. "}}
{"author": ["Sudhanshu S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Head Of Business Development"], "date": ["Nov 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The sales application has helped work on the go. You can access everything on the phone. Make calls through the application write up follow up text etc.", "What do you dislike?": "Still need a little work on the dashboard on the application.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot sales has helped me keep a track on my sales interns."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Massimo F"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Content Management Specialist"], "date": ["Jul 31, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I find HubSpot to be extremely user friendly. Everything is where it should be and I very rarely have issues finding what I need on the platform. HubSpot is generally very fast at performing tasks.", "What do you dislike?": "It lacks some customization options and it may be a little redundant at times. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Setting up website pages, landing pages, blog posts, social posts is a breeze (most of the times). This makes me save a lot of precious time."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 31, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is my go-to and I use it for pretty much everything. Everything is in one place and easily tracked. ", "What do you dislike?": "There a few simple things that HubSpot can't do at the moment. However, the forum is great for suggestions and ideas. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm still learning new things with HubSpot. This is the first CRM I've used and I love how accessible everything is. It's the first thing I log into every morning. "}}
{"author": ["Michelle S"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Content Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 21, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Everything is organized pretty logically in the system, and the support resources are very extensive.", "What do you dislike?": "There's a slightly difficult learning curve for a new user. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Spend a lot of time up front to make sure the system is set up the right way.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We were trying to set up a platform for marketing automation, and it enables us to do so. We also use it to host our blog. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Love the integration between campaigns and sequences to help monitor activity between us and our database. ", "What do you dislike?": "Not intuitive without training on the system. Can be cumbersome for some sales individuals to learn and get the hang of utilizing all the tools available. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Able to track much more conversation between sales and database, as well as the actual interaction from a lead with the communication sent out to them. Helps gauge what messaging is successful and the interest level. "}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 10, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Certain features are spot on. If you don't have the time or are just getting started you can drop and email capture form on your site in no time.", "What do you dislike?": "Feels like you are just drowning in tabs and sub menus. I do not find it easy to do anything and I can't commit to the dozens of hours that would be required to become even remotely comfortable. I feel like using 3 purpose built tools that are all simple and do their job well is a better approach.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Trying to use it for lead-gen but haven't gotten much past a basic blog and email capture."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "They are pretty simple to set up making it easy to do things quickly and clone workflows that we use regularly. We automated tasks that would once take us hours to do manually.", "What do you dislike?": "How long the contact lists takes to load when you are reviewing a workflow before turning it on. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am solving segmentation issues with HubSpot by having a clear view of all the interactions our customers take online. "}}
{"author": ["Stacey C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love using workflows to automate mundane tasks. It helps us streamline our business operations and makes us much savvier sales professionals.", "What do you dislike?": "The functionality around Deals and Deal Properties are pretty limited compared to Contacts and Contact Properties, which has held us back from using the software to its full potential in the past.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helps us stay organized, streamlines operations and makes them more efficient, and allows us to track our data. We also use Zapier, which is compatible with Hubspot, to multiply the benefits and connect with all of the other software we use."}}
{"author": ["Brad B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator"], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How so many things are integrated under one platform - web pages, e-mail marketing, SEO/analytics, contact/lead management", "What do you dislike?": "The SEO/web site analytics facet could offer more insights into competitor web sites", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Creating workflows for generating leads and handling them."}}
{"author": ["User in Hospital & Health Care"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has many capabilities that make a marketers life easy! Integrating landing pages, emails, lists, forms etc. the list goes on and on. The customer service is also incredible. Whenever I have a question, no matter how small, the team takes the time to walk me through everything needed to make sure I understand how to accomplish what I am trying to do.", "What do you dislike?": "There is room for improvement with some integrated apps", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Clear, concise data while also being able to build pages and emails"}}
{"author": ["Elizabeth L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Assistant", "Computer Networking"], "date": ["Sep 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I liked that throughout the whole course there were tasks for each section based upon what we had just learned to try it out ourselves.", "What do you dislike?": "I disliked the quizzes. As I am paying attention throughout the course, I did not listen to exact details and was not successful during those. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are now completely implementing HubSpot and it has helped us create Marketing emails, social media posts, and monitor all of our reports. "}}
{"author": ["Rachel O"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing and Communications", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to click through a lead and easily see their entire path and source.", "What do you dislike?": "List/field management can be a bit tricky.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "With HubSpot, we\u2019ve easily set up automated funnels based on actions. This has freed up a ton of time, and resulted in an increase in leads."}}
{"author": ["Rachel R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Lead Marketing Coordinator", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that I can customize all properties and the view of these fields on the contact record. ", "What do you dislike?": "The expense of the upgraded Marketing package is a bit out of a small business range.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Communication between marketing and sales. Since implementing Hubspot, we've been able to have anyone log in and see exactly where a prospect is in the sales cycle and who touched base with them last. This is an invaluable tool for us to improve the client/prospect experience."}}
{"author": ["Rahul P"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Sr. BDE"], "date": ["Nov 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We utilise the Hubspot tool majorly for our marketing team's efforts and productivity-boosting. We utilise the tool for automating our marketing processes which resulted very beneficial for us as a team and we have seen factual growth since the implementation", "What do you dislike?": "Comparing to other tools in the similar set, there is nothing wrong here with Hubspot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Very Effective tool for New-Age Businesses", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing Automation, Prospect Database, Marketing Campaigns, Customer Persona significance."}}
{"author": ["Todd W"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["CMO"], "date": ["Aug 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Great functional coverage and intuitive design.  Simple licensing model.", "What do you dislike?": "No challenges to date - am still evaluating reporting and integration capabilities.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot has allowed us to evolve our prospect and customer targeting journeys and lead management."}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 16, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot understands the challenges faced by marketers and has created a tool that not only allows for easy execution and management of campaigns, but also has the analytics chops to review your efforts and help you make sound business decisions. The scalability of the tool is great for all size businesses. I would recommend HubSpot to anyone looking to emplify their marketing efforts.", "What do you dislike?": "For the most part HubSpot integrates into the majority of CRMs, but like any tool, implementation can take some work. It's WELL WORTH the effort of getting HubSpot set up.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allowed our team to seamlessly schedule and execute campaigns in a variety of channels without causing chaos or redundancy. We utilize the analytics on a daily, weekly, monthly basis to help drive our marketing decisions and their education/training keeps us up to date with the best marketing tactics and their evolving tools."}}
{"author": ["Donald R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Business Development"], "date": ["Aug 06, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to capture leads and place them in target workflows for conversion. ", "What do you dislike?": "No wrap around text in email editor.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 07, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I enjoy the landing page and email analytics. I feel like I can better decisions for future landing pages and emails based on these analytics.", "What do you dislike?": "It's not a major issue but uploading a file for social media is slightly cumbersome. It's still easy, just not as easy as everything else with HubSpot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Workflows can get tricky to think out but are worth it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have become more streamlined while also becoming more transparent. The benefit is, everyone is held accountable and is more organized."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 30, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot provides the great CRM for a free verison. This was finally the first CRM I was able to use and add multiple users. Other CRMs did not allow this feature for their free version. Since I work in a small company this helped alleviate costs while still being able to get the job done. ", "What do you dislike?": "Integrating my current from excel to this software was a bit time consuming. I had to edit alot to be able to get it integrated. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It organizes sales leads and to keep track of them. It also had a feature for sales employees to call leads from the software to keep a better record. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is very straightforward to use. If you're not skilled in automation, it is simple to grab a hold of. It's very easy to launch workflows and build out emails within HubSpot. Their support team is also great. ", "What do you dislike?": "HubSpot is nothing like Oracle's Eloqua. If you're expecting to build out robust workflows, most of the time you'll have to enroll contacts into other workflows as it lacks advanced automation features. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot for our client on-boarding and application processes. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It was very simple to integrate the widget on my website, I just had to add an html snippet to my website. I like the dashboard where I can manage all the conversations.", "What do you dislike?": "Not much, It does what it is supposed to do. Maybe they could send me an email notification if I get a new chat message.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Giving website visitors the opportunity to quickly ask a question about my products."}}
{"author": ["User in Retail"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 22, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We love that we can integrate most of our online assets, channels and automation in one place. In marketing, we use heavily use Hubspot for email automation, social media and blog publishing, and most importantly landing pages/COS and campaign management. We'll check in daily when we close a sale in-store to see where that individual came from and what series of interactions lead to the final conversion - and that's invaluable information that drives our marketing decisions. All thanks to Hubspot.", "What do you dislike?": "The cost of add-ons can add up for a small business, but they're worth it if you know how to truly optimize the tool for your goals/industry. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take the time to complete the academy courses so you can truly understand how to use (and sometimes hack) the tools.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As a brick and mortar retailer, we use Hubspot and inbound methodology to generate awareness and interest in our products across the web and ultimatlye drive foot traffic to our store. Since our conversion funnel usually takes several visits before a person makes a purchase, we also use nurture campaigns to keep them coming back."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Food & Beverages"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 08, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is turning into a heavy-lifting software [like Marketo, Eloqua, etc.], while staying quite agile. I've used Salesforce Pardot before as well. Hubspot is big, and has a LOT of functionality, but it's easy to maneuver and has amazing support. Need to add a field? You can do it on the fly. Having trouble with emails not working how they should? Contact support and they'll help you. Unsure best practices for something? They have unending resources. \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Being in a digital marketing role, this software really is built to help with a content/inbound strategy. "}}
{"author": ["Juana L"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 25, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Que la herramienta te permita tener un hist\u00f3rico de todo lo que ha pasado con un usuario por lo que permite hacer seguimiento mas efectivo. ", "What do you dislike?": "tener que actualizar la pagina para verificar que ha actualizado el contact result por ejemplo", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "La gesti\u00f3n de mis clientes, hacer seguimiento cercano de todo el proceso."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Construction"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 29, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I like most about Hubspot is that they are constantly looking to make it better. They believe in not only having a great product but also educating those that use their product to learn and grow. ", "What do you dislike?": "It seems like sometimes I get lost in the vastness of the program. With so many moving parts it can be easy feeling a little overwhelmed with how the pieces connect and function. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are turning our website traffic into leads that more often than not turn into sales. I have a hard time understanding how business don't use hubspot or something like it to keep everything organized and analyzed. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is user friendly on the backside. It's very easy to post blogs and all.", "What do you dislike?": "It's hard to change the design on the front. You have to be really good at coding and have the time to watch all the tutorials.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are a news service, do not use HubSpot. It's costly and hard to use.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is beneficial to view who is coming to the website and getting information about them."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Nicole S"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Entertainment"], "date": ["Oct 13, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love being able to organize everything, from emails to campaigns to social. ", "What do you dislike?": "Managing social in Hubspot is not great. Hootsuite is a better social tool. I do not like the interface of their social. I also hate using it on mobile, Hubspot needs to be able to be mobile friendly. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot is awesome! It organizes everything so incredibly well. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easier to manage campaigns, ability to manage almost all aspects of your business "}}
{"author": ["Robert W"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Lawyer"], "date": ["Oct 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The best thing about HubSpot are the real-time marketing analytics that the platform tracks. You can alter your marketing campaigns based on this data which is very helpful for increasing effectiveness.", "What do you dislike?": "The platform can be expensive, and the workflows can feel limited as workflows are always based off of \"Yes or No\" propositions.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Utilize the abundant resources for troubleshooting issues available on the hubspot website.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation and client development."}}
{"author": ["Consultant"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It helps me keep track of my clients involvement and I can really appreciate  all the tutorials and extra tools to help me further into great and stay connected with the newest technologies and techniques .", "What do you dislike?": "A lot of the information comes off is it supposed to be easy to learn and I believe that unless you do these tasks on a regular basis they aren\u2019t as easy as marketed", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": " Connect more with your customers and find out exactly what is wrong and what can be fixed as if they were going to truly use forever.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "A lot of the information comes off is it supposed to be easy to learn and I believe that unless you do these tasks on a regular basis they aren\u2019t as easy as marketed"}}
{"author": ["Romy R"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Director", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Dec 15, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Simple and elegant, HubSpot allows our team to automate emails, manage our social media, PPC, and reporting, all from one platform.", "What do you dislike?": "Migrating all of our forms from Marketo has been challenging to do on our own. Would have liked to have HubSpot dedicated support to help with that.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation at scale\r"}}
{"author": ["Alex M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Church Engagement Lead", "Philanthropy"], "date": ["Dec 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot provides us an awesome email marketing experience. We're able to collaborate, schedule through work flows that are followed by our sales team. ", "What do you dislike?": "Email collaboration can be difficult, as only one person can make changes at a time. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot for all email marketing and sales follow up. It has allowed us to unify our sales and marketing teams, setting communication expectations and consistent follow through. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 18, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot makes it easy to manage all parts of marketing automation in one place, from the blog to forms to email campaigns to social media.", "What do you dislike?": "They appear to no longer be including Facebook in the social posting section, which isn't ideal but I would imagine has more to do with Facebook than anything else.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has helped us better track and understand our customers, better optimize our SEO efforts, more easily create and post blogs (our previous blog was hosted on WordPress), and be able to provide our leads with a customized experience."}}
{"author": ["Arri B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Facebook Growth Hacker", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how you can track all of your contact's activity inside your CRM.", "What do you dislike?": "They charge quite a lot for contacts so if you have an e-com business, it's probably won't be suitable for you.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure you are fully aware of the potential number of contacts you'll be getting because it can get expensive really fast.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm solving my content marketing needs through the Hubspot platform."}}
{"author": ["Kate K"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development Strategist", "Hospital & Health Care"], "date": ["Jan 23, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of use and functionality are my favorite parts about hubspot. I love that it optimized my blogs and offers a checklist throughout the process", "What do you dislike?": "On Safari I occasionally have issues with social posting, but Chrome seems to work perfectly. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is an amazing platform. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have optimized our blog content, utilized A/B testing for different landing pages and increased traffic to our site."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that you can customize the experience for my clients and the emails look professional. I like how you can put in graphics and other neat things into emails to make them look very presentable. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the HTML email formats are not easy to manipulate for my liking, for example moving some of the blocks in the already made templates messes up the whole email and at that point it becomes difficult to do anything about it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I've been able to reach my clients with good looking emails and create great marketing material that then entices my clients to reach out to us more and close more business. "}}
{"author": ["Ahmed K"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Business Development"], "date": ["Jan 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how it manages contacts and it can also track the progress of the interactions.\r", "What do you dislike?": "It makes tracking much visual and easier. By clicking on a contact, you can see the emails and whether it was opened or not. You can see stats of your emails and communication.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I like their academy and materials and training they have online.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Not sure how to remove an email I sent from my activity feed."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The biggest upside is that you can schedule posts for Instagram. There aren't too many tools that allow you to do that.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish there was a way to posts multiple photos in an instagram post, but other than that I really like hubspot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are looking for a tool that will help you schedule and monitor your social media and email marketing, Hubspot is a great tool to use. I would recommend this tool for any company looking for a one-stop-shop for their digital marketing needs/tools.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're solving problems about monitoring our name online, scheduling posts to coincide with our campaigns and engaging with our followers."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Building Materials"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 29, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Great analytics and landing page and e-mail templates that are easily customizable. A lot of their tools are very intuitive and I like how you can see all the different parts of a campaign and how they are performing in one spot. They also easily integrate within your website and even have tools for creating tracking urls for Google Analytics and Adwords.", "What do you dislike?": "The workflows and lists can get confusing over time, especially if you are jumping onto an existing account.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Talk to their customer service team and do a demo.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Engaging with our subscribers through automated e-mail workflows and capturing new leads with offer landing pages."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The CRM compiles all contacts and connections on its own. ", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot doesn't recognize duplicates and doesn't allow you to copy a deal and edit some information. You must create all deals ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Its a great product but like all technology it has its defects. Its nothing that should take away from the productivity of the software. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "IT allows our company to keep track of the connections we've made. We utilize the notes most as everyone plays a role in marketing and communication "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "breakdown of dashboards, easiness to write blog posts, visual-ness of it", "What do you dislike?": "It would be great to have the ability to tag individual people on Linkedin (not sure if this is a privacy issue), to be able to enable twitter cards from the blog, and to have some kind of marketing expert/guide to help you use the app as with Hootsuite/Facebook. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm working on content marketing, so trying to drive traffic through blog and social. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Social scheduling planner. Helps me to have a field of vision that is months out. ", "What do you dislike?": "When I need help, it's nearly impossible to get someone to answer me. And when they do, it feels like they dodge my question and try their best to not understand what I need assistance with. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Support is lacking. I've seen a lot of benefits when it comes to insights and understanding how my customer engages with my material. "}}
{"author": ["Chris K"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Strategist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jul 19, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how I can access all the tools I need for marketing automation all from within the unified Hubspot platform.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot is an awesome tool and they are continuously updating the product. Sometimes some tools will be moved around without my knowledge, and I need spend some time to refamiliarize myself.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot training is excellent. Watch their videos, read their blogs, work through their projects. Call their support if you still have questions.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The Hubspot platform provides us with a single, unified platform to conduct all of our online marketing activities, and integrated reports to demonstrate results. As a partner agency, Hubspot has also provided us with the training necessary to provide inbound marketing as a service to our clients."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We use Hubspot for everything. I appreciate that anything from Sales to Social media is managed in the platform.", "What do you dislike?": "In the past with website redesigns we have had difficulty with making minor changes that totally end of messing up the whole website. It isn't an issue with global editing features, but with some bugs in the system. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can easily access key metrics that fuel our companies lead generation and revenue growth. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Cloud based marketing software. HubSpot is easy to learn and use. It's more affordable than other software. The support is really good. They help and get back to me fast. 24/7 support is amazing. The free trail offer is nice but I dont think 7 days is long enough. Normally trials are 30 days.", "What do you dislike?": "It requires a 12-month contract thats billed annually. Id rather have a month to month plan and be able to cancel or skip months. It seems to be costing more and I dont understand the prices. I should have gone back to check prices and comparisons. ITs just really expensive overall.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "All the data is really useful and helps a lot but you have to be really tech savvy and put the time into learning."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really enjoy using the work flow feature. This feature allows me to automate emails for every campaign. I have created a campaign for every holiday and annual event. The work flow feature allows me to plan extremely far ahead. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish there was an easier way to separate contact information. We have 13 branches and each branch would like certain privacy associated with the contact information that they recieve. This is something that I would like to see implemented in the future.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "N/A"}}
{"author": ["Raymond John I"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["SDR", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Like about this application it makes sending of email fast and manage proper arrangement of sequences and has a statistic of email status", "What do you dislike?": "sometimes no advice regarding updating of platform, other than that no problem encounter ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Cool to used", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "it notify me if the email is globally bounce, Helps me to manage email. "}}
{"author": ["Dave B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Coordinator", "Education Management"], "date": ["Dec 29, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is easy to use and has seemingly endless possibilities. I can create workflows and customer lists that, once activated, populate themselves and are executed behind the scenes. It takes some front end work, but once the plan is set and you have all of the steps in order it takes care of itself.", "What do you dislike?": "They change things... a lot. It's good that they are always updating the site, but right as I get used to doing things one way they come out with a new layout or look and throw me off. However, there is always the option to revert to the old look for a while, but in those few seconds before you realize there is a change, you're lost. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would definitely recommend trying this software. At first, the price tag may seem a bit high, but the ROI is definitely worth it, not to mention the time you will save.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use this software for basically every aspect of our digital marketing. It schedules social media posts, hosts our blog, creates and hosts landing pages, hosts content, tracks customer life cycles, automates emails, etc. I'm sure I'm forgetting something. There's just so much that we use it for, and our online presence has never been stronger."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I've long wanted to use HubSpot and finally landed at a company already using it. It is everything I dreamed it would be, and more!", "What do you dislike?": "The difficult learning curve for me because our backend is completely messed up by a previous user. Once we fix it (in the works) I will shine.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Learning the details of email deliveries; bad addresses vs. quality ones. The benefit is cleaning up our list so only the valuable contacts remain."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The idea of Hubspot itself is so great:) These apps just limit the unwanted manpower and I can feel the improvement through less complexity. Life was meant to be simple:D", "What do you dislike?": "The only reason I gave a 9 for recommendation is that it force logs out often and yeah, it creates some bumps you know.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "This is legit, a stone made of butter maybe. So smooth to handle but the most trustworthy:)", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use it for scaling ourselves and to be frank we kinda totally depend on Hubspot for our customer relationships and it has never gone wrong:)"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 19, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like having so many marketing tools in one system.", "What do you dislike?": "Because Hubspot tries to be all things to all people, none of its tools are as easy or powerful as tools made by companies that specialize.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Once you build your site on it, you're practically married to it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Template builder is terrible. Reports are inaccurate. Cost is high. But it's the industry standard and lets me manage almost everything in one place."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 01, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Full integration, ease of use, variety of capabilities - HubSpot has been such a useful platform for our clients who need to move to a new website, revamp their social media, increase email marketing, etc. It's such a useful tool and encompasses the needs for well-rounded marketing. ", "What do you dislike?": "Steady change of platform template - Although it's nice to see HubSpot is putting effort into keeping their software as up to date as possible for users, the template gets changed quite often and it can delay usage because the roll out tends to slow work down slightly. That being said, they are very responsive to whether or not users are pleased with the changes. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Full marketing integration - most of the time we are fully moving a customer to HubSpot, website and all marketing activity. This helps us create consistency across all marketing - social, email, content, etc. \r"}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is easy to use and create templates, and provides avenues to create custom designed websites and applications, through an excellent api. Also has excellent workflow and automation abilities", "What do you dislike?": "It takes some a while to learn all the features and pricing structures", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Able to automate many different workflows due to an open API, and build modules for to make it easy for clients to edit and update their website, "}}
{"author": ["Anna H"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Marketing and Community Success"], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love being able to schedule posts for certain times and that HubSpot suggests good times to post. I also really like that you can monitor Twitter mentions and conversations from the platform.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that I cannot upload videos or multiple images to Instagram through HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can monitor follower growth and I can see the exact amount of followers whereas on Instagram it is to the nearest 100"}}
{"author": ["Riadul H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Full Stack Web Developer Associate "], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like HubSpot\u2019s vast array of resources for building great products/pages. From API to design tools I love how flexible HubSpot is and how deep you can get into perfecting your page.", "What do you dislike?": "There aren\u2019t much that I dislike about HubSpot but the top navigation can be confusing from time to time.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We built both simple and complex landing pages with email workflow to drive the leads to our customer journey."}}
{"author": ["Jorge P"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Owner", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Jan 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has all the features for my marketing, from forecast to goals tracking and much more. This is one of the best inbound marketing tools I have ever used. ", "What do you dislike?": "so far I can't find any issues with Hubspot, it just works.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you need to track your  marketing, this is the solution !", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can keep track of all marketing channels, deals, goals etc.                                         "}}
{"author": ["User in Medical Practice"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The queues make it easy to go from task to task and make sure nothing is missed. You can also have separate queues to keep tasks organized. ", "What do you dislike?": "I do not like the new Beta View. I feel like it slows me down and everything looks cluttered. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot helps make sure that leads are being contacted in a timely manner. With the integrations, I have all the tools I need in 1 place. Texting, email, and task lists. "}}
{"author": ["Adnane L"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Executive", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Feb 13, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "- The endless marketing automation possibilities as well as the smooth user experience.\r", "What do you dislike?": "- User-friendly with the possibility of managing almost every single inbound action", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "If there will be one thing to improve in HubSpot, is the software crashes sometimes due to the coding part."}}
{"author": ["James W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Web Developer and Content Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["Jan 24, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot offers a broad suite of powerful automation tools inside a simple WYSIWYG editor that can be used by even non-technical team members. ", "What do you dislike?": "To make use of all of Hubspot's features, you need to lock yourself into hosting content inside Hubspot's platform. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Prepare to spend a good amount of time studying the capabilities and workflow through the Hubspot academy videos and documentation. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We wanted a way to track visitors to our site through the various stages of sales conversion. For the most part, Hubspot delivers the data we need to convert more visitors to clients. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 04, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has such a wide range of tool for you to use to make marking your business a breeze. I also long the classes they have available to hell further your knowledge and abilities.", "What do you dislike?": "I have yet to find anything withing HubSpot that I dislike. It is great for all levels and has something for everyone.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am solving the problem with my lack of knowledge in the area and my experience. I am learning new skills everyday that had helped my business excel."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Very complete platform, flexible to the company's needs.", "What do you dislike?": "The set up is a bit complicated and can get confusing when trying to create fields and ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It does everything we need in terms of basic Sales & Marketing CRM. The more fancy marketing modules are quite costly but I believe the ROI would be worth it - it just wasn't right for us at the time. The sales module is actually free, so that's a great way to start using the tool and ensure it meets all your needs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Sales and marketing CRM."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is not only have the instruction for the users to explore the functions of within this tool, but also give the users the instruction how to create ot design a sale or marketing process.", "What do you dislike?": "Many functions are locked because of free (which is very understandable though) , but it somehow makes the startups company will search the other tool to replace hubspot.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Good for the first level marketer to learn and use.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot can link you ad account and help you insert pixel to track how your ads works, it can help the advertisers to know what content is more effective to attract the customers,and then we can go on the right track after."}}
{"author": ["Lisa M.  D"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Manager, Event Marketing", "Construction"], "date": ["Apr 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the Integration with GoToWebinar.", "What do you dislike?": "Inability to change templated items quickly", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are currently using any of the programs that integrate with HubSpot, I would say that is the biggest advantage. We were able to immediately see who had signed up for a webinar but was unable to attend, and then turn around to send an \"In case you missed it\" email for another upcoming session. The fact that I don't have to go into our webinar program, then download a list, format the list and then re-upload the list into our marketing automation software is a game changer. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We recently started using HubSpot over a different marketing automation software and are seeing immediate improvement in deliverability and integration with GoToWebinar. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 12, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has many features so many that is even hard to know them all, is a very easy to use platform, intuitive and handy. ", "What do you dislike?": "you still have to plan a great content strategy to get results from this tool, support for other languages is not available and is expensive, once you start working with this tool is hard to stop doing it because you mount all your marketing on their platform.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Please consider that as you grow your contacts data base the software will cost more, and since you upload everything to their platform is hard to quit.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation, nurturing campaigns, database management"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how hubspot helps us keep track of all of our leads. ", "What do you dislike?": "At first it was hard to navigate but it has gotten easier with time. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I recommend having someone customize your CRM so it functions correctly. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are solving the issue of keeping track of all of our leads and automating a lot of the follow up. We are realizing the benefits of the automated follow up campaigns. "}}
{"author": ["Joshua A"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Mr"], "date": ["Apr 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The fact that hubspot make my communication between me and my marketers ", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing really but more advancement sould be carryed out as time goes on", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The companies should keep doing the best", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Communication problem between me and my marketers"}}
{"author": ["Ashley E"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["Founder", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 23, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I enjoy the email tracking capability. It updates me everytime an email is opened, which is great for my sales strategy. I also enjoy the way I'm able to manage my team.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike the heavy price tag, but once I expand this won't be so bad. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot is great for educational purposes. Make sure you're utilizing their classes! ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot lets me know when my emails are being opened, which assists with my email pitching. "}}
{"author": ["Georgina B"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Sales and Marketing Consultant "], "date": ["Jul 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the marketing hub! It is amazing to have a campaign management all together", "What do you dislike?": "The Live chat is not as good as others  -Olark was much better.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "collation of guest details, Campaign management, Automated Workflows."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the accessibility and how easy it is to use. I am new to this CRM and it's really straightforward and love the multiple aspects of it. Their help desk is also phenomenal . ", "What do you dislike?": "I do not love the technical issues that comes up, although it is very rare. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Work flow, communication - it streamlines all our work and the team can work together with the tagging aspect. I love that we can email via the CRM. "}}
{"author": ["Jazmin G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Sales and Marketing Administrator", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is always looking for ways to improve the website. They are also quick to respond to any concerns you may have. ", "What do you dislike?": "I don't really dislike anything. Although I wished the support team knew more HTML and CSS", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "How to get a URL at the bottom of a form. I am reaching out to the HubSpot community for help with CSS"}}
{"author": ["User in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's user friendly. The email features work well. There's a lot of information to figure out what you need to do. The customer support is also helpful.Adding code for tracking is really easy, easier than WordPress or other website management systems. The pages generally look great. The basic stats and charts are helpful", "What do you dislike?": "The stats are limited for more advanced attribution if you're looking to find attribution for marketing qualified leads. The website editor is a bit wonky and more difficult to use unless you're doing the most basic functions like editing text.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "marketing automation. email. website. customer management system. sending lists to Google and Facebook ads. "}}
{"author": ["Chris R"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Video Production Coordinator", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Sep 21, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the ability to see when someone has opened an email and whether they have clicked a link or not. Every time I get a notification an email has been opened, I check to see if I've received a response. Knowing whether an email has been opened and how many times it has been opened is more informative than you might think. It's like running a friendly spy operation on your clients.", "What do you dislike?": "It's a little difficult to sync up with Outlook 365 in a corporate environment.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely install this and give it a try! You'll like it more than you think you will.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Tracking email actions and automating responses."}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I am frequent user of HubSpot's ads reporting features. The Ads reporting is a comprehensive, yet easy-to-navigate reporting experience that easily tracks the contacts and closed deals I've influenced or created through my advertising efforts.", "What do you dislike?": "There are a few quirks to learn in reporting and channel attribution, but if you have a good HUbSpot rep, there is no issue.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easily track and report on my ad performance at a high-level with minimal effort."}}
{"author": ["Renaud K"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder & Managing Partner", "Automotive"], "date": ["Feb 14, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of use of the setup. I did implement various CRM systems in large companies and I am totally surprised of how easy it was to get going with Hubspot.", "What do you dislike?": "There is no integration with Mac email programs. That is a big draw-back. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are tracking our opportunities pipeline much better than before thanks to Hubspot. This was very tricky to do only with emails. We now are able to capture their information right from our website and then follow and track all the exchanges between potential clients through the pipeline."}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 31, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is very helpful tool for webmarketer. Through it we saves time and energy, automates features like emailing, collects info from the data entered and provides valuable insight", "What do you dislike?": "Need to improve customer support .I try to talk to customer support for trouble shooting but not get proper revert", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Through ir automation system our team saves time and energy, automates features like emailing, collects info from the data entered and provides valuable insight"}}
{"author": ["User in Management Consulting"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 31, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "This marketing automation software is helping us grow our business and meet marketing objectives more quickly.", "What do you dislike?": "Designing drip campaigns isn't as user-friendly as some other systems ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely, take all the courses offered in the HubSpot Academy if you are a member of either the Sales or Marketing teams. Taking all the courses will give you a better understanding of the methodology of content marketing and how marketing and sales fit together, so that you can ensure every activity you engage in is helping both teams meet their objectives.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Growth, designing automated drip campaigns, professional development through HubSpot Academy, analyzing ROI."}}
{"author": ["User in Retail"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 03, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There are a lot of features that can be built into hubspot and it has good functionality. I enjoy the user interface for the most part and like the way it presents email analytics", "What do you dislike?": "There are certain features that are very difficult to use, such as editing email templates. Often times things are 2-3 steps harder than they probably need to be.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are sending lead generation emails and monitoring our sales funnel. We enjoy the ability to see when our emails have been opened/clicked."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Consultant"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Managing everything on one place (tools to create Landing Pages and Blogs, automation of mail, workflows, lot of reporting options, etc.).", "What do you dislike?": "Maybe would be better to have all the reports at one place, and not some under modules and some under reports module.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I better understand what it has to offer and what can be done in the solution itself, and later connect that knowledge with how it works as integration with other (BI) tools."}}
{"author": ["User in Utilities"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 31, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that the user can move around in the program easily. It is very user friendly and anyone can sit at the control and find their way. The way that HubSpot is set up for the user in comparison to other marketing tools I have used or seen is fantastic.", "What do you dislike?": "There are not any features I do not like in the small amount of experience I have had with the program.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Comparable to other industry leaders with a better price point. It reaches companies like us who are not so big that we are in need of a larger package, but large enough to make an impact with a great program like HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The issues that can arise with Marketing getting to the right audience can be eliminated with this program. We are able to monitor social interactions, website hits, drivers, and newsletters."}}
{"author": ["Estefania C"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Specialist"], "date": ["Jul 16, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "For  me it's perfect for Marketing Optimization", "What do you dislike?": "I don't know, just i'm learning to use all oportunities", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Landing Pages without developer\r"}}
{"author": ["Duru T"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketeer"], "date": ["May 20, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I can have all marketing tools, email, ads, social, website in one place and it keeps improving everyday", "What do you dislike?": "It still needs to improve a lot as many it only covers the basics of marketing. Social, ads and email beed to have more features with more variety options and better reporting. For example social is only status updates. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "One spot for all marketing purposes. Easy to use and connect people. Can align with the while team. "}}
{"author": ["Cristin P"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Admissions Recruiter", "Higher Education"], "date": ["Jan 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how we are able to utilize it for things other than marketing. We use it to connect with our prospective students on many different levels. We use it for transcript evaluations, planning student meetings, sending college information out and much more.", "What do you dislike?": "I do not like how it is hard to import and export contacts. We deal with so many students on a daily basis that exporting their information to another database for mass mailings has proven to be difficult. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would highly recommend using this product for anyone looking to expand their business. I would also recommend it if you are looking to gain/generate leads. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are making it easier to stay in touch with our prospective students. We are able to send out timed mailings and marketing materiel. "}}
{"author": ["User in E-Learning"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 06, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that hubspot is able to track leads and connect directly to salesforce. Hubspot has reporting capabilities and can gather information with the requirements you set, very good customization. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that hubspot does not have as many capabilities as salesforce lead tracking system, though hubspot is cheaper than salesforce add on. It would be nice to just have one system for all lead tracking. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot has made our lead tracking process much easier, if this is something you are looking for, great option. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have solved our issue of being unable to connect our CRM system to salesforce to automatically have data transfer over when a lead comes in. Much easier! Less manual work. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Telecommunications"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 15, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The easy use. Its products and services aim to provide tools for social media marketing, content management, web analytics and search engine optimization.", "What do you dislike?": "Price tag. For $200 per month, the Basic package allows you to grow and refine your business as you build momentum with inbound marketing. This package allows you to have three user logins, with a maximum of 100 contacts, but you are welcome to add to your network for an additional $100 per 1,000 contacts.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Simple, easy, and does not take long to learn as compared to other companies I\u2019ve operates with before. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is one of the best-integrated CRM platforms on the market and no other free CRM solution can offer the same level of integration"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It combines lots of tools into one. Unfortunately they're all lacking in one way or another.", "What do you dislike?": "If you like sales people that lie, unhelpful account managers and vague and evasive customer support reps, then I can whole-heartedly recommend HubSpot.\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "In all seriousness, the product is vastly overpriced and doesn't deliver on it's promises. There are countless tools that need improving and are missing basic functionality. Despite this, they keep releasing half-baked add-on products for their sales team to push onto their customers before fixing fundamental issues with their core product. A great example of a sales-first company neglecting the quality of their product."}}
{"author": ["Amanda J"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Managing Editor"], "date": ["Dec 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is great for tracking eblast and web traffic performance. Developing an email campaign is relatively easy and straightforward. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some file management could be better/easier to use and access. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Worth the investment if you're looking to generate more data analysis on website users and track website and e-newsletter traffic.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot helps with driving traffic to our websites, track website and e-newsletter performance and campaign management."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I have been using Hubspot for over 4 years. Our every data is at one place just because of Hubspot and also the very good analytics report providing by Hubspot.", "What do you dislike?": " The only thing I can think of is that we cannot schedule videos for business However, I think that may be an issue with the Instagram API rather than HubSpot themselves.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Best tools for Marketing and Sales.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using Hubspot for our inside sales and Marketing Operations, Many a thing are in one place because of the Hubspot only and easy to understand and since we have been using Hubspot there is not problem of KT for Sales and Marketing team.\r"}}
{"author": ["Anne Marie C"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 05, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hub Spot is not only functionally, a very good resource for marketing, it is also a great source for training material. They have a lot of good video demos and content for employees that are new to marketing. ", "What do you dislike?": "There is not a whole like that I disagree with on HubSpot. Overall, I think more companies should use it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are solving our inbound progress tracking. Once our sites go live, we can continue to track progress. Prior to Hubspot implementation, we had difficulty doing this task. "}}
{"author": ["Trish B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Product Marketing", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 20, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is so easy to use, and their support is fantastic when we do have questions. It is nice to see everything in one place - webstats, social media, landing pages, blogs, contacts, emails, etc. It's a great all in one solution that is cost effective and easy to use. ", "What do you dislike?": "Very little i dislike. One thing might be it calculates stats a little differently than google analytics, but once you know the differences it is fine. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have save a lot of money streamlining our marketing. We also have saved money by having everything in one place. "}}
{"author": ["Jenni S"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Strategic Planner", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 11, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the ease of use Hubspot provides. It's very simple to create emails, forms and landing pages with just a few clicks of the mouse, and customize them to my needs. Not only is creation simple, but the end result always looks completely professional!", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing. I truly think this platform is the best tool an inbound marketer can have in his arsenal. Sure they could offer more features, but with a company like Hubspot I have no doubt that the capabilities will be more robust year over year.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you want to grow your business, pull people into your site that are primed to hear what you have to say and nurture relationships in an organic way that is data informed, then Hubspot is the ultimate tool for your marketing arsenal.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Inbound marketing - developing blog posts, emails, ebooks, etc. to pull users into sites and appeal to them with content that meets their needs."}}
{"author": ["Robert B"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Digital Marketing Specialist"], "date": ["Nov 15, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There were a lot of different templates and modules I liked how they are organized.  I also liked how I could sort them.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it was unclear from the description what the module did.  I wish that it had more visual details of the module.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is helping us create landing pages for our trade shows.  I am realizing how visually impactful those landing pages can be."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 15, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Good campaign setup to tie different campaign activity together. Great social automation features. Easy to navigate and use", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the customisation options and design editors can be a bit laborious. Changing an email design or creating interesting looking mailshots is not as straight forward as it could be.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Regular social posting on behalf of busy sales team,  marketing automation and analytics to understand effectiveness of campaigns"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 08, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is set up so non-tech savvy users can navigate everything very well. I love how I can make website changes, manage forms, manage contacts, set up email workflows, and collaborate with sales, all in one software.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes things are set up so that you can't do individual, tailored things as easily. For example, the blog template is great to standardize things, but it can be hard to make large individual changes to specific blog posts. Not impossible, but just a bit harder. Too many of the features are also add-ons, like Reporting (I think Reporting is an essential enough feature that it should just be included with every price level!)", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to handle almost all of our marketing tasks and workflows within one software. This helps the team, since we don't have to learn multiple softwares, and we can keep updated on what team members are doing, in marketing, sales, and account management."}}
{"author": ["Hayley R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Specialist"], "date": ["Sep 20, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I used HubSpot Marketing. There were SO many features built-in, it was such an awesome one-stop-shop for our landing pages, blog, email marketing, forms, and more. Easy to use and amazing support.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes a bit difficult to customize. They have their own coding language and you have to know it to do deeper customization.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Really dive in with HubSpot and take advantage of ALL their features. There is so much to use and you'll really feel like you're getting your money's worth when using everything they have to offer.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We needed a solution for landing pages, email marketing, forms, and collecting leads. HubSpot helped us realize all these needs."}}
{"author": ["Brian F"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Transportation Planner", "Transportation/Trucking/Railroad"], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The great thing about Hubspot is that many of your marketing tools are connected all in one place -- for example, project management, email marketing & analytics", "What do you dislike?": "The system isn't as user friendly as it could be. The dashboard is slightly confusing on how best to navigate.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Major problem it is solving is email marketing -- then occasionally use it to manage multiple people on a project."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 12, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's just like an apple product: pretty, intuitive, and part of a fully-compatible, internal ecosystem. ", "What do you dislike?": "It's just like an apple product: pretty, intuitive, and incredibly difficult to creatively customize to your needs without shelling out for templates or knowing significant coding.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Built in analytics have allowed our growing team to look backward at historical performance without having consciously built those materials for analytics tracking the first place."}}
{"author": ["Gaidak M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager", "Luxury Goods & Jewelry"], "date": ["Aug 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is easy in setting up integrated marketing campaigns and tracking results from various channels: social media, email marketing efforts, landing pages. Great for a/b testing, provides actionable insights for campaign improvements", "What do you dislike?": "Lacks flexibility in terms of design, a lot of modules have to be coded so a decent knowledge of HTML bis required for quality assurance", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Tracking campaigns in one platform, implementing complicated campaigns, building landing pages and blogs"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 17, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's great that team members can contribute to the HubSpot on different marketing and sales leads so we can all be kept up to date on the progress of business leads.", "What do you dislike?": "It's not the easiest user interface to use if you are new, so it might take some time to get used to.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take some time to familiarise yourself with the website, because there is a learning curve with the system.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using it to keep track of our business leads, and as a growing business with a small team, it is very helpful to coordinate our efforts and ensure we are progressing well with our leads."}}
{"author": ["May M"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is easy to uses perhaps the best-known tool in its class; it's one that includes use cases for micro businesses, midsize companies, and large enterprises alike", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it can be a little slow if there is a large volume of data involved. Also the price", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "comes with unique, tangential sales-related items, such as a Live Chat product called Messages that lets organizations deploy live chat to any web page", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "automation workflows are created via templates and a custom builder. The 10 out-of-the-box templates are called \"Recipes"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot rocks at social sharing and scheduling to LinkedIn and Facebook, along with an easy-to-use platform for e-mail marketing.", "What do you dislike?": "However, I don't like the tracking URLS and alt-text replacement for the paid accounts.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hire an expert!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I have realized that if you're e-mail lists AREN'T segmented per LOB (due to alternative domain names within your company) that it can cause an ugly duplication mess within your contacts."}}
{"author": ["User in Farming"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The HunSpot Academy courses offered to HubSpot customers have really helped me expand my knowledge of inbound marketing and inspired my content marketing process. The number of tools HubSpot offers keeps expanding, and the more we integrate it into our company, the more I love it!", "What do you dislike?": "The new HubSpot Messages sales tool needs some work. We previously used another online chat tool and found it was much more capable of handling our chat traffic and was easier for operators to use.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot is great for inbound marketing but their Messages software has many issues.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Bringing in customers through content marketing, including blogs, email marketing, and and social scheduling."}}
{"author": ["John W"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 03, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The support from the staff makes you feel like you are part of the team.  The Academy and learning center are a wealth of knowledge", "What do you dislike?": "Little hard to navigate the website gets confusing options could be simplified. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing Automation thought leadership development, lead scoring is our goal, the templates and integration make it easy to post and track visitors."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Kristen C"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["System Administrator & Marketing Director", "Legal Services"], "date": ["May 20, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The best thing about Hubspot is the endless training & resources available. There are hours of classes and webinars to watch and learn from. They also provide tutorials for using programs you have already (e.g. PowerPoint/Keynote, Word/Pages) to make eye-catching graphics to include on your site. ", "What do you dislike?": "Learning curve for most people is 2-3 months.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "We tried to hire local SEO & Social Media firms and individuals before committing to Hubspot. It was a very good decision to use Hubspot, and after 5 months we are seeing constant growth. We had many problems with marketing agencies and individuals.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We came very close to hiring an agency to run Hubspot for us, but determined that running it in-house is the best plan. No one knows our business like we do. \r"}}
{"author": ["User in Veterinary"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Utilizing the templates/sequences increases overall efficiency.  Also the ability to integrate with other programs which increases the automation of leads/sales/customer retention is a big winner.", "What do you dislike?": "The mobile app needs to be more friendly.  The current model mimics the web version - which on the phone does not operate as expected.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use the tutorials they have - very comprehensive.  Also explore the ability the program has to integrate and automate work flows for staff efficiency.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Managing sales leads, all incoming/outgoing emails, phone calls, tasks, business information and staff member contacts"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to organize contacts and use tracked emails to send to clients", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes when beginning to use Hubspot it can be hard to navigate around", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use as much of the automation and analytics tools as possible", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are realizing the abilities to track calls and potential clients calling in and organizing them based on industries, potential spam, etc. \r"}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 03, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Once you have polished landing page and email templates developed, Hubspot is so easy to use when it comes to creating and deploying content. They've done a great job making it easy for marketers to bypass engineering for content creation purposes.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "High-level trend reports and performance of any piece of content or automation workflow is well done.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "To be able to include all the information and necessary material when working, be it contacts or companies with which I must relate. ", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it does not drag all the information when they are related from some web page", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "None, is totally adequate and easy for its use", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "You can manage accounts in a Marketing portal, in addition to their forms are designed to collect information about visitors to your website, these can also be used by your internal users to send contact information offline. Organization and easy access to information and inestigacion carried out by the entire working group"}}
{"author": ["Jessica D"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Affiliate Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I know if my clients are receiving my emails and how frequently they check their emails. It is interesting to see which clients open the email multiple times and how quickly they receive the emails.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes I have clients respond to my emails, but on Hubspot it doesn't show the client opening up the email. Also, if you CC someone, it seems to get confused and can't track who exactly is opening it.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Try out the free trial and see if it benefits your work. Also keep in mind they can read your emails, so don't submit personal information there.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Some people weren't responding to my emails, and others I just couldn't get in touch with. When I saw someone was not opening my emails, I knew that I had to check other sources to find the right contact. I also knew whether they were ignoring me or actually having trouble reaching me."}}
{"author": ["Dedra A"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Music Artist"], "date": ["Aug 02, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the great advertising and merging abilities you can achieve with the Hubspot platform. I got great results on many more twitter followers and greater interaction with my posts when using this software platform. The automated posting feature is a wonderful time saver and gets excellent results!! This can be scheduled for up to a month in advance which is fantastic. True set it and forget it. A fulltime marketer in a box!", "What do you dislike?": "I had to really study the platform to maximize my ability to use it. It was well worth the time to do this for the time savings and fantastic exposure and results. it is also expensive but worth it.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you want real results with minimal time spent daily this is for you. I recommend it for maximum immediate results.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Using Hubspot solves getting greater marketing reach, more interaction with posts and getting greater sales results and leads."}}
{"author": ["Julie V"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Co-Founder", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["May 19, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot software gathers together the essential elements of digital marketing and puts them to work in a unified process called inbound marketing, which is much more powerful than using elements like social media, email marketing, analytics on their own.  I have been in digital marketing since 2000 and HubSpot is my favorite tool.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "In a nutshell, HubSpot has freed my time from getting tools to work and gathering data to easily seeing and sharing campaign results and improving strategy. Strategy is where the value in digital marketing lies.  Other marketing software can be heavy on technological implementation, while HubSpot implementation is about learning how to start deploying campaigns that generate results.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot seems to go through and re-invent each component of the company fairly frequently.  The only areas that were not state-of-the-art at this writing were the billing system -- renewal notices could be automated into a workflow. In the file system it would be nice if you could see the list of all images and not have to tab through many pages. Both of these are not game-changers for me."}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ability to connect all the dots on a contact's activity. I like the user-friendly side of Hubspot. Also having one central location for all your contacts' activities makes it easier to retell the story. ", "What do you dislike?": "Reporting is poor and the ability to link deals and contacts need improvement. Ability to link the deals with contacts and the fact that contacts do not automatically get associated with companies is a big minus. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If outbound marketing is your focus, then this tool might be problematic for you.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We run all marketing and sales in Hubspot currently. We do have the landing pages of our website build in HS, as well as the Social Media that we run is also done in Hubspot."}}
{"author": ["Jeff B"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Marketing Strategist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 09, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is a premiere marketing automation tool that keeps you in touch with customers and prospects while strategically distributing content on several platforms.", "What do you dislike?": "HubSpot is not for the novice.  There needs to be a marketing strategist on hand to help map out the plan.  They rely heavily on their consultant network which can be costly to the companies using them.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Ensure that you map out a clear content marketing strategy before integrating the solution.  It is very advanced and will cost a lot of time and money if done after integration", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Communicating with customers and prospects to nurture them into future sales."}}
{"author": ["Jessie-Lee N"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Art Director", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 03, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is truly an all-in-one platform. From a single login you can manage social, workflows, email, contacts, landing pages, calls-to-action, your website and now even more with newly released add ons.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I've been using HubSpot for over four years, and in that time the platform has grown drastically, but it has always been results focused. Better yet, HubSpot wants their customers and their partners to succeed. They are constantly updating a vast library of resources to help understand the methodology and the accompanying technology. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "- Ability to create workflows based on any sort of triggers\r", "What do you dislike?": "- Ability to track all sorts of performance metrics, from email marketing to CTA clicks", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "- Landing page builder is not comparable to other players in the market", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Make sure you understand how to get value out of it, cause the learning curve takes time."}}
{"author": ["Beth K"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing"], "date": ["Oct 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that HubSpot makes it possible to have all of my contacts in one place and that it is possible for me to easily search for a contact rather than having to dig around in my emails.", "What do you dislike?": "I have not had any issues with HubSpot so far while using it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is great to be able to make notes on each individual so that I can easily remember and have access to the places I have met them or communications we have had."}}
{"author": ["Mauricio  P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 23, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "the asy way we can made landing page and the way we can use code source in the templates ", "What do you dislike?": "that we can no upload a bunch of pictures to the slide module you need to do it one by one", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "yes", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "we can have access to the page the clients visit, that help us to create a better marketing"}}
{"author": ["User in Hospital & Health Care"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The information is very relevant to real-world use. I liked the fact that there are blogs and supporting materials on most topics.", "What do you dislike?": "Some examples in the videos seemed outdated or used for personal gain/attention.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's easy to use and navigate. The lessons in the tracks are easy to follow and are applicable to real-world situations. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Improving marketing strategy and sales enablement. We definitely need to bring marketing and sales together to achieve the highest possible results."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot combines the 20+ tools I used before (CRM, CMS, mailtool, analytics,...). ", "What do you dislike?": "We sometimes reach the limits on hubspot when it comes to multilanguage features or large enterprise needs (several business units, but only one community possible).", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do it. The software is a real addition to any marketing plan. The software is ever-evolving. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are finally able to build the entire inbound flows for our contacts in one tool and follow-up leads from start to finish. "}}
{"author": ["Agency"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 06, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Centralization of data, assets & processes.", "What do you dislike?": "Piece meal pricing, tiers are broken down to accommodate for things you want and might not need. This makes strategy conversations difficult and can ultimately limit the type of service you provide based on the package tier your client chooses.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot has a deep knowledge base & community you can tap into.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead generation, education through content & automating manual processes to streamline efficiency"}}
{"author": ["Consultant"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 17, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is really good at helping me keep my pipeline running and organized. The setup with tasks, emails, calls, etc. has proven to be effective for me.", "What do you dislike?": "From time to time HubSpot crashes. I don't know if its technical reasons or updates, but it throws off my flow whenever it happens.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Being able to link hubspot with my email and JustCall has really helped me stay organized."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has streamlined and simplified our marketing efforts across every channel. The social scheduling tool is especially user-friendly, intuitive, and reliable in comparison to other platforms. HubSpot also allows us to view the complete cycle of the user experience which is extremely valuable in reporting.", "What do you dislike?": "Could grow some capabilities in terms of social media and analytics as they are somewhat limited.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Inbound marketing, monitoring, reporting, social media management. This platform has streamlined our operations."}}
{"author": ["Chris M"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is easy to use, the data is presented in a straightforward way, and there are a host of trainings available to make the most out of use.", "What do you dislike?": "It is not always cost-effective for our clients. Very expensive.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The commitment and expense can seem daunting, but this product is worth the price!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have been able to prove consistent ROI for clients using HubSpot, and have been able to show a trajectory of growth in website traffic. The benefits of automation have saved time and extra, unnecessary work."}}
{"author": ["Jack M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing and Communications Officer", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Landing pages/ forms and contacts/ editing live pages and making changes on the fly.", "What do you dislike?": "Needs multiple dependent fields\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "needs multiple 'click to reveal' fields\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Go ahead"}}
{"author": ["Ali A"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Graphic Designer"], "date": ["Nov 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use workflows, plus it works well with SalesForce. ", "What do you dislike?": "A little on the pricey side and it's SEO-based marketing functionality has room to improve. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are creating our companies first outreach campaigns. We have used HubSpot to campaign a webinar from start to finish. "}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is a combination of all the essentials for digital marketing, including SEO, content management, analytics etc. It makes it a one stop go to product.", "What do you dislike?": "I haven't extensively used the product to face any dislikes as yet. But, I am not sure if I can deploy this for larger corporates.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HUbspot has a transparent and flexible pricing which comes in handy. You can choose to complicate it as much depending on your need. It can be used by a product or services company which is definitely an indication that its about the marketing and does not really differentiate the company's vertical.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I used it to identify better marketing tactics for my inbound marketing team. They have realised good insight on various forms of data. "}}
{"author": ["Dan K"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Founder & President", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jul 26, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "All my digital marketing tools are in one place - website, email, social, blog, PPC programs ", "What do you dislike?": "Because it is a Saas platform, they frequently update it (good) but occasionally I have to go searching for where a menu item has moved to.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Don't try to do it yourself - even as a partner, we got help putting it up the first time.  And #2, be prepared to feed the constant monster - the system only works if you are creating new content.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It has made our marketing far more productive - we are able to do more with fewer people.  The CRM they added made our lead qualification process easier as well."}}
{"author": ["Taylor L"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Analyst", "Apparel & Fashion"], "date": ["Nov 01, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The thing that is most appealing for us as a small team is the ease of use and robust nature of the platform.", "What do you dislike?": "You can't be all things to all people so there are times where a feature lacks the depth needed but for the most part it is great.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Understand that HubSpot does a lot of programming and shifting of the platform.  The changes do disrupt work sometimes but on the whole the changes are good.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are solving the need for marketing automation and inbound marketing.  We have realized increased sales and more customer engagement than ever before."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Noha A"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Inbound Marketing Lead"], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love HubSpot's end-to-end experience. Not only they provide you with the marketing automation tools you need, but also they transfer as much knowledge as they can in the process. They never fail to support you with any learning resources.", "What do you dislike?": "They need to enhance their website builder. The Content Manager needs more access and authorities.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has provided marketing solutions for our company and helped us track our results."}}
{"author": ["Connor S"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Jul 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot allows you to do pretty much anything you would want in marketing automation and its easy-to-use interface allows for a faster org-wide adoption", "What do you dislike?": "Not so much of a dislike as a lack of use. You can get pretty detailed in analytics and reporting in Hubspot but perhaps not as much as Marketo. Again, for what MOST people use the platform for, it does the job. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Keep everyone in the loop as to what functions of your marketing programs are being integrated. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Streamlining marketing attribution and marketing tactic processes. "}}
{"author": ["Juan B"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": ["Digital Entrepreneur"], "date": ["Jan 23, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I liked integration with email, but lately it is not working properly, at least with free accounts. ", "What do you dislike?": "Free accounts are getting less and less features. Nowadays I am not sure if using Hubspot for free is really something with value.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "CRM"}}
{"author": ["Ryan L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Director", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Nov 25, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot has paid very close attention to aligning their message to their platform. It is absolutely as advertised, and if you execute the inbound marketing strategy that they advocate, the platform is set up very well to support you.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I'm also impressed with how well the data integrates within Hubspot. Your campaigns, contact properties, events, etc. thread throughout the entire system so that everything plays nicely together. Unlike some marketing platforms that are clearly a hodge-podge of poorly integrated acquisitions, you can tell Hubspot was built as one.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Shraddha S"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Specialist", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Mar 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Training courses and assistive technology along with the web tutorials ", "What do you dislike?": "vague organization of the training courses", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "leave everything else and use this software for your marketing management and automation purposes\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "solving email marketing issues and checking on open rates"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 07, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "One of the best features about HS is definitely the customer service. They do an incredible job as teaching me the ins-and-outs of the platform. ", "What do you dislike?": "There are a couple of functions that HS can't perform... yet, but they are very minor. One that comes in mind is the inability to post multiple photos on LinkedIn and Instagram. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I've had a lot of help with creating email lists. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 31, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's a well thought out platform. Each one their tools connects intuitively with the next. It's easy to get a lot done in a short period of time.", "What do you dislike?": "The CMS components are getting better, but are limited for more advanced marketing orgs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're leveraging HubSpot to operationalize our entire lead funnel. From lead acquisition to customer marketing. Having the majority of our tech needs in one platform makes it much easier to see the results of our efforts."}}
{"author": ["Consultant in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is intuitive, easy to use and frankly makes doing integrated marketing communications a joy. I can do everything from Social content calendar sharing to Email Marketing and SEO actions to improve organic traffic volumes. I would give HubSpot my highest recommendation.", "What do you dislike?": "There are not many things to dislike! If I really had to pick one, I wish that it was easier to make new template/ Edit existing templates for non-developers.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I highly recommend HubSpot Growth Suite", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Helps us to keep track of our performance online, Helps us to better measure leads and to automate tasks that otherwise would have been done manually. "}}
{"author": ["User in Staffing and Recruiting"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 12, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the training Hubspot offers. It's great to get to know things that can be used elsewhere. Even though a lot of the info may already be known, refreshers can never hurt. ", "What do you dislike?": "How hard it is to accomplish seemingly easy tasks. Hubspot doesn't integrate well with our business model. It's one of those things that would be amazing for some companies, but our company has many seperate legs that we are in charge of. For us, Hubspot has in some ways hurt where it should've helped. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "PLEASE consider your particular business model. This may be the perfect software for you.. If you have a fairly straightforward business model, it could be great. Otherwise, beware and make sure you know what you're getting yourself into. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Not really solving any business problems right now. Wish we were though! We are trying to heighten some SEO, but it's not working great for us. "}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 09, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that this is truly an all in one solution for a sales/marketing team.", "What do you dislike?": "I do with that there was a feature that allowed you to send large amounts of emails through the system at once.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Try out their free trial and talk to a representative on their team about what you're looking for. Everyone is extremely helpful and sometimes you learn about features you wouldn't have known about otherwise.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It's a ton of great sales & marketing tools on a single consolidated platform. Tons of time saved because of the ability to automatically sync with your email provider and track activity. The reporting dashboard helps you stay on track with your goals and it's easy to sign in and have a bird's eye view of your pipeline within a few clicks. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to simultaneously manage all aspects of a campaign and report in real time the effectiveness of our nurturing/lead generation efforts across channels. ", "What do you dislike?": "The lack of differentiation regarding their Workflows tools. Specifically setting workflows that automate field updates and routing vs. developing campaigns (nurture/drip/etc.) ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead nurturing. With HubSpot we've been able to more efficiently and cohesively put together a content and implementation strategy to increase the number of qualified leads marketing is generating. "}}
{"author": ["Mackenzie B"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager"], "date": ["Oct 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of use and one-stop-shop nature of HubSpot makes it a no brainer for our business.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes the backend of the templates get a little complicated, but once you get over the learning curve, it's not too bad.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Tracking is our biggest thing. We are able to efficiently answer data-related questions in a timely manner because everything is tracked, start to finish, in one spot."}}
{"author": ["Jim K"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Product Marketing Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how easy it is to manage users, campaigns and landing pages in Hubspot. ", "What do you dislike?": "Managing pages that are in multiple languages can be a challenge to find all of the pages in the system if you don't have a very good naming convention. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use Hubspot for lead nurturing and capture. It is really good at progressive profiling and marketing automation.  "}}
{"author": ["Faigie Dina G"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Founder", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Apr 14, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot marketing automation enables us to manage our clients growth marketing and lead generating efforts with clear guidelines and streamlines processes. The results are a clear trajectory of metrics. ", "What do you dislike?": "I don't work directly on Hubspot, as I have a trained team managing the tool. We don't often come across challenges, and if we do, the hubspot team is responsive and helpful. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot's inbound methodologies are integral to a companies growth marketing strategies. By integrating a marketing automation platform, my clients have a methodological system for maximizing their marketing reach, optimizing their content, and creating lead generating landing pages, emails and much more. The benefits realized are both streamlined operation as well as clear acceleration of inbound leads and marketing reach. "}}
{"author": ["User in Staffing and Recruiting"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 07, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I came into my current role with a bit of coding experience, but Hubspot makes building pages so easy that I rarely have to use the coding part! Typically I will only go into the code to make small edits to colors or copy. The live view is really great and updates quickly and they recently updated their user interface, which looks really crisp and clean. I love the option to preview on various different devices. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish the responsiveness of the pages was automatically built in without having to create smart rules. It does make your images smaller, but the text seems to stay the larger, desktop size. When handing projects off to various team members, it can sometimes be hard to remember to go back in and edit those rules for mobile and tablet sizes as we make changes.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using HubSpot to create landing pages. Our current company-mandated CMS is clunky and complicated and HubSpot has greatly reduced the amount of time it takes to go from a Word doc of copy to a fully-fledged, functional landing page."}}
{"author": ["Scott W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager"], "date": ["Dec 29, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Initial overview and training was easy to understand and support offered was very helpful. Could instantly see a use for the software ", "What do you dislike?": "Only thing I didn\u2019t like was that how to measure the effectiveness of blog content, you had to use a different url for the blog, it couldn\u2019t be coded into already existing blog on current store", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Get full buy in from senior management first before going ahead ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Insights into what content works and what targeted market are reading on your website. Insights into what keywords are working and also ability to see what is working for competitors. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How easy is to create blast e-mails, or to edit a hubspot-based webpage. I find the system to be very easy and intuitive, we use it mostly as a full marketing tool combining contact database, email manager and of course, the websites. ", "What do you dislike?": "If we need to go further with a new characteristic, sometines it's not available yet by Hubspot developers. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have a coherent system to organize and update our contacts, so the sales and marketing team is now aligned. Besides, our websites contact forms are directly linked to our CRM! E-mail marketing is great. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 15, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that I can search a company or a name and come up with so much information about a client or partner.", "What do you dislike?": "No hashtag tracking.  I would love to be able to track a new hashtag every time we had an event.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I like the social media scheduler. I realized the calendar function enables be to better plan out my posts throughout the month."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 14, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I use it inside Gmail most and the email tracking and scheduling features have been my favorites. It helps me see what clients are opening vs. not opening and allows for more targeted and strategic followups.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it disconnects randomly from Gmail, and the email scheduling also does not have a way to unschedule automatically if the client replies. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can clear my inbox quicker and keep track of deals in the pipeline that I would normally just leave in the inbox or lose track of what deals are where."}}
{"author": ["Marc G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Demand Generation Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["May 18, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use, intuitive and extremely useful for marketing automation.", "What do you dislike?": "Too pricey. It is probably the best marketing automation tool available but still too pricey compared to other marketing automation platforms. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Generating and managing leads"}}
{"author": ["Internal Consultant"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Excellent UI , easy to find what you're looking for. Also hubspot academy and the whole approach of the content you're sharing with us is really good. ", "What do you dislike?": "All the platform is built on a contact approach and not company approach. This has a lot of limitations when the company offers b2b services. Also deal workflows doesn't cross coperate with contact workflow. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It's one the most effective tools to use in order to build a really good Inbound sales strategy . "}}
{"author": ["Ricardo V"], "company_size": [], "role": ["President", "Mining & Metals"], "date": ["Feb 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "1. Is free\r", "What do you dislike?": "2. Is integrated with my Gmail\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "3. Is not complex to use"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that they have offer a ton of training courses and workshops to learn more about the application.", "What do you dislike?": "It is pretty standard in terms of templates so if you don't have design experience or team, it is hard to have a lot of creative liberties in the process. its also a difficult platform to jump in to on your own without taking an introductory class. its a little difficult to collaborate between the different teams that use it (analytics, creative, communication) Each team knows how to use it for their specific focus or use but aren't so familiar with it to use cross-team. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Take one or more of their training courses- the people are very nice and helpful in walking you through specifics of the platform and answering all of your questions. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing and blogging"}}
{"author": ["Tracey T"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Project Manager"], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "That so many tools are contained in one software platform. ", "What do you dislike?": "That sometimes the tool can be inconsistent during use. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Instead of having many mediocre tools, we can use just Hubspot to fulfill many of our marketing needs. "}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 18, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is an excellent CMS, whether it's for small or large businesses. We are partnered with them and have many clients migrating to their system. Email automation and funneling are amazing features and are unparalelled.", "What do you dislike?": "While it's a complicated tool, the training marketing and sales certifications are uselessly hard and complicated. I prefer a much more generalized approach with optional details.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Many clients can now track their leads, automate emails and meetings. Informations are very customizable and classifiable."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a one stop shop platform for marketers. It's super easy to set up landing pages, email nurturing flows, social media campaigns and analyze the results. ", "What do you dislike?": "The fact that you have to pay so much more for every little add-on. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We can now quickly and easily create landing pages and set up email nurturing flows (we never had email automation before and creating website pages was a big hassle). "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 15, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is exceptionally well designed and easy to navigate. They also invest in educating their customers, and you always feel like you are supported as you ramp up.", "What do you dislike?": "The PRICING! We thought we were getting a great deal (paid a monthly fee), but we needed many additional features and needed to expand our contact database - and both of those things meant lots more money. When all was said and done, we could have purchased a higher end platform for about the same cost.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We tried Hubspot on our search for the perfect marketing automation platform (we're still searching). We did find that we were able to effectively create and manage campaigns, but after realizing the price tag was above our budget, we had to move on - and that transition period set us back."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Internet"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 25, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot's UI is always changing for the better. The user experience is extremely intuitive and it covers all the basics you need to run a successful marketing funnel in an SMB to Mid-Market size company. Support is probably the best perk. Their support team is accessible and helpful via email, chat, or phone. ", "What do you dislike?": "Reporting capabilities are limited and slow - though I believe they offered \"premium\" reporting services at a higher cost now. Certain features are limiting: lack of complexity in lead scoring and limited A/B testing with workflow emails.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're using HubSpot for all of our email marketing and campaign activities before Sales engagement. Having all that data in one place with multiple integrations to other tools has been really beneficial for understanding the buyer's journey."}}
{"author": ["Marissa B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Communications Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["Dec 22, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love how easy Hubspot is to use. It's incredibly intuitive to learn. Hubspot makes it really easy to set up a social media calendar, and their reporting is super helpful. Their email reports are great summaries that are valuable to share with leaders in your team. ", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot sometimes has bugs and kinks that need to be worked out, but their support team is easy to work with. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is a great way to capture leads, track your progress, manage email campaigns, post pages to your website, and manage your social media accounts.  "}}
{"author": ["User in Consumer Goods"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I LOVE, LOVE all of the resources (HubSpot Academy!) that HubSpot offers. ", "What do you dislike?": "I don't like that the social reporting side of HubSpot doesn't report all the metrics I need to measure.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The CRM side of HubSpot has been amazing. It's been able to help clean up our data and help streamline our sales pipeline.\r"}}
{"author": ["Agency in Media Production"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 05, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What is great for a nonprofit that works with your able to collect and life and evaluate and Payne fix that on a weekly basis modifying the best or ali what is great for nonprofits that work with your able to collect and life and evaluate and Payne success on a weekly basis modifying the best ROI", "What do you dislike?": "I am a huge fan, only wish we could build out more", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure your admins are highly savvy in digital trends and best practices ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We streamline content marketing and social engagement for NPOs by automating their marketing process and sending campaign updates with insights and recommended pivots to increasing donor engagement and social reach "}}
{"author": ["User in Oil & Energy"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to store massive amounts of data in one intuitive CRM. This allows you and your team to stay up to date with outbound and inbound sales, as well as keeping up to speed with developments in existing account management to ensure sales, marketing, and account management are coordinated and professional.", "What do you dislike?": "The sheer number of functions and large operational capability can make the learning curve quite steep. It takes a long time to master. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Perfect for enterprise level businesses.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Solved the problem of coordinating across multiple teams to ensure all members of each team were up to speed with the businesses operations. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 06, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "All the platform features and the ability to empower me to create, manage and optimize a campaign with all the assets required. The reports enable me to track and optimize my campaigns and automate workflows. ", "What do you dislike?": "Landing pages are not always designed for mobile. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Ensuing my workflows are optimized and goal-focused - breaking the workflows into small ones which are goal-focused to measure the conversion rate. "}}
{"author": ["TaKeisha B"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Graduate Assistant", "Higher Education"], "date": ["Oct 07, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "this program is the best marketing tool for inbound marketing, sales, and promote your product/skills/services to your target market", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that this tool has been only available to me in my work environments and not personally. I would love to use this program for a project I am developing for nonprofit organizations.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "learning how to utilize this marketing tool to expand the brand to communities, individuals, and groups who do not have access to Hubspot or marketing data to help their initiative. "}}
{"author": ["Richard K"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager", "Leisure, Travel & Tourism"], "date": ["Jul 08, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of training was excellent.  Building froms, landing pages, email campaigns, etc. is very intuitive in the UI and often times does not require significant training and/or reading to get up to speed on execution in a short-manner of time.", "What do you dislike?": "Channel source reporting specific data becomes significantly less exact when we stopped hosting our site on HubSpot's UI.  Hosting on HubSpot's servers also significantly diminished our flexibility from a design standpoint.  When the design of the website failed to keep up with our stage as a company, we started hosting the site ourselves to in order to give our designer more options in changing the overall look and feel of the site.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If the price is in your budget, I would suggest looking into all of its capabilities as the tool saved us significant amount of time", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead generation. Lead nurturing. Content management.  It has removed a significant amount of manual work involved with moving marketing leads through the sales funnel."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Service Hub, consumer care section is the most beneficial. CRM has its challenges in lack of reporting and breaking out each country. ", "What do you dislike?": "CRM, lack of email segmentation, breaking out the consumers. building better reports in teh dashboards in email marketing and campaigns. less html coding. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great for small businesses and not a large consumer list base", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "order imports for all customer information, customer lists, events, landing pages dedicated"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Mining & Metals"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We have been able to get rid of over 4 individual programs we used on our marketing team by switching to Hubspot. we use it all day, everyday and the ability to access all of our information in one place is amazing. ", "What do you dislike?": "The only feature our team dislikes is the messages feature, there is no ability to send screen shots through the chat when applied to our website. For this reason, we needed to continue to use our outside live chat program. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It solves communication issues we had with sales and marketing teams. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I absolutely LOVE how Hubspot is the most complete and user friendly CRM software out there. Marketing has never been so smooth to conduct.", "What do you dislike?": "I would only say that I'd like to see more RAW data but above all it reallly has nothing to dislike about.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am solving everything. Traffic management, leads, social media engagements, blog posts and more. I've benefited and realized how truly smooth and easy digital marketing can be with them."}}
{"author": ["Peter S"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Chief Executive Officer", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jul 26, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Single platform for engagement, buyer persona functionality, intuitive features, constant improvement, analytics, the people behind it rock...they believe in the business needs that drive the development and use", "What do you dislike?": "It's glitchy at times but support is knowledgable", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot is simple to use but deep. Don't try to boil the ocean with execution. Phase your use across a quarterly calendar and celebrate both qualitative and quantitative wins. It's still just a tool. Just because you own a hammer doesn't mean you are a carpenter. It takes time to become a craftsman.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Eliminating disparity and driving adjustments in managing to the right results for engaging a very difficult to reach c suite audience"}}
{"author": ["Megan T"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["VP of Marketing", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Oct 06, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I've used virtually all of the MA software out there. I admit I was skeptical when I first used Hubspot. I really believed it existed for small business. I was pleased I had another look and decided to go with Hubspot at my last company. I've had no regrets, and been pleasantly surprised.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is the most integrated, and for marketers today, this is key. With the built in COS, I have my site, blog, landing pages, email, contact database, social, SEO, reporting and now ad management all in one system- and the benefits of that are many, not just because I am lazy.\r"}}
{"author": ["Daniel S"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Account Director", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is very user-friendly and gets the job done. We use hubspot to automate our outbound email campaigns. The data provided is very clean and easy to digest. ", "What do you dislike?": "It does not have that many integrations with other platforms. The Salesforce integration is very useful but would love to be able to integrate into other solutions. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "This is a great product to help businesses automate their marketing process. It is not the most comprehensive but probably the most user-friendly.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automate outbound email marketing. We do not have to hire as many staff to control our email marketing."}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 28, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Workflow tool - a simple drag and drop design which makes it easy to create sophisticated workflows.", "What do you dislike?": "You don't get beautiful looking emails out of the box - there's a lot of development required to in the back end to create consistent, eye-catching templates. Even once that's done the framework is quite rigid.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's not a market leader for no reason. Definitely a tool you should consider when conducting automation analysis.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Cross-platform visibility into user behaviour. Now we can track our leads and their activity across multiple sub-domains and intervene with timely, personalized emails."}}
{"author": ["Agency in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 15, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hotspot offers endless resources for learning, guidance,  and inspiration within their marketing tools making mastering all they have to offer as easy as possible. ", "What do you dislike?": "After taking several of their classes,  I feel some of the content gets very repetitive. They have so much to offer, I feel the classes could be broken up as shorter videos that are less repetitive from each other, and easier to get through. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "A great tool if you are willing to put in the time to get all you can out of it.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": " It has sped up, managed, and tracked our inbound marketing strategies."}}
{"author": ["Internal Consultant"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 08, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Their customer service. I can get a representative on the phone or on a chat within 5 minutes for whatever problem I'm having or random question I have.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes their updates take some time to adapt to, and I wish we had the choice to stay with some of the older versions. Not a big deal, but it just takes time to find things that you used to know where they were.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation, email marketing, report analyzation, all in one"}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 26, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Templates are easy to use and much more effective than traditional mail merges. On the sales side, being able to see all of your deals in one place is so much more efficient and easy to stay organized.  Hubspot has truly transformed my outbound activities and created more inbound opportunities as well.  ", "What do you dislike?": "Hard to say, if I had to nitpick it would be that when you send an email to multiple people it loses some tracking functionality. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Find the challenges in your current methods and try Hubspot free version, if your efficiency improves then it's worth the upgrade.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Efficiency was the issue prior to sing Hubspot, mail merges were ineffective and day to day tasks like managing deals, tasks ect. were just not effective in general.  The benefits are less bounce backs and more inbound leads.   "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Many integrations, functionality supports almost everything you need to do. Some workarounds are necessary, but as long as you understand everything the software can do, you'll be in great shape to obtain all the data you need to report on just about any sales/marketing/support activity.", "What do you dislike?": "Some basic features are still unavailable, expected to be addressed in time. Wish the workflow functionality was built out to be a little bit more robust at a base level so not as many workarounds were necessary.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Dynamic content marketing to a repeatable, scalable sales process - Organization of contacts and deals is very intuitive and lends to a collaborative environment."}}
{"author": ["User in Education Management"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is a way to help with organizing businesses and non-profits into what they're known for. For us, we track volunteers, schools, demographics of students, and the population we serve. This is all segmented into different categories, and by staff members as well. ", "What do you dislike?": "It's a bit difficult to navigate the many features of HubSpot, as well as formally adding deals, projects/tasks to it as well.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're solving our volunteer numbers, and impact that we're creating through it, as well, as allowing ourselves to track the number of schools, students, and volunteers we serve. "}}
{"author": ["Kate H"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Founder", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Sep 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It\u2019s easy to navigate and aesthetically clean. Makes it easy to get in and get out.", "What do you dislike?": "The desktop site is significantly more thorough than my mobile options it seems.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead tracking and communication. Everyone is on the same page now and I myself know where things stand."}}
{"author": ["Andy  L"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Assistant "], "date": ["Apr 30, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how it keeps track of all our client and guests that want to attend an event. ", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes it does mess up, and will put our clients into the wrong folder or event. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Organization "}}
{"author": ["User in Publishing"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 27, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": " Although I do not use every feature, some of my favorites are the ease of uploading lists, exporting content, and tracking email to see who has opened them. ", "What do you dislike?": " I\u2019m not in love with contacts and companies being separate, for my use it would be helpful that they are connected more easily.  I have a workaround for this when I add my own lists. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The free stuff is a no brainer. The paid services are pricey for very small businesses. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": " One of the most important things is being able to track who has opened my email. I am off and sending introductory messages, or proposals. I like to know who\u2019s actually looking at it so I can follow up in a timely and relevant way  "}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User in Market Research"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We're grateful to our customers whose votes have garnered awards for the HubSpot platform on Gartner Peer Insights, G2, TrustRadius & more. We are more improved than We have a few different fields that need to be updated when a lead becomes a customer. When the sales who we send product update emails to when we want to update our customers specifically about something.", "What do you dislike?": "Those fields are used in lists that determine who we send product update emails to when we want to update our customers specifically about something every lapping stuff. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "No advice likely. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are not. Facing any time of problem. "}}
{"author": ["Dan F"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Account Executive", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Sep 28, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like having the ability to track which of my emails are getting received by my prospects.  Additionally, it gives me near instant feedback on which email campaigns are working and which ones are not and how I can change it on the fly.", "What do you dislike?": "I wish it had the ability to track multiple emails within one email.  It seems as if anytime I bcc anyone on an email it will just show up as someone viewed your email which does not help me too much.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Go all In or don't use the tool.  You will not see the benefits if you dont buy the entire suite and actually buy into the technology.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helps maximize the efficiency of my time by allowing me to delay when emails are going out so I can no work on more flexible hours."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "User interface\r", "What do you dislike?": "Clear navigation\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Easy testing\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Self-help recommendations"}}
{"author": ["Kirsty A"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Operations Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Fast, easy to use, intelligent. Automation is very useful ", "What do you dislike?": "Lots of features only available on the marketing package which is expensive ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It\u2019s brilliant. Highly recommend ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Organisation, communication "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really like having the ability to build out landing pages and forms, and trigger workflows based on a wide variety of parameters - I feel like I can trigger a workflow for almost anything.", "What do you dislike?": "There are some real limitations to reporting that have made it difficult to see the performance of our emails on anything more than the most basic level. I have to filter by dates and then copy and paste into excel because there is no export option. There is no option at all to view the performance of personalized body content. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have used landing pages to create pages on our own when we were stretched for development hours internally. I really like using forms to capture customer feedback and data. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Internet"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 29, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot's blog is an easy setup thanks to their support team. They scraped our site to mimic our branding and theme which was great and took a load of work off of our plate. A feature I really enjoyed for creating blog posts was the ability to get optimization tips which really helps with SEO.", "What do you dislike?": "For me, HubSpot is trying to be something much larger than what it actually is. Their sales team reallllllly tries to sell you on the entire package, which is massive,extremely expensive, and completely unnecessary unless you are a giant company. It was very obvious when they made backend changes to the platform because everything immediately became extremely buggy (and without communication around these changes, it was very frustrating). ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Do your research and make sure this is the correct product for the problem you are trying to solve. They tried to push their expensive, all-inclusive package on us multiple times and with a little research, we figured out that we were eligible for the start-up package, which was 90% off! While blogging platform did as it said, it wasn't extremely intuitive and could be rather frustrating when attempting to create/publish a heavy text AND image post.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We mainly implemented HubSpot as a blogging platform with the hopes of also exploring and possibly implementing their CRM and other marketing/sales features. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 11, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Simple and easy to use. Excellent and friendly customer support.", "What do you dislike?": "Data security. I feel it is very open. As a business we need more control over users like restricting access outside office. It would be good if we can secure customers data.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great for startup business who has limited experience and money", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing and sales automation. Its a great and easy to use tool for building workflow for team."}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 15, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is by far the best marketing automation software I have ever used. The price is affordable, the capacity is almost unlimited, and the automation/drip campaign capabilities are easy to utilize. At my first job out of college I was able to setup complex automation email trees and blast 10,000+ leads per month. It was far easier and cheaper than Marketo. ", "What do you dislike?": "Keeping data clean, cross-checking, and ensuring prospects do not get double touched can be difficult. Large teams often find themselves stepping on top of each other. Segmentation is a error-prone process....", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Consider this as a a secondary CRM, a separate silo, it's best used as a separate silo if you have SalesForce.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot took the pain and headache out of sending news letters and followup emails. I was able to touch the entire database of contacts once or twice per month with a few clicks of a button. It was beautiful. "}}
{"author": ["Adam R"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["COO"], "date": ["Jul 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The support function is fantastic. Always responsive and usually very useful. \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I've used it frequently as some of the design tools aren't always the most intuitive. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Higher Education"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The flexibility of Hubspot is tremendous. It's a one-stop shop, in many cases, for digital advertising needs. While Hubspot can function as an email marketing tool, leveraging the automated workflows and lead scoring elevates the tool to an impressive level. And if you have a question or problem, Hubspot's support team is one of the fastest I have seen!", "What do you dislike?": "As Hubspot grows, it continues to fracture its pricing model and hide more and more features behind \"Add-on\" paywalls. It is disappointing to see these previously free tools made inaccessible. In addition, turnover seems to be high at Hubspot HQ as we have had a new account rep every year that I have been a customer.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot makes automated marketing accessible for a smaller operation like ours. It augments the abilities of our over-taxed marketing and sales teams."}}
{"author": ["Agency in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 10, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really enjoy their social media integration when using this platform, it allows you to see how others are reacting to your posts and what times you should be posting to engage with your followers effectively.", "What do you dislike?": "Support isn't the best, I have contacted them twice about issues and it seems as if they just copy and paste what's in the FAQ's when you ask for help on a topic.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It is a fairly easy tool to use, I would recommend you spend some time messing around with the features before you start creating anything serious with it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use Hubspot for creating buyer personas, blogs, and social media. I love that almost every social media platform is available for use with their software and they recently added Instagram as well! "}}
{"author": ["Kathleen B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Coordinator", "Commercial Real Estate"], "date": ["Dec 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It\u2019s easy to manage everything in one place, including email campaigns, contacts, social media and more.", "What do you dislike?": "They are still beta testing some things so some things don\u2019t work how I\u2019d always like. They are very helpful and have great support though. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We can manage all of our email campaigns and everything else really in one place, including leads and contacts. "}}
{"author": ["Derek J"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Vice President of Marketing", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Nov 05, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "So many things to name:\r", "What do you dislike?": "- Everything you need is under one roof -- blogging, landing pages, call to action buttons, CRM, social media posting and monitoring, competitor tracking, and so much more\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "- Their support has always been great, nearly resolving our questions on the first call every time. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "- Continious updates - they have an ideas forum so you can recommend feature enhancements and see which ideas they are working on"}}
{"author": ["Georgi M"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 18, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Very easy to use and great support. All the tools are pretty straightforward and require minimal technical skills.", "What do you dislike?": "Lacking some functionality around advanced lead scoring, multi-touch attribution and dynamic content.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation, landing page creation, email sending and design. We have automated several lead follow-up processes and content delivery. "}}
{"author": ["Andrew H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Graphic Designer", "Media Production"], "date": ["Mar 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There are so many features that work together and they are rolling out new tools and improvements all the time.", "What do you dislike?": "It can be hard to understand how all the tools work together.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "CRM, Digital Marketing, Tracking"}}
{"author": ["Patrick N"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Researcher & Data Associate", "Graphic Design"], "date": ["Dec 15, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I am enthralled by its multipurpose use. For instance, you can call your contacts directly, you can track those who visit your website as business prospects and leads. I like it very much and i am when I use it because of its intuitiveness. I also like the fact that you can have data or information of your business prospects safe in hubspot ", "What do you dislike?": "I do not dislike anything about it but it requires some training to become an expert", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Very intuitive and efficient", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We now easily identify  the possible business leads by tracking those who visit our website"}}
{"author": ["Ashley  J"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like having everything in one place as a one-woman marketing team! ", "What do you dislike?": "The styling restraints!!! It is frustrating not being able to move things around easily on landing pages, emails, etc. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "All of our marketing efforts website hosting, social media, email campaigns, landing pages, sales CRM, blogs, etc."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 14, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "There are a lot of general features (email, landing pages, forms) and reporting that is useful for my team.", "What do you dislike?": "Limitations in the email development platform. Dynamic/smart content functionality is limited to use within only Rich Text fields. Email development isn't flexible, custom coded modules are bulked up with extra and necessary causing a lot of code bloat. Simple features like email forwarding, or displaying preview text within the email is not available.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Being able to create landing pages without a full development team. My team has mentioned reporting benefits but as a developer I do not directly work with that data. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that HubSpot strives to make improvements to their system constantly and supports integrations with a number of other tools.", "What do you dislike?": "I would like for there to be more in-depth reporting functionality.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you want an easy to use system with great customer support, HubSpot is for you.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows us to hone in on the leads that will generate business through their easy to create workflows, as well as giving us insight into how effective our marketing efforts truly are."}}
{"author": ["Bridget D"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Social Media & PR Chair, Board Member", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Mar 21, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has second-to-none support and education they provide to users. They've helped me become an expert, and stay one.", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't really anything I can think of. Every now and then I run into a feature I wish HubSpot had, but even then I generally can connect with someone to find a solution.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Don't be afraid to use the tools, support, and education they provide you! They're there to help you... and they will! :) ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Marketing automation, analytics, strategy ... and more! "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(Myself Only)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 11, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the lead capture, tracking, and website A/B testing features.", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimed, I wiish it was completely FREE.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "There are a couple free versions you can start with until you need additional features.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot integrates with our website. Contact form submissions go directly to our call center reps.  As the Marketing Director, I appreciate the layer of accountability HubSpot provides.  Even if a Call Center rep fails to log a lead in our CRM, the HubSpot Marketing dashboard still logs all leads that have come in through subscription or contact form submissions.  So, we never miss a lead."}}
{"author": ["Paulo Diogo D"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Regional Operations Manager"], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Using the email tamplates directly on outlook 365", "What do you dislike?": "Some times the add crash on the outllook, and we neet to repeat the login", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Control all the leads in just one plataform."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 08, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use, intuitive and well organized. Support is easy to reach and quick to provide guidance. All of the features play well with each other and new integrations are provided often. Pricing is not user based so our organization can provide access to many individuals.", "What do you dislike?": "Certain features are buried within a few menus and require additional clicks to access. Deal tracking has limited view options and lacks the ability to track retainers or ongoing revenue.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Try the free options first and you will find that it is easy to implement.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use HubSpot for marketing automation, sales and deal tracking and as a CRM. Each of these functions works well with each other to provide a smooth experience."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the easy ability to post across multiple social media platforms, blog templates and customer development tools.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't like that we are missing a CRM tool that is HIPPA compliant.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are building our brand in our community with HubSpot through education with blogs and increasing awareness to special offers through CTAs, landing pages and social media campaigns."}}
{"author": ["Mara G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Manager", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jun 20, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's seamless. \r", "What do you dislike?": "They're always updating it to be better and more useful for their customers. \r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Their customer service is great and always willing to help you with the product.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I like how it aligns the sales and marketing  teams together.\r"}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 05, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how you don't have to be a web developer to create custom designs via HubSpot for landing pages, newsletters, forms emails, etc. I also like how powerful the Marketing portion of HubSpot is for our team!", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that customer service can be slow and uneducated on the platform depending who I talk to. There is also usually a pretty long wait time to get someone on the phone. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely, take advantage of the demos provided as well as the certifications offered (free). I found they were super helpful to me in getting to know/understanding the HubSpot Marketing Platform. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are solving cost associated issues because we use an extensive amount of software programs and since I came on, our team has been able to cut a ton of costs by taking advantage of the HubSpot power and broad tools offered to us through our service. "}}
{"author": ["Ethan W"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Sales and Operations Specialist", "Biotechnology"], "date": ["Jul 07, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like cross-platform integration the best. It easily syncs with email and allows me to transfer emails into contacts.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike how the different menus may not be intuitively obvious. I spend a fair amount of time wondering where things are.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helps us track our contacts and leads."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is an extremely modern platform that is constantly updating its design, as well as its features, to comply with the ever changing trends of marketing. I always feel that my content looks the best it could look, that I'm pulling all of the data that I need and that ", "What do you dislike?": "There are some restrictions when pulling reports.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are looking to dive deeper into your Marketing Analytics and streamline activity between your marketing and sales department, then HubSpot is the right platform for you. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can now handle all of my marketing out reach and sales follow up within one platform. "}}
{"author": ["Rebecca W"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 06, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Email tracking, amazing and quick support, easy blog publishing and analytics", "What do you dislike?": "Reports/dashboards could be better, when building the website some of the code is automatically populated in a way that is difficult/frustrating to someone with experience", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Able to analyze success of campaigns, built entire new website on the platform"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is easy to learn and has a lot of tools that are helpful for SEO, inbound marketing, and email marketing. The forums are helpful for users to connect over troubleshooting or tips.", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the tools are outdated or need to be updated.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our email list has grown exponentially since we started using HubSpot last summer. It is easy to make email marketing campaigns."}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot provides a lot of resources to really help those that aren't necessarily versed in marketing to the marketing professional who needs a basic solution to streamline Sales and Marketing. ", "What do you dislike?": "It feels dated and clunky. The integrations aren't very seamless. The idea is to replace HubSpot with other platforms, but it doesn't operate as well as those other platforms.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Perfect for SMBs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Streamlining Sales and Marketing. It's easy to create emails, landing pages, tracking, etc. It's pretty user friendly and provides a lot of training."}}
{"author": ["User in Textiles"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Abundant tools - allows you to build custom landing pages, track web visitor history, drip campaigns, etc.", "What do you dislike?": "The robustness of the program can sometimes make it difficult , or not so intuitive.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Probably the leader in inbound marketing automation, this tool can more than likely meet the needs of most organizations. Probably best to have a 3rd party assist with on-boarding, unless you are an experienced inbound marketer.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Inbound marketing to existing and new prospects. Allows us to automate email follow ups with interested prospects."}}
{"author": ["Angelique T"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": ["Independent Marketing Consultant", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Easy to use, excellent customer support, lots of flexibility and many options for personalization and tracking", "What do you dislike?": "email modules not as easy to work with as we'd like.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "lead gen"}}
{"author": ["Michael B"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Founder", "Public Relations and Communications"], "date": ["Nov 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I use the email tracking service the most.  It's great for following leads and knowing when to follow up with them.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that it costs so much to use every year.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Give it a try, if it benefits your company then it's worth the high cost every year.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Monitoring leads and pitches to publication editors with the email tracker.  It's helped us follow up when a lead is warm, and knowing when someone simply isn't opening our emails"}}
{"author": ["Fernando V"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Head of Marketing & Product Squad Leader", "Internet"], "date": ["Jan 27, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Web & Social Tracking, Reports & Dashboards and Integrations. \r", "What do you dislike?": "UI & UX Design needs urgent improvement. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are getting started and use PipeDrive's CRM switch to Hubspot's Sales Free. The integration between Marketing and Sales will improve your management and growth. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Problems: Lead Qualification and Integration between Marketing and Sales.\r"}}
{"author": ["Adam W"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Head of Marketing", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["May 15, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Having used Marketo, Pardot, and Eloqua before making the transition to HubSpot - I feel comfortable saying, HubSpot is the most dynamic and easiest to use out of the box, marketing automation solution on the market.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot's plethora of tools enables our marketing team to do everything from building site and landing pages, to managing social media, publishing blog articles, improving search engine optimization, building CTA's and measuring our success.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Suzanne D"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Inbound Marketing / Content Strategist (Consultant)", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Oct 28, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really like the concept behind Hubspot/Inbound Marketing.  If you're a company offering a product/service, you have information that is helpful to your potential customer.  Its just good karma to put it out to them so that as they search for information, you can help them and they can be predisposed to understand what you're product offers.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Their approach to Marketing Automation is unique (based on their Inbound Marketing religion ;-) and so your dashboard defaults to your \"persona's\" ie, your market segments, and how well you're doing with them.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Rachid E"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["President/IT Consultant", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Apr 12, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "None of the product component was easy to use, and you have to pay for training to learn their product. and worse you have to do all configuration yourself.", "What do you dislike?": "Too many components you need to configure and use, complex setup, you need to spend way too much time with no guarantee on result, also over priced", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Don't subscribe to this service, you will spend most of your time trying to learn the product with no guarantee on ROI, considering paying high price for just the product and more for training, and way too much time to learn it, it is not worth it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Was looking for simple marketing too, and this by no means simple and automated"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot does such a great job of visualizing marketing automation processes. From automating data or sending out drip campaigns, Hubpsot makes it eaaaasy. ", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspot's reporting isn't quite up to snuff with competitors. We get around some of that with their Lists function.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Connecting with all of our customers or prospective customers. Managing forms on landing pages. Marketing touches before passing in data to Salesforce."}}
{"author": ["Jihane K"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Online Acquisition Manager"], "date": ["Dec 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Great tool, with all must-have marketing automation features. Great onboarding and reactive support team", "What do you dislike?": "Pretty expensive, some basic features are not available in the enterprise edition (A/B) testing for example. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our data was not centralized and we were looking for a tool that integrates seamlessly with Salesforce. Now, we have one sing version on the truth in both interfaces."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Email creation is easy due to the templating ability.", "What do you dislike?": "Workflow creation and query building are not that complex.  Nest queries are not possible.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great all around tool.  If you need advanced query building and complex workflows than this is not the tool for you.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is the backbone of our marketing efforts.  We use it as the marketing database, we have created a lead scoring model to push the right leads to sales at the right time.  We utilize the tracking capabilities to calculate program and channel ROI.  We use the social features to schedule and manage all of our posts."}}
{"author": ["Lori M"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Director Of Development", "Non-Profit Organization Management"], "date": ["Nov 25, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I liked how easy it was to navigate the interface and to learn how to use the different features.", "What do you dislike?": "It could be challenging to get the reports torun at times. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Creating a smooth marketing pipeline with better response time for inquiries."}}
{"author": ["Consultant"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I like best in hubspot is the task creation tool since it keeps me updated if I need to reach out to the client again. ", "What do you dislike?": "The downside I'm experiencing in hubspot is that we cannot segregate the properties that we need for carrier and enterprise products.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easily track the deals assigned to me and contacts that i need to reach out to."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 29, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Everything works together very well together, mainly tied together by the workflows elements. You can see a whole load of information on users of your website, and take actions based off their behaviour. ", "What do you dislike?": "Quite expensive, especially to start out if you're interested in specific features. Worked well in my b2b role, but can't see it working as well in my new b2c work. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is mainly used for leadscoring for us, and it's forms functionality was used on our website for lead capture. It was really easy to imement and update, and Hubspot gives you back a great amount of detail. "}}
{"author": ["Prince A"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "For marketing automation software, there is only 1 software and that is Hubspot.\r", "What do you dislike?": "I have been using Hubspot for about 3-4 years now and I just love it.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I have used it for small businesses with 5-50 employees to Medium sized businesses with over 500 employees.\r"}}
{"author": ["User in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 03, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The upsides of Hubspot is that we can do all our work in 1 database (Hubspot). This has assisted our business greatly since integrating over to Hubspot, I myself use Social Media, and hubspot makes it very simple and easy to use for someone that has never had previous experience in scheduling content. Thanks hubspot! ", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't too much to not like, we have everything that we require to do our job in 1 place", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "For my primary job, We use hubspot for our data reports and deals. We use this to record our conversations with potential clients and for our revenue. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 18, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really liked starting with a free CRM and slowly building up to the paid features. It was a nice transition so once the gates opened and we were able to take advantage of all of the new paid features it wasn't overwhelming. We had a plan and knew what to do next.", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the UI can be a little cumbersome and not as intuitive as some other tools. It never entirely hindered our ability to work but sometimes it was frustrating. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It helped us get everything organized and in order. Our Marketing efforts were relatively scrappy and disorganized before, so moving to Hubspot made a big difference. "}}
{"author": ["Ouali B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["CEO & Founder", "Education Management"], "date": ["Oct 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Probably the best marketing platform for U.S market.", "What do you dislike?": "not very friendly in other languages / markets.  Hubspot still has work to do in spanish and portuguese speaking markets. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "great marketing crm to handle all your needs. I love the email template features connected to my gmail account.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I track my website traffic, emailings, and organize all my clients and leads in one place."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 25, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The best part about HubSpot is it's all-in-one capabilities. Being able to turn to one platform for social media, landing pages, analytics, workflows, email campaigns and more has turned out to be incredibly beneficial for our team.  ", "What do you dislike?": "The one flaw in HubSpot we've found so far is the capabilities in the email design and template tools. Sometimes it can be difficult to achieve the exact result we are looking for and often times the templates get wonky for no apparent reason. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "As a two-person marketing team, HubSpot has allowed us to complete a variety of our marketing efforts on one platform. Saving time and man power in the long run. "}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 24, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The email tracking capabilities and breakdown of site traffic allow marketers to understand the effectiveness of their marketing activities and campaigns.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Having inbuilt email and social media tools lessened the trouble taken to move between platforms and keep track of analytics from each.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
