{"author": ["Alba E"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "que me mantiene al d\u00eda de todos los movimientos de los usuarios de mi p\u00e1gina web", "What do you dislike?": "que hay veces en que se queda colgada la p\u00e1gina", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "al darme informaci\u00f3n de las visitas de los usuarios de mi p\u00e1gina, logro un algo porcetaje de ventas"}}
{"author": ["Gretchen R"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Independent Marketing Consultant", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jan 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is great for their information! The HubSpot Academy always has fresh content that is tapped into the newest trends in the digital marketing world. It is a go-to source for everything marketing. The HubSpot Blog always offers great perspectives, insights, and trending info. ", "What do you dislike?": "I don't use the inbound marketing service of HubSpot, so I really don't have anything to offer for this feature. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot does a great job of having their finger on the pulse. "}}
{"author": ["User in Human Resources"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 08, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Analytics on Hubspot allow you to see where your marketing efforts are best focused. This could be how many people are reading blogs or opening emails etc. This helps build an overall marketing strategy that is based on what works best. Basically it\u2019s the clarity it gives you that is best about Hubspot.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "The customer support is pretty top too. It\u2019s hard to put a price on the calls we have with our Customer Success Manager.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "This is only a small complaint as it's much harder to do this without Hubspot - but their social media multi posting system is quite clumsy. Needs a bit of work."}}
{"author": ["Jamie S"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Director", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Nov 29, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We were looking for a marketing automation tool to help us send targeted campaigns.  HubSpot hit the spot with it's ease of use and ability to automate campaigns.", "What do you dislike?": "A little more flexibility in the list management to better sort and create lists.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The ability to send targeted campaigns on behalf of our sales team, as well as pre-trade show emails. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Events Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 27, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the HubSpot support team. They are truly problem-solvers and can help you with any unique need or troubleshoot any issue. They are also always adding features and relying on user feedback to improve. ", "What do you dislike?": "I think the reporting at the Pro level could be improved. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use it for inbound and content marketing including blogging. We see an uptick in our digital leads and close-rate. Brand awareness is also much higher. "}}
{"author": ["Ashley D"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Associate", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Feb 01, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that it is easy to navigate, and easy to find things on the website.", "What do you dislike?": "There isn't anything I dislike about hubspot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We currently use HubSpot to post for social media as well as post blogs."}}
{"author": ["Maria S"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Events & Communications Manager"], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the ability to post to all platforms at once while also being able to make any necessary changed for each particular platform.  It is so nice to be able to see everything together on one screen.,=", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes the picture sizing can be annoying - usually have to have my graphic designer make tweaks.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Efficiently posting to social in a timely, well-thought way."}}
{"author": ["Logan H"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Owner"], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot keeps all of my contacts in order, documenting all of my conversations, documents, and deals. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish the flow of the email history was a little more clear. Sometimes it can be a bit repetitive in viewing prrevious emails.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "View point of email, touchpoint history within the contact or company page. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am solving my organization of pipeline, deals, and everything in between. "}}
{"author": ["Mark E"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Managing Director"], "date": ["Jul 07, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Beautiful interface, very easy to use. Was extremely easy to implement. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some functionality could be improved. Overall pretty good. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Much faster than waiting for an administrator as with other CRM's"}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I use Hubspot allows for quick and intuitive social media scheduling, however other team members use several of its other features. The social media report facility makes it easy to compare the results of social media activity and understand which channel had the most engagement.", "What do you dislike?": "Very often Hubspot's metrics are not accurate, as I noticed regularly comparing the engagement results that appear on my Hubspot reports and the \"likes\" effectively received on Facebook/LinkedIn/Twitter.  It's not a big deal to me at the moment, but I understand that it could be for other users. \r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Additionally, when you delete a post from Hubspot, it's still counted in the analytics even if it doesn't appear on the actual social media, lowering the average engagement-per-post results reported. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Consumer Goods"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 17, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The fact that the UI is so easy to follow and that the connectivity to other systems can be done with very little technical knowledge is awesome. ", "What do you dislike?": "I feel that there are things that HubSpot can do that would not require connectivity to other systems one simple things would be to do their own mail sends etc not use 3rd party.  Less mess. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "we are predominantly using it to see website traffic to see what local companies we can target.   No business realized yet as we are fairly new to the process and product. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The email tracking that stores and files messages that might otherwise be lost in a sea of emails is Hubspot\u2019s greatest feature.", "What do you dislike?": "I would prefer that Hubspot have a to-do list capability that would allow users to see all assigned tasks as a pop-up when first logging in.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is allowing Alliance Connection to effectively track client and partner interactions with precision that makes follow ups a breeze!"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 19, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I love about Hubspot is that it has help me better gauge the interest level of potential clients. No longer do I have to wonder if they have read an email.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't know if have any dislikes at this time.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "All you have to do is sign up for their free version and give it a run. You won't be disappointed unless you don't use it. Hubspot is a key component in our daily sales and marketing.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It has helped with sales, prospecting and follow up. The number one benefit is an increase in confidence when it comes to following up and keeping the lines of communication moving forward. "}}
{"author": ["User in Financial Services"], "company_size": ["(5001-10,000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 16, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "the availability of the details/activities of each contact, and the easiness to set up workflows.", "What do you dislike?": "you can't customize the lifecycle stage. and you are not allowed to send emails to contacts before they explicitly subscribe to your email (which can be a good thing for the audience). Also, their pricing is based on the # of contacts you store, which means the cost will keep increasing as long as you are growing your contact database. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "very easy to use, and they have great customer support", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "we used it for email marketing and content management"}}
{"author": ["Consultant in Higher Education"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The integration of  all systems into one and the overview and ease of use that follows. Eg. being able to work with e-mails, flows and lead capture in the same system.", "What do you dislike?": "The individual systems are not as sexy and sleek as dedicated services eg. MailChimp for e-mail and InstaPage for landingpages. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The agility of being able to make use of the system \"from day one\" because of the integration with our websites and social ads. The relative ease of testing out different ways of capturing leads."}}
{"author": ["Agency in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 13, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has a really great free option. I can add client info, initiate deals, assigner users and can keep up with all of the basic management needs for my clients. ", "What do you dislike?": "I wish that some of the free features were a little more robust. I do have to use HubSpot in conjunction with other software and it would be nice to have a fuller solution, but I can't really complain because I'm not paying anything for it :) ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows me to keep track of client info, set followups, schedule meetings and assign tasks to my team.  "}}
{"author": ["Craig J"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Connection Strategist", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Aug 31, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The Hubspot platform is easy to use and is intuitive, but allows for quick learning and deeper dives into the software to get more out of the service and platform.  New features are added on a regular basis.", "What do you dislike?": "Lead Scoring has been improved in the last year and has a little bit of a learning curve.  A few more updates to lists could be incorporated.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use all the tools that are available to get the best use of the product.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Inbound lead generation and segmenting customers into the funnel.  Lead Generation and having marketing and sales work with the product together."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that Hubspot has a clean interface and great integrations.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that the contacts are separated from the record itself. I wish that there were an easier way to see a full list of the company contact and a quick glance at last interaction at the company level. I also dont like that with the gcal integration the edits you make to the invite in hubspot are reflected on the prospects side of the invite.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Don't count on always having access as I often find it inaccessible. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Account Management"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot has a wealth of resources to teach you not only the software but the sales and marketing best practices that maximize the efficiency of using HubSpot.", "What do you dislike?": "HubSpot has taken a long time to understand the begin using practically. It's overwhelming for a small company with no dedicated IT department.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to analyze our website, email and social media traffic and segment our contacts easily."}}
{"author": ["Sophie K"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Sales and marketing operations"], "date": ["Jan 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love seeing the online internet activity of our leads ", "What do you dislike?": "You can't tap into CRM functions and export all data you need", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We do all lead and deal tracking in HS and maintain system of record here "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "How easy to navigate it is. Being able to switch between the everything right from the workflow I am working on is very nice.", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing really, so far I haven't run into anything I don't like.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It makes marketing automation very easy.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easy email automation, we do a lot of webinars and Hubspot makes marketing these events very easy through emails/landing pages. "}}
{"author": ["Jordon S"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development Account Executive", "Financial Services"], "date": ["Feb 23, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Very simple and cost-effective. You certainly get what you pay for. ", "What do you dislike?": "Not much functionality in regards to reporting. I still don't know how to update someone's email address. The import is a total burden. You can't drill down on any reports. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Again, you totally get what you pay for. It's a cost-effective solution. I have pushed for Salesforce since I've been here at Divvy. It's fine, but as we grow and scale we will need to get something better because this simply doesn't cut it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Typical sales CRM. Tracking deals, contact information, etc. "}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "- Easy to use\r", "What do you dislike?": "- The marketplace has templates you can use\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "- Covers social media, email, and blog all in once\r"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The Hubspot Support Team is always there when I need them. When I needed help they replied within 24 hours.", "What do you dislike?": "When we were receiving e-mails in the inbox, we couldn't forward the e-mail with the attached files and had to download and add them again. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Everything is in one place, I have a great overview. We can solve almost every problem of the marketing daily routine."}}
{"author": ["Tom J"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Founder and Director", "Environmental Services"], "date": ["Nov 20, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "All the info you need is in one place and it fulfills all your mayor marketing needs. good web management needs.", "What do you dislike?": "Their support is not great. Sometimes there are glitches with emails.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Easy to design website and generated inbound leads."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["User in Apparel & Fashion"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 03, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "What I liked best was the classes and certification options that Hubspot has available. I'm now certified in inbound and Mobile marketing and It's given me a ton of leverage in my job search.", "What do you dislike?": "I had a love hate relationship with the video aspects of the learning process. On one hand I loved them because many people are visual learners but on the other hand I found myself drifting off and getting distracted often during the longer 20+ minute videos.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Maybe have less video's and add more interactive questions. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot really helps simplify the information overload that comes with being a digital marketer. By having all the tools needed to not only learn but do Hubspot is a great all in one platform to help excel. "}}
{"author": ["Emily G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Art Director", "Computer & Network Security"], "date": ["Nov 10, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The Hubspot support staff is always timely and extremely knowledgeable and the tool itself is easy to use. ", "What do you dislike?": "The calendar tool seems like it should integrate better with the projects tool for project management, but they're pretty separate. Project management is one of the few tools my department uses other software for even though most tasks involve Hubspot. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Whether your marketing department has experience with prior automation tools or not, Hubspot cannot be matched in terms of continuous updates, support knowledge, and lead generation tools. It's absolutely worth the investment. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Lead generation and reporting are the largest benefits"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Wireless"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how HubSpot is able to house both marketing and sales information making it easy to store all of our activities in one data base. ", "What do you dislike?": "Once you start to integrate HubSpot you need to change all platforms to be HubSpot compatible.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are using to track sales and marketing efforts and measure ROI. It is extremely effective in helping to add visibility to how our teams operate and maximizing results."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the design of Hubspot. user experience is good and easy to figure out. Also the chat / customer service people are very helpful", "What do you dislike?": "When automating an email, I wish you could select a time to send out the emails instead of just delaying it by a certain number of days. Would be great if I could select a day of the week or time of day to send the emails out.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Automating emails to better keep in contact with customers. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 27, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I have been using the new view for over a month now. I feel that the layout provides quicker access between contacts, deals and company information. There is a lot less scrolling now. If you properly keep your HubSpot records clear, the new layout will increase efficiency. I also like the introduction of 'Products' and hope to take advantage of it soon.", "What do you dislike?": "The Email window is a little clunky. The sizing and scrolling within that window is touchy. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows our marketing and sales team to succeed at high levels by providing an easy to use and manage CRM. As HubSpot continues to develop,  our lead to close time continues to get better by using sales tools such as sequences, snippets, queues and task to name a few."}}
{"author": ["User in Outsourcing/Offshoring"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 09, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a very useful tool for tracking contact and deal activities", "What do you dislike?": "Filters in the dashboard are very restricted. I think it needs more flexibility ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Hubspot is a powerful tool for lead/deal management", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Deal activities and monitoring - you can easily track deal activities and it makes life easier for our Sales Team. Task/deal assignment is also a powerful tool in deal management."}}
{"author": ["Alison S"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Creative Content Lead", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 21, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love that for such an expansive, dynamic platform it rarely runs amuck. I experience little to no disruptions in connectivity or productivity. ", "What do you dislike?": "I live in the Content part of the portal, and I wish it had a more intuitive interface for content creation and entry, akin to Grammarly or HemingwayApp. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It has a function for everyone on your team. It's a no-brainer for a cross-functional team. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I'm looking at 2018 as the year of the Content Pillar, and HubSpot's going to help me get there with its add-on on topic to the dashboard and content degree. "}}
{"author": ["Grace W"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Corporate Marketing Communications Specialist", "Insurance"], "date": ["Oct 03, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Education/Training - The HubSpot Academy is an amazing resource. You learn the ins and outs of every tool in HubSpot and tips for best use. You can also select a project by goal to get step by step advice.", "What do you dislike?": "Social Media Analytics - You only get analytics for posts through HubSpot and you can't post more than one photo to Facebook through the system. So anytime we have a post that includes a few photos, we have to do it through Facebook and the analytics don't get synced with HubSpot. We don't really get to use the social media reporting tools for that reason.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot is used by our marketing department to attract and convert leads. Previously, we used separate vendors for email marketing, social media and blogging. Now we use HubSpot for everything."}}
{"author": ["Executive Sponsor in Management Consulting"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 12, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ability to easily build campaigns and the use of pillar pages to management marketing content", "What do you dislike?": "The recent phase out of embedded SEO analytics has been a pain. The solutions was more valuable with Google like analytics support. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Study your marketing process and workflow before you buy and implement. Document as much of the process as possible. This is a flexible and robust platform; it can adapt to changes but planning saves a lot of headache later.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Inbound Content marketing, traditional email campaigns, lead nurturing.  "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the convenience of the dashboard and different tools, as well as the built-in reporting", "What do you dislike?": "The apps for mobile and tablet aren't sufficient versions of the desktop version, and since i want to do a lot of my marketing work on my iPad Pro on the road, this gets really frustrating", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are managing our customers and helping uncover issues with accountability with our sales team"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Hospital & Health Care"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 03, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot was a great platform for getting started with inbound marketing, specifically lead gereration. It is relatively easy to use, the setup process is pretty straightforward, and the SEO functions are probably the best of any other solution. ", "What do you dislike?": "After the first year, they transitioned us to a new account manager who really stopped caring about us as an account. You could tell their support was starting to lack and we kept having to find workarounds for everything we were doing, especially as it related to the SalesForce integration. It was frustrating that our CRM and Marketing Automation tools didn't quite communicate as well as they wanted to and the longer our program went, the more our inside team struggled to get the information they needed to follow up on the inbound leads. Also, upon completion of our first year, the product become so expensive it was really difficult to justify keeping it. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are a SalesForce user just know that the integration is not really that amazing. But if you don't use SalesForce and if you just want to start blogging and generating inbound leads, this is great! ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allowed us to create strategies around inbound lead generation. It helped cut our content promotion budget because we were able to promote our content to a wide audience much easier. The blog functionality and SEO features were also really helpful in understanding what it took to rank higher on search engines and reach a higher volume of potential customers. Additionally, the marketing email tool was much easier to use than what we were previously utilizing through SalesForce. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Oil & Energy"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Leaving notes on each customer, included the automated emails that are saved and phone calls logged without me having to do any extra work.", "What do you dislike?": "Seems like there is some functionality missing. It's a very broad software, so there are no industry specific components.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use it!! There's no harm in trying, since most features are free. Great product!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We needed a way to organize our contacts on a low budget, and HubSpot has exceeded our expectations and been a huge help!"}}
{"author": ["Agency"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 17, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The flexible template builder for website pages.", "What do you dislike?": "Wish there was more flexibility in changing design/layout directly in a page as opposed to creating new templates for every different layout. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Problem: How to create a custom looking website using a free template pack. Benefits: I've realized it's very easy to create new layouts and edit css to get a more customized look and feel for our client."}}
{"author": ["Ashley C"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing and Data Analytics Intern", "Market Research"], "date": ["Apr 04, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ability to schedule marketing posts on various platforms and track the success.", "What do you dislike?": "Can be overwhelming to navigate without training.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Utilize the help from Hubspot customer support. They are super helpful!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Using the analytics tools, we are able to compare marketing reach from working with an agency to in house marketing efforts."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 13, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The intuitive, easy to use UI is what makes HubSpot stand out. It allows marketers to implement sophisticated workflows and create emails and web pages without having a strong technical knowledge or rely on a technical team. ", "What do you dislike?": "The Design Manager can be tricky to use for a marketer who has limited coding experience. It's also quite expensive for a small business.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are now able to easily create involved nurturing email campaigns, have all our marketing and sales analytics in one place, and maintain up-to-date and valuable CRM data."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 22, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I'm on the marketing side most and I love the automation and workflows that can be created and ultimately provides a nice user experience.", "What do you dislike?": "It can get very deep technically and set up is the hardest, most time consuming part. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "All my marketing in one place keeps me organized and better able to assess how our marketing campaigns and strategies are performing."}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 10, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Works pretty well for automating events such as setting campaigns and syncing with Salesforce / CRM data. Fairly customizable based on what your business needs. ", "What do you dislike?": "Not very robust with the CRM and CMS portion of the product. Doesn't really support scaling over 100k contacts. CMS is limited and will require custom code if you want to make a website. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It tries to be a lot of things, but doesn't necessarily do any of them VERY well. Definitely good for smaller businesses, but it is difficult to scale with. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "-Email marketing \r"}}
{"author": ["User in Public Relations and Communications"], "company_size": [], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 25, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The large database of contacts was very useful, and the 'deal' function was also very useful. It allowed us to keep up to date with our PR requests from our influencers very efficiently. ", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes, the process of inputting contacts and creating deals could be time-consuming. An option to add a deal whilst adding a contact would be much more efficient. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would definitely recommend other companies to use Hubspot but bear in mind that it does take some getting used to. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot has allowed us as a company to keep track of our contacts and our deals. It has helped us keep track on our current PR requests very well, and it is great to have everything we need in one place. "}}
{"author": ["User in Higher Education"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 27, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It was awesome being able to see when and where my emails were read.  Being in sales, it's hard to know if people are just ignoring my email or if my email is going straight to junk and I am unaware.  It was nice having the reassurance that my email delivered and someone actually read it.", "What do you dislike?": "It really messed up my emails and my sales tactics.  I use apple mail, and we later found out that Apple mail did not support this extension.  Hubspot would add a HUGE link to the end of all my emails and I had no idea this was happening until someone responded and told me.  This then caused confusion and made me look very unprofessional.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you are using HubSpot for the email reading feature, I highly recommend not using with Apple Mail. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It really helped knowing if my emails were going to junk or to their inbox.  It gave me a better idea of what time of day sales emails were read as well. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 21, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot makes is easy to manage our website even if you don't have much web development experience. It's simple and intuitive and it can scale as your company grows into many other areas such as sales and support.", "What do you dislike?": "There have been cases when the platform doesn't suit our specific need, for instance in the case of setting up a chatbot given to a certain scenario. However these cases are rare and they are usually just small inconveniences.  ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot helps us solve many marketing tasks ranging from social media management, website, blog and content management to CRM. The marketing department works more efficiently and due to the platform's analytics, we are constantly improving our work. "}}
{"author": ["Nathan Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Digital Marketing", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Jul 31, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot brings all the things you do into one space, saving time, money, and headaches. ", "What do you dislike?": "They're reporting is good, but I'd like the add-on reporting features to be standard. At their price-point, I feel like that value should be expected.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you're wary, start with the basic and move into the professional as it blows you away. Use your support at Hubspot. They want to help. They really do.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are solving the problems of easy collaboration and tracking what is really working. The benefits are better communication, more time spent on good, effective content, and less frustration with platforms not working together."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot makes it easy to publish content and track results from that content. I love the marketplace to try new templates for emails and landing pages. I also love how they truly seem to listen to customers about changing they want to see. ", "What do you dislike?": "I would like reporting that was a little more comprehensive. I want data that is a little more granular. \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I also wish they would work on Lead Flows. It\u2019s a cool tool, but it should be able to integrate with Hubspot forms. I also wish the Lead Flow could simply be a floating CTA that visitors could click on without having to fill out form."}}
{"author": ["Adam H"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing Director"], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The platform makes testing a breeze! Publishing, editing, and creating a consistency of experience for my users.", "What do you dislike?": "I think the design tools could be strengthened. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Highly recommended! Best tool in the business, I've implemented it in two companies and for my own small business! The Support is phenomenal, the implementation is smooth, and the growth potential is what's needed for long term relationships. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "New client on-boarding."}}
{"author": ["Lyssa T"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketplace Analyst", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Dec 07, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's super easy to schedule social posts and duplicate posts across channels. ", "What do you dislike?": "Literally nothing. There are some features that I'd love to see them roll out in the future, but they are continuously innovating and changing things up so I know it's only a matter of time.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email marketing, landing page creation, social media posting, blog writing/maintenance, SEO optimizations---the list goes on and on."}}
{"author": ["Mike P"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Contract: Marketing Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Dec 29, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot CRM provides all the features I need to manage customer relationships at a price that's right - $0!", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing much to dislike. It does what it says on the tin..", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you're looking for free CRM, HubSpot is great.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Allows me to manage my customer relationships easily, and syncs with my marketing automation platform nicely."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 13, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Having my tracking, publishing, sales reporting, contact database and web development all in one system", "What do you dislike?": "They have monetized it very well. you get to use some really excellent features such as sales pro up and contacts up to a limit before it then gets really costly to increase capacity.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We have been able to properly co-ordinate our Sales and marketing efforts"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 11, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the email builder the best, although it has some very frustrating elements to editing that need to be addressed. ", "What do you dislike?": "The automation needs work. Campaign progress needs work, big time. You cannot clearly see who is getting what email, and when, and what is next for the, etc. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Only purchase this platform if you have the resources to use it 100%, not 90% or less. Get a lighter weight solution if you do not intend to use ALL of the features available to you on Hubspot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We've used it very well for landing pages, forms, webinars, and more."}}
{"author": ["Marian R"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Social Media & Community Engagement Executive", "Consumer Electronics"], "date": ["Oct 25, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot offers a visual dashboard with a real-time view of the entire sales funnel. Users can track customer interactions automatically through email, social media or phone calls and every interaction is stored in a timeline organized by lead.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot enables users to create and manage email templates and track how well those emails are performing. The solution can also send real-time notifications for events such as when a contact opens an email or downloads an attachment."}}
{"author": ["Dan E"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Director", "Design"], "date": ["Jun 03, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The integration of many pieces of software", "What do you dislike?": "Inability to post video's to instagram is a little bit of an issue..... also waiting for Linkedin integration!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Packaging up so many pieces of software into one spot, with the ability for the team to get across all elements with ease."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 22, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how user friendly HubSpot is. It is really easy to get familiar with and they have great courses to help you with best practices and how to use them on their platform.", "What do you dislike?": "I would like a spot to find the sources for landing pages as a whole not just by individual page.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot can be used for both beginners and experienced marketers. I can say enough how user-friendly it is.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We like being able to easily add landing pages and track who is filling those out."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 15, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Very easy to manage all of your leads and create multi-email sequences that send out automatically. Also, provides great feedback and analytics on how a lead is interacting with your emails and the historic communication with every lead in the system. ", "What do you dislike?": "Design opportunities are limited when it comes to email creation. Can't function properly as an email campaign software which would be more valuable for the companies I've worked with.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If you're looking for an email mass marketing tool, then I recommend going with MailChimp. If you are looking to organize your leads and conversations, go with Hubspot. Ideally, a Hubspot/Mailchimp combo would service everything you need. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Managing, generating, and interacting with quality leads. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 02, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It is a great software that has just gotten better.  They are adding more features all the time. Much easier to setup than salesforce, but does a lot more than most other tools.  Used to be just for marketing, but not handles all CRM stuff as well.", "What do you dislike?": "Apparently no way to export your data.  They release new features often, but maybe some before they should have, as things can be a little buggy.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We needed an easy way to get our CRM, marketing automation, and customer workflows in one place, this does that."}}
{"author": ["User in Internet"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 15, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like how you can set up workflows and create forms, etc. I use it a lot to send automated emails in response to someone submitting a form on a website.", "What do you dislike?": "Hubspots integration with splash & salesforce can be a little tricky sometimes. I'm an event coordinator and we use splash to register people for events. Sometimes when someone submits their info via splash, hubspot will change their contact info and you have to go in and see what happened.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We use it for a lot of marketing related functions. We also use it as our main salesforce integration from various other platforms."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 14, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Not only is HubSpot's interface user-friendly (they are always improving the design so it gets easier and easier to use over time), but their tech support is amazing! Very helpful AND, most of all -- especially for an extremely busy marketer that needs decisions made quickly -- very responsive.", "What do you dislike?": "There are several technical areas that can be improved upon or implemented that are pretty basic in terms of a typical marketer's day-to-day reporting and workflow needs.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The ability for deep prospect intel really allows our marketing and sales teams to know what marketing initiatives are working and what our prospects are interested in."}}
{"author": ["Lawrence K"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": ["Vice President of Marketing", "Information Technology and Services"], "date": ["Jul 26, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Having a free CRM solution for basic needs is very helpful. The connections to other applications work and we are able to customize to a point to fit our basic needs", "What do you dislike?": "As a free service, it is hard to dislike anything. One could ask for more features within the free version, but that is it.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Needed an interim marketing CRM solution and this has served that purpose"}}
{"author": ["Gillian N"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Junior Talent Manager", "Internet"], "date": ["Feb 23, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the fact you can track analytics and it keeps you organized and on track", "What do you dislike?": "I feel like there should be a more smooth interface. Maybe some help guides to utilize it better.  A way of shortlisting candidates for a data base (mapping them out).", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "smoother process ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "none at the moment"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 30, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a great place to keep contacts and leads organized and top of mind. I love the deal screen where you can see what stage a prospect is in and quickly determine what you can do to move them to the next stage. ", "What do you dislike?": "There isn\u2019t much to dislike about Hubspot. It is very user friendly and intuitive. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am able to keep tasks associated with business development organized so that I can easily see what needs to get done each day. "}}
{"author": ["Terence B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Senior SEO Executive", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 02, 2016"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Its simple to use and provides a great interface! It requires little training and theirs so many online resources for training. \r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The integration makes life easier, whether it's SEO, lead management, blogging or CTAs. Hubspot is a great all in one solution. \r"}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 19, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We use Hubspot for our marketing campaigns and publishing social media and tracking website visits and for blogging. It's very easy to use (especially compared to past products). I really like how it's good for SEO, it suggests you different blog titles or keywords to make sure every piece of content or email is SEO optimized!", "What do you dislike?": "Sometimes we find minor issues, like you can't exclude competitors automatically, you have to manually do it for each email campaign you send out. These are all minor issues with the tool that we hope will be fixed in the future.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Before we used Hubspot, we were using Marketo. However, Hubspot had a great onboarding program and we also used their consultants to help us come up with a good marketing strategy to bring more inbound leads and nurture \"outbound\" leads from trade shows and other sources. The blogging tool helped increase brand awareness and SEO."}}
{"author": ["Savannah H"], "company_size": [], "role": ["Founder", "Sports"], "date": ["Mar 05, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I wouldn\u2019t know, even after calling tech support multiple times, it still doesn\u2019t allow me to log in.", "What do you dislike?": "I CAN\u2019T LOG IN. Tech support has been completely useless altogether, I\u2019ve never been able to manage my client email base. It has been a nightmare since day one.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "STAY FAR AWAY.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "My coworkers seem to like it when it works for them. I seriously have no idea what it even really does."}}
{"author": ["User in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Feb 19, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The analytics in Hubspot are awesome. The second you send an email, you can start seeing in real time the open rates, click rates, etc and drill down to exactly who is doing what. ", "What do you dislike?": "The email templates are not as user friendly as I\u2019d like but once you build out a template you like it\u2019s pretty easy and intuitive. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Overall it is great tool especially for inbound marketing. It is a little more difficult with outbound tasks that should be easy. However, with time you can figure out workarounds and once you do that you are set. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Creating more pipeline for our sales team. The benefits I\u2019ve seen is that with various workflows and real time data, we are able to work smarter and produce impactful campaigns "}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 17, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the visuals, and the ability to pull reports out of the UI. Other than that, it's not really the best platform. There's not a lot a like about it. For certain purposes I'm sure it works better than others, but for the purpose running paid search campaigns in AdWords and Bing, it's pretty non-functional.", "What do you dislike?": "I don't like how it's difficult to view paid search results specifically on the platform. The views available are not really set up to be able to easily optimize. If they could mimic the AdWords UI a bit more that would be helpful. I also really do not like how you reports or exports get emailed to you. I wish they would just download straight from the engine. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Definitely don't rely on it as a sole point of truth. I need to heavily rely on my engine data for paid search purposes. Also their help team is not very helpful.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We're able to see multiple channel performance in one consolidated place, which is very helpful. We can also get the actual names and email addresses for our leads in an easy view."}}
{"author": ["Kris B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Executive Director"], "date": ["Feb 07, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "This platform offers plethora of information. It's my go-to for all marketing needs, from social media, to website management, etc. And most of them are free!", "What do you dislike?": "There's not really anything I dislike about HubSpot!", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "I would recommend HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Not only do they offer very thoroughly explained marketing techniques you can easily implement, but also their software is amazing and easy to use. I always got great results in all my marketing endeavors."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "We use HubSpot to manage our websites, contact lists and also interface with our sales database, Salesforce.", "What do you dislike?": "We've been through a few rounds of users, and mistakes from the past are apparent, such as mislabeled contacts, improperly created forms and pages, etc.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are a global company and HubSpot helps keep us all on the same page and our marketing messages consistent."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "You can easily find everything you need on Hubspot. You can fold your campaigns, upload easily your pictures and work with your team efficiently. ", "What do you dislike?": "That I can't post the same content twice in the same day on twitter... but I understand that we don't want to flood our audience ;)", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "More brand awareness generate with the automated posting, lots of time saving!!"}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Computer Software"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 24, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Generally easy to use and navigate. Make a lot of updates throughout the year to improve. Easy to setup different lead nurturing campaigns", "What do you dislike?": "Wish they would respond more to suggested ideas in the community. Pricing is also a bit steep. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Gather all of the assets you need to switch ahead of time - makes it much easier to get up and running. It also helps to have someone dedicating to using the system day-in and day-out, so they are aware of changes and updates.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are able to successfully nurture almost all of the leads that come to us. We are able to customize the streams based off the quality of the leads and where they came to us from."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Sep 29, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I\"ve used HubSpot for over 6 years and can't imagine doing marketing without it. I appreciate how intuitive it is, yet it offers such a robust feature set. ", "What do you dislike?": "I don't have any major dislikes, though I occasionally run into a situation where it would be nice to have added functionality in some areas. HubSpot is always open to hearing about ideas for enhancements though, and there's never been a situation I wasn't able to work around in the meantime.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Able to maintain virtually our entire online presence with one platform. Primarily used for lead generation and engagement with prospects."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot is super easy to use, they release regular training videos and updates, and they are always at the front of innovation. ", "What do you dislike?": "We don't really have many complaints about HubSpot. It took some time to get used to how to use the software, but the team loves it. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We manage our communication with clients through HubSpot. We have noticed that we remember to be more communicative with clients and prospects. "}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 25, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Ability to share updates with colleagues in regard to comments, notes, and status changes on new contacts. This allows for easy management of contacts in order to assign contacts to their respective owners and quickly move them along the pipeline.", "What do you dislike?": "A bit pricey for features that are often accessible elsewhere for free or much lower cost. Basic/Free model doesn't offer A/B testing.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Utilize the free training on marketing, great blogs and templates.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Organization, prior to Hubspot, our contacts, leads and prospects were scattered on spreadsheets, there was no way to keep real time updates on contacts made, notes or progression through the sales pipeline."}}
{"author": ["Executive Sponsor"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jun 21, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of use, automation, and insight we get into our sales and marketing efforts.", "What do you dislike?": "The platform is built for B2C sales which makes the CRM difficult to use for a B2B company.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot really requires a full time employee to monitor and manage.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot solves our marketing automation and analytics needs. It has led to an increase in quality inbound leads for our sales team."}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Ashley W"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Marketing Manager", "Market Research"], "date": ["Nov 09, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is the most intuitive and easy-to-use marketing automation platform for small and medium size businesses. It's has all capabilities you need to grow your business from email automation to lead scoring and campaign reporting. It's also the best solution for training new team members. They have extensive training programs and articles. ", "What do you dislike?": "As our department grew, we realized there we're a lot of limitations. Lead scoring was limited to tracking only Hubspot engagement activities and couldn't integrate sales activities from Salesforce (i.e. calls, emails, demos, etc.).", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot allowed us to build our first personalized marketing campaigns. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 03, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Impressive prebuilt workflows. Simple workflow creation. Ties in nicely with related customer relationship management (CRM) and sales tools.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": " \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 23, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the analytics tool in Hubspot that let's you view all your data. The campaign and workflow tools are also a great way to help save precious time and money!", "What do you dislike?": "It's not the best when it comes to price as compared to the other alternatives available in the market", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great platform to get started and eventually grow the marketing funnel. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Basically every aspect of marketing is take care by hubspot from emailing to website to analytics. "}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The features allow non developer users to get around and create cool stuff easily.", "What do you dislike?": "It might be necessary to have a developer to be able to create complex layouts/structures.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The platform lacks amp features for website/landing pages."}}
{"author": ["User in Legal Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 12, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's a great CRM software for our small company (15 or so people). I work primarily in the marketing section of the software and it's great for emails and landing pages, easy to use for my colleagues and easy enough to use the design manager to create new emails and landing pages. You can tell Hubspot is making steps to improve the software and support gets back in a timely manner. Easy software to learn, great UX.", "What do you dislike?": "Not sure how I like the new design. Also, by using contact emails we ran into issues where we would have duplicate companies when we imported new users from our software and since we used to have Salesforce connected, we could not merge them to clean up our companies.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Great for organizing contacts and segmenting our contacts to send emails to them. Our sales guys also find Hubspot helpful in tracking what part of the sales funnel contacts are in. I find the Design Manager useful when trying to tweak the look of email and landing page templates as well."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Staffing and Recruiting"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I enjoy being able to customize templates for marketers to use.  More so, having a robust platform to perform lead generation, store contacts, and launch websites streamlines work to provide increased efficiency.", "What do you dislike?": "As a product HubSpot is still maturing and there are significant changes as well as many Beta products that have existed for 1+ years.  Online documentation contains outdated information.  Multiple rebrands, mean UI changes frequently.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot uses a Python-like templating engine and feels similar to Django and Jinja.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows our team to quickly set up landing pages for special events and send emails based on user interaction.  The HubDB functionality allows our team to add content to templated sites more easily."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 01, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Same UI across products making it easy for a one-woman show to handle all aspects of marketing. Also love the crossover with the sales products.", "What do you dislike?": "Some documentation is out of date - I get it's hard to keep up but little things like that are frustrating when you're trying to learn how to do something. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email communication and automated notifications for product. Easily capturing leads on blog sites."}}
{"author": ["Phillip M"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development Associate", "Internet"], "date": ["Oct 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Amazing Interface.Very Easy to Use and makes my whole process more efficient", "What do you dislike?": "Cant pull up contacts sometimes, bad search engine", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Task management, reminders, organization"}}
{"author": ["Han M"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Very easy to track all marketing efforts.", "What do you dislike?": "The landing page and email templates require some background dev knowledge, but other than that, Hubspot is very easy to use. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can track my prospect journey from awareness all the way to customer. Hubspot's integration with Salesforce ties both our marketing and sales efforts together. "}}
{"author": ["Consultant"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "User friendly tools provide a terrific overview. I like the new weekly reports!", "What do you dislike?": "I wish that the Comments threads would expand be able to comment on. No images/content shown. Must log in to Social platform at the same time and cannot use anything else other than an emoji 'Like.' With multiple Centers that becomes clumsy.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Your academic component is terrific!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Immediate response for customer validation."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot accomplishes in Marketing Automation what Apple did to mobile technology.They found a way to simplify it but keep the tool robust enough to function at a high level.", "What do you dislike?": "You may find yourself asking for a little more complexity from the tool. While simplicity is great, it can sometimes limit your ability to perform tasks you want it to do. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We mostly use HubSpot for marketing automation. Simply put, if we didn't have HubSpot our inbound marketing efforts would be drastically reduced. HubSpot. It also gives us the analytics we need to determine what is working, with this we can steer our ship in the right direction."}}
{"author": ["User in Graphic Design"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The integrations help make tasks quicker and easier.", "What do you dislike?": "The technical back-end aspects that relate to website and form construction sometimes conflict with our desired behavior; The tools provided aren\u2019t as customizable as we need.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We\u2019re helping our clients understand what products / services they offer are in most demand by their consume base and helping them get in touch with these niche audiences."}}
{"author": ["User in Medical Devices"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 04, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Allows me to work with various members of my team from a remote location and stay in touch while working remotely.", "What do you dislike?": "I don\u2019t use the software enough to notice a downside, except there have been a few \u201coutages\u201d recently where the servers were offline.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "This allows me to keep up to date with a traveling team of salespeople as well as my office colleagues even if I\u2019m working remotely."}}
{"author": ["Shannon F"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Office Assistant", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Nov 24, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I really like the Free HubSpot CRM option that is offered on their website, so you can at least test run the product before committing.", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike how the free option doesn't let you trial run all the different variations of HubSpot.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I am able to solve issues related to analytics and tracking. The benefits I have realized is how easy it is to use this platform. Anyone can learn how to use the software."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 05, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I enjoy that the Hubspot system easily integrates into my gmail account, allowing for simple turn on/turn off tracking selection and sidebar access. I also like that it lets me know who has opened the emails I send out and when. Not only does it allow me to know that the information I have sent has been received, it also implies when a person has read the content and then is ready for a next-step discussion on the information provided. ", "What do you dislike?": "I dislike that so many read notifications come back without any categorization. If I send an email to 50 people, it will often let me know that \"xx number of people have opened your email\", but rarely lets me know which email addresses have opened that email (I experience this problem most often with large group emails). If I can receive specific open notifications for one-off or small group emails, why can I not for larger ones? ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I have realized several benefits since using Hubspot. For one, I know how many people have opened and email and read it, which allows me to know who on the team is up to speed at any given time. Also, by letting me know who has opened an email when, I also know about how long it takes for my coworkers to get to their email, allowing me to make inferences regarding to their current workload. Additionally, easy integration into my email provider meant less setup and learning time, saving my business hours. "}}
{"author": ["Caitlin Z"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Product Marketing Manager", "Consumer Services"], "date": ["Mar 30, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I loved using Hubspot! It was so easy to build and manage our website. They had beautiful templates and we could easily plug in content and publish. It was also easy to make landing pages and view reporting.", "What do you dislike?": "Nothing, I highflying recommend this product and have advocated for it at other companies.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "N/A", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Content creation, website management, reporting. It\u2019s so easy to create a great website and track usage."}}
{"author": ["User in Marketing and Advertising"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's a super initiative marketing tool that allows someone who isn't a graphic designer to easily create compelling emails and landing pages and build out strategic campaigns. This eliminated the lag time of having to go back and forth with our individuals to get work done. ", "What do you dislike?": "I loved every aspect of this tool at my previous company and hope to use it in the future. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use it to it's full capacity ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot is a money and time investment because it takes only one person to execute a task in an hour that would usually take a few people over the course of a week to complete. "}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 25, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is great because they have a free a version, that is very easy to use right out of the. If you work for a smaller company and don't have previous experience with any CRM's Hubspot is intuitive and you can pick up on it quickly.", "What do you dislike?": "To really get going with automation you have to upgrade and the cost ramps up very quickly. I've used other enterprise CRM's and marketing automation tools and the cost of Hubspot can be comparable very quickly", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Tracking communications , sales follow up and pipeline"}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(1001-5000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 09, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The ease of the tool for marketers - this is a great tool for marketers without a web development background.", "What do you dislike?": "It's extremely rigid in terms of restrictions on web development. HubSpot uses its own coding language (HUBL), which requires hiring a HubSpot developer for most features and functionality that would otherwise not require outsourced development. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "If your business relies on innovative website experiences and data-based analytics and decision making, you may want to look at alternatives.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Our business feels we've outgrown HubSpot due to their deficiency in reporting and analytics capabilities. "}}
{"author": ["Linda O"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": ["Director of Marketing/Business Development", "Hospitality"], "date": ["Oct 07, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like the integrations. Both on the marketing, creative, & automation side and the sales integrations. ", "What do you dislike?": "Some of the templates and web design tools are still a little cumbersome to maneuver in, it's still a little foreign if you want to customize them.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "CRM & nuturing workflows. By being able to track within one app instead of many....a real time changer!"}}
{"author": ["Julie G"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Global Marketing Events Coordinator", "Marketing and Advertising"], "date": ["Oct 07, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Really useful training course, got me started and has been helpful to refer back to. ", "What do you dislike?": "You can't edit static contact lists once they are made, this is a bit frustrating!", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Use the help function if you are stuck!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Great for communicating with clients for events and have set up workflows which reduces time spent wondering who has and hasn't received information. "}}
{"author": ["User in Apparel & Fashion"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 30, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The best thing about Hubspot so far is the ability to manage all of my digital platforms in one spot and to see how my marketing efforts are affecting our sales pipeline in real time. I also love the amount of training and support available to our team", "What do you dislike?": "There are a lot of things we could be getting for free elsewhere. ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Make sure this is the right fit for your business first. Hubspot can get pretty expensive pretty quick so if you have a large team or are on a tight budget it may not be the best solution for you right now", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We are a small company with a 3 person sales/marketing team. That means we need to automate as much as possible to get the most from a few people. The biggest benefit we've seen so far is the ability to engage more prospects in less time and keep them engaged so they can be converted more quickly. "}}
{"author": ["Cvetilena G"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Digital Marketing Manager", "Computer Software"], "date": ["Oct 27, 2015"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is a really solid tool we use on a day to day basis. We were able to move away from a Wordpress form + Unbounce + Mailchimp and Zapier environment. All the automation tasks are not managed inside Hubspot and synced to Salesforce.", "What do you dislike?": "It is not really possible to generate unique, behavior based, nurture flows. Also in depth customization of emails and landing pages is not always as easy as expected. While it is possible to change almost all the elements, usage of the knowledge base and some hardcore HTML/JS/CSS skills are required \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "(this is only a problem for tech savvy marketers that love to fiddle around with templates and pixels)."}}
{"author": ["User"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 02, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The HubSpot Academy and live support chat", "What do you dislike?": "There are many common CRM features that aren't included, the social media feature is terrible, certain reporting features are not available", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "It's great for beginners and small businesses, but if paying for it, I'd suggest shopping around.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "It's great for automatically adding contacts to our database from our website and the ability to organize/filter"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 28, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I like that it's free, and not just because FREE, but because it's a great option for a small company (and as the only sales person) I can't justify a huge expense for CRM without demonstrating a need.  So many other CRMs were hugely out of our budget. HubSpot has made it easy for me to make use of a CRM to help me grow. It's an easy-to-use dashboard. My favorite thing is the gmail integration that virtually ELIMINATES cut/pasting of contact information. ", "What do you dislike?": "No phone support for CRM free level, so when I've had issues I've had to go through a thousand emails to get a simple question answered. Notifications that I've seen hundreds of times still pop up. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "solving: tracking and sharing contacts, having it cloud accessible is good too. \r"}}
{"author": ["Daniel B"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": ["Marketing manager"], "date": ["Sep 26, 2019", "Aug 24, 2019"], "reviews": {}}
{"author": ["Ashley W"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": ["Senior Marketing Manager", "Market Research"], "date": ["Nov 09, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Hubspot is the most intuitive and easy-to-use marketing automation platform for small and medium size businesses. It's has all capabilities you need to grow your business from email automation to lead scoring and campaign reporting. It's also the best solution for training new team members. They have extensive training programs and articles. ", "What do you dislike?": "As our department grew, we realized there we're a lot of limitations. Lead scoring was limited to tracking only Hubspot engagement activities and couldn't integrate sales activities from Salesforce (i.e. calls, emails, demos, etc.).", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Hubspot allowed us to build our first personalized marketing campaigns. "}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Dec 03, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Impressive prebuilt workflows. Simple workflow creation. Ties in nicely with related customer relationship management (CRM) and sales tools.\r", "What do you dislike?": "\r", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": " \r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "\r"}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 23, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I love the analytics tool in Hubspot that let's you view all your data. The campaign and workflow tools are also a great way to help save precious time and money!", "What do you dislike?": "It's not the best when it comes to price as compared to the other alternatives available in the market", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Great platform to get started and eventually grow the marketing funnel. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Basically every aspect of marketing is take care by hubspot from emailing to website to analytics. "}}
{"author": ["User in Information Technology and Services"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Oct 24, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The features allow non developer users to get around and create cool stuff easily.", "What do you dislike?": "It might be necessary to have a developer to be able to create complex layouts/structures.\r", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "The platform lacks amp features for website/landing pages."}}
{"author": ["User in Legal Services"], "company_size": ["(11-50 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Apr 12, 2017"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "It's a great CRM software for our small company (15 or so people). I work primarily in the marketing section of the software and it's great for emails and landing pages, easy to use for my colleagues and easy enough to use the design manager to create new emails and landing pages. You can tell Hubspot is making steps to improve the software and support gets back in a timely manner. Easy software to learn, great UX.", "What do you dislike?": "Not sure how I like the new design. Also, by using contact emails we ran into issues where we would have duplicate companies when we imported new users from our software and since we used to have Salesforce connected, we could not merge them to clean up our companies.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Great for organizing contacts and segmenting our contacts to send emails to them. Our sales guys also find Hubspot helpful in tracking what part of the sales funnel contacts are in. I find the Design Manager useful when trying to tweak the look of email and landing page templates as well."}}
{"author": ["Administrator in Staffing and Recruiting"], "company_size": ["(10,001+ employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Nov 01, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "I enjoy being able to customize templates for marketers to use.  More so, having a robust platform to perform lead generation, store contacts, and launch websites streamlines work to provide increased efficiency.", "What do you dislike?": "As a product HubSpot is still maturing and there are significant changes as well as many Beta products that have existed for 1+ years.  Online documentation contains outdated information.  Multiple rebrands, mean UI changes frequently.  ", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "HubSpot uses a Python-like templating engine and feels similar to Django and Jinja.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "HubSpot allows our team to quickly set up landing pages for special events and send emails based on user interaction.  The HubDB functionality allows our team to add content to templated sites more easily."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["May 01, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Same UI across products making it easy for a one-woman show to handle all aspects of marketing. Also love the crossover with the sales products.", "What do you dislike?": "Some documentation is out of date - I get it's hard to keep up but little things like that are frustrating when you're trying to learn how to do something. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Email communication and automated notifications for product. Easily capturing leads on blog sites."}}
{"author": ["Phillip M"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": ["Business Development Associate", "Internet"], "date": ["Oct 08, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Amazing Interface.Very Easy to Use and makes my whole process more efficient", "What do you dislike?": "Cant pull up contacts sometimes, bad search engine", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Task management, reminders, organization"}}
{"author": ["Han M"], "company_size": ["(51-200 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jan 26, 2018"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "Very easy to track all marketing efforts.", "What do you dislike?": "The landing page and email templates require some background dev knowledge, but other than that, Hubspot is very easy to use. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "I can track my prospect journey from awareness all the way to customer. Hubspot's integration with Salesforce ties both our marketing and sales efforts together. "}}
{"author": ["Consultant"], "company_size": ["(501-1000 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Jul 10, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "User friendly tools provide a terrific overview. I like the new weekly reports!", "What do you dislike?": "I wish that the Comments threads would expand be able to comment on. No images/content shown. Must log in to Social platform at the same time and cannot use anything else other than an emoji 'Like.' With multiple Centers that becomes clumsy.", "Recommendations to others considering the product:": "Your academic component is terrific!", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "Immediate response for customer validation."}}
{"author": ["Administrator"], "company_size": ["(201-500 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Mar 26, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "HubSpot accomplishes in Marketing Automation what Apple did to mobile technology.They found a way to simplify it but keep the tool robust enough to function at a high level.", "What do you dislike?": "You may find yourself asking for a little more complexity from the tool. While simplicity is great, it can sometimes limit your ability to perform tasks you want it to do. ", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We mostly use HubSpot for marketing automation. Simply put, if we didn't have HubSpot our inbound marketing efforts would be drastically reduced. HubSpot. It also gives us the analytics we need to determine what is working, with this we can steer our ship in the right direction."}}
{"author": ["User in Graphic Design"], "company_size": ["(2-10 employees)"], "role": [], "date": ["Aug 28, 2019"], "reviews": {"What do you like best?": "The integrations help make tasks quicker and easier.", "What do you dislike?": "The technical back-end aspects that relate to website and form construction sometimes conflict with our desired behavior; The tools provided aren\u2019t as customizable as we need.", "What problems are you solving with the product?  What benefits have you realized?": "We\u2019re helping our clients understand what products / services they offer are in most demand by their consume base and helping them get in touch with these niche audiences."}}
